. 9-१०.{{/F}}(V)--the constellation (Canopus) that moves fast above ध्रुवमण्डल. Br. II. २१. १०१; वा. ५०, १५५. [page१-009+ २६](VI)--a hill of that name. M. १२४. ९७.(VII)--born of गर्भ; born later as दत्तालि; {{F}}1:  वा. २८. २२; Vi. I, १०. 9.{{/F}} (Dattoli-वि।). residence (भवन) at महामलय; {{F}}2:  वा. ४८. २३.{{/F}} relation of, to पोतृयण; {{F}}3:  वा. ५९. ९३, २०८.{{/F}} Udayantaka Mt. brought by; and his wife. {{F}}4:  वा. १०८. ४४, ५३.{{/F}}(III)--born from a pitcher into which Mitra and वरुण dropped their वीर्य at the sight of the charms of उर्वशी: a brother of वसिष्ठ. {{F}}1:  भा. VI. १८. 5; Br. IV. 5. ३८ M. ६१. २१-31; २०१. २९; २०२. 1.{{/F}} Dwarfed the Vindhyas, made a home in लङ्का: seeing the universe troubled by तारक and other Asuras caused the ocean to dry up by drinking the waters and brought relief to the Devas: performed तपस् seated on Mount Malaya with his wife लोपामुद्रा: white in colour, with four hands, अक्ष माला and कमण्डलु, narrated the story of अजामिल: {{F}}2:  भा., VI. 3. ३५; M. ६१. १७; ३६-41; Br. III. ५६. ५३.{{/F}} pre- sent at राम's अभिषेक. {{F}}2: (a) Vi. IV 4. ९९.{{/F}} Visited by परशुराम, initiated him to the कृष्णप्रेमामृतम् mantra which he heard from शेष, the नाग king. Spoke to him of the threefold भक्ति and its characteristics. {{F}}3:  Br. II, ३२. ११९; III. ३४. ५०; ३५. ३४, ४१, ४८; ३६, 1-५९; ३७, 2; ५६. २३.{{/F}} A ब्रह्मिष्ठ, versed in वैखानस; a देवऋषि, versed in Vedic literature. {{F}}4:  M. १४५. ९३, ११४.{{/F}} The guest of Ilvala who cooked वातापि for him. {{F}}5:  भा. VI. १८, १५.{{/F}} Roaming about, he found all creatures engrossed in ignorance. Reaching काञ्ची, he prayed to कामाक्षि and एकाम्रशिव. Here हयग्रीव Vis2n2u appeared before him and pointed out ways to redeem the ignorant millions. Was entertained with the story of शक्ति by हयग्रीव. {{F}}6:  Br. IV. 5. 3-२९; 6. 1; ३९. 7.{{/F}} Praised शिव out to ruin Tripuram. {{F}}7:  M. १३३. ६७.{{/F}} He who worships Agastya becomes lord of the seven worlds. {{F}}8:  M. ६१. ४४-55.{{/F}}--see