t of Dharma. Yama heard this and approved it. अजामिल, thus rescued from Death, felt peni- tent, and while making तपस् at गङ्गाद्वार, he cast off his body and reached विष्णुलोक। भा. VI. 1. २०. to the end; Ib. VI. ch. 2 & 3.--one of Danu's sons. वा. ६८. 5.(also अधोमुखस्)--a group of पिशाचस्. Br. III. 7. ३८१; वा. ६९. २६३, २६७.--one of the ten sons of हृदीक: Father of three powerful sons: सुदम्ष्ट्र, सुनाभ and कृष्ण. M. ४४. ८२-4.(I)--the son of विधिसार and father of Dar- bhaka (Arbhaka-वि। प्।). भा. XII. 1. 6; Vi. IV. २४. १४-15.(II)--the son of भूमिमित्र. {{F}}1:  वा. ९९. ३१७.{{/F}} His reign lasted for २५ (२७?) years. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ७४. १३१; M. २७२. १०.{{/F}}--a pupil of कृत. Br. II. ३५. ५२.--one of the nine sons of Ugrasena. M. ४४. ७५.--an Apsaras. Br. III. 7. 8.--the name of Siva's bow (also आजगवम्). M. २३. ३७; वा. ९०. ३१.--a kingdom. Br. III. ७४. २१८; वा. ९९. ४०६.(I)--a Rudra, and a son of भूत and सरूपा; the भूत chieftain {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 6. १८; Br. III. 3. ७१; वा. ६६. ६९.{{/F}} one of the eleven Rudras. {{F}}2:  M. 5. २९.{{/F}} [page१-034+ २७](II)--the agni at शालामुखि; see उपस्थेय। Br. II. १२. २५. वा. २९. २४.(III)--a मुहूर्त of the night. Br. III. 3. ४२.(I)--a son of बलाक and father of कुश. भा. IX. १५. 3-4.(II)--the son of Sunaha (Suhotra-वा। प्।, and Sumantu-वि। प्।) and father of बलाकाश्व; {{F}}1:  Br. III. ६६. ३०; ७४-126; वा. ९१. ६०-61; Vi. IV. 7. 8.{{/F}} ruled for २१ years (३१ ? वा।). {{F}}2:  वा. ९९. ३१३.{{/F}}(III)--the son of दिलीप. M. १२. ४८.--a son of Maya. Br. III. 6. २९.(I)--a son of Hastin. Had three queens of Kuru line; प्रियमेधा and other ब्राह्मन्स् belonged to his family. Father of कण्व and बृहदिषु. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २१. २१-22; वा. ९९. १६६; Vi. IV. १९. २९-30, ३३; M. ४९. ४३-5.{{/F}} By नलिनी he had a son नील. {{F}}2:  भा. IX. २१-30; वा. ९९. १९४; Vi. IV. १९. ५६.{{/F}} ऋक्ष was another son of his. {{F}}3:  भा. IX. २२. 3; M. ५०. १९. Vi. IV. १९. ७४.{{/F}} Sons born through the grace of भरद्वाज. {{F}}4:  वा. ९९. १६९.{{/F}}(II)--an अङ्गिरस and मन्त्रकृत्। A क्ष- triya-dvija. Br. II. ३२. १०९; III. ६६. ८७; M. १४५. १०३; वा. ९१. ११६; ५९. १००.--a mindborn mother. M. १७९. २४.(I)--the parent of Buddha. (अञ्जन-Burnouf). भा. I. 3. २४.(II)--a name of कृष्ण-Hari. भा. X. 3. 1 & 5; 6. २३. [page१-030+ ३३]--the kingdom of ऋषभ, later known as भारत. भा. V. 4. 3; 7. 3; XI. 2. २४.--a son of अङ्गिरस् and सुरूपा: a gotrakara. M. १९६. 4.--a place fit for performing श्राद्धम्, noted for the tree विरजा; {{F}}1:  Br. III. १३. ४८.{{/F}} the shadow of gods seen at the place in पर्वस्; the पाण्डवस् performed श्राद्धम् at. {{F}}2:  वा. ७७. ४८.{{/F}}--on the back of the शिशुमार (s.v.) {{F}}1:  भा. V. २३. 5.{{/F}} the southern course. Here are three kinds of sunrise, one in मूल and the other two in two आषाढस्; on its south was पितृयान: consists of three constellations--मूल and आषा- ढस्--पूर्व and उत्तर। {{F}}2:  Br. II. २१. ७६ & १५९; III. 3. ५१; M. १२४. ५३-8; वा. 1. ९३; ६६. ५१; Vi. II. 8. ८५.{{/F}} [page१-031+ २८]--the son of Darbhaka and father of Nandivar- dhana. भा. XII. 1. 6, 7.--one of the eleven Rudras. M. १५३. १९.--a पारावत god; also a वैकुण्ठ god. Br. II. ३६. १४ and ५७.--a sage who sold his second son शुनःशेफ to Rohita to be sacrificed in his place. भा. IX. 7. २०-21; IX. १६. ३०.--a पारावत god. Br. II. ३६. १३; वा. ६२. १२.--a son of हविर्धान. Br. II. ३७. २४; वा. ६३. २३; Vi. I. १४. 2.--a शुक्र deva. वा. ३१. 9.(I)--a manifestation of Hari during the epoch of Manu चाक्षुष. In this period the क्षीरोद was churned and nectar was secured. {{F}}1:  भा. II. 2. 5; VIII. 5. 9-१०.{{/F}} Praised by ब्रह्मा. {{F}}2:  Ib. VIII. 5. २५-50.{{/F}} Advised gods to befriend Asuras and then get अमृत by churning the ocean, with their co-operation, to be able ultimately to prevail against them; {{F}}3:  Ib. VIII. 6. १८-25.{{/F}} began to take part in अमृतमथन when the efforts of others produced no results. {{F}}4:  Ib. VIII. 7. १६; X. 2. २०; X. ५१. ४८.{{/F}}(II)--a पृथुक god. Br. II. ३६. ७४.(III)--the name of Hari born in स्वारोचिष epoch from तुषिता. Br. III. 3. ११४.(I)--the goddess following भवमालिनी. M. १७९. ७१.(II)--the mother of devas known as Ajitas. वा. ६७. ३३. [page१-033+ ३०](I)--a group of gods with आयुष्मन्त formed १४ गणस् whose residence was Maharloka. From there they go to Janaloka. Br. III. 4. २७; IV. 1. १२२.(II)--a देवगण; {{F}}1:  वा. १०. २१.{{/F}} they are Asama, उग्रदृष्टि, Sunaya, शुचिश्रवस्, Kevala, विश्वरूप, सुदक्ष, Madhupa, Turiya, Indrayuk. {{F}}2:  Br. II. 9. ४६; १३. ९०.{{/F}} Remembered by ब्रह्मा. {{F}}3:  वा. ३१. 4.{{/F}}(III)--sons of Ajita and Ruci in the स्वायम्- bhuva Manvantara. वा. ६७. ३३.--of तमस् quality and the source of all dffi- culties; the enemy to knowledge; creates a thirst for desire (राग)। If not got rid of, one attains तिर्यक्-योनि। Br. IV. 3. ४१ and ४९; 4. २३. वा. १०२. ६२, ६९.--its significance in ओं; {{F}}1:  वा. २०. 8ff.{{/F}} the source of ६३ varn2as; {{F}}2:  वा. २६. २८.{{/F}} the primordial स्वर and its place in creation. {{F}}3:  वा. २६. २९ff.{{/F}} [page१-002+ ३१]--the house of, to the north of मातृका. Br. IV. ३६. २०.--a son of तामस Manu. M. 9. १७.--a son of खशा and a राक्षस: {{F}}1:  Br. III. 7, १३६; वा. ६९, १६७.{{/F}} an Asura in the सभा of हिरण्यकशिपु. {{F}}2:  M. १६१. ८१.{{/F}}--a sage of the तामस epoch. M. 9. १५.--a class of पिशाचस्. Br. III. 7. ३७९.--a काद्रवेय na1ga. Br. III. 7. ३३.--the son of गम्भीर. Of his wife was born Brahman. भा. IX. १७. १०.(I)--a son of त्वरितायु or simply आयु. M. ५०. ३७.(II)--a son of अयुतायु and father of देवा- tithi. वा. ९९. २३२.--a son of सम्हताश्व. Br. III. ६३. ६५; M. १२, ३४. [page१-003+ ४६]--one who has not had tonsure: his death leaves pollution for one night; pollution after चूड is for three nights. M. १८. 3.(I)--a ब्राह्मन् invited for the राजसूय of युधिष्ठिर to officiate as a priest. भा., X. ७४. 9.(II)--a पौराणिक. Learnt one of the four मूलसम्हितस् from the disciple of व्यास; {{F}}1:  भा., XII. 7. 5, 7.{{/F}} a pupil of Roma- हर्षण; otherwise known as काश्यप. {{F}}2:  Vi. III. 6. १७.{{/F}}(III)--a sage. Br. II. ३५. ६३.(IV)--the Brahman boy rescued by परशु- राम, his guru, from the jaws of a tiger. {{F}}1:  Br. III. २६. 3; ३०. २१; ३४, 8, २९; ३५. ३७.{{/F}} Advised to take courage and console his mother; condoled with him on the loss of his parents. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ३७. १०; ३८, 2, ३५; ३९. १३; ४१. १५, १७; ४३, ३१; ४४. 1, ३०.{{/F}} Accompanied परशुराम, to Mandira for a twelve years' penance and to Mahendra for another course of austerities. Helped परशुराम in his अश्वमेध and the penance after. {{F}}3:  Br. III. ४६. 3, २८; ४७. ३४, ५९.{{/F}}(I)--a Yadu prince; welcomed कृष्ण to द्वा- raka. {{F}}1:  भा. I. ११. १६; १४, २८.{{/F}} The foremost of the sons of श्वफल्क and गान्दिनी; married a daughter of Ugrasena and had two sons, देववान् and Upadeva (Deva and Anupadeva-वि). {{F}}2:  भा. IX. २४. १५, १७, १८; Br. III. ७१. ११३; Vi. IV. १३. १२६; १४. 7, १०; वा. ९६. ११२.{{/F}} Stayed in Madhu- रा (मथुरा) when the Yadus migrated. {{F}}3:  भा. X. 2. 4 [].{{/F}} Once visited Brah- मःरद. {{F}}4:  भा. X. २८. १६.{{/F}} कंस sent for him and asked him to take in his chariot कृष्ण and राम to the capital for the Dhanur- याग (‘festival of arms’) at which they were to be killed. Returned home with this message. {{F}}5:  भा. X. ३६. २७-40; Vi. V. १५, 9, १२.{{/F}} When the night passed by, अक्रूर started for the व्रज of Nanda thinking all the way of the meeting and embraces of कृष्ण and राम who had made friends with people of ब्रिन्दावन्. Reached Gokula by evening. {{F}}6:  भा. X. ३८, 1-२४ Vi. V. १५. २४.{{/F}} Saw राम and कृष्ण in fine deportment and form, milking cows: prostrated before them in divine ecstasy. Welcomed in the proper way by the brothers and Nanda, अक्रूर was lost in wonder, and did not feel the fatigue of the journey. {{F}}7:  भा. X. ३८. २५-43; Vi. V. १७. 2-२५.{{/F}} Gopis who came to know of अक्रूर's mission called him क्रूर for taking away कृष्ण from their midst. {{F}}8:  भा. X. ३९. २१-26.{{/F}} It was early morning when अक्रूर and the two brothers started after morning prayers. Reaching the यमुना, अक्रूर went to the river for a bath, asking the brothers to stay in the cha- riot. But he was surprised to see the brothers in the waters, and at the same time in the chariot also. He also saw Hari reclining on शेष. {{F}}9:  भा. X. ३९. ३२-57; Vi. V. १८. ११ and १९.{{/F}} अक्रूर's praise of Hari. {{F}}१०:  भा. X. ४०. (whole).{{/F}} Con- gratulating himself on his luck to have had a दर्शन् of Hari, he drove कृष्ण and राम to मथुरा before sunset. {{F}}११:  भा. X. ४१. 4-6.{{/F}} Invited कृष्ण to his home, and the latter agreed to go to his place only after कंसवध. Informed कंस of [page१-004+ ४९] कृष्ण's arrival in the camp, and went back to his house. {{F}}१२:  भा. X. ४१. ११-18.{{/F}} Attended the wrestling match. {{F}}१२: (a) Vi. V. २०. २८.{{/F}} Gopis took Uddhava to अक्रूर. {{F}}१३:  भा. X. ४६. ४८.{{/F}} Was visited by कृष्ण with राम and Uddhava to whom अक्रूर gave a royal welcome. {{F}}१४:  Ib. X. ४८. १२-28.{{/F}} कृष्ण told अक्रूर that they looked to him for guidance, and that he was their गुरु। Was requested by कृष्ण to go to हस्तिनापुर to find out the exact position of the पाण्डवस्. {{F}}१५:  Ib. X. ४८. २९-35.{{/F}} Visited हस्तिनापुर and returned to मथुरा after meeting Kunti and ascertain- ing the evil intentions of धृतराष्टृअ against the पाण्डवस्. {{F}}१६:  Ib. X. ch. ४९ (whole).{{/F}} One of those stationed by कृष्ण to defend the western gate of मथुरा, {{F}}१७:  Ib. X. ५०. २०[4].{{/F}} was consulted by कृष्ण on the eve of his attack on जरासन्ध. {{F}}१८:  Ib. X. [५०. (V). 8].{{/F}} A member of the यादव sabha1. {{F}}१९:  Ib. X. [५२. (V). १५].{{/F}} Satya- भामा refusing to part with the jewel Syamantaka (s.v.), अक्रूर suggested with कृतवर्मन् to शतधन्वन् Bhoja its seizure from सत्राजित as he had failed to keep his promise to marry his daughter to them. {{F}}२०:  Ib. X. ५७. 3; वा. ९६. ५७, ९७; Vi. IV. १३. ११५-26.{{/F}} Asked by शतधन्वन् for help against कृष्ण, अक्रूर refused; Bhoja शतधन्वन् killed सत्राजित, the father of सत्यभामा, and secured the jewel but placed it in अक्रूर's custody. {{F}}२१:  भा. X. ५७. १४-18.{{/F}} Became afraid, after शतधन्व's death at the hands of कृष्ण and बलराम, and left द्वारका. Evil portents in the city and cessation of rains. It was said that rain fell where अक्रूर lived. Was sent for by कृष्ण to return to द्वारका; gave his sister in marriage to कृष्ण who after duly honouring him, requested him to show the jewel in public, so that राम might not misunderstand him. He did so in the सभा of the सात्वतस् but कृष्ण placed Syamantaka back in his hand. {{F}}२२:  Ib. X. ५७. २९-41 [1-4]; Br. III. ७१. ५९ and ८३; Vi. IV. १३. ६७-90.{{/F}} Was sent back to द्वारका after the राज- सूय for its defence. {{F}}२३:  भा. X. ७६. 7 [5] १४.{{/F}} Visited स्यमन्तपञ्चक on the occasion of the solar eclipse. {{F}}२४:  Ib. X. ८२. 5.{{/F}} Fought with Bhoja, deluded by कृष्ण. {{F}}२५:  Ib. XI. १२. १०.{{/F}} Got killed in the यादव contest at प्रभास. {{F}}२६:  Ib. XI. ३०. १६.{{/F}} [page१-005+ २६](II)--a काद्रवेय na1ga. Br., III. 7. ३६.(III)--महासेन: a वरमूर्ति. Br. IV. ४४. ५०.(IV)--a son of Jayanta, married रत्ना, शैब्य's daughter; father of eleven powerful sons. M. ४५. २७-8.(III)--the wife of पृथुसेन and mother of Nakta. भा. V. १५. 6.--gourds unfit for श्राद्ध। Vi. III. १६. 8.--the gourd-vessel of the नागस् to milk the earth cow. Br. II. ३६. २१३; M. १०. १९.--एकार्षेयस्. M. २००. 3.--a श्रुतऋषि. Br. II. ३३. 4.--the city of यक्षस् in कैलास. Capital of Kubera. {{F}}1:  Br. II. १८. 2; III. 7. १६३; वा. ४७. 1; भा. IV. 6. २३.{{/F}} पुरूरवस् and उर्वशी sported here for a time; {{F}}2:  वा. ९१. 6; Br. III. ६६. 6; Vi. IV. 6. ४८.{{/F}} as seen by भार्गव Ra1ma. {{F}}3:  Br. III. ४१. १८-23.{{/F}} [page१-115+ २६]--is Kubera. वा. ४७. 1; ६९. १९६.--The R. in कैलास: a branch of गङ्गा issuing out of the city of ब्रह्मा descends the southern slopes of Meru. Her course can be traced from the Gan- धमादन. Traversing the हेमकूट and Himalayas as also the continent of Bharata and dividing itself into seven branches it enters the sea on the south. A bath in this stream is equal to performing अश्वमेधस् and other sacri- fices. A महानदी: borne by शिव on his head for more than a hundred years: Elevated Sagara's sons to heaven. भा. IV. 6. २४; V. १७. 5 and 9; IX. २९. ४२; Br. III. ४१. २१; ५६. १२; Vi. II. 2. ३४, ३६; 8. ११३-20; वा. ४१. १८. ४२. २५-35; १०८. ८०.--a mindborn mother. M. १७९. २२.--an Apsaras. Br. III. 7. 6; IV. ३३. १८; वा. ६९. 5.--depend on वर्ण, स्थानयोग and नाट्य: Three places of origin--neck, head and mind: 4 वर्णस्, eight विकल्पस्, and sixteen deities: Different kinds of, described: {{F}}1:  Br. III. ६२. 2-२३.{{/F}} ३०० varieties distinguished. {{F}}2:  वा. ८७. 1-3, १०-21.{{/F}}(I)--a pupil of दत्तात्रेय: a sage who realised the force of हरिमाया। भा. I. 3. ११; II. 7. ४४.(II)--a son of Dyumat, and father of Sannati. He retained his youth and ruled for ६६,000 years. The ब्र्। पुराण and the विष्णु पुराण make him the son respectively [page१-116+ २८] of Vatsa and Pratardana, and father of Sannati. {{F}}1:  Br. III. ६७. ६९, ७२; Vi. IV. 8. १६-18; भा. IX. १७. 6-8.{{/F}} A राजऋषि of काशी; attained longevity through the grace of लोपामुद्रा. Killed the राक्षस Ks2emaka and recovered his capital. Two ancient verses in his praise. {{F}}2:  M. १८०. ६८-9; वा. ९२. ६६-8.{{/F}}--a deity. Br. IV. २७. ३८.--a daughter of इरा, and mother of trees. Br. III. 7. ४६०-1.--the son of गोमतीपुत्र and the father of शान्तकर्ण. Vi. IV. २४. ४७-8.--a tribe. वा. ४५. १२०.--a काद्रवेय na1ga. Br. III. 7. ३५.--attained by वृत्र. भा. VI. १२. ३५; Br. II. १९. १५३.--a god of Sumedhas group. Br. II. ३६. ५९.--a ray of the sun. Vi. II. १२. 8.--their irritation against king, a cause of internal dissensions; to be banished after being deprived of possession, for doing wrongs: Residence of. M. २२३. 9; २२७. १६०; २५४. २१-22. [page१-083+ ३१]--the time when पितृस् worship moon and when the sun, moon and constellations meet together in the same मण्डल; पितृस् drink the nectar of the moon (1/१५) part of it remaining; there is no moon, middle sun--half night half day. {{F}}1:  Br. II. १०. ६२. ६५; २१. १५३; २३. ७०; २८. 6; १७. १९; M. १७. 2; १२६. ६६. ७२; १४१. ४२-49; वा. ५२. ६४; ५३. ९२; ५६. 1, 6, ४२ and ४९{{/F}} यज्ञस् with २१ सम्ज्ञस्। {{F}}2:  Br. III. ११. १४. वा. ७४. १३.{{/F}} Only when two of its कलस् remain, the moon enters the orbit of the sun and stays in the ray called अमा and hence the period is अमावास्या, {{F}}3:  Vi. I. २०. ३८; II. 8. ८०; १२. 8; III. १४. 7-१०.{{/F}} fit for श्राद्ध। {{F}}4:  Vi. III. १४. 7-१०.{{/F}}(I)--a son of Aila. Him अच्छोदा adopted as her पितृ and lost her yogic powers; son of पुरूरवस् and उर्वशी. Father of भीम. Br. III. १०. ५६ and ६८; ६६. २२; M. १४. 5, 7. वा. ९१. ५१. 2; Vi. IV. 7. 1 and 2.(II)--the son of आयु; a Vasu passing through the sky loved by अच्छोदा. वा. ७३. 5.--a शक्ति devi1 on the सोडशपत्राब्ज। Br. IV. ३२. १२.--called कुहू because it casts the length of time a cuckoo takes to say कुहू। M. १४१. ४२, ४९.(I)--a mountain kingdom. M. ११४. ५६.(II)--a मरुत् गण। M. १७१. ५२.--Heaven noted for the pleasure-park Nan- dana. A description of the city, occupied for some time by Bali. {{F}}1:  भा. VIII. १५. ११-22 and ३३; वा. ७७. २६.{{/F}} Though it was really the capital of Indra, the latter says that it belonged to कृष्ण. {{F}}2:  भा. X. [६७ (V) २६]; Vi. I. 9. २५.{{/F}} When it is midday here, the sun rises at Samyamana. {{F}}3:  Br. II. २१. ३७; III. १३. २६ and ३०; M. १२४. २७.{{/F}}--on the western side of गन्धमा- dana. M. ११३. ४८. [page१-082+ २८]--(Mt.) the sacred hill at the top of माल्यवत्. Here अङ्गिरस् performed penance for fifteen crores of years; here is the R. विशल्यकरणी, forming a part of Kalinga; सिद्धिक्षेत्रम्, noted for श्राद्ध offering, {{F}}1:  Br. III. १३. 4-१६.{{/F}} and पितृ पिण्ड; a क्षेत्र of the नर्मदा by name जलेश्वरा; sur- rounded by the hill रुद्रकोटि; superior to कुरुक्षेत्र; {{F}}2:  M. २२. २८; १८६. १२-34; १८८. ७९ and ८२; १९१. २५; १९३. ५४; १९४. ४४.{{/F}} its crest lustrous as the प्रलयाग्नि; there were golden कुशस् touching the bank of the south नर्मदा; here अङ्गिरस्, once after Agnihotra saw the step to स्वर्ग or heaven; on the west is a tank, bordering on Kalinga another holy place. Sung even by शुक्र. {{F}}3:  वा. ७७. 4-१६; ११२. ३२.{{/F}}--a place sacred to शिव. M. १८१. २६.--a दानव. M. १७७. 8.--another term for Heaven whose lord was Indra. Br. IV. 6. ११ and ३२.--a son of शुक्राचार्य. भा. VII. 5. 1, ४८.--the son of Susandhi and father of सहस्वान्. Vi. IV. 4. १११.--the son of Sandhi and father of Mahasvat. भा. IX. १२. 7.--a देव गण with Yama as their lord. Br. III. 1. ५२.(I)--a daughter of the king of काशी noted for her beauty: and a queen of विचित्रवीर्य. भा. X. ६०. ४७; Vi. IV. २०. ३६.(II)--the saviour of the world, with her पुरुष Sada1s4iva. Br. IV. 8. ३३; १९. ८१; ३३. १७.(III)--the queen of वर्ष-r2tu. Br. IV. ३२. २९.(I)--an Asura follower of वृत्र in his battle with Indra. भा. VI. १०. १९.(II)--sacred to विश्वकाय. M. १३. २७.--R. from the slope of the Meru; flows through देवभ्राजम्, महाभ्राजम्, वैभ्राजम् enters सितोदा, the lake in the west, and then goes round the सुपक्ष hill, शिखिपर्वतम्, कङ्कम्, वैदूर्यपर्वतम्, Kapilam, गन्धमादनम्, पिञ्जरम्, Sarasam, कुमुदा- calam, Madhumanta, मुकुट, कृष्णश्वेतम्, सहस्रशिख- ram and पारिजात into the केतुमाल and falls into the western ocean. वा. ४२. ४४-57.(I)--the son of नाभाग. A devotee of Hari. The curse of दुर्वासस् proved ineffective in his case. Though lord of seven continents, अम्बरीष knew that glory was perishable. He devoted himself to the service of Hari, and got to know the power of His योग। A saintly king. Performed the अश्वमेध in a desert region so as to compel R. Sarasvati flow back towards it. Pleased with him, Hari presented his चक्र to him. He observed the द्वादसी व्रत, for a year at the end of which he gave gifts to ब्राह्- मणस् and was preparing to feed them. There then came दुर्वासस् who agreed to be fed. He went to the यमुना for bath and was engaged in contemplating on Brahman. The time for breakfast came and the sage did not return. [page१-089+ ३३] So the king broke his fast with only water and waited food expecting the sage's arrival. The sage on his return found that the king had broken his fast, and grew angry and created a flaming goddess to attack him. Hari's चक्र burnt her, turned towards the sage who ran everywhere and to the त्रिमूर्तिस् in vain. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. 4. १३-71; II. 7. ४४; Br. III. ३४. ३९; वा. ८८. १७१.{{/F}} Advised by Hari, the sage apologised to the king who prayed to the चक्र and set the sage at liberty. The king who had not taken food requested him to accept his hospitality which दुर्वासस् gladly did. Bless- ing the king, the sage went back to Brahmaloka. Later the king bestowed his kingdom on his sons and retired to the forest for a life of penance and prayer. {{F}}2:  भा. IX. 5 (whole).{{/F}} Had three sons विरूप and others. {{F}}3:  भा. IX. 6. 1; Br. III. ६३. 6, १७०-172; Vi. IV. 2. 6, 7; 4. ३६.{{/F}} A मन्त्रकृत् who made the १६ great gifts. {{F}}4:  M. १२. २०, ४५; १४५. १०२; २७४. ११.{{/F}}(II)--a son of मान्धातृ and बिन्दुमती. Adopted by his grandfather. Father of युवनाश्व. (not the युवनाश्व, father of मान्धातृ). भा. IX. 6. ३८; 7. 1; Br. III. ६३. ७२; वा. ८८. ७२; Vi. IV. 2. ६७; 3. 2.(III)--an अङ्गिरस and मन्त्रकृत्। Br. II. ३२. १०८; वा. ५९. ९९.(IV)--a काद्रवेय na1ga. Br. III. 7. ३६; वा. ६९. ७३.(V)--a son of Pulaha and क्षमा. वा. २८. २६.(II) (च्)--kingdom: Capital of Suvrata: Its king failed in hitting the fish target in लक्ष्मणा's स्वयम्- वर। भा. X. ८३. २३; Br. III. ७४. २२; M. ४८. २१; वा. ९९. २२.(I)--the name of the mahout of कुवलया- पीड killed by कृष्ण for leading it against him. भा. X. ४३. 2 and १४. [page१-090+ ३८]--a people; {{F}}1:  भा. X. ८३. २३.{{/F}} country of. {{F}}2:  Vi. II. 3. १८.{{/F}}--derived from भा। वा. १००. १८२.--is अङ्गारि Agni. Br. II. १२. ३०.--the wife of आयुष्मत्, and mother of ऋषभ (Hari). भा. VIII. १३. २०.(I)--Wife of शिव. {{F}}1:  भा. III. १२. १३.{{/F}} Daughter of दक्ष reborn of मेना. {{F}}2:  Ib. IV. 7. ५९.{{/F}} Pacified by Citraketu. {{F}}3:  Ib. VI. १७. १७.{{/F}} Surname of पार्वति and योगमाया. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. 2. १२.{{/F}} Gave भिक्षा to वामन. {{F}}5:  Ib. VIII. १८. १७.{{/F}} In her honour a festival was celebrated at a sacred spot called अम्बिकावन. In this Gopas participated. {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ३४. 1-3.{{/F}} Represents Soma while शिव is Agni. {{F}}7:  Br. II. २७. ११२; IV. १४. 6; १५. ५२; ४४. ८६.{{/F}} Worshipped in ceremonials before digging tanks. {{F}}8:  M. ५८. २६.{{/F}}(II)--a daughter of the King of काशि and wife of विचित्रवीर्य. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २२. २४. Vi. IV. २०. ३६.{{/F}} Mother of धृतराष्टृअ. {{F}}2:  भा. X. ४८. ३४.{{/F}}--a portion of the मन्त्रशास्त्र-- intended to condone the sin of drinking wine. Br. IV. 7. ७०.--a forest sacred to अम्बिका on the banks of the सरस्वती. Here was a festival in honour of शिव and देवी. To this, Nanda and others went. When he was there, [page१-091+ २५] Nanda was seized by a reptile, and was released by कृष्ण. {{F}}1:  भा. X. ३४. 1-१८.{{/F}} Before her marriage रुक्मिणी went to worship in this shrine. {{F}}2:  Ib. X. ५३. ३९.{{/F}}--a hill-citadel of शाकद्वीप. Br. II. १९. ८९.--an attribute of विष्णु. Br. IV. ३४. ८४.--a son of ब्रह्मधान. Br. III. 7. ९८.--a kingdom watered by the R. सीता. Br. II. १८, ४५.--a daughter of ऋषा: gave birth to four kinds of crocodiles. Br. III. 7. ४१४ and ४१६.(I)--a son of Jaya. भा. IX. १५. 2.(II)--a सुधर्माण god. Br. IV. 1. ६०. [page१-084+ २७](III)--a मन्त्रकृत् of the अङ्गिरस branch. वा. ५९. ९८.(I)--one of the three deva गणस् of the first epoch of सावर्णि Manu; {{F}}1:  Br. IV. 1. १२, १६ and १८; Vi. III. 2. १५.{{/F}} twenty branches mentioned. {{F}}2:  वा. १००. १३-17.{{/F}}(II)--a group of gods of the Raivata epoch, fourteen in number. Br. II. ३६. ५१ and ५४; Vi. III. 1. २१.--the son of Nikumbha and father of कृशाश्व. Vi. IV. 2. ४५-6.--a son of धर्मराज--Janaka and father of काण्डिक्य. Vi. VI. 6. 7-8.--a Marut of the second गण। Br. III. 5. ९३.--one of भण्ड's eight councillors. Br. IV. १२. १२.--a son of the fourth सवर्ण Manu (ऋतु Sa1varn2a Manu). Br. IV. 1. ९४; वा. १००. ९९. [page१-085+ २६](I)--A son of Sutapas and father of बृहद्- राज. भा. IX. १२. १२-13.(II)--the son of सुपर्ण and father of बृहद्भाज. (भरद्वाज-वा। प्।). Vi. IV. २२. 5-6; वा. ९९. २८६.--a तीर्थ, and its merits. M. १९१. ११८-25.--a शक्ति on the द्राविणिका mudra1. Br. IV. ३६. ७६.--in the नर्मदा. M. १९४. 1.--goddess enshrined at विपाश. M. १३. ३५. [page१-088+ ३३]--another name for ब्रह्मतीर्थम्: an elephant-like stone is established in the midst of waters here: fit for पिण्ड offering. M. १९१. १०५-7.(I)--an अमिताभ god. Br. II. ३६. ५३; वा. ६२. ४६.(II)--a son of भरताग्नि. वा. २९. 8.(III)--one of the seven divisions of प्लक्षद्वीप. भा. V. २०. 3.(I)--a शक्ति devi1; the goddess enshrined in a Vindhyan cave. Br. IV. ४४. ८४; M. १३. ४२.(II)--the goddess enshrined at वेण. M. १३. ४९; १२२. ३३.--R. of the प्लक्षद्वीप. Br. II. १९. १९; वा. ४९. १७; Vi. II. 4. ११.--a गुप्त शक्ति. Br. IV. १९. २०; ३६. ७१; ४४. १२०. [page१-087+ ३२](I)--a group of rain-giving नाडिस् with the sun. Br. II. २४. २७; वा. ५३. २०.(II)--one of the fourteen clans of Apsaras, born of waters. Br. III. 7. १९; वा. ६९. ५६.(I)--the juice from medicinal herbs of the Candra hill of प्लक्षद्वीप. Br. II. १९. 8; २४. २७ and ३१.(II)--nectar arising out of the churning of milk ocean by gods and Asuras. Others that came out of it were curds, liquor, Soma, लक्ष्मी, horse, Kaustubha, पारिजात, and lastly कालकूट. Then appeared Dhanvantari. Distri- bution of अमृतम् by मोहिनी, the form assumed by Hari to delude the Asuras. When राहु was seen, partaking of it, [page१-086+ २८] had his head cut off. Finding themselves deceived, the Asuras began war. M. 1. 9; २४९. १४ to the end; cha. २५० and २५१ (whole); वा. २३. ९०; ५२. ३७; ९२. 9; Vi. I. 9. ८०-111.--the fourth देवासुर battle, in which Indra defeated प्रःलाद. {{F}}1:  Br. III. ७२. ७३ and ७९; IV. 6. 7.{{/F}} Also the fourth of twelve incarna- tions of Hari by name Indra; with details of the battle. {{F}}2:  M. ४७. ४३ and ४८; २४९. ५१; वा. ९७. ७४. ७९.{{/F}}--gods of सावर्णि epoch. भा. VIII. १३. १२.--R. of क्रौञ्च dvi1pa. भा. V. २०. २१.--a शुक्रदेव. वा. ३१. 8.--an attribute of वारुणी. Br. IV. ३५. २९.(see अमृतम्)--suggested by Hari- Ajita to secure immortality for gods. It was to churn the क्षीरोद with Mandara as stick and वासुकि as rope. The Asuras agreed to aid the gods in securing अमृत। Hari took hold at first of the head, and when the Asuras protested, of the tail of वासुकि. Seeing exhaustion on the part of gods owing to obstacle of विघ्नेश, Hari propped up the Mandara hill, assuming the form of a tortoise. With continuous effort, the churning went on. First appeared हालाहल which was consumed by शिव on an appeal from the प्रजापतिस् and with the permission of पार्वती. Then came out कामधेनु which sages appropriated for agnihotra; उच्चैश्श्रवस्, a horse which Bali took; then ऐरावत: कौस्तुभ gem appropriated by Hari, then पारिजात, अप्सरस् women and then स्री married to Hari. Then came out वारुणीदेवी whom Asuras seized, then Dhanvantari with a pot of अमृत। There was then a rush on both sides to get the अमृत first when Hari assumed the form of मोहिनी and arrested their attention. Moved by her beauty, both gods and Asuras agreed to let her distribute the अमृत to all of them. She began with the gods and was serving them first. Noticing this राहु took the guise of a god. On being pointed out by the sun and moon, Hari cut off his head with his चक्र। The Asuras found that they had been deluded by Hari and set their face against Him. See अमृतम्। भा. VIII. 6. २१-25, ३१-32. Ib. ch. 7-9 (whole); Ib. १०. 1.(I)--Name of a god with the Hemanta sun; a तुषित god. Br. II. २३. १६; ३६. ११.(III)--the राक्षस who resides in the sun's chariot during the month of मार्गशीर्ष. Vi. II. १०. १३.(II)--an आदित्य. वा. ६६. ६६; Vi. I. १५. १३१. [page१-092+ ३६](I)--a playmate of क्र्ष्ण. भा. X. २२. ३१.(II)--the name of the sun in the month of Saha (मार्गशीर्ष). {{F}}1:  भा. XII. ११. ४१.{{/F}} the आदित्य of the month Citra, possessing ७००० rays. {{F}}2:  Br. II. २४. ३४ and ३८.{{/F}} An आदित्य. {{F}}3:  Br. III. 3. ६७; Vi. I. १५. १३१.{{/F}}(III)--one of the ten devas of the Harita गण। वा. १००. ८९.(IV)--The son of Purumitra and father of Sat- vata. Vi. IV. १२. ४३.(I)--son of असमञ्ज(sa)(s), devoted to grandfather Sagara. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. 8. १५; Br. III. ५१. ५१; ५२. 1; M. १२. ४३; वा. ८८. १६६; Vi. IV. 4. 7-३२.{{/F}} Went in search of the consecrated horse of Sagara, met Kapila and belauded his greatness. {{F}}2:  भा. IX. 8. १९. २७; Br. III. ५४. १७ and ५१.{{/F}} Pleased with him, Kapila sent back the horse, adding that the सागरस् would obtain release by the waters of the Ganges. {{F}}3:  भा. IX. 8. २८-29; Br. III. ५६. २९.{{/F}} Succeeded Sagara as king. {{F}}4:  भा. IX. 8. २८, ३१.{{/F}} Was engaged in penance to get the गङ्गा for the liberation of his uncles. Before he could achieve this, he died. His son was दिलीप. {{F}}5:  भा. IX. 9. 1-2; Br. III. ५६. ३०; ६३. १६५; Vi. IV. 4. ३४.{{/F}} Anointing him, अंशुमत् retired to the forest.(II)--one of the यादवस् deputed to go with कृष्ण's sacrificial horse with a view to its protection. भा. X. ८९. २२[3]. [page१-093+ ३२](III)--an आदित्य. M. 6. 4.(IV)--the son of पञ्चजन; married यशोदा, mindborn daughter of हविष्मन्त Pitr2s: Father of दिलीप. M. १५. १८.(V)--a son of कौशिक: in previous births born as चक्रवाक in मानस. M. २०. १८.(VI)--a horse of the moon's chariot. M. १२६. ५२.--१००० crores × नियुतम्। Br. IV. 2. ९८ and १०२.--a sage who had transcended the force of माया. (Burnouf makes this into two names अमूर्ति and Aya). भा. II. 7. ४४.(I)--one of the four sons of कुश. Br. III. ६६. ३२; वा. ९१. ६२.(II)--a son of अन्तिनार. M. ४९. 8.--a son of शूर and भोजा. Br. III. ७१. १४९ and १८९; M. ४६. 3.--a राजऋषि; a brother of Vasudeva. वा: ९६. १४८; वा. ९९. १२७.--son of Asmaki. वा. ९६. १८६. [page१-054+ ३५]--those who do not perform यज्ञस्, as opposed to अग्निहोत्रिन्स्। वा. ३०. 6.--a bath in the prescribed manner for a month in the प्र्याग; attained by (oneness with god- head). M. १०८. 2 & १४.--a daughter of दक्ष: a consort of कश्यप, and a mother goddess. Fond of eating. Br. III. 3. ५६; 7. ४६८; M. १७१. २९.--Had Araru and other four sons; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 6. ३०.{{/F}} mother of diseases. {{F}}2:  M. १७१. ५९.{{/F}}(I)--the son of उपदानवी: The वैभ्राज king of पाञ्चाल: Father of Brahmadatta. M. २१. ११.(II)--a Mauneya. वा. ६९. 1.(III)--a son of Trasu. वा. ९९. १३३.(IV)--a son of ऊर्ज and वसिष्ठ; a sage of XIth epoch of Manu. Vi. I. १०. १३: III. 2. ३१.--a R. of शाकद्वीप. भा. V. २०. २६.(I)--a Vasava, (तेजस्) has a son कुमार through स्वाहा. शाख, विशाख, and Naigameya were other sons (see अग्नि). Married शिवा, daughter of Hari and had two sons born with qualities of fire. Father of Skanda and सनत्कुमार. Br. III. 3. २१; M. 5. २१-5; २०३. 3; Vi. I. १५. ११०, ११५; वा. ६६. २०, २४.(II)--a chief monkey. Br. III. 7. २३५.(III)--a hill of the राक्षसस्. वा. ३९. ५३. [page१-053+ ३०](IV) (अग्नि)--one became threefold at the instance of पुरूरवस्; {{F}}1:  Vi. IV. 6. ९४.{{/F}} the presiding deity of स्वर्ण or gold; {{F}}2:  Vi. V. 1. १४.{{/F}} different kinds of; {{F}}3:  वा 53. 5.{{/F}} five kinds of, overcome by कृष्ण in बाण's war. {{F}}4:  Vi. V. ३३. २०.{{/F}}(V)--the son of निषध and father of Nabhas. Vi. IV. 4. १०६.(I)--a son of युधाजित्. Father of Nimna, and शिनि. A third son was वृष्णि. भा. IX. २४. १२-14; Br. III. ७१. २०.(II)--a son of Nighna: went to the forest for penance. M. १२. ४७-8.(III)--the youngest son of माद्री and वृष्णि (Sumitra-वि। प्।). Father of Nighna, शिनि, (Chini-वा। प्।) युधाजित्, वृषभ and क्षेत्र. M. ४५. 2-3, २२ & २५; वा. ९६. ९९; Vi. IV. १३. 9; १४. 1.(IV)--a son of माद्री. वा. ९६. १९; Br. I. 1. १२३. [page१-052+ २६](I)--a मध्यमाध्वर्यु। Br. II. ३३. १७.(II)--another name of God of Love, after he was burnt to ashes by शिव. M. 7. २३; २३. ३०; १५४. २७२; २९१. ३२; वा. १०४. ४८. [page१-049+ २८]--was the Apsaras sent by Indra to ruin Hari's तपस्। M. ६१. २२.--a शक्ति devi1. Br. IV. ४४. १२५.--a शक्ति devi1 on the 7th parva of Cakra- राजरथ. Br. IV. १९. २५; ४४. १२५.--sacred to Hari: to be begun on Sunday when the star Hasta, पुष्य or Punarvasu was in the ascendant: duration being १३ months: originally com- municated by Indra. M. ७०. ३३-62.--a शक्ति devi1 on the 7th parva of Cakra- राजरथ. Br. IV. १९. २५.--a शक्ति devi1 on the 7th parvan of the चक्रराजरथ. Br. IV. १९. २६.--a शक्ति devi1 on the 7th parvan of the चक्रराजरथ. Br. IV. १९. २५; ४४, १२४.--a शक्ति on the 7th parvan of the चक्रराजरथ. Br. IV. १९. २५; ४४, १२४.--a शक्ति devi1. Br. IV. ४४. १२४.--a शक्ति devi1. Br. IV. ४४. १२५.--the courtesan who observed the विभूति- द्वादशी-व्रतम् and became प्रीती, the co-wife with Rati, to the Lord of Love in her next birth. M. १००. १८ & ३२.--a शक्ति devi1 on the 7th parva of चक्रराज- ratha. Br. IV. १९. २५. [page१-050+ ३६](I)--the तामसी Kala1 of Hari. Followers of सात्वत तन्त्र designate him सङ्कर्षण. He bears the Earth on one of his १००० hoods. From between his agitated brows came out Rudra exhibiting in eleven forms. The नाग princes make obeisance to him for his blessings. He wears the वैजयन्ती garland. His glory is sung by नारद and Tumburu in the court of the Creator. Also known as शेष. {{F}}1:  भा III. २६. २५; IV. 9. १४; V. २५. 1-११; VII. 7. १०-11; Vi. II. 5. १३-27; V. १८. ५४.{{/F}} Identified with बलराम, the seventh son of देवकी. {{F}}2:  भा. X. 1. २४; 2. 5.{{/F}} At the time of the deluge, withdraws the universe unto him- self. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ६८. ४६.{{/F}} Identified with Hari; {{F}}4:  Ib. XI. १६. १९.{{/F}} a नाग; {{F}}5:  Br. IV. २०. ५३.{{/F}} एत्य्। of; {{F}}6:  M. २४८. ३८.{{/F}} बलराम, an incarnation of. {{F}}7:  Vi. V. २५. 3; ३५. 3; भा. I. १४. ३५.{{/F}}(II)--the sacred hill. Br. III. १३. ५८.(III)--a king and the son of वीतिहोत्र (वीर- hotra-वा। प्।). Father of Durjaya. Br. III. ६९. ५३; वा. ९४. ५३.--the wife of स्वायम्भुव Manu. M. 4. ३३.--A भार्गव gotrakara. M. १९५. २०.--a manifestation of Hari, as reposing on शेष. M. २७६. 8.--see गिरितनयाव्रतम्। M. ch. ६२. [page१-051+ २५](I)--see दधिवाहन। Br. III. ७४. १०२.(II)--the son of अङ्ग and father of Diviratha. Vi. IV. १८. १५; Br. III. ७४. १०३.--an apsaras. Br. III. 7. 5.--a क्षेत्रम् in the नर्मडा. After a bath here, there is no need to fear a hell. M. १९३. 1-3; १९४. १७.(I)--the son of Trasaddasyu and father of हर्यश्व (पृषदश्व-वि। प्।); killed by रावण in his दिग्- विजय। भा. IX. 7. 4; Vi. IV. 3. १७-18.(II)--the son of सम्भूत, killed by रावण. Br. III. ६३. ७४; वा. ८८. ७५-6.(III)--the son of Sarvakarman. M. १२. ४७.--a पिशाच clan. वा. ६९. २६४.--a follower of वृत्र in his battle with Indra. भा., VI. १०. १९, ३१.--a कश्यप and a त्रयार्षेय. M. १९९. १२.--the wife of the sage Atri (s.v.) and a daughter of Kardama (दक्ष-वा। प्। and वि। प्।). Mother of Datta, दुर्वासस्, and Soma; {{F}}1:  भा. I. 3. ११; III. २४: २२; IV. 1. १५; Vi. I. 7, 7, २५.{{/F}} mother of five आत्रेयस् and a daughter श्रुति. {{F}}2:  वा. १०. २८, ३१; २८. १८-9; Br. II. 9. ५२ and ५६; ११. २२.{{/F}}--the wife of बाणासुर. Illtreated by mother-in-law and sister-in-law she was initiated into a मन्त्र by नारद to control them and to be ever pleasing to her husband. By this she left the strict path of chastity; offered gifts to the sage who refused them on the plea of his plenty. M. १८७. २५-52. [page१-063+ २७]--an Apsaras. वा. ६९. ४८.(बहव--s.v)--son of Cakora and father of शिवस्वाति. भा. XII. 1. २६.--an Apsaras. वा. ६९. ४८.--the egg shaped universe; the व्यक्त-रूप of विष्णु described. See also पुरुष। Vi. I. 2. ५४-60.--consisting of भूर्लोक, भुवः, सुवर्, महर्, जन, तप and सत्य; all in the shape of an umbrella, each covered by ten प्रकृतिस् more than the preceding. {{F}}1:  वा. ५०. ७८-81.{{/F}} A shell of egg encircling the dark regions beyond the लोकालोक; encircled by water ten times the earth in space; waters encompassed on the outer surface by fire, fire by air; air by sky; sky by Anger of elements; and that by intellect; the last girt by chief principle, अनन्त। {{F}}2:  Vi. II. 4. ९५: 7. २२-5.{{/F}}--beyond आलोक. Here are the seven conti- nents and earth surrounded by a sea of clouds. {{F}}1:  Br. I. 1. ४३f; II. १९. १५४-5, १६०; २१. २४; III. ५९. २७; IV. 2. २३०-1.{{/F}} The golden egglike अण्ड emerges from ईश्वर's seed and attains योनि (प्रकृति), the latter being the embodiment of नारायण, in a period of a thousand years. It became heaven and earth, आकाश being in the middle. {{F}}2:  M. 2. २९-32; २४७. ४३; २४८. 1.{{/F}} The outside is covered with waters ten times the अण्ड-- covered by तेजस्,--successively covered by वायु, by आकाश, this by भूतादि; that by महत् and that in turn by अव्यक्त each ten times the mass of its predecessor. These are the seven प्रकृतिस्। अव्यक्त is क्षेत्र and ब्रह्मा क्सेत्रज्ञ। {{F}}3:  वा. 1. ५०-52; 4. ८२-9; १०१. २२७; Br. I. 3. २६.{{/F}} ब्रह्मा born of. {{F}}4:  वा. 9. १२२.{{/F}} Like the moon in कुम्भ राशि at the commencement of the शुक्ल पक्ष; there are several अण्डम्स्, each covered by seven characteristics of प्रकृति। {{F}}5:  वा. ४९. १४७-51.{{/F}}--R. of भारतवर्ष. भा. V. १९. १८.(I)--a son of सात्वत [सात्वती (Kausalya)]: suspected कृष्ण of having taken away Syamantaka. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २४. 6; Br. III. ७१. 1. ३६, ५३; वा. ९६. 2; Vi. IV. १३. 1.{{/F}} A महाभोज who married the daughter of कङ्क and was father of four sons, Kukura and others. {{F}}2:  M. ४४. ४८-61; Vi. IV. १४. १२.{{/F}}(II)--son of Anu and father of Dundubhi. भा. IX. २४. २०.(III)--a son of Viloma, and a friend of Tum- buru: also known as Danodakadundubhi. Br. III. ७१. ११८.(IV)--a commander of भण्ड. Br. IV. २१. ८२.(V)--the 8th among twelve incarnations, after the battle of that name. Here Trayambaka slew thou- sands of Asuras: {{F}}1:  M. ४७. ४४-50.{{/F}} in the वराह Kalpa. {{F}}2:  वा. ९७. ७५.{{/F}} [page१-067+ ४१](VI)--the asura killed by शिव: आडि and Baka were his sons; attempted to abduct the देवी in the presence of शिव in the महाकालवन of Avanti. Smitten by पाशु- pata, blood came out of his body, out of which were born numberless Andhakas (s.v.) who overpowered Rudra. The latter created a number of मातृस् who were not enough to meet them. वासुदेव was thought of, and he created one शुष्करेवति who drank off the blood of Andhakas. On his submission he was admitted to the group of गणेशस्. M. ५५. १६; १५६. ११-12; १७९. 2-४०; २५२. 5-१९.(VII)--an elder यादव advised in the council to secure the return of अक्रूर; it was adopted. Vi. IV. १३. ११४-137.(I)--a son of Dyutimat after whom the kingdom अन्धकार came to be known. Br. II. १४. २२, २५. [page१-068+ २७](II)--the eighth battle of Devas and Asuras. Br. III. ७२. ७५ & ८२; वा. ९७. ७५.(I) (च्)--a kingdom of क्रौञ्चद्वीप: also a name of the hill in that region. Br. II. १४. २५; १९. ६७ & ७२; M. १२२. ८१, ८५; वा. ४९. ६१, ६७.(II)--a Mt. in क्रौञ्चद्वीप. M. १२२. ८१; Vi. II. 4. ५०.(III)--a son of द्युतिमान्; after his name a Janapada. वा. ३३. २१, २३; Vi. II. 4. ४८.--a surname of शिव. Br. III. २५. १२.(I)--a community of the यादव tribe {{F}}1:  भा. I. ११. ११; १४. २५; II. 4. २०; वा. ८६. २८.{{/F}} defending द्वारका; at द्वारवती their overlord was Ugra- sena. {{F}}2:  भा. X. 1. ६९; ३९. २५; ४५, १५.{{/F}} Praise the heroic deeds of Hari. {{F}}3:  भा. IX. २४. ६३.{{/F}} Relieved by Kamsa's death. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ४५. १५.{{/F}} Ended their lives by fighting their kins- men. {{F}}5:  Ib. XI. २९. ३९; ३०. १८.{{/F}} कृष्ण, an Andhaka. {{F}}6:  Br. III. ६१. २३; ७१. ८५ & १४३-144.{{/F}} Kingdom of. {{F}}7:  M. ११४. ३६.{{/F}} Their line; {{F}}8:  M. ४४. ६१. ८५; ४७. ३३.{{/F}} fetch बलराम and कृष्ण to द्वारक. {{F}}9:  वा. ९६. ८४.{{/F}}(II)--the Asuras born of the blood of Andhaka Asura, hit by the पाशुपत of Rudra. To counter- act their evil propensities Rudra created a number of मातृस् who could not bring about the desired effect. Hence वासु- deva created a शुष्करेवती who brought about their des- truction by drinking off their blood. M. १७९. 7-३७.--one of the २८ hells. Those who do not follow the prescribed course of life and who have no sym- pathy for the sufferings they inflict on others are subject to affliction in this hell. भा. V. २६. 7 and १७.--one of २८ hells. Here the person who deceives the husband and robs him of his wife and property is made to suffer. भा. III. ३०. २८ & ३३; V. २६. 7 & 9.--a hell. Vi. I. 6. ४१.--one of the five देवीस् on the third parva of the किरिचक्र of ललिता. Br. IV. २०. 9 & ३८. [page१-069+ ३१](I)--born of दीर्घतमस् and Bali's wife. (Burnouf's reading--ओड्र). भा., IX. २३. 5.(II)--the son of दृषदश्व (वृषदश्व-वा। प्।). Br. III. ६३. २७; वा. ८८. २६.(III) (च्)--a Janapada under the देवरक्षितस्. वा. ९९. ३८५; Vi. IV. २४. ६४.--the शुङ्ग, ruled for 2 years. वा. ९९. ३३९.--succeeded the कण्व dynasty of kings. Thirty of them ruled for ४५६ years. Kingdom of: Br. III. ७३. १०९; ७४. १६०, १७०, १७८, १९७, २२९-30; वा. ९८. १०८; भा. XII. 1. २२-28.--a people of the southern country ruled for ३०० years; {{F}}1:  भा., XII. 1. २२; वा. ४५. १२७; ४७. ४४; ७८. ६९; ९९. २६८, ३६१.{{/F}} a sinful tribe got purified by praying to Hari; {{F}}2:  भा. II. 4. १८.{{/F}} defeated by Bharata. {{F}}3:  Ib. IX. २०. ३०.{{/F}} See आण्ध्रस्। {{F}}4:  M. ५०. ७६.{{/F}}--people of an eastern kingdom. Br. II. १६. ५३; वा. ४५. ११.--a Pravara. M. १९६. ३१.--a son of Raucya Manu. Br. IV. 1. १०४.--a son of Anala. M. २०३. 6.--a son of Raucya Manu. वा. १००. १०९.(I)--the son of Kakustha (पौरञ्जय-भा।) of पृथु. भा. IX. 6. २०; Br. III. ६३. २६; वा. ८८. २५; Vi. IV. 2. ३३.(II)--a son of आयु and father of शुद्ध. भा. IX. १७. 2 and ११; Br. III. ६७. 2; Vi. IV. 8. 3.(I)--the father of Vena; knew the power of कृष्ण's योग। {{F}}1:  भा. II. 7. ४३; Vi. I. १३. 6.{{/F}} A son of Ulmuka (Kuru and आग्नेयी-- [page१-020+ ३८] वि। प्।). His wife was सुनीथा, the cruel-faced daughter of मृत्यु. Finding the son's conduct cruel and unbecoming, he departed from the city. {{F}}2:  भा. IV. १३, १७-18.{{/F}} Once he performed the अश्व- मेध but the gods did not partake of the offerings. When he consulted the learned assembly, was advised by it that he could get a son by worshipping Hari. But the son born, Vena, was so mischievous that the king abandoned the king- dom in distress. Though messengers were deputed in search of him, his whereabouts remained untraced. {{F}}3:  Ib. IV. १३. २४-49.{{/F}} Devoted to Hari, sought refuge with Him. {{F}}4:  Ib. IV. २१. २८; X. ६०. ४१.{{/F}} According to the ब्रह्- माण्ड, मत्स्य and वायु पुराणस् he was the son of ऊरु and आग्नेयी. {{F}}5:  Br. II. ३६. १०८ & १२६; वा. ६२. ९२-3; M. 4. ४४.{{/F}} A प्रजापति of the family of स्वायम्भुव Manu (of the Atri line. वा।) {{F}}6:  M. १०. 3-4; वा. ६२. १०७.{{/F}}(II)--A क्षेत्रज son of Bali: born of दीर्घत- mas. Father of खनपान (अनपान-वा।). {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २३. 5 & 6; M. ४८. २५ & 9; वा. ९९. २८, ८५; Br. III. ७४. २७, ८७.{{/F}} After him was the अङ्गदेश. {{F}}2:  Vi. IV. १८. १३-14.{{/F}} Father of दधिवाहन, born without अपान (anus). {{F}}3:  Br. III. ७४. १०२; वा. ९९. १००.{{/F}} The last king of his line was वृषसेन. {{F}}4:  Vi. IV. १८. २९.{{/F}}(III) (च्)--An eastern kingdom. Its king got war elephants from Devas. Br. II. १६. ५१; १८. ५१; III. 7. ३४९; ७४. २१३; M. ११४. ४४; १२१. ५०; वा. ४७. ४८; ९९. ४०२.(IV)--a son of हविर्धान. M. 4. ४५.(V)--the son of विश्वजित् Janamejaya and father of कर्ण. M. ४८. १०२; वा. ९९. ११२. [page१-021+ ३१]a southern country. Br. II. १६. ५९.(I) (मर्स्)--an inauspicious planet; tra- verses each of the signs of the zodiac once in three fortnights. {{F}}1:  भा. V. २२. १४.{{/F}} The planet with Skanda as presiding deity; fed by सम्पद्- वसु ray of the sun, attains लौहितम् स्थानम् or the लोहित region. Consists of nine rays and looks in size equal to बृहस्पति: Placed above शुक्र at a distance of २००,000 योजनस्। Also known as लोहित and वक्र। {{F}}2:  Br. II. २४. ४८, ७०, ८२, ९५ & १०५; Vi. II. 7. 8-9.{{/F}} The first of Planets, originally वीरभद्र who destroyed दक्ष's sacri- fice; son of mother Earth; fought with Soma. {{F}}3:  M. २३. ४०; ७२. १६ & २३; ९३. १३; १३३. २०.{{/F}} Day sacred to. {{F}}4:  M. १९३. 8-9.{{/F}} व्रतम् in honour of, conduces to health and prosperity; the शूद्रस् observe it; described by शुक्र in detail. {{F}}5:  M. ७२. 5-३६.{{/F}} The तनु of शर्व (Agni) by विकेशि. {{F}}6:  Br. II. १०. ७८; वा. २७. ५१.{{/F}} Born in आषाढ। {{F}}7:  Br. II. २४. ८२, १३३.{{/F}}(II)--a Rudra. Br. III. 3. ७०; वा. ६६. ६९.(III)--a name of Skanda. वा. ५३. ३१; ११२. ५२.--name of a hell. Br. IV. ३३. ६१.--sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ३५.--a R. in the भद्राश्व continent. वा. ४३. २६.--a place sacred to अङ्गारक on the R. नर्मदा. M. १९०. 9; १९१. ५९-60.--a तीर्थम् sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ५१. [page१-022+ ३५](I)--a son of लक्ष्मण. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. ११. १२; Vi. IV. 4. १०४.{{/F}} Capital कारयन in the अङ्गद kingdom. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ६३. १८८; वा. ८८. १८७-8.{{/F}} (कारपथ-वा।).(II)--a son of वालि: married the eldest daughter of Mainda; father of Dhruva. {{F}}1:  Br. III. 7. २१९-20.{{/F}} Present at राम's अभिषेक। {{F}}2:  Vi. IV. 4. १००.{{/F}} Helped राम in his expedition to लङ्का. {{F}}3:  भा. IX. १०. १९-20.{{/F}} Bore the sword when Bharata carried the पादुका of राम. {{F}}4:  Ib. IX. १०. ४४.{{/F}}(III)--a kingdom with its capital कारयन. Br. III. ६३. १८९.(IV)--a son of बृहती. Br. III. ७१. २५६; वा. ९६. २४७.--the residence of हृद्देवी and others. Br. IV. ३७. ४०.--the capital of कारपथ des4a(?) वा. ८८. १८८.--a part of जम्बूद्वीप inhabited by Mlecchas. वा. ४८. १४-18.--a daughter of ब्रह्मा. M. 3. १२.--A northern kingdom. Br. II. १६. ४९.--a tribe. वा. ४७. ४३.--kingdom of. M. १२१. ४३.--wife of वामन, the elephant. Br. III. 7. ३३९.--killed by Arjuna. Vi. V. ३८. ४७.(I)--a मानस son of ब्रह्मा, born of his mouth. {{F}}1:  भा. III. १२. २२, २४; Br. II. ३२. ९६; M. 3. 6; 5. १४; १५. १६.{{/F}} Married श्रद्धा, (पित्री-वि। प्।) a daughter of Kardama. {{F}}2:  भा. III. २४. २२; Vi. I. 7. 5, 7; १५. १३६.{{/F}} Father of four daughters. His two sons were Utathya and बृहस्पति. {{F}}3:  भा. IV. 1. ३४-5; M. १०२. १९; १०६. १७.{{/F}} Had not yet realised the Supreme Being. {{F}}4:  भा. IV. २९. ४३.{{/F}} With his pupils visited भीष्म lying on his bed of arrows. {{F}}5:  भा. I. 9. 8.{{/F}} Came to see परीक्षित् practising प्रायोपवेश। {{F}}6:  Ib. I. १९. 9.{{/F}} Married two of the daughters of दक्ष. These were स्वधा and सती. His sons were पितृ and अथर्वान्गिरस्. A प्रजापति. {{F}}7:  Ib. VI. 6. 2, १९; Br. II. ३७. ४५; M. १६७. ४३; १७१. २७; वा. 1. १३७; 3. 3; २५. ८२; ३०. ४८; ६५. ९७-101.{{/F}} Once [page१-023+ ३९] called on Citraketu, the king of शूरसेनस्, who was childless and blessed his first queen with a son. The jealous co-wives of the king administered poison to the baby and it died. Finding the king and queen weeping bitterly, अङ्गिरस् accompanied by नारद came to the palace. These two sages appeared there in अवधूत form. अङ्गिरस् consoled the king and cited the story of King Bhoja. {{F}}8:  भा. VI. १४. १४-30, ३७-61; १५. १०; १२, १७-26 [1-4].{{/F}} Went back to ब्रह्मलोक with नारद. {{F}}9:  Ib. VI. १६. २६.{{/F}} Was appointed by King Rathi- kara to produce sons on his wife. {{F}}१०:  Ib. IX. 6. 2.{{/F}} The sage presiding over the month of नभ। {{F}}११:  Ib. XII. ११. ३७; M. १२६. १०.{{/F}} Was present at the anointing of वामन. {{F}}१२:  भा. VIII. २३. २०.{{/F}} Came to see कृष्ण at स्यमन्तपञ्चक. {{F}}१३:  Ib. X. ८४. 5.{{/F}} Went to द्वारका to ask कृष्ण to go back to वैकुण्ठ. {{F}}१४:  Ib. XI. 6. 2.{{/F}} Had another son named Samvarta (s.v.). {{F}}१५:  Ib. IX. 2. २६.{{/F}} Cursed विद्याधर Sudars4ana (s.v.) to become a reptile for mocking at him. {{F}}१६:  Ib. X. ३४. १३-15.{{/F}} Performed a sacrifice when शरयाति explained on the rituals of the second day. {{F}}१७:  Ib. IX. 3. 1.{{/F}} Stood near the wheel of the chariot त्रिपुरारि in defence; served प्रयाग and lived in Benares; a महऋषि and मन्त्रकृत्। {{F}}१८:  M. १३३. २०, ६१, ६७; १४५. ९०, १०१; १४६. १७; १८४. १५; १९२. १०; वा. ५९. ९८.{{/F}}(II)--a son of Ulmuka. भा. IV. १३. १७.(III)--author of अङ्गिरस् कल्प; a master of अथर्व सम्हिता। भा. XII. 7. 4.(IV)--one of the sages who left for पिण्डारक. भा. XI. 1. १२. [page१-024+ ३५](V)--born in वारुणि यज्ञ by an oblation in the अङ्गार (fuel) from it, and hence the name. Agni there- fore claimed him to be his son, and so अङ्गिरसस् became आग्नेयस्. भारद्वाजस् and Gautamas belong to this line; performed penance at अमरकण्टक, praised Soma and spoke on the श्राद्ध कल्प to his son शंयु at दारुवन. {{F}}1:  Br. II. 9. १८, २३; III. 1. २१, ३९-40, १०१; १३. 5; २०. १९; IV. 2. ३३ and ४७; वा. ६४. 2; ७३, ६३; ७५. ५६; ७७. 5; ८८. 7; Br. II. २७. १०३.{{/F}} Married सुरूपा, daughter of मरीचि and had ten sons. {{F}}2:  वा. ६५. १०५-8; M. १९५. 9; १९६. 1; २४५. ८६.{{/F}}(VI)--A son of कश्यप; married स्मृति and had two sons and four daughters; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ११. १७; 9. ५५; वा. २८. १४.{{/F}} flourished in स्वायम्- bhuva antara; a देवऋषि. {{F}}2:  Ib. ३१. १६; ३०. ८६; Br. II. ११. १७; १३. ५३.{{/F}}(VII)--with the sun for the months Nabho- nabha (Nabha-वि। प्।). Br. II. २३. 9; Vi. II. १०. 9.(VIII)--the name of व्यास in the fourth द्वापर; अवतार् of the lord Suhotri. वा. २३. १२६.(IX)--one of the आत्रेयस् of the Raivata antara. {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३६. ६२.{{/F}} Sprung out of charcoal in which ब्रह्मा offered a second oblation: adopted by Agni as his son and hence अङ्गिरस् called आग्नेयस्. {{F}}2:  Ib. III. 1. ४०-42.{{/F}} See अङ्गिरस्। V.(X)--a son of ऋषभ, the ninth अवतार् of महेश्वर. वा. २३. १४४.(XI)--A son of Atharva: {{F}}1:  वा. २९. 9.{{/F}} known as Atharvan. {{F}}2:  Ib. ६५. ९७; Br. I. 5. ७०.{{/F}} [page१-025+ २५](I)--a son of आग्नेयि and ऊरु (Kuru-वि। प्।). M. 4. ४३; Vi. I. १३. 6.(II)--the fourth part of अथर्व वेद। Vi. III. 6. १४.--name given to a portion of अथर्व वेद। Br. II. ३५. ६२ and ८२; वा. ६१. ५४.--born of रथीतर's wife and अङ्गिरस्. Hence क्षत्रिय-चुम्-ब्राह्मण. भा. IX. 6. 3.(I)--the name of a देवगण. Br. III. 1. ५०.(II)--the thirty-three sages, all मन्त्रकृत्स्। वा. ५९. १०२.--a R. of प्लक्षद्वीप. भा. V. २०. 4.--is eight times a यव। For other details see मत्स्य प्। १२ अङ्गुलस्: 1 वितस्ति। २१ अङ्गुलस्: 1 रत्नि २४ अङ्गुलस्: 1 हस्त Br. II. 7. ९६; IV. 2. १२१; M. २५८. १८-21; वा. 8. १०२; १०१. १२१ and १२२.--a pupil of कृत. Br. II. ३५. ५३; वा. ६१. ४६. [page१-026+ २८]--rings to be presented in connection with वृक्षोत्सव। M. ५९. १४.--gifts, receiving of gifts, होम, feeding, बलि offering, all to be done. वा. ७९. ८८.--the continent lying round श्याम hill. M. १२२. २३.--a son of देवानीक and father of पारियात्र. भा. IX. १२. 2.--a son of first सावर्ण Manu Br. IV. 1. ६५.--a son of Arka Agni. वा. २९. ४०; Br. II. १२. ४३.(I)--The God of Wind invoked. {{F}}1:  भा. III. 6. १६.{{/F}} A surname of वायु; {{F}}2:  Br. II. २५. १२.{{/F}} father of भीमसेन. {{F}}3:  Vi. IV. १४. ३५; भा. IX. २२. २७.{{/F}}(II)--a वासव: married शिवा and had two sons --Manojava and अविज्ञतगति. See इशान। Br. II. १०. ८०; III. 3. २१; M. 5. २१; २०३. 3; वा. ६६. २०, २५; Vi. I. १५. ११०, ११४.(III)--The वायु पुराण narrated by Wind-god with समास बन्धस् and rhythm; {{F}}1:  वा. 3. 8.{{/F}} २३,000 stanzas. {{F}}2:  वा. १०४. 7.{{/F}}(IV)--a son of कृष्ण and मित्रविन्दा. भा. X. ६१. १६.(I)--an ऐश्वर्य, one of the eight kinds; {{F}}1:  Br. I. 2. ३९; II. २९. ८२; III. 3. ६५; ३६. १७; ६७. १६; वा. 2. ३९.{{/F}} the first to be attained by the yogin; {{F}}2:  वा. १३. 3 and १०.{{/F}} leading to siddhi. {{F}}3:  वा. ५७. ७६; ९२. १५.{{/F}}(II)--Siddhi देवी on the 9th parvan of Cakra- राजरथ; one of Uttama siddhis. Br. IV. १९. 4; २५. ५९; ३५. १०४; ३६. 5; ४४. १०८.(I)--One of the four forms of Hari. {{F}}1:  भा. 1. 5. ३७; Vi. १६. १८; X. १६. ४५; ४०. २१; XII. ११. २१. M. २७६. 9.{{/F}} In- voked as a principal divinity. Source of all sounds (शब्द- योनि); presiding over the mind as fourth in order. {{F}}2:  भा. III. 1. ३४.{{/F}} The supreme ruler of all senses. {{F}}3:  Ib. III. २६. २८; IV. २४. ३६.{{/F}} Created specially in the battle of ललिता with भण्ड. {{F}}4:  Br. IV. २९. १२८.{{/F}}(II)--the son of Pradyumna and Rukma- vati; carried away by air by चित्रलेखा, to the harem of the daughter of बणा at her instance. For him बाण had his arms reduced from thousand to two. Married रोचना, grand-daughter of Rukmin at भोजकट to which कृष्ण, बलराम and others went. Came back to द्वारका with his newly wedded wife. {{F}}1:  भा. X. ६१. १८. २३[9], २५-26 & ४०.{{/F}} Seen in a dream by उषा. Picture of him drawn by चित्रलेखा, who made him enjoy उषा's [page१-055+ ४२] company at शोणितपुर. बाण came to know of this and imprisoned him to the great regret of his daughter. {{F}}2:  