; १०. ७९-80; वा. ७०. ८४; ९१. ४३.--father of Udaka and वारुणी. Br. II. ३६. १०४.--forest deities in the Himalayas. Br. III. २२. २७.--a son of अनायुषा and father of the great asura Dhundhu. Br. III. 6. ३१.--a measurement of length equal to a cubit. Br. II. १७. २६; III. ११. 7; वा. ४६. २६; ७४. 7.--the son of अजातशत्रु and the father of Uda- yana. Vi. IV. २४. १५-16.--the द्विजस् of: became व्रात्यस् after Puram- jaya's days: {{F}}1:  भा. XII. 1. ३८.{{/F}} a western kingdom sacred to ललिता. {{F}}2:  Br. II. १६. ६२; IV. ४४. ९४.{{/F}}--१०,00,००,000 (१० crores). वा. १०१. ९५.--a tribe, of the south, fought with their kins- men and ended themselves. {{F}}1:  भा. XI. ३०. १८; M. ११४. ५१; वा. ४५. १३१.{{/F}} Country of. {{F}}2:  Vi. II. 3. १६.{{/F}} [page१-112+ ३५]--the R. sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ३८.--of Hari. Worship of Hari's image is said to promote one's welfare. Some special places devoted to. This form is prevalent even in त्रेता युग; {{F}}1:  भा. VII. १४. २८-40.{{/F}} to be worshipped in the पयोव्रत। {{F}}2:  Ib. VIII. १६. २८.{{/F}} अर्चा is राजस। Mere idol worship condemned. When proper; {{F}}3:  Ib. III. २९. 9, २१-25{{/F}} अर्चा may be of gold, silver, [page१-105+ ३२] of earth or water or other substance. {{F}}4:  Ib. IV. 8. ५६.{{/F}} उपासना of, a means to concentration on the Absolute. {{F}}5:  Ib. XI. २०. २४.{{/F}} Worship may be offer- ed on the ground, fire, sun, waters, ब्राह्मण or any other thing. Image of eight kinds including stone, wood and metal; may be moveable or immoveable. The mode in worship. Subsidiary worship to the ornaments, imple- ments and attendants on Hari. Founding a shrine, flower- garden and instituting festivals form part of the worship. {{F}}6:  Ib. XI. २७. 9-४३,{{/F}} Only people of little तपस् are engaged in अर्चा, this being regarded inferior to worshipping Brahman. {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ८४. १०; ८६. ५५.{{/F}}--founding of shrines is a form of भक्ति to Hari. भा. XI. ११. ३८.--(see सुवर्चला--Burnouf)(I)--the female child born from the arms of Vena, churned by the sages. An अंश of लक्ष्मी, and a queen of पृथु. {{F}}1:  भा. IV. १५. 5-6.{{/F}} Follows पृथु to the forest and at his death performs सति, evoking praise from goddesses. {{F}}2:  Ib. IV. २३. १९-28.{{/F}}(II)--Wife of क्र्शाश्व and mother of धूम्र- केश. भा. VI. 6. २०.--a मन्त्रकार and आत्रेय. वा. ५९. १०४. [page१-106+ ४८]--a सुतप god. Br. IV. 1. १५; वा. १००. १५.--a daughter of सारण. Br. III. ७१. १६८; वा. ९६. १६६.--one of the seven sons of वसिष्ठ. वा. २८. ३६.--one of the four sons of the ३३र्द् Kalpa. वा. २३. ५९.--from हिरण्यगर्भ: two parts, male and female; the male half divided into eleven parts called Rudras by crying and running (oozing); each became a गणेश्वर; the female half came to be divided into two, शुक्ल (right) and कृष्ण (left); from her came प्रज्ञा and श्री and these in turn spread over the whole world in thousand ways. वा. 9. ७५-98; ४१. ३६.--शिव became this by worshipping शक्ति: {{F}}1:  Br. II. २७. ९८; IV. 5. ३०; ४४. ४८.{{/F}} Image of; with details of dress and ornaments. {{F}}2:  M. ६०. २५; १९२. २८; २६०. 1-१०.{{/F}}--आत्रेय गोत्रकरस्। M. १९७. 3.--one of the ten पीठस् for images. This yields one a number of sons. M. २६२. 7 and ११, १८.--a मन्त्रकृत्। M. १४५. १०७.--a name of शिव. वा. ९७. १७२.--An attendant on Hari. भा. II. 9. १४.--a group of people defending द्वारका, and related to पाण्डवस्. भा. I. ११. ११; १४. २५. [page१-114+ ३२](I)--a king of Konka, Venka, and कुटक led astray by the teachings of ऋषभ. Gave up his स्वधर्म and adopted the path of heretics. भा. V. 6. 9.(II)--a name of शिव. Br. III. ७२. १७३.--the Asuras who performed penance on the नर्मदा, were deluded by विष्णु मायामोह to give up Vedic path and take to other non-Vedic doctrines. Vi. III. १८. १३.--आर्षेय pravara (अङ्गिरस्). M. १९६. १०.--the son of त्वष्टा. वा. ३३. ५९.--A विघ्ननायक. Br. IV. २७. ८२.--one of the two अमिताभ गणस्। वा. १००. १६.--a son of कृष्ण and भद्रा. भा. X. ६१. १७.(I)--a son of श्वफल्क and गान्दिनी. भा. IX. २४. १६; Br. III. ७१. १११.(II)--a son of Upamadgu. Vi. IV. १४. 9.(III)--a son of Kuru वा. ६२. १२; ९९. २१८.(I)--a son of गान्दिनी. वा. ९६. ११०.(II)--a son of Upamadgu. Vi. IV. १४. 9.--a बृहद्रथ king who ruled for ५० years; with him were ३२ kings commencing with बृहद्रथ altogether a १००० years of rule. Br. III. ७४. १२१; वा. ९९. ३०८. [page१-098+ ३२]--the son of शिवस्वाति and father of गोमती- putra. भा. XII. 1. २६.--a daughter of दक्ष, one of कश्यप's wives and mother of Kinnaras and Gandharvas; {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 6. २५, २९; M. 6. 1 and ४५; १४६. १८; वा. ६६. ५५; Vi. I. २१. २५.{{/F}} expert in music. {{F}}2:  Br. III. 3. ५६; 7. ४६७.{{/F}}(I)--a son of Danu. {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 6. ३०.{{/F}} Took part with Bali in the देवासुर war. {{F}}2:  Ib. VIII. १०. २२.{{/F}} A दानव with मनुष्य धर्म। {{F}}3:  वा. ६८. १५.{{/F}} Known for music. {{F}}4:  वा. ६९. ७३.{{/F}}(II)--the son of Mitra and रेवती. भा. VI. १८. 6.(III)--an asura friend of कंस. {{F}}1:  भा. X. 2. 1; Vi. V. 1. २४; 4. 2; १२. २१.{{/F}} Came once to the व्रज of Nanda in the form of a terrific bull. Gopas and gopis got afraid as also the cattle there; attacked कृष्ण who vanquished him. {{F}}2:  भा. X. ३६. 1-१६; ४६. २६; II. 7. ३४; Br. III. ७३. १००; IV. २९. १२४; Vi. V. १४ (whole); १५. 1; २९. 4.{{/F}}(IV)--a son of Vaivasvata Manu. M. ११. ४१; Vi. III. 1. ३३.(V)--a son of Bali; took part in the तारकामय war. M. १७३. २०; १७७. 7.(VI)--one of the nine sons of Manu; killed by कृष्ण. वा. ८५. 4; ९८. १००.--the mother of eight apsaras. वा. ६९. ४८.--indicators of death; he who would not see अरुन्धती, Dhruva and the shadow of Soma would not live beyond ११ months; and so on; dreams, interpretation of. वा. ch. १९ (whole).--A son of अटमान [पटुमान् (वि। प्।)] and father of हालेय (हालाहल-वि। प्।) भा. XII. 1. २५. Vi. IV. २४. ४६.(I)--the son of Purujit [Kurujit (वि। प्।)] and father of श्रुतायुस्. भा. IX. १३. २३; Vi. IV. 5. ३१. [page१-099+ २८](II)--an Asura resident of Tripura. Parti- cipated in the देवासुर war between Bali and Indra. भा. VIII. 6. ३१; १०. २२.(III)--the Gandharva presiding over the month of पुष्य; {{F}}1:  भा. XII. ११. ४२.{{/F}} called on परीक्षित् practising प्रायोपवेश। {{F}}2:  Ib. I. १९. 9.{{/F}}(IV)--(Apratiman) ग्रामणि with the He- manta sun: married four daughters of दक्ष. Br. II. २३. १८; ३७. ४५; M. 5. १३; १४६. १६; वा. ५२. १८; ६३. ४२; ६५. ११२.(V)--a प्रजापति: {{F}}1:  Br. III. 1. ५४; वा. ६३. ४२.{{/F}} married the four daughters of दक्ष and became father of १६ children. {{F}}2:  Vi. I. १५. १०३, १३४.{{/F}}(VII)--the यक्ष who resides in the sun's chariot during the month of पौष। Vi. II. १०. १४.--a second wife of Sagara by name Sumati (s.v.); sister of सुपर्ण. Br. III. ६३. १५५; वा. ८८. १५६, १५९.--a son of the elephant मृग. Br. III. 7. ३३३. [page१-100+ २६]--served as calf to milk the earth. Br. II. ३७. १७-18.(I) (कार्तवीर्य)--son of कृतवीर्य. Lord of seven islands and of हैहयष्, सम्राट् and चक्रवर्तिन्। By the grace of Hari he got १००० arms and enjoyed अष्ट- ऐश्वर्यस्। Learnt the merit of योग from दत्तात्रेय. Ruled in peace for ८५,000 years {{F}}1:  भा. IX. १५. १७-19; २३. २४-27; Br. III. ३०. 4. ७५; ६९. 9, ४९, ५६; Vi. IV. ११. ११-21; M. ४३. १५; वा. ९४. १०.{{/F}} and was ambitious to have more territorial possessions. {{F}}2:  भा. XII. 3. 9; I. १२. २१.{{/F}} Was engaged in water-sports with women wearing the garland of Vaijayanti. {{F}}3:  भा. IX. १५. २०.{{/F}} Imprisoned रावण in his capital माहिष्मती and released him on an appeal from Pulasya. {{F}}4:  भा. IX. १५. २१-22; Br. III. ३३. ५०; M. ४३. ३७-40;{{/F}} In the course of a hunting expedi- tion, he came to the hermitage of Jamadagni who enter- tained him with the help of his कामधेनु. The king, envious of the sage's prosperity, desired its possession, and on being refused by the sage, he took the cow by force. {{F}}5:  भा. IX. १५. २३-26; Br. III. २६. 7 whole chapter, chaps. २७ and २८; ३०. 4.{{/F}} परसुराम who was away, heard the story on his return, went to Arjuna's capital, cut off his head with his axe after a terrible battle in which मत्स्यराज took part and recovered the cow and the calf. {{F}}6:  भा. IX. १५. २७-36; Br. III. ३०. 5-१५; ३२. ६१; ३८ 8, २७; ४०. १९; ४१, ३७, ३८; ४४. १४; ४७. ६३, ८८.{{/F}} Jamadagni regretted his son's action as the king was a नरदेव, and killing him was an offence greater than ब्राह्मनिचिदे. {{F}}7:  भा. IX. १५. ३७-41; Br. III. ३८. 8.{{/F}} Had १००० (?) sons, (१०० sons) all of whom except five died in battles. These sons killed Jamadagni when राम and his brothers were gone out. {{F}}8:  M. ४३. ४६-51;{{/F}} These five were great warriors. {{F}}9:  भा. IX. १६. 9-१२.{{/F}} His minister was the evil Candragupta and the पुरोहित, Garga. {{F}}१०:  Br. III. २८. ३१-63.{{/F}} Incarnation of विष्णु Cakra; {{F}}११:  Br. III. ३७. २७-28; ४०. ६६.{{/F}} to his family belonged तालजङ्घ; {{F}}१२:  वा. ९४. ५०.{{/F}} performed thousands of यज्ञस् with golden यूपस् and वेदिस्, which were attended by gods. A राजऋषि, पशुपाल, क्षेत्रपाल. {{F}}१३:  M. ४३. १३-25.{{/F}} Defeated कर्कोटक's son at माहिष्मती and established his city on the banks of the Nar- मदा. Could control the waters of the नर्मदा and the fury of the ocean: a terror to Asuras in पाताल as also to राक्षसस् and Uragas. Defeated रावण and released [page१-107+ ४०] him at the intervention of Pulastya: burnt down the Hema- तालवनम्, residence of आपव and was cursed that a भार्- gava and a ब्राह्मण would chop off his १००० hands. {{F}}१४:  M. ४३. २५-43; वा. ९४. 9-२४.{{/F}} A गाथ in his honour by नारद. {{F}}१४: (a) Vi. IV. ११. १६.{{/F}} Once आदित्य in the guise of a ब्राह्मण asked to be fed at the expense of all im- mobile things (स्थावर) in the world and it was granted. This included आपव's hermitage also. {{F}}१५:  Br. III. ७०. 3-१०; M. ४४. 3-१३.{{/F}} Performed the सौभाग्यशयन-व्रतम् and made the १६ gifts. {{F}}१६:  M. ६०. ४९.{{/F}}(II)--a son of Raivata Manu. भा. VIII. 5. 2.(III)--a पाण्डव, son of Indra and कुन्ती and father of श्रुतकीर्ति. Had a son इरावान् by उलूपि and another son बब्रुवाहन by the daughter of मणिपुरपति. Father of Abhimanyu by सुभद्रा. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २२. २९-33; Br. III. ७१. १५४ and १७८; Vi. IV. १४. ३५; २०. ४०; V. १२. १७-24; ३५. २८.{{/F}} Promised द्रौपदी to cut off अश्वथाम's head and place it before her for his killing her sons when asleep. अश्वथाम heard this and ran for escape. Arjuna pursued him. Unwilling to slay the son of his preceptor, he bound him with ropes and took him to his queen's presence. She requested Arjuna to release him on the ground that he was a ब्राह्मण, a son of the guru, and for the sake of his old mother गौतमी. भीम was not for the release. But Arjuna took the hint from कृष्ण, and after depriving him of his crest-jewel, banished him. {{F}}2:  भा. I. 7. १५-57.{{/F}} Accompanied युधिष्ठिर to see भीष्म on the eve of his death. {{F}}3:  Ib. I. 9. 3.{{/F}} A playmate of कृष्ण. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. २२. ३१.{{/F}} Had a chariot with monkey standard. When he was once in the forest with कृष्ण, they met कालिन्दी, daughter of the Sun god anxious to marry कृष्ण. When Arjuna burnt खाण्डव, कृष्ण was his charioteer. Drove away the princes who attacked [page१-108+ ४६] कृष्ण returning with सत्या of कोशल. {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ५८. 4, १३-25, ५४.{{/F}} Commended by Indra to कृष्ण's protection. {{F}}6:  Ib. X. [६७ (V) ३६]; Vi. V. १३. १७-18.{{/F}} Consoled by कृष्ण when banished to the forest. {{F}}7:  भा. X. ६४. 9.{{/F}} A great name among the Kurus. {{F}}8:  Ib. X. ६८. २८.{{/F}} Joy at कृष्ण's visit to Indraprastha. By burning the forest he released Maya and enjoyed कृष्ण's company. Went to the eastern countries. Went again with कृष्ण and भीम disguised as a ब्राह्मण to Girivraja. Revealed himself before जरासन्ध who thought that he was not his equal. Returned after जरासन्ध's fall. {{F}}9:  Ib. X. ७१. २२-30, ४५-46; ७२. १३-16, २९ and ३२; ७३. ३१ and ३४.{{/F}} Entertained elders at the राजसूय of Yudhisthira. On seeing the enemy's army in the battle-field, his teachers, kith and kin among them, he expressed to कृष्ण his reluctance to fight them. कृष्ण taught him the truth (गीता), showed him his विश्वरूप and roused him to action. He fought, कृष्ण serving as charioteer. {{F}}१०:  Ib. X. ७५. 5; [७८. (V), २१-25]; XI. १६. 6-8.{{/F}} Victory due to कृष्ण. {{F}}११:  Ib. IX. २४. ६७.{{/F}} Heard of Abhimanyu's death and vowed to kill Jaya- dratha the following day, which he did. {{F}}१२:  Ib. X. ७८. [३१-35].{{/F}} Was taken by कृष्ण to कैलास where शिव blessed him. Took part in the स्वयम्वरम् of लक्ष्मणा. His arrow touched the fish target but did not hit it. {{F}}१३:  Ib. X. ८३. २४.{{/F}} In the course of his pilgri- mage he heard at प्रभास that his uncle's daughter Subha- द्रा was being proposed by बलराम to Duryodhana. He wished to marry her, and with this object spent four months in द्वारक as त्रिदण्डी ascetic. At this time राम invited him one day for भिक्षा। When he and सुभद्रा met, both exchanged their love by their eyes. On a day of festive occasion सुभद्रा came out, when Arjuna carried her off in a chariot with the approval of कृष्ण. राम protested but कृष्ण pacified him. Finally राम sent presents to his sister. {{F}}१४:  Ib. X. ८६. 1-१२.{{/F}} On a visit to स्यमन्तपञ्चक. {{F}}१५:  Ib. X. ८४. ५७.{{/F}} Once a ब्राह्मण of द्वारक preferred a complaint during कृष्ण's अश्वमेध that his children died imme- diately after their birth. Arjuna offered to recover them [page१-109+ ४५] for him, though कृष्ण had his own doubt. Accompanying the ब्राह्मण, Arjuna guarded the delivery room. The child was born and soon died. At this Arjuna went to Indra's place, and Yama's, and to the abodes of all gods, with the resolution to fall in a fire in case he did not rescue the child. Unable to recover it, Arjuna was about to plunge into the flames when कृष्ण prevented him. He was taken to the abode of नारायण and all the children were recovered. Returned to द्वारका to attend कृष्ण's अश्वमे- ध, after bringing joy to the ब्राह्मण. {{F}}१६:  Ib. X. ८९. २२-64.{{/F}} Other exploits of Arjuna were defeating Indra at खाण्डव, pleasing शिव in किरात's disguise, and vanquishing निवातकवचस्. {{F}}१७:  Ib. X. ८९. ३४ [4-5]; M. 6. २९.{{/F}} Went once to Heaven to please Indra, when he slew single- handed ६०,000 दानवस् who obstructed यज्ञस्। {{F}}१८:  भा. VI. 6. ३६.{{/F}} Went to द्वारका to see his relations. Was advised to take यादवस् to Indraprastha as द्वारका was about to be swallowed by the sea. Performed the last rites to the dead in द्वारका, and took the remainder to his place. Was defeated by rob- bers and आभिरस् after the departure of कृष्ण to Heaven. Informed युधिष्ठिर of कृष्ण's departure to Heaven and of his great sorrow, and also of the almost end of the यादव stock. Crowned Vajra king. {{F}}१९:  Ib. I. १२. ३६; १४, 1 and २२; १५. 5-२७ and ३२; XI. ३०. ४७-48; ३१. २१-25; M. ७०. १२. Vi. V. ३८. 5-6, १२-24, ३४-36.{{/F}} Arjuna knew and realised the माया of हरि। {{F}}२०:  भा. II. 7. ४५.{{/F}} Observed the आदित्यशयनम् vow. Visited the वामन temple at कुरुक्षेत्र during his तीर्थ- यात्रा and asked शौनक to narrate the circumstances of that अवतार् after वाराह. {{F}}२१:  M. ५५. ३२: २४४. 4.{{/F}} Was asked by व्यास to per- form penance expelling death. {{F}}२२:  Vi. V. ३८. ३७-92.{{/F}} Put down the prowess of कार्तवीर्य by the curse of आपव. {{F}}२३:  वा. ९४. ४५; ९९. २८०; Br. III. ६९. ४६.{{/F}} Known as पार्थ, Dhanamjaya, जिष्णु.--a तीर्थ sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ४३.--a son of शमीका and सुदामिनी. भा. IX. २४. ४४.--The reference is to both पाण्डव Arjuna and कार्तवीर्य Arjuna, both noted for military prowess. परीक्षित् is compared to them. भा. I. १२. २१. [page१-110+ ३१](I)--a son of Vasu, and a Vasu. Wife वासना. Sons तर्ष and others. भा. III. २१. ५१; VI. 3. १४; 6. ११ and १३.(II)--the son of Puruja, and father of Bhar- म्याश्व. भा. IX. २१. ३१. [page१-104+ २८](III)--the son of Vivici Agni; see विविध; he had a number of sons like अनीकवान्, etc. वा. 1. १४५; २९. ४०; Br. II. १२. ४२.--a name of शनैश्चर. M. ९३. १०.--a गण of the पिशाचस्, resembling mon- keys, with residences in trees; short and pushing nature. Br. III. 7. ३८२ and ३९०; वा. ६९. २७१.--a Mauneya Gandharva. Br. III. 7. 2.--a युगादि for साधारण श्राद्ध। M. १७. 2, 5.--see सूर्यवम्श। Ila was common ancestor. M. १२. १४.--of kings: to collect taxes in proper seasons, as the sun's rays draw water for 8 months. M. २२६. ११.--(Arbuda, Wilson); a sacred place. (?) Vi. VI. 8. २९.--four in number, पृथ्वी, अन्तरिक्ष, दिव्य and मह। वा. १०१. १३.--the goddess enshrined at वैद्यनाथ. M. १३. ४१.--born of धर्म and बुद्धि: {{F}}1:  भा. IV. 1. ५१; I. 2. 9.{{/F}} Its ills; {{F}}2:  भा. XI. २३. १७-21.{{/F}} not to be earned by a king by illegitimate means and not to abuse it by giving it to undesirables. {{F}}3:  M. २२०. ११; वा. २३. ८१; ६१. १३०.{{/F}}--a देवी. Br. IV. ३६. ७१. [page१-111+ ३२]--a Janapada. वा. ४५. १११.--one of the १८ विद्यस्: {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३१. २३; ३५. ८९; वा. ५८. २३; ६१. ७९.{{/F}} Science of Polity pleaded by Indra in extenuation of his destruction of Diti's गर्भ: {{F}}2:  M. 7. ६३; १०. ३२; Vi. III. 6. २८.{{/F}} No regard for the शास्त्र during पृथु's reign: Budha learned in; {{F}}3:  M. २४. 2.{{/F}} to be learnt by a prince. {{F}}4:  M. १४४. २३; २२०. 2.{{/F}}--the son of साध्य गण। भा. VI. 6. 7.--the son of Setu and father of गान्धार. Br. III. ७४. 7-9; वा. ९९. 7-9.(I)--a son of Danu: {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 6. ३०.{{/F}} the राक्षस with the sun in the months नभ and नभस्य। {{F}}2:  वा. ५२. १०; Br. II. २३. १०.{{/F}}(II)--a sage of the eleventh epoch of Manu. भा. VIII. १३. २५.(III)--The son of हर्यश्व, and father of Tri- bandhana. भा. IX. 7. 4.(IV)--a son of Mura (s.v.). भा. X. ५९. १२.(V)--a son of कृष्ण. भा. X. ९०. ३३. [page१-101+ २९](VI)--a hill near (on the other side of-वा। प्।) कैलास, the residence of गिरीश and full of medicinal herbs. At its foot is the शैलोदा lake from which rises the R. शिलोदा on whose bank is the forest सुरभी. Br. II. १८. १८-23; वा. ४७. १७-22.(VII)--A son of विङता and brother of गरुड. {{F}}1:  Br. III. 7. २९; M. 6. ३४; १५०. १५१-2; Vi. I. २१. १८.{{/F}} The charioteer of the Sun. He is said to yoke the seven horses bearing the names of metres (छन्दस्)। {{F}}2:  भा. V. २१. १५-16; वा. २८. ३२; Br. II. ११. ३७.{{/F}} Came to see परीक्षित् practising प्रायोपवेश। {{F}}3:  भा. I. १९. ११. वा. ६९. ६६.{{/F}} Married गृध्री (श्येनी-वा। प्।) who gave birth to सम्पाति and जटायु; {{F}}4:  Br. III. 7. ४४६; वा. ६९. ३२६.{{/F}} A personification of Dawn: Image of. {{F}}5:  M. २६१. 7.{{/F}}(VIII)--a son of Raivata. M. 9. २१.(IX)--a साध्य. M. १७१. ४३.(I)--R. of प्लक्ष dvi1pa. भा. V. २०. 4.(II)--an apsaras. Br. III. 7. 5. [page१-102+ ३२](III)--a देवी. Br. IV. १९. ४८; ४४. ४१.(I)--the sons of Dullola. Br. III. 7. ४४३.(II)--of the क्षत्रियस् of शाल्मलि dvi1pa. Vi. II. 4. ३०.(I)--a daughter of Kardama, sister of Par- vata and नारद, (काश्यप) and wife of वसिष्ठ; {{F}}1:  भा. III. २४. २३; वा. 2. १०; १९. 2; ३०. ७३; ६९. ६५; ७०. ७९.{{/F}} a sur- name of hers was ऊर्जा. Mother of seven sons, Citraketu and others, all sages of renown. {{F}}2:  भा. IV. 1. ४०.{{/F}} Did not feed कुमार while the wives of other six sages fed him. {{F}}3:  Br. III. १०. ४०.{{/F}} Mother of शक्ति. Goddess among Satis; meditated on the १०८ names of देवी as narrated to attain fruits of yoga. {{F}}4:  M. १३. ५३, ६१; १८७. ४५; २०१. ३०.{{/F}} [page१-103+ २३](II)--a daughter of दक्ष, and one of Dharma's wives: gave birth to पृथिवी and all विषयस्; (gave birth to all earthly objects, वि। प्।). Br. III. 3. 2 and ३४; 7. २८; 8. ८६; M. 5. १५ and १९; २०३. 2; वा. ६६. 2 and ३५; Vi. I. १५. १०५, १०८.(I)--a son of ब्रह्मा, who remained celibate: {{F}}1:  भा. IV. 8. 1; VI. १५. १३.{{/F}} a sage. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ३६. 6.{{/F}}(II)--went with कृष्ण to मिथिला. भा. X. ८६. १८.--R. of celestial mango juice flowing from the top of Mandara and irrigating the eastern part of इलावृत. In this river bathe यक्ष damsels, who are attendants of पार्वती. भा. V. १६. १७ and १८.--a sacred lake in Meru (in the east-वा। प्।) (in इलावृत-वि। प्।). M. ११३. ४६; वा. ३६. १६; Vi. II. 2. २६.--a देव of हरित गण। वा. १००. ८८.--a मन्त्रकृत्। वा. ५९. ९७.--a daughter of रिष्ट. Br. III. 7. १३; वा. ६९. ४८.--the people of a Janapada on the other side of the Vindhyas. (अनूपस्--वा। प्।)। M. ११४. ५४; वा. ४५. १३४.--a son o