८. [page१-134+ २८]--a daughter of वाका and विश्रवस्. वा. ७०. ५०.--an Ajita deva. Br. II. १३. ९३.--a काकुत्स्थ; the son of Sagara by केशिनी. Father of अम्शुमान्: In previous birth as a वैश्य he discovered a treasure. A spirit guarding it asked him to quench his hunger with cow's flesh and carry away the treasure. But he took it without providing food. So when born to केशिनी, the spirit entered him as wind and hence demented; used to throw his playmates into the सरयू; was banished by his father. He left the capital after bringing them back to life by his wonderful yogic powers. भा. IX. 8. १५-19; M. १२. ४२-43; Br. III. ५१. ३८-69; ६३. १६० & १६५; वा. ८८. १६०, १६५-66; Vi. IV. 4. 5-१०.--the son of Kambalabarhis and father of Susamaujas. {{F}}1:  Br. III. ७१. १४२; वा. ९६. १४१.{{/F}} [असामञ्जस् (मत्स्य प्।)] तमोजात was his son. {{F}}2:  M. ४४. ८३.{{/F}}--calculated by राशि and not by enume- ration. वा. १०१. १०८-9. [page१-135+ २४]--a name for हव्यसूद. वा. २९. २२.--the son of युयुधान. M. ४५. २३.--the queen of Bali, and mother of बाण and other sons. भा. VI. १८. १७.--a mother goddess. M. १७९. २९.--creation of, by ब्रह्मा. वा. 9. ५२; Br. II. 8. ५४.--८००० मण्डलस् traversed by the sun in a year. Its own मण्डल in one day. वा. ५२. ४६.--the son of वामदेव. वा. ६५. १०२; ९९. १४१.(II)--a sage; the brother of बृहस्पति; wife, ममता. वा. ९९. ३६.--a दानव. Br. III. 6. 5. [page१-123+ ३१]--the goddess following भवमालिनी. M. १७९. ७१.--a क्षेत्रज son of कल्माषपाद (Mitrasaha- वि।) born of मदयन्ती, queen of सौदास, to वसिष्ठ, with the king's assent. The period of pregnancy lasted for seven years when वसिष्ठ bit the queen's stomach with a stone. Father of मूलक. भा. IX. 9. ३९-40; Br. III. ६३. १७७; वा. ८८. १७७; Vi. IV. 4. ७२-3.--the people of a southern kingdom. Br. II. १६. ५८; M. २७२. १६.--the mother of शूर. Br. III. ७१. १४५ & १८९. [page१-124+ २५]--the chief minister of शन्तनु; made certain ascetics teach देवापि heretical doctrines (अश्मसारिओ --Cal. edn.). Vi. IV. २०. २१.--a त्रयार्षेय; not to have mari