tside by its being pierced by the tip of the toe of Trivikrama's left foot; in course of time she reached the celestial region known as विष्णुपद; held sacred by Dhruva and the seven sages; crossing the region of the [page२-525+ ३३] moon she reaches the city of ब्रह्मा; there she divides into four branches and falls into the western and eastern seas. भा. V. १७. 1-9.--the son of दिलीप and father of श्रुत (Suhotra वि। प्।); by penance on the banks of the Bindusaras he succeeded in bringing the Ganges; was asked how she was to dispose of the sins of men discharged into her waters; भगीरथ said that साधुस् and others among whom was Hari would take off the sins from her: was asked to pray to शिव to check her course; so he prayed to शिव and it was heard; by this he was able to shake off the sins of his ancestors; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. 9. 2-१३ and १६; Br. II. १८. २५; M. १२. ४४; १५. १९; १२१. २६; वा. ८८. १६७; Vi. IV. 4. ३५-6.{{/F}} a राजऋषि; went to the forest of the Gaura hills in search of गन्गा; {{F}}2:  वा. ४७. २४.{{/F}} his lust after more territory; {{F}}3:  भा. XII. 3. १०.{{/F}} after him [page२-526+ २३] गन्गा became the भागीरथी; so-called after the seventh branch of the Ganges. {{F}}4:  Br. III. ५४. ४८-51; ६३. १६६-8; वा. ४७. ४०.{{/F}}--not to marry with the members of the वसिष्ठ and Indra Pramati groups. M. २००. १३.(I)--a शिव gan2a. Br. III. ४१. २७; IV. १४. 7; १७. 4; १९. ७८-9; ३३. १७.(II)--An epithet of Rudra; the form assumed by शिव when गौरी returned from penance; She became भैरवी; {{F}}1:  M. १५८. २४; १७९. 1.{{/F}} Image of, to be placed in each temple but not in मूलायन्तन। {{F}}2:  Ib. २५२. १०; २५९. १४.{{/F}}(I)--a तीर्थ on the banks of चर्मन्वती sacred to the पितृस्. M. २२. ३१.(II)--तपस् performed by ब्रह्मा. वा. २६. १०. [page२-585+ २८]--an Apsarasa clan from मृत्यु. वा. ६९. ५७.--an incarnation of शिव (Bhairava s.v.). M. 1. 8.--an epithet of उमा; when शिव is Bhairava, उमा is भैरवी; {{F}}1:  M. १५८. २५.{{/F}} a mother-goddess. {{F}}2:  Br. IV. 7. ७२; ४४. २२.{{/F}}(I)--(B