sed even by परशु- राम. Leader of a thousand legions, called सहस्राणी; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २२. १९-20; I. 9. 4-6, ३०; M. १०३. 5. वा. ९९. २४०. Vi. IV. २०. ३३; V. ३५. 5 and २७.{{/F}} Informed by Uddhava of बलराम's visit to हस्तिनापुर: was invited for the राजसूय of युधिष्ठिर; {{F}}2:  भा. X. ६८. १७ and २८; ७४. १०.{{/F}} went to स्यमन्तपञ्चक for the solar eclipse and there met कृष्ण and the वृष्णिस्. Left it for his home. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ८२. २४; ८४. ५७, ६९ [1].{{/F}} Joined Duryodhana's army and was commander for ten days when he was mortally wounded; while on his death- bed he welcomed the sages and the royal guests, who visit- ed him; {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ७८. [९५(v)१६], [२८]; I. 9. 8-१०; १५. १०.{{/F}} told the पाण्डवस् that they were safe under the guidance of कृष्ण; {{F}}5:  Ib. I. 9. ११-14.{{/F}} युधिष्ठिर addressed B. lying on a bed of arrows on the various aspects of dharma and especially मोक्ष धर्म। The discourse was over when it was उत्तरायन, B. cast off his mortal coil with his mind fixed on कृष्ण Va1sudeva. His praise of कृष्ण; {{F}}6:  Ib. I. 9. २५-42; XI. १९. ११-12.{{/F}} was [page२-567+ ४०] seen among others by अक्रूर, कृतवर्मन्, कृष्ण and बलराम; {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ४९. 1; ५२. [५६(v)4, and ११]; ५७. 2.{{/F}} one of the twelve, who knew the धर्म ordained by Hari; {{F}}8:  Ib. VI. 3. २०. {{/F}} gave पिण्ड in विष्णुपद; {{F}}9:  वा. १११. ६९.{{/F}} Baladeva's respect for; {{F}}१०:  Vi. V. ३५. ३६; ३८. १६, ४७, ४९ and ६४.{{/F}} narrated to Nakula what he heard from his Brahmana friend कालिन्गक, on the mystery of birth and death; {{F}}११:  Ib. III. 7. 8.{{/F}} the best of the Kurus; {{F}}१२:  Ib. III. 7. ३५.{{/F}} heard a legend from वसिष्ठ as to who was a नग्न। {{F}}१३:  Ib. III. १७. 7.{{/F}}--a place near Benares. M. १८३. ६२.--the invincible king of Vidarbha, capital of कुण्डिन (Berar); {{F}}1:  भा. III. 3. 3; Vi. V. २६. 1.{{/F}} had five sons (Rukmi one of them) and a daughter, known as वैदर्भी and रुक्मिणी. Agreed to his son, Rukmi's wish to give रुक्मिणी in marriage to शिशुपाल: on the eve of the day of marriage, the city was decorated; prayers were offered to पिट्र्स् and Devas; प्रेसेङ्त्स् were given to Brahmanas to exalt मन्गलम्। दमघोष and other friends of the Cedi King were welcomed. Housed राम and कृष्ण in comfortable lodgings. But कृष्ण won her in the स्वयम्वर; {{F}}2:  भा. X. ५२. १६, २१-22; ५३. 7-३५; Vi. V. २६. 3-6.{{/F}} was stationed by जरासन्ध on the northern side during the siege of Gomanta; {{F}}3:  भा. X. ५२. ११[15].{{/F}} went to the स्यमन्तपञ्चक for the solar eclipse. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ८२. १५.{{/F}}--a tribe. Br. IV. 7. १९.--those who could not find the one in the three but think of them as separate and even as superior to one's own. Some call the one God ब्रह्मा, प्रजापति, शिव and विष्णु; these will be troubled by यातुधानस् and पिशाचस्. वा. ६६. १११-8.--as against तत्वदर्शि--sectarians in reli- gion. Br. III. 3. ८९-90. ९७.--a son of मणिभद्र. वा. ६९. १५५.--a son of हृदिक. वा. ९६. १३९.--a son of हृदिक. Br. III. ७१. १४१.(I)--(मार्ग) taught by नारद to the children of दक्ष; {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 5. ३६.{{/F}} duties of. {{F}}2:  M. ४०. 1, 5.{{/F}}(II)--(see also Yati) main व्रतस् five; and sup- plementary, five; main:--ध्यानम्, समाधि of the senses, begging at seven houses, silence and release from sangha. Supplementary:--Purity in conduct, discipline (vinaya) शौचम्, non-retaliation and सम्यक्दर्शनम्, besides non theft, Brahmacarya, non-covetousness, ahimsa, non-anger, service to the Guru, medicated food, daily study, alms, resig [page२-561+ २९] nation, generosity, etc., becomes one with ब्रह्मा for observing such dharma. Br. II. 7. १७९; वा. 8. १८६-7; १६. १८-9; ५९. २५; १०५. २५; Vi. III. 9. २४-42.--the people of the southern country. Br. II. १६. ५८; वा. ४५. १२७.(I)--the capital of the नागस्, compared to the city of Puramjana; {{F}}1:  भा. I. ११. ११; IV. २५. १५.{{/F}} north of वासुकिह्रद, a sacred spot of प्रयागा. {{F}}2:  M. १६३. ८०.{{/F}}(II)--the name of गन्गा in पाताल. भा. X. ७०. ४४.--son of शेष, the नाग king. Br. III. ७४. १८०; वा. ९९. ३६७.--a Rahasya योगिनी Devi1. Br. IV. १९. ४८.(I)--a Yadu prince. He once dreamt that he ate the remnants of the food of his enemy, and that his enemies deprived him of his wives, and kingdom. This caused deep misery in his mind. He left his home and bestowed all his thoughts on परमात्मन् from that day: entered ब्रह्मनिर्वाण। Fought with अक्रूर at प्रभासा. भा. X. ३६. ३३; VI. १५. २६ [1-4]; XI. ३०. १६. Br. III. ६१. २३. [page२-586+ ४१](II)--a king noted for his large elephant forces. Br. II. ७१. १२६-7.(III)--a son of Bali. Br. III. 5. ४३.(IV)--a son of जाम्बवती. Br. III. 7. ३०३.(V)--a son of प्रतिक्षेत्र and father of हृदीक. M. ४४. ८०.--usually a title of a monarch; {{F}}1:  Br. III. ७१. १९४, २२३; वा. ९६. १९०.{{/F}} शमीक, abandoned this title being a राजऋषि. {{F}}2:  M. ४६. २८.{{/F}}(I)--the queen of Viravrata: mother of Manthu and Pramanthu. भा. V. १५. १५.(II)--the wife of शूर; mother of ten sons and five daughters. M. ४६. 1.--the capital of Rukmin: the city founded by him for his residence, as he wanted to keep his word not to enter कुण्डिन without killing कृष्ण. Here was celebrat- ed the marriage of Aniruddha and which बलराम and others attended and then left for द्वारका; {{F}}1:  भा. X. ५४. ५२; ६१. १९ and २३ [5]; ६१. २६ and ४०.{{/F}} the स्वयम्वर of Pradymna's daughter took place at. {{F}}2:  Vi. V. २८. 9.{{/F}} [page२-587+ ३१]--Mt. of क्रौञ्चद्वीप. भा. V. २०. २१.(I)--a Vindhya clan; {{F}}1:  Br. II. १६. ६४; वा. ४५. १३२; ८६. २८.{{/F}} in द्वारवती: one of the five clans (गणस्) of the Haihayas beginning with Druhyu, son of ययाति; {{F}}2:  Br. III. ६९. ५२; ७४. २६५; M. ३४. ३०; ४३. ४८; ४४. ६९; १६३. ७२; वा. ९४. ५२.{{/F}} had two hundred branches; {{F}}3:  Ib. ९९. ४५२.{{/F}} all of them क्षत्रियस्; {{F}}4:  Ib. ३२. ४८.{{/F}} कश्यप gotraka1ras. {{F}}5:  M. १९९. 2.{{/F}}(II)--a यादव tribe to which Kamsa belonged: were related to the पाण्डवस्; {{F}}1:  भा. X. 1. ३५, ३७ and ६९; IX. २४. ११ and ६३; I. १४. २५; M. ११४. ५२; २७३. ७०.{{/F}} defended द्वारका against the enemies and praised the heroic deeds of कृष्ण; {{F}}2:  भा. I. ११. ११; IX. २४. ६३.{{/F}} Kamsa planned in vain to vanquish them. Fought with their kith and kin and ended their lives; {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ३६. ३३; ३९. २५; XI. ३०. १८.{{/F}} line of the, traced from महा- bhoja; kings of मृत्तिकावर Pura; hence मार्त्तिकावरस्: killed सात्वत S4atrughna and left द्वारका with अक्रूर. {{F}}4:  Vi. IV. १३. 7, ११.{{/F}}--resides in the वैभ्राज hill of प्लक्ष. Br. II. १९. १३.--a son of घृतपृष्ठ of the प्लक्षद्वीप. भा. V. २०. २१.--a गण of the epoch of Bhautya Manu: these are the seven rivers; {{F}}1:  Br. IV. 1. १०६-8.{{/F}} a group of gods of the XIV epoch of Manu. {{F}}2:  Vi. III. 2. ४३.{{/F}}--a भार्गव gotraka1ra. M. १९५. २४.--an आर्षेयप्रवर; (Angiras). M. १९६. २१.--of Siddhi: to go about as if aimlessly and with an absent mind induced by the inner soul. वा. १२. 7, ११ and १२.--a daughter of शिशुमार and wife of Dhruva; mother of Vatsara. भा. IV. १०. 1; १३. ११.--a Mauneya. वा. ६९. 3.--त्रयार्षेयस्. M. १९९. १०.(I)--born from fire; one of the ten mind-born sons of ब्रह्मा; born of his skin; married Kardama's daugh- ter ख्याती and had two sons and a daughter; married the daughter of Puloma and brought forth twelve sons besides Cyavana and आनुवन्; married two daughters of दक्ष; a sage of the चाक्षुष epoch; {{F}}1:  भा. III. १२. २२-23; २४. २३; IV. 1. ४३; M. 3. 8; 5. १४; 9. २२; १९५. 8; Vi. I. 7. 5, 7, २६, ३७; 8. १५.{{/F}} a महऋषि; a मन्त्रकृत्; a Pra- vara; accompanied ब्रह्मा going to हिरण्यकशिपु; was present at the anointing of वामन Hari and praised the Lord and Aditi; learnt the क्रिययोग from ब्रह्मा; {{F}}2:  M. १४५. ९०, ९८; १७१. २७; १९५. २९.{{/F}} and the Vedas from Manu. {{F}}3:  भा. VII. 3. १४; VIII. २३. २०-27; XI. २७. 3; १४. 4.{{/F}} Deputed by the sages to find out the greatest of the Gods, went to his father's court without invoking him in praise; ब्रह्मा grew angry but restrained his anger. Then he went to शिव, who embraced him. भृगु told him that he did not like his behaviour when शिव grew angry and started to attack him with his trident. He was stopped by पार्वती's intervention. Next he called on Hari and kicked him while sleeping, on His chest. Hari coolly bore it, bowed to him and said that only then he became purified and united with लक्ष्मी. भृगु wondered at his patience and concluded that he was the greatest of all the gods. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ८९. 2-१९.{{/F}} Wonder- ed at मार्कण्डेय's व्रत; took part in crowning Vena to avoid the evils of anarchy; did not find fault with Hara violating धर्म। {{F}}5:  Ib. XII. 8. १२; IV. १४. 1; २९. ४३; VI. १७. १२.{{/F}} Officiated at विश्वसृज यज्ञ when he cursed the followers of शिव to become पाखण्डिस्; created [page२-580+ ३२] ऋभुस् to put down the Pramathas and others who disturb- ed दक्ष's sacrifice; was bound by मणिमन् and the beard cut off. It was शिव's wish that the beard of a sheep be substituted for his original one. {{F}}6:  Ib. IV. 2. २७-8; 4. ३२; 5. १७ and १९; 7. 5.{{/F}} Was born again of चर्षणि and वरुण {{F}}7:  Ib. VI. १८. 4.{{/F}} acted as अध्- वर्यु in Soma's राजसूय; {{F}}8:  M. २३. २०.{{/F}} cursed विष्णु to take the form of a human being seven times for slaying his wife to protect Indra. {{F}}9:  Ib. ४७. ३९, १०५.{{/F}} Praised शिव out to burn Tripura. {{F}}१०:  Ib. १०२. १९; १२६, १०; १३३. ६७.{{/F}} Performed penance on the नर्मदा but was not free from anger; cursed शिव's riding animal when it was sent to examine his mind; but still he prayed to the Lord who blessed a तीर्थ at that place in his honour.(II)--a sage and a contemporary of कृष्ण; came to see कृष्ण at स्यमन्तपञ्चक; one of the sages who left for पिण्डारक; came to see परीक्षित् practising प्रायोपवेश. भा. X. ८४. 4; XI. 1. १२; I. १९. 9.(III)--a ऋषि presiding over the month of Nabha- sya; {{F}}1:  भा. XII. ११. ३८.{{/F}} in the Sun's chariot in the month of भाद्रपद. {{F}}2:  Vi. II. १०. १०; वा. २९. 9; ५२. 9.{{/F}}(IV)--the father of अथर्वण Agni. Br. II. १२. १०.(V)--one of the eighteen authors on architec- ture. M. २५२. 2. [page२-581+ २४](VI)-