iculties and dangers the sages appealed to ब्रह्मा and learnt that it was due to शिव; hence they made images of लिन्ग and offered worship for a year; the Lord appeared before them, and was praised by all; {{F}}1:  Br. II. २७. 2-९०;{{/F}} the sages were treated by शिव on भस्मस्नानविधि. {{F}}2:  Ib. II. २७. १०५, १२८.{{/F}}--a degraded क्षत्रिय clan. Br. III. ६३. १४०.--servants entertained in a श्राद्ध; {{F}}1:  M. १७. ५७ and ६२; वा. ६०. ३७.{{/F}} appellation of the शूद्रस्. {{F}}2:  Vi. III. १०. 9.{{/F}}--a commander of भण्ड. Br. IV. २१. ८५.--see दशार्हस्. भा. XI. ३०. १८.--शतध्वज (s.v.) was their king; when they heard of कृष्ण going to मिथिला they met him with presents. भा. X. ५२. ११ [१२]; ८६. २५.--a Tirtham in Benares; {{F}}1:  M. १८५. ६८.{{/F}} fit for श्राद्ध. {{F}}2:  वा. ७७. ४५.{{/F}} [page२-080+ ३०]--here were born as hunters the seven sons of कौशिक. But they remembered their previous births and refrained from cruel deeds. M. २०. १२-4; २१. 9 and २८.--a name of राम, who destroyed रावन and his clan. वा. ७०. ४८.--the fisher-woman, who took birth as सत्यवती and begot विचित्रवीर्य by शन्तनु. M. ५०. ४५; वा. ७३. २१; ९९. २४०.(I)--Slaves as present to learned men. Br. II. ३४. ३९. [page२-086+ २९](II)--of four kinds, देवदासि, ब्रह्मदासि, स्व- तन्त्र and शूद्रदासिक; the first two occupy the status of a क्षत्रिय lady; the third enjoys the status of a dancing girl (वेशि), and the last that of a low caste (हीनजाति). {{F}}1:  Br. IV. 8. ११-12.{{/F}} A synonym of परिचारिक or a servant-maid. {{F}}2:  M. २९. १७-23.{{/F}}--a Mukhya गण of the सावर्ण्य epoch; {{F}}1:  वा. ९४. ५६; १००. १८;{{/F}} a Sukha God. {{F}}:  2) Br. IV. 1. १९.{{/F}}--a वैकुण्ठ God. Br. II. ३६. ५७.--the country of, (दार्विक--Wilson) under the म्लेच्छस्। Vi. IV. २४. ६९.(I)--a son of दारुक, an अवतार् of the Lord. वा. २३. १९६.(II)--the previous अवतार् of उमा; stars regarded as her daughters; {{F}}1:  M. १३. १०; १२८. ५०; १९९. २०.{{/F}} a daughter of दक्ष; {{F}}2:  Br. I. 1. ५९.{{/F}} became हिंअवान्'s daughter by worshipping शिव. {{F}}3:  Ib. III. 7. ४७२; IV. ११. 2-5.{{/F}}--a काश्यप gotraka1ra. M. १९९. 5.--a sage; a त्रयार्षेय pravara. M. १९६. २५; १९७. 6.--(द्राविडस्); southerners; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३१. ८२; वा. ५८. ८२; ९८. १०७.{{/F}} to be conquer- ed by Kalki. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ७३. १०७.{{/F}}--कौशिकगोत्रकरस्. वा. ९१. १०१.(I)--a ऋषिक, who became a sage by सत्य; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३२. १०२.{{/F}} a मन्त्रकृट् {{F}}2:  M. १४५. ९८.{{/F}} Heard the विष्णु पुराण from Stambhamitra and narrated it to सारस्वत. {{F}}3:  Vi. VI. 8. ४४.{{/F}}(II)--urged दक्ष to invite पशुपति to the sacrifice. वा. ३०. १०३-7.(I)--(also दध्यञ्ज, Dadhyanga) the son of Atharvan and Citti. {{F}}1:  भा. IV. 1. ४२.{{/F}} A sage of much eminence. Taught अश्वाशिरस् मन्त्र to अश्विन्स् and नारायण वर्म to त्वष्ट्रि, who gave it to विश्वरूप. The Lord advised Indra to meet the sage whose bones would serve as best weapons to cut वृत्र's head. When the gods waited on him with this desire, he argued at first that no one would be willing to part with his life. But, he would agree for their sake to sacrifice his life. When he cast off his body, विश्वकर्म made it a Vajra for the use of Indra. {{F}}2:  Ib. VI. 9. ५१-55; १०. 2-१३; ११. २०.{{/F}} दधीचि's is an example of one, who gave up life in service. {{F}}3:  Ib. VIII. २०. 7.{{/F}}(II)--the son of Cyavana भार्गव; married सरस्वती and father of सारस्वत; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 1. ९३-4; वा. ६५. ९०.{{/F}} Sage by garbha; {{F}}2:  Ib. ५४. ९४.{{/F}} a मन्त्रकृत्. {{F}}3:  Ib. ५९. ९६.{{/F}}(III)--the son of वैराज Manu. वा. २१. ४१; ३०. १०२.--a Marici God. Br. IV. 1. ५८.--a sea that surrounds the शाकद्वीप. {{F}}1:  भा. V. 1. ३३; २०. २४.{{/F}} (क्रौञ्चद्वीप ब्र्। प्।) also Dadhisindhu. {{F}}2:  Br. II. १९. ७७; IV. ३१. १९; M. १२२. ९२. Vi. II. 4. ५७.{{/F}}--a काद्रवेय Na1ga. Br. III. 7. ३५; वा. ६९. ७२.--a ऋत्विक् at ब्रह्मा's यज्ञ। वा. १०६. ३७.--the son of Bali and king of Anga, born without अपान, due to the blunder of सुदेष्ण; hence अनपान; father of Diviratha (see सुदेष्ण). Br. III. ७४. १०२-3; M. ४८-91; वा. ९९. १००. [page२-069+ ३६]--the son of Atharva Agni. Br. II. १२. १०; वा. २९. 8.--one of the eleven Rudras. M. १७१. ३९.--born as Agastya to Pulastya. भा. IV. 1. ३६.--are कापिलेयस्. वा. ६९. १७७.--the Asuras from Diti; {{F}}1:  वा. ६६. 1.{{/F}} one of the Marut गणस्. {{F}}2:  वा. ४६. ३५; ६७. १२९.{{/F}}--astrologers, residences of. M. २५४. २६.(I)--a son of प्रत्युष and a देवऋसि. Br. II. ३५. ९४.(II)--a son of परियात्र (पारिपात्र-वा। प्।) and father of Bala. Br. III. ६३. २०४: वा. ८८. २०४.(I)--a son of Marutta, and father of राज्य- vardhana. भा. IX. 2. २९.(II)--a son of क्रिया. Br. II. 9. ६०.(III)--a सुधामान God. Br. II. ३६. ३७.(IV)--a god of the आभूतरय group. Br. II. ३६. ५५.(V)--a वैकुण्ठ God. Br. II. ३६. ५७.(VI)--a son of नरिष्यन्त, a दण्डधर and father of विक्रान्त. (राष्त्रवर्धन-ब्र्। प्।; Rajavardhana- वि। प्।). Br. III. ६१. 8; वा. ८६. १२; Vi. IV. 1. ३६.(VII)--an आर्षेय pravara of भार्गवस्. M. १९५. ३६.(VIII)--a son of मणिवर. वा. ६९. १६०.(IX)--a Mukhya गण. वा. १००. १८.(X)--a son of रिष्यन्त. वा. ७०. ३०. [page२-073+ ३२]--a king of the Cedis; queen श्रुतश्रवा; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २४. ३९. Br. III. ७१. १५९. Vi. IV. १४. ४४.{{/F}} (पटुश्रवा and रुजकन्या) father of शिशुपाल (Caidya: {{F}}2:  भा. VII. 1. १७. वा. ९६. १५८.{{/F}} s.v.), performed preliminaries to the marriage of his son with रुक्मिणी; when he went to कुण्डिन, he was entertain- ed by her father भीष्मक. {{F}}3:  भा. X. ५३. १४-16.{{/F}} He was stationed on the south during the siege of Gomanta by जरासन्ध; {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ५२. ११ [8].{{/F}} went to स्यमन्तपञ्चक for the सोलर् eclipse. {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ८२. २६.{{/F}}(I)--a son of Vasudeva and रोहिणि. Br. III. ७१. १६५; M. ४६. १२. वा. ९६. १६३.(II)--a commander to aid विषन्ग, killed by कामेस्वरी. Br. IV. २५. ३०, ४६, ९४.(III)--a son of Angirasa. M. १९६. 2.(IV)--the अवतार् of the Lord in the third द्वापर; had four sons, विशोक, विकेश, etc. वा. २३. १२३.(V)--a ऋत्विक् at ब्रह्मा's sacrifice. वा. १०६. ३६.--a sage; exclusion of marriage with the Angirasas. M. १९६. २९.(I)--a