ntry. वा. ४४. १७. [page२-076+ २६](I)--a son of अजातशत्रु and father of Ajaya. भा. XII, 1. 6.(II)--ruled for ३५ years. Br. III. ७४. १३१.(I)--vanquished by कृष्ण. भा. II. 7. ३४.(II)--a Mt. of the भारतवर्ष. वा. ४५. ९०.(I)--a son of सारण. वा. ९६. १६५. [page२-075+ २३](II)--a son of बलराम. Br. III. ७१. १६७.--(Aridyota-ब्र्। प्।)--the son of Dundubhi and father of Punarvasu. भा. IX. २४. २०.--born of Pulaha. Br. III. 7. १७८.(I)--born of Dharma and Unnati. भा. IV. 1. ५१.(II)--a son of लक्ष्मी. Br. II. 9. 8; वा. १०. ३४.--a looking-glass to be installed by the side of a deity. M. ५७. १८; २६५. १९; २८९. १०.(I)--the son of धाता and सिनीवालि. भा. VI. १८. 3.(II)--a son of कृष्ण and कालिन्दि. भा. X. ६१. १४.(III)--a son of ब्रह्मा and मन्त्रसरीर: a Jayadeva. Br. III. 3. 6; 4. 2; वा. ६६. 6; ६७. 5.--one of the five queens of उशीनर; father of Suvrata. M. ४८. १६, १८. [page२-077+ २३]--a king of Magadha; ruled for २५ years. वा. ९९. ३१८.--a name for the २७थ् Kalpa; here Soma became पौर्णमासि. वा. २१. ६७, ६९.--a यक्ष; son of पुण्यजनी and मणि- bhadra. Br. III. 7. १२५.--a sacrifice performed by Bharata. भा. V. 7. 5.--one of the wives of उशिनर and mother of Suvrata. Br. III. ७४. १८ and २०. वा. ९९. १९.--a hill tribe; {{F}}1:  Br. II. १६. ६७.{{/F}} a mountain kingdom. {{F}}2:  M. ११४. ५६; वा. ४५. १३६.{{/F}}--one of Danu's sons. वा. ६८. 9.--see रावन. Vi. IV. 4. ९७; १४. ४८-9; १५. 7-8.(I)--the son of निर्वृत्(t)i, (निधृति-व्। प्।, वीदूरथ, म्। प्।), and father of Vyoma; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २४. 3; X. ३६. ३३; M. ४४. ४०.{{/F}} a man of much prowess. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ७०. ४१; Vi. IV. १२. ४१.{{/F}}(II)--a son of घर्मात्मा. वा. ९५. ४०.--(also दशार्हकास्) a tribe related to the पाण्- डवस्. They defended द्वारका when attacked. {{F}}1:  भा. I. ११. ११; १४. २५; III. 1. २९.{{/F}} Praised कृष्ण's heroism. {{F}}2:  Ib. IX. २४. ६३.{{/F}} Felt relieved at Kamsa's death as they heard of his plan to vanquish them. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ३६. ३३; ३९. २५; ४५. १५.{{/F}} Followed बलराम to द्वारका and fought their own kinsmen. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ६१. ४०; XI. २९. ३९; ३०. १८.{{/F}}--a R. in भारतवर्ष from the र्क्ष; sacred to पितृस्. Br. II. १६. ३०; III. १३. १००; M. २२. ३४; वा. ४५. ९९. M. १४४. २५.--a Vindhya tribe enlisted by जरासन्ध against the Yadus. भा. X. [५०. (v) 3]; Br. II. १६. ६४; वा. ४५. १३२.--a तीर्थ on the नर्मदा; west of गन्गेश्वरम्. १९३. २०-2.(I)--रावन (s.v.). {{F}}1:  भा. VII. १०. ३६; Br. III. 7. २६२; ७१ 159.{{/F}} शिशुपाल in previous birth. {{F}}2:  वा. ९६. १५३.{{/F}}(II)--an Asura in the सभा of हिरण्य- कशिपु. M. १६१. ८१.--रावन killed by राम. भा. II. 7. २३-25.--the याम gan2as who stand in ten parts in the वैराज. वा. १०१. ६४.--a northern kingdom. Br. II. १६. ४८.--a tribe. वा. ४५. ११७.--a tribe. M. ११४. ४२. [page२-078+ ३०](I)--a son of मूलक, and father of ऐड- विड. (इलीविल-वि। प्।). भा. IX. 9. ४१; V. IV. 4. ७५.(II)--a son of Aja (पाल) and of इन्दुमती; and father of श्री Ra1ma (दाशरथि Ra1ma-वा। प्।) and three other sons, being the अम्शस् of Hari. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. १०. 1-2; Br. III. ६३. १८४; IV. ४०. १००; M. १२. ४९-50; वा. ८८. १८३-4; १११. ६४; Vi. IV. 4. ८६-7.{{/F}} A friend of Roma- पाद to whom he gave his daughter शान्ता in adoption. {{F}}2:  भा. IX. २३. 7-8; Vi. IV. १८. १७-8.{{/F}} King of अयोध्या. Having no sons worshipped त्रिपुरसुन्दरी at the capital and spent seven days at काञ्ची praying to कामाक्षी who blessed him with four sons. {{F}}3:  Br. III. ३७. ३१; ६३. १८४; IV. ४०. ८८.{{/F}}(III)--a son of Navaratha, and father of शकुनि (एकादशरथ-ब्र्। प्।). भा. IX. २४. 4-5; Br. III. ७०. ४३-4. वा. ९५. ४२; Vi. IV. १२. ४१.(IV)--a son of Satyaratha (Citraratha: वा। प्।). (Known also as लोमपाद). M. ४८. ९४; वा. 9. १०३.(V)--a Maurya king who ruled for eight years; son of सुयशा and father of Samyuta. M. २७२. २५; Vi. IV. २४. ३०.--the images of राम and Bali. M. २५९. 1.--the bow of शिव with ten colours. वा. १०१. २७०. [page२-079+ ३३]--a northern kingdom. Br. II. १६. ५०.--a son of मार्ताण्ड or the Sun; {{F}}1:  वा. ८४. २४. Br. III. ५९. २५;{{/F}} one of the अश्विन्स्. {{F}}2:  वा. ८४. ७७.{{/F}}--the name of Budha, son of तारा and Soma who forcibly seized her from बृहस्पति; {{F}}1:  Br. III. ६५. ४१; वा. ९०. ३७.{{/F}} called Budha after तारा revealed his real father. {{F}}2:  वा. ९०. ४३.{{/F}}--The आभिरस् and Mlecchas; unfit for श्राद्ध; {{F}}1:  Br. III. १४. ४३; Vi. V. ३८. १३; २५. २७. ४९७.{{/F}} checked by ययाति; {{F}}2:  Br. III. ६८. ६७.{{/F}} dharma of the; {{F}}3:  Ib. III. ६३. १९४; वा. ४९. ५५; ७८. ३४; ८८. १०५.{{/F}} seized १६००० ladies of कृष्ण due to a curse by the Lord; {{F}}4:  M. ७०. 7.{{/F}} cudgels as chief weapons of; {{F}}5:  Vi. V. ३८. ५१, ७०, ८२, ८४.{{/F}} killing milch cows. {{F}}6:  वा. ९३. ६६.{{/F}}--an आन्गिरस and मन्त्रकृत्. Br. II. ३२. १०८.(II)--a sage of the स्वारोचिष epoch. M. 9. 8.(I)--the son of the sage Atri and Ana- सूया and an अवतार् of विष्णु according to पौराणिकस्; brother of दुर्वास; by worshipping him, the Yadus, Haiha- yas, etc., got knowledge of yoga. {{F}}1:  भा. II. 7. 4; IV. I. १५ and ३३; XI. 4. १७; Br. III. 8. ८२; IV. २८. ८९; वा. ७०. ७६-8.{{/F}} He knew Hari yoga, {{F}}2:  भा. II. 7. ४५.{{/F}} and followed Hari going to पृथु's sacrifice. {{F}}3:  Ib. IV. १९. 6.{{/F}} A Siddha; {{F}}4:  Ib. VI. 8. १६; १५. १४.{{/F}} worshipped by Arjuna (Haihaya), to whom he imparted yoga; {{F}}5:  Ib. IX. १५. १७; २३. २४; Br. III. ३०. ३५; ३४. 4; ३८. १४; ४०. ४३, ५७, ६६; ६९. १०; M. ४३. १५.{{/F}} in the tenth त्रेतायुग the 4th incarnation with मर्कण्डेय as Purohita; {{F}}6:  Br. III. ७३. ८८; M. ४७. २४२; ९९. १४; वा. ९८. ८९.{{/F}} was worshipped by Arjuna who got four boons from him one of which was १००० hands; {{F}}7:  वा. ९४. १०-11; Vi. IV. ११. १२.{{/F}} श्यामस्, Mudgalas, गविष्ठिअस् and others belong to this वम्श. {{F}}8:  Ib. I. १०. 8.{{/F}}--a son of प्रीता and Pulastya; an Agastya in previous birth. वा. २८. २२; Vi. I. १०. 9.--a son of उमा. Br. III. १०. १८. [page२-068+ २६](I)--a Paulastya and one of the 7 sages of the स्वारोचिष epoch. Br. II. ३६. १८.(II)--given by Manu to Ahi as son; see उत्तान- पाद. Br. II. ३६. ८५; III. ४७. ६५.--in honour of दुर्गा. Br. IV. ३८. 5.--is Bharata (s.v.) noted for his sacrifices and love of people; परीक्षित् compared to him. भा. I. १२. २०.--to be worshipped in house-building. M. २५३. २६. [page२-137+ २४]--palace officials. M. २१५. ३०.son of वर्क्षी (मारिषा-वि। प्।) and Pracetas (प्रा- चेतसष्-वि। प्।); a प्रजापति. He first created the Devas, Asuras, men and others inhabiting the sky, earth and water. Finding the creation incomplete, he went to the Vindhyas for तपस् by bathing in the Agha- मर्षण and propitiating Hari with the hymn of हम्सगुह्य। To him the Lord appeared and urged him to marry असिक्नी, daughter of पञ्चजन and thus increase the created beings. {{F}}9:  Ib. VI. 4 (whole); Vi. I. १५. १०, ८०-1.{{/F}} Of असिक्नी he begot १०,000 sons called हर्यश्वस्. The latter proceeded to the western direction to the sacred lake नारायणसरस् at the estuary of the Indus. Purified by the bath and instructed by नारद on the bondage of सम्सार, these took to the path of ‘not returning’ (अन्वर्तन)। दक्ष lamented and begot by the same wife a thousand sons, शबलाश्वस्. These again followed the path trodden by their elder brothers, advised by नारद. The enraged दक्ष cursed that नारद, the corrupter of youth, was ever to be a wanderer and to have no settled home. The sage submitted to it without retaliating. {{F}}१०:  भा. VI. 5 (whole); Vi. I. १५. ८२-104.{{/F}} Con- soled by ब्रह्मा, दक्ष further begot sixty daughters of असिक्नी (वैरिनी-म्। प्।). He bestowed ten on Dharma, twelve on कश्यप, twenty-seven on Soma, two each for भूत, Angiras, and कृशाश्व, and the remaining five, of whom only four seem to be named (in v. २१) on तार्क्ष्या. {{F}}११:  भा. VI. 6 whole; Ib. V. 5. २२; Br. III. 1. 8 and १२; 2. 1-३१; M. १४६. १५-7; भा. III. १४. १२-3; Br. III. 3. 3, 5-५५; 8-5.{{/F}} Elsewhere it is said that thirteen daughters were given in marriage to कश्यप. [page२-060+ ३५] Went with ब्रह्मा to meet हिरण्यकशिपु; was present at the anointing of वामन; father of Aditi; {{F}}१३:  भा. VII. 3. १४; VIII. २३. २०; IX. 4. ५४; 1. १०.{{/F}} cursed Moon god with consumption (यक्ष्म)। {{F}}१४:  Ib. X. ८८. ३२; XI. 6. ३६.{{/F}} Wondered at मार्कण्डेय's vrata; {{F}}१५:  Ib. XII 8. १२.{{/F}} had not yet seen the Supreme Being; identified with Hari. {{F}}१६:  Ib. IV. २९. ४२; XI. १६. १५.{{/F}} Drank of the सौभाग्य from the thigh of Hari and brought forth a daughter सती married by शिव; {{F}}१७:  M. ६०. 6-7, १०-11; १४५. ९०.{{/F}} a महऋषि; heard the पुराण from ब्रह्मा along with other sages; {{F}}१८:  Vi. I. 2. 8.{{/F}} son of ब्रह्मा, married ऊर्जा. {{F}}१९:  Ib. I. 7. 5-7.{{/F}} ^१२) M. २३. १५;(II)--in previous birth son of ब्रह्मा, now born of मारिषा and Pracetasas. Was made a chief progeni- tor on the eve of the चाक्षुष epoch; {{F}}1:  भा. IV. ३०. ४९-51; Br. IV. 1. २४, ३९-44.{{/F}} a grandson of Soma; created men with two feet and four feet, of different faces, ears, etc., also म्लेच्छस् and women; also produced १००० sons with पाञ्चजनि, named हर्यश्वस्. नारद asked them to go into the world over but they perished in their sojourn. So he begot another १००० of वैरिणी, and these were शबलस् set by नारद in quest of the whereabouts of their brothers. They also perished. {{F}}2: M. 4. ४९-55; 5. 2-१४.{{/F}}(III)--the son of Citrasena, and father of मीढ्वान्. भा. IX. 2. १९. [page२-061+ ३२](IV)--a son of उशीनर. भा. IX. २३. 3.(V)--created from प्राण, half तेजस् of Pracetas and half of Soma; created creatures, two-legged and four- legged, in the Vaivasvata epoch; {{F}}1:  Br. I. 5. ७०; वा. ६३. ३५-48; ६५. १२१-158.{{/F}} Lord of प्रजापतिस्. {{F}}2:  वा. ७०-5; १०१. ३५, ४९.{{/F}} Got प्राचेतसत्वम् in the epoch of चाक्षुष by the curse of Trayambaka; father-in-law of the seven sages. {{F}}3:  Br. II. १३. ४०-69.{{/F}}(VI)--an Asura, and a son of बाष्कल. Br. III. 5. ३८.(VII)--Heard the पुराण from तृणबिन्दु and narrated it to शक्ति. Br. IV. 4. ६५.(VIII)--a son of देवातीथि. M. ५०. ३७.(IX)--a son of भृगु; one of the twelve विश्वे- devas. M. १९५. १३; २०३. १३; वा. ६६. ३१.(X)--a son of Angirasa; {{F}}1:  M. १९६. 2; वा. ६५. १०५.{{/F}} through his daughter a son, प्रियाय. {{F}}2:  वा. १००. २४.{{/F}}(XI)--a pravara sage. M. १९६. ३०.(XII)--with the sun in the months of माघ and फाल्गुन. वा. ५२. २३.(XIII)--a son of Jambha. वा. ६७. ७८. [page२-062+ २६](I)--a Mind-born son of ब्रह्मा, born of his thumb, and father of मूर्ति. A progenitor and guardian of the world, born for the creation of worldly beings. {{F}}1:  भा. III. १२. २२-3; Ib. II. 6. ४२; 7. 6; Br. II. ३२. ९६; ३६. ८४; Ib. III. 3. ३०; ६५. २१; Ib. IV. 2. ३३, ४७; M. 3. 9; 8. 4; १५४. ३५३; १७१. २७, ४९; वा. २५. 2, ८२, ९०; Vi. I. २२. 4; IV. 1. 6.{{/F}} Married प्रसूती, daughter of स्वायम्भुव Manu. Had sixteen daughters of whom he gave thirteen to Dharma, one to Agni, one to पितृस्, and one to शिव. {{F}}2:  भा. III. १२. ५६; Ib. IV. 1. ११, ४७-9; Vi. I. 7. १९-27; Br. I. 1. ५६-64; Ib. II. ३७. ३८-50;.{{/F}} To the Satra of विश्वसृक् Daks2a came and was welcomed by all standing, except ब्रह्मा and शिव. On this दक्ष burst into anger against शिव and insulted him saying he had eyes like a monkey, was a breaker of law and convention, lord of the भूतस् and गणस्; he then cursed that शिव should have no more share in sacri- fices and went away. Nandi got enraged at this and im- precated a curse on दक्ष that he would lose all knowledge of आत्मन्, and assuming the face of a sheep, would become dull-witted. भृगु then pronounced a counter-curse that those propitiating शिव shall become पाखण्डस्. {{F}}3:  भा. IV. 2 (whole). M. १३. ११-55, ६०; १८३. २२-3.{{/F}} Appointed by ब्रह्मा as the overlord of all प्रजापतिस्, दक्ष began the sacrifice of बृहस्पतिसव to which all gods went in groups. सती also expressed her desire to go and requested permission of शिव, who reminded her of the insult offered to him. {{F}}4:  Ib. IV. 3. (whole).{{/F}} As she was persistent, she was allowed to attend. Going, she found that she was not properly welcomed by her father. The enraged सती sat facing the northern direction in yoga and cast off her body by means of the fire of समाधी to the distress of gods and others. On this the गण followers of सती attacked दक्ष, when भृगु created a class of gods, ऋभुस् who vanquished these गणस्. {{F}}5:  Ib. IV. 4 (whole).{{/F}} Having heard of all this from नारद, शिव grew angry; out of his anger sprang वीरभद्र who was ordered to ruin दक्ष's sacrifice. The beard of भृगु was cut off, and दक्ष's head was severed from his body and thrown into the दक्षिणाग्नि. {{F}}6:  Ib. IV. 5 (whole). वा. ३० (whole).{{/F}} The Gods waited upon ब्रह्मा who proceeded to कैलास. He conciliat- ed शिव and pleaded for the revival of दक्ष and continuation of his यज्ञ promising a share to him. {{F}}7:  भा. IV. 6 (whole).{{/F}} शिव agreed but [page२-059+ ४३] said that दक्ष should have the face of the sheep, Bhaga, Mitra's eye, and भृगु the beard of a sheep. Agreeing to this ब्रह्मा went with शिव to the sacrificial hall of दक्ष. Now दक्ष began to praise शिव. When विष्णु's offering was poured to secure the continuation of the sacrifice, विष्णु presented himself in person when दक्ष, ऋत्विक्स्, Sadasyas, Rudra and others present, spoke in his praise. Pleased at this, Hari remarked there was no difference among the त्रिमुर्तीस्. दक्ष brought the यज्ञ to a successful end. {{F}}8:  Ib. IV. 7 (whole); २९. ४२.{{/F}}--a R. of the केतुमाला. वा. ४४. १९.--given by स्वायम्भुव Manu to Atri. वा. ६२. ७३.--bathed King Gaya with the waters. भा. V. १५. १०.--the ninth Manu born of वरुण. {{F}}1:  भा. VIII. १३. १८.{{/F}} Three groups of twelve gods in each of पार, मारीचिगर्भ and सुधर्मान. Their Indra was Adbhuta. Savana, Dyu- timan and others were seven sages. Father of धृतिकेतु and other sons. {{F}}2:  Vi. III. 2. २०-24.{{/F}}--as sister and wife of यज्ञ and mother of १२ Ya1ma1 gods. Vi. I. 7. २१.--a daughter of Ruci and आकूती; consort of सुयज्ञ, an अवतार् of Hari. Had twelve sons who were known as तुषित gods (यामस्) of the period of स्वायम्- bhuva Manu. भा. II. 7. 2; IV. 1. 5-8; Br. II. 9. ४४.--the Malaya hill; residence of Agastya. M. ६१. ४०. [page२-064+ ३५]--represents the face of the Veda. वा. १०४. ८५.--in गया. वा. १११. ५०.--a kingdom over which the three sons of Sudyumna ruled; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. 1. ४१.{{/F}} includes the नर्मदा region; {{F}}2:  Br. III. १०. ९८; ६३. 9-१०; M. १५. २८; ११४. २९; वा. ४५. १२४.{{/F}} ruled over by about twenty (forty-eight-वि। प्।) of इक्ष्वा- ku's sons. {{F}}3:  वा. ८८. ११; Vi. IV. 2. १४.{{/F}} गार्ग्य's place of penance. {{F}}4:  Vi. V. २३. 2.{{/F}}--the southern Sun at नैमिष. वा. १०९. २१.--The sun moves fast in; {{F}}1:  वा. ५०. ९२, १३६; ५१. ७३.{{/F}} moves in the midst of पुष्करद्वीप. {{F}}2:  Br. II. २१. ३५-6. Ib. II. २१. ६७.{{/F}}--(Taijasa bandha in other books). वा. १०२. ५९. [page२-063+ २४]--a kingdom through which ऋसभ passed. भा. V. 6. 7.--a तीर्थ; from उत्तरमानस one should go to दक्षिणमानस in silence and thence to उदीची- तीर्थम् where there are three तीर्थस्. वा. १११. 6-8.--of three streets, अजवीथि and the street of constellations श्रवण, धनिष्ठ and सतभिषक् and the street of वैश्वानरी, भाद्रपद and रेवती. Br. III. 3. ५३.--a R. of the South. वा. ७७. 8.--the country to which पुरञ्जन went by the entrance of the पितृस्, allegorically प्रवृत्तिशास्त्र. भा. IV. २५. ५०; २९. १३.--the southern route to the abode of Yama: the place for burial grounds. Br. II. २७. १२५; ३५. १४७; वा. ६१. १२३.--generally the southern people. Vi. II. 3. १६.--the Bay of Bengal. M. १२१. ४४.--a daughter of दक्ष, and a wife of Dharma; mother of Abhaya; {{F}}1:  भा. IV. 1. ४९-50.{{/F}} a शक्ति. {{F}}2:  Br. IV. ४४. ८९.{{/F}}--consequent on the Asuras not obtaining अमृत for all their labours in the अमृतमथन, war broke out. It was on the seashore and mainly a hand- to-hand fight; description of; at last Indra invoked Hari, who appeared on the scene and on him कालनेमि flung his शूल; with the same weapon Hari flung him down; so also माल्य- van, मालि and सुमालि were put to death. Fight continued till नारद stopped it. {{F}}1:  भा. VIII. १०. (whole); ११. 1-४४; वा. ९२. ७६.{{/F}} Twelve in number, after which the whole earth and यज्ञ came over to the Devas. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ७२. ७०, १०६.{{/F}} Hearing the Asuras slain by Hari, Diti went to the earth and performed मदनद्वादशि व्रतम् to get able bodied sons to kill Indra; {{F}}3:  M. 7. 2-7.{{/F}} one, of three hundred years between Indra and प्रह्लाद. Indra with the help of Raji, a son of आयु vanquished him. {{F}}4:  M. २४. ३७-8; ७०. २६-32.{{/F}} Asuras under ह्राद vanquished the Gods after the battle which continued for a hundred divine years. The gods withdrew to the north of the milky ocean and prayed to विष्णु for suc- cour. The latter deluded the Asuras in मायामोह form and the Asuras were defeated. {{F}}5:  Vi. III. १७. 9-४४; १८. ३४-36.{{/F}}(I)--human body; as a temple; philosophical interpretation of. Br. IV. ४३. ५३-54 ff. [page२-136+ २४](II)--one of the twenty अमिताभ gan2as. वा. १००. १७.--a Yogasiddhi. Br. IV. ३६. ५३.--an अमिताभ God. Br. IV. 1. १७.--regions different from राष्ट्रस् and Janapadas. Br. III. ५०. 6.--a provincial or District Governor; acquainted with the produce of the देश and expert in con- trolling officials and keeping accounts. M. २१५. १७.--ordinary teachers. Br. IV. 8. 5.--Guru. Br. IV. ४३. 7.(I)--the name of the 6th Kalpa. M. २९०. 4.(II)--with fourteen faces; born from the four- faced ब्रह्मा with different colours and sounds; from these were born १४ Manus. वा. २६. २७-30. Vi. I. 5. ३३-4.(III)--one of विश्वामित्र's sons. वा. ९१. ९६.(IV)--a son of अक्रूर and उग्रसेनी. वा. ९६. ११२.(V)--a son of Devaka. वा. ९६. १२९.--a Mt. with a Janapada on it; afraid of Hira- ण्यकशिपु's prowess. M. १६३. ८८. [page२-132+ २८]--abodes of the Devas; meddling with, was punished by death. M. २२७. १७४.--playing grounds of the Devas--four; Caitraratha,^8 Nandana, वैभ्राज and Saviturvana (garden of the Sun). वा. ३६. १०.--building of temples, an act of cha- rity. Br. IV. 7. ३३.--the homes of the nine planets; {{F}}1:  Br. II. २३. ९५; वा. ५२. ८५.{{/F}} temples visited by परशुराम; {{F}}2:  Br. III. २४. ४१; २७. ११; IV. ३८. ५७; M. ९६. २५; २५७. 6.{{/F}} see also देवगृहस्.--a son of Uttama Manu. Br. II. ३६. ३९.(I)--a Mt. in कुशद्वीप. भा. V. २०. १५.(II)--a son of क्षेमधन्व and father of अनीह (अहीनगु-ब्र्। प्।, अहीनक-वि। प्।). भा. IX. १२. 2; Br. III. ६३. २०३; M. १२. ५३; वा. ८८. २०३; Vi. IV. 4. १०६. [page२-131+ ३२](III)--a son of (Dharma) सावर्ण Manu. वा. १००. ८४. Vi. III. 2. ३२.--a son of कालनेमि. Br. III. 5. ३९; वा. ६७. ८०.--a son of Auttama Manu. वा. ६२. ३४.(I)--a son of प्रतीप and brother of शन्तनु; renounced the home and turned मुनि; requested by शन्तनु to take up the throne; he spoke impeaching the Vedas. He took to yoga living in कलापग्राम. He was to establish the Lunar race in the कृत Yuga; Purohita of the Devas; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २२. १२-18; XII. 2. ३७; वा. ९९. २३४.{{/F}} un- acceptable to the people as he suffered from leprosy. {{F}}2:  M. ५०. ३९-41; २७३. ५६.{{/F}} A राजऋषि and a gotrapravartaka of the Treta yuga {{F}}3:  वा. ३२. ३९.{{/F}} and a Paurava.(II)--a Paurava king who continues to live in Kali in कलापग्राम; क्षत्रप्रणेतार in the २४थ् Catur- yuga. Originator of क्षत्रियस् in the कृत. {{F}}1:  वा. ९९. ४३७-8; Vi. IV. २४-118.{{/F}} A son of Pra- तीप. Even as a child retired to forest. The famine in his brother Santanu's (s.v) kingdom was said to be due to his elder brother देवापि having been passed over for succes- sion. Infected with heretical views through the minister of शन्तनु by means of ascetics in the forest; thus disquali- fied for the throne. {{F}}2:  Vi. IV. २०. 9-३०.{{/F}}--a great forest on the banks of the लौहित्या lake. वा. ४७. ११.--one of the ten sons of हृदीक. Father of कम्बलबर्हिष. M. ४४. ८२-3; वा. ९६. १३९; Vi. IV. १४. २४.--the brother of Vasudeva. वा. ९६. १४७. [page२-134+ २५](I)--a son of Krodhana and father of ऋष्य. भा. IX. २२. ११. Vi. IV. २०. 5.(II)--a son of Akrodhana. M. ५०. ३७; वा. ९९. २३२.(I)--a son of सात्वत and father of Babhru; equal to Gods; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २४. 6-१०; Vi. IV. १३. 1-3.{{/F}} sonless he performed penance on the banks of the पर्णाशा (s.v.) which became transformed into a maid, married him and became mother of Babhru. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ७१. १६-15; M. ४४. ४७-59; वा. ९६. 6-१५.{{/F}} The वायु पुराण says that when he made austerities, he touched the waters of the सवऋणा when सावित्री appeared as a lady, received his तेजस् and brought forth a good son in the ninth month. This was Babhru. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ७१. १६-15; M. ४४. ४७-59; वा. ९६. 6-१५.{{/F}} Belonged to the Anu line and was much praised by poets and scholars. ६६०८ disciples of his, obtained immortality. {{F}}3:  Vi. IV. १३. 6.{{/F}}(II)--a son of कौशल्य. वा. 1. १४५; ९६. 1. [page२-133+ ३६]--a Mt. of क्रौञ्चद्वीप. M. १२२. ८२.(I)--a son of हृदीक, and father of Kam- बलबर्हिष. भा. IX. २४. २७; Br. III. ७१. १४१. [page२-119+ २४](II)--the second son of प्रीती and Pulastya. Br. II. ११. २७; वा. २८. २२.(III)--a Paulastya and a sage of the Rai- vata epoch. Br. II. ३६. ६१. M. 9. १९.(I)--a son of देवमिढ and मारिषा; husband of कम्सा and father of Citraketu and बृहद्बल. भा. IX. २४. २८, ४०.(II)--a son of शूर; father of महाभाग. Br. III. ७१. १४९. १८८.(III)--the father of Uddhava. M. ४६. २३.(IV)--a brother of Vasudeva. वा. ९६. १४७. Vi. IV. १४. ३०.--a forest. वा. ४२. ४६.--the milkman who milked the cow-earth in the epoch of Uttama Manu. वा. ६३. १५.(I)--a शुङ्ग ruler and son of भागवत, ruled for १० years; killed by his minister Vasudeva who became king. (क्षेमभूमि-वा। प्।). Br. III. ७४. १५५. वा. ९९. ३४४. [page२-120+ २४](II)--the son of समाभाग, ruled for ten years. M. २७२. ३१.--the son of भागवत the last of the शुन्- gas; killed by his अमात्य Vasudeva. भा. XII. 1. १८-20. Vi. IV. २४. ३६-7, ३९.--a sacred place in कालसर्पी; {{F}}1:  Br. III. १३. ९९.{{/F}} on the slopes of the मुण्डपृष्ठ; {{F}}2:  वा. २३. १९५; १०८. ६६.{{/F}} a तीर्थम् sacred to पुष्टि. {{F}}3:  M. १३. ४७.{{/F}}--a pupil of Kabandha; he divided the Sam- hitas into four among his four pupils. Br. II. ३५. ५७; Vi. III. 6. 9-१०.(I)--a chief नाग of पाताल. भा. V. १४. २४; २४. ३१; VI. 9. ३५.(II)--the son of उरुश्रव and father of अग्निवेश. भा. IX. 2. २०-21. [page२-117+ २८](III)--the horse of Kalki. भा. XII. 2. १९.--see महेश्वर. Br. IV. 2. २५७.--शिव. Br. III. २२. ७८.--the city of Indra on the मानसोत्तर, east of Meru. भा. V. २१. 7.--musicians in heaven; were overjoyed at the देवी's starting for war. Br. III. ६३. ५३; IV. २०. १००.--the son of देवताजित् and आसुरि; husband of धेनुमती and father of परमेष्ठी. भा. V. १५. 3.--thirty-three in number. वा. ६६. ८०.--a son of हृदिक and father of शूर. Vi. IV. १४. २४-5.--a R. of कुशद्वीप. भा. V. २०. १५.--Mt. a hill in भारतवर्ष. भा. V. १९. १६.--planets as houses of Gods and which stand until Pralaya. Br. II. २४. 2; वा. ५३. 2.--(देवगुही-ब्र्। प्।); the husband of सरस्वती and father of सार्वभौम Hari. भा. VIII. १३. १७.--see बृहस्पति. M. २३. ३०-47. [page२-116+ २९]--the father of योगेश्वर. भा. VIII. १३. ३२.--in the सालग्राम; here नागराट् takes the पिण्ड of the deserving and rejects that of the undeserving. Br. III. १३. ९०.--the entrance on the north side of the city of पुरञ्जन, {{F}}1:  भा. IV. २५. ५१; २९. १२.{{/F}} allegorically the left ear.(I)--a daughter of स्वायम्भुव Manu, and sister of Priyavrata and उत्तानपाद; wife of Kardama and mother of Kapila; {{F}}1:  भा. II. 7. 3; III. १२. २७, ५५-6; २१. 3; २२. 9; VIII. 1. 5.{{/F}} heard of Kardama's greatness from नारद and fixed her mind on him; accepted by Kardama; seeing her playing with balls in her mansion विश्वावसु fell down in a fit of stupour; married Kardama with gifts from her parents; devoted herself to her husband's service like पार्वती to शिव; enjoyed his company in an aerial car well furnished with new cloths and ornaments after her bath in the सरस्वतिसरस्, where she was attended by many maids; roamed in all lovely parks throughout the earth. After a hundred years of enjoyment देवहूती gave birth to nine daughters at a time, when Kardama told her of his depar- ture for yoga; देवहूती requested means for protection of herself and the new-born ones; was told that विष्णु would be born in her womb and he would bring comfort to her. Soon she gave birth to Lord Kapila when ब्रह्मा and other seers called on Kardama. After they left, Kardama got his daughters married, and after praising Kapila, and with his permission he went away for penance. Heard all relating to the साङ्ख्य शास्त्र from Kapila and spoke in praise of him. Following the path prescribed by Kapila she attained निर्- वाण। The place where she attained siddhi became known as शिद्धपद। {{F}}2:  Ib. VIII. Chh. २२ to २४ (whole); ३३. 1-३१; IV. I. 1 and १०.{{/F}} From her, Hari manifested Himself for imparting धर्म and ज्ञान। {{F}}3:  Ib. VIII. 1. 5.{{/F}}(II)--the wife of पुरूरवस्. वा. 2. १६. [page२-130+ २२]--the son of संयम. भा. IX. 2. ३४.--(देवजननी-वा। प्।) the wife of मणिवर, the यक्ष; gave birth to a number of sons who in their turn became the fathers and grandfathers of several children. Br. III. 7. १२१, १२७; वा. ६९. १५३, १५८-163.--a त्रयार्षेय. M. १९६. ४३.(I)--a Bhoja, and son of आहुक (आहुकान्ध- वा। प्।); brother of Ugrasena, hated by Kamsa. {{F}}1:  भा. I. १४. २७; III. 1. ३३; X. ३६. २४ [३१] and ३४; Br. III. ७१. १२९-30; M. ४४. ७१-2; Vi. IV. १४. १६-17.{{/F}} देवकी was one of his seven daughters, all of whom were married to Vasudeva. Father of four sons देववान् and others. {{F}}2:  भा. IX. २४. २१-23; वा. ९६. १२८-9; Vi. IV. १४. १८-19; V. 1. 5.{{/F}} Gave rich presents to his daughter देवकी when she was married. {{F}}3:  भा. X. 1. ३२.{{/F}}(II)--a son of युधिष्ठिर by पौरवी (Yau- धेयी-वि। प्।). भा. IX. २२. ३०. Vi. IV. २०. ४४.--a class of people in क्रौञ्चद्वीप. भा. V. २०. २२.(I)--(देवकभोजपुत्री Suna1ma1) a Bhoja princess; a daughter of Devaka, one of the wives of Vasu- deva and mother of eight sons of whom कृष्ण was one, all of them comparable to the eight Vasus; {{F}}1:  भा. I. 1. १२; III. 1. ३३; 2. २५; IX. २४. २३, ४५, ५३; X. 1. 8 and २९; ३६. १७; Br. I. 1. १२५; M. ४४. ७३; ४६. १३-15; ४७. 2; वा. 1. १४८; ९६. १६३, १७२-4; Vi. IV. १४. १८; १५. १८. २६-30.{{/F}} oppressed by Kamsa and relieved by कृष्ण; was about to be murdered by Kamsa who heard a divine voice that her eighth child would be the cause of his end; on Vasudeva's assurance to give up the babies as they were born she was allowed to go. Her first child कीर्तिमत् was taken to Kamsa who returned the baby. She was imprisoned with Vasudeva to watch over the birth of her sons. During her seventh pregnancy the धाम of Hari in her womb was transferred by योगमाया to that of रोहिणी and it was said that देवकी aborted. Then the अम्श of Hari entered her womb and she grew beautiful every day. ब्रह्मा, शिव and other Gods waited on her on the eve of कृष्ण's birth and said that her son was to kill [page२-114+ ३८] Kamsa: addressed the new-born कृष्ण. In the स्वायम्- bhuva epoch she was पृश्नि and Vasudeva was Sutapa. In another epoch she was Aditi and Vasudeva was कश्यप. यशोदा's daughter exchanged for देवकी's son and Kamsa was told of the birth of a girl; was released from prison along with Vasudeva; forgave and advised Kamsa; was saluted by कृष्ण and राम. {{F}}2:  भा. X. Chh. 1-4; ४४. ५०-51; ४५. 1-१२; भा. I. 8. २३. ३३; ११. २८; X. ३६. २०; ४३. २४. Vi. V. 2. 2; 4. १४; १८. 7-8.{{/F}} युधिष्ठिर asked Arjuna about her welfare. {{F}}3:  भा. I. १४. २७.{{/F}} कृष्ण's respects to, after his return from Indra's abode. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. [६७ (V) ४८].{{/F}} देवकी came to रुक्मिणी's palace with Vasudeva and कृष्ण; {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ५५. ३५.{{/F}} felt concerned at कृष्ण not returning from the cave of जाम्ब- वान् and aided by others prayed to दुर्गा for कृष्ण's return; {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ५६. ३४-5.{{/F}} wondered at the discourses between Nimi and the sages, sons of ऋषभ; {{F}}7:  Ib. XI. 5. ५१.{{/F}} embraced यशोदा at स्यमन्तपञ्चक and enquired after her welfare; {{F}}8:  Ib. X. ८२. ३७.{{/F}} praised कृष्ण and राम and desired to see her sons who had been killed by Kamsa; saw them with joy when taken back from Sutala by कृष्ण; in her presence they left for heaven. {{F}}9:  Ib. X. ८५. २७-33, ५२, ५६-70.{{/F}} Her grief at the decease of राम, कृष्ण and others; entered fire. {{F}}१०:  Ib. XI. ३१. १८; Vi. V. ३८. 4.{{/F}}(II)--a goddess enshrined at मथुरा. M. १३. ३९.(III)--the mother of Yaudheya by युधिष्ठिर. M. ५०. ५६.--the seventeenth व्यास; अवतार् of गुहावासि. वा. २३. १७४.--Temples where dancing girls were enter- tained in service. M. ७०. २८. [page२-115+ २५]--a daughter of पूर्णिमन् and mother of प्रस्ताव; having washed विष्णु's feet became a celestial river. भा. IV. 1. १४; V. १५. 6.--(दवशैल-वा। प्।). A Mt. to the cast of मेरुमूल, full of गरुड birds. भा. V. १६. २७; Br. III. 7. ४५२; वा. ३५. 8; ३७. २८; ४०. 1; ४२, २१; ४३. १२.(I)--a Siddha, and a son of धिषणा and कृशाश्व, and identified with Hari; {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 6. २०; १५. १२; XI. १६. २८.{{/F}} came to see परिक्षित् practising प्रायोपवेश; {{F}}2:  Ib. I. १९. १०.{{/F}} knew the yoga power of विष्णु; {{F}}3:  Ib. II. 7. ४५.{{/F}} told शुक्र the story of Citraketu; {{F}}4:  Ib. VI. १४. 9.{{/F}} cursed हूहू to be born a crocodile; {{F}}5:  Ib. VIII. 4. 3.{{/F}} did not comprehend Hari's माय, {{F}}6:  Ib. IX. 4. ५७.{{/F}} came to see कृष्ण at स्यमन्तपञ्चक; {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ८४. 3.{{/F}} a ब्रह्मवादिन्; {{F}}8:  M. १४५. १०७.{{/F}} exclusion of marriage alliances with कश्यपस् and Asitas. {{F}}9:  Ib. १९९. १९.{{/F}}(II)--a son of प्रत्यूष and father of two sons; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 3. २७; वा. ६६. २६; Vi. I. १५. ११७.{{/F}} a Vasava. {{F}}2:  M. 5. २७; २०३. 7.{{/F}} [page२-125+ २७](III)--a son of Asita and एकपर्णा; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 8. ३२; १०. १९; वा. ७०. २७; ७२. १७.{{/F}} a Brahma- वादिन् and the best among the शाण्डिल्यस्. {{F}}2:  Br. II. ३२. ११३; III. 8. ३२; वा. ५९. १०३; ७०. २८.{{/F}}(IV)--a son of Vasudeva and उपदेवी; (शिशिरा- वती-ब्र्। प्।). Br. III. ७१. १८२; M. ४६. १७.(V)--father of Sannati, a queen of Brahmadatta, the पाञ्चाल king. M. २०. २६.(VI)--a son of the श्वेत अवतार् of the Lord. वा. २३. २०५.(VII)--the son of पारियात्रक and father of वच्चाल. Vi. IV. 4. १०६.--people living in म्लेच्छ regions and ineligi- ble for श्राद्धा purposes. M. १६. १५.--of कौशिक gotra. Br. III. ६६. ७२. वा. ९१. १००.--seven in number--भू