ted. देवयानि reported शर्मिष्ठा's con- duct to her father शुक्र who left the palace in disgust. The king implored him on his knees, when शुक्र agreed to stay on if शर्मिष्ठा would be appointed as servant of his daughter. This was agreed upon, and शर्मिष्ठा became her servant. When देवयानी was married to ययाति, शुक्र presented शर्मिष्ठा as his daughter's maid. She had two sons Yadu and Turvasu. Learning of her husband's connec- tion with शर्मिष्ठा during her own pregnancy, देवयानी left for her father's house. ययाति followed her and was cursed by शुक्र to fall a prey to old age. ययाति appealed to him to mitigate the curse as his desire for enjoyment with his daughter was still keen. Then शुक्र said that if anyone would give him his youth and take up old age then he could regain his youth. His son पूरु agreed and once more the king enjoyed the company of देवयानी; {{F}}2:  भा. IX. १८. 7-५१; M. २५. 7; Chh. २६ to ३२.{{/F}} heard the story of an ewe loved by a ram from ययाति, and thought it was an allusion to her; became detached and cast off her body with her mind on Hari. {{F}}3:  भा. IX. १९. (whole); Br. III. 1. ८६; ६८. १५; वा. ९३. १५-16.{{/F}} ^1 भा. V. 1. ३४; M. २४. ५२-3; वा. 1. १५५; ६५. ८४; ९८. २०; Vi. IV. १०. 4, २०.(II)--a daughter of जयन्ती and a grand- daughter of Indra. M. ४७. १८६.--a festival being celebrated at द्वारका when Arjuna carried off सुभद्रा. भा. X. ८६. 9.--four; गन्धर्वास्, आध्यस्, पिशाचास् and अन्तास्; their relative positions and powers. वा. ६९. २०३.--ten in number. वा. ६१. १३१ [page२-123+ २४]--see Indra. Br. III. 7. २६९; IV. १२. ३५; M. १४६. २०; Vi. I. 8. २६; 9. १६, १३९. [page२-135+ २५]--Gods of prime importance, of secondary importance; share in sacrifices; they are Gurus, Lords, Kings and Forefathers; protect the subjects. वा. ६४. २१-23.--ललिता. Br. IV. १४. 1.(I)--the first charioteer; a शक्ति. Br. IV. 6. १७; २०. ९१.(II)--the image of. M. २५८. ७५; २६६, ४२.(III)--an Apsaras. वा. ६९. 6.--utterance of, in दीक्षा। Br. IV. ४३. ११.--the observance of th