 of the Lord; स्वर्ग as the sun. Br. II. १०. ८२; वा. २७. ५४.--a son of Vaivasvata Manu and father of नाभाग. भा. VIII. १३. 2; IX. 1. १२; 2. २३; Br. II. ३८. ३१; III. ६०. 3. Vi. IV. 1. 7.(I)--a daughter of दक्ष, and wife of कश्यप. {{F}}1:  भा. III. १४. 7; वा. ६६. ५४; Vi. I. १५. १२४, १४०.{{/F}} Her sons generally known as Daityas. Mother of हिरण्याक्ष and हिरण्यकशिपु. {{F}}2:  भा. VI. 6. २५; १८. ११; VII. 1. ३९; Br. III. 3. ५६; M. 6. 1-8; वा. ६७. ४९.{{/F}} Mother of Dantavaktra by the sage's curse. {{F}}3:  भा. IX. २४. ३७.{{/F}} Her sons प्रह्लाद and Hari were devotees of Hari. {{F}}4:  Ib. VI. १८. १०.{{/F}} Always set her mind on truth; {{F}}5:  Ib. VII. 2. ६१.{{/F}} daughter सिम्हिका; {{F}}5: a) वा. ६७. ६०.{{/F}} (आदित्य्-वा। प्।). Finding her sons slain by Hari to help Indra, she became enraged, and asked her husband to bless her with a child to kill Indra. The un- willing husband offered it on condition of her observing certain vows for १०० years. So she observed them and Indra came to assist her. One day he found her sleep- ing in an unorthodox posture and entering her womb cut the embryo into seven and then into ४९ pieces; but at her request he gave all of them the status of gods, known as Maruts. {{F}}6:  भा. VI. १८. २३-77; Br. I. 1. ११२; ch. 5 (whole); 7. ४६५; IV. 9. 3; M. 6. ४७; ch. 7 (whole); वा. ६७. ८६, १३५; Vi. I. २१. ३०-41.{{/F}} Impelled by passion and desire for children she approached her husband one evening for sexual intercourse. कश्यप said that it was the hour when शिवगणस् moved about and for him, to offer the शन्ध्य-prayer. But she persisted and gained her object. She however requested to be redeemed of the sin. कश्यप [page२-088+ ३४] remarked that since she approached him at the wrong time, her sons would have पैशाच-character and would be killed by Hari. For her penitence she was blessed with a righteous child among her grandsons. {{F}}7:  भा. III. १४ (whole).{{/F}} Held the तेजस् in embryo for a hundred years when darkness enveloped all directions. The two door-keepers of वैकुण्ठ cursed by seers for preventing them from having दर्सन् of Hari were born as her two sons, when there were evil omens. {{F}}8:  Ib. VI. १५. 1-१०; १६. ३५; १७. 2-१५.{{/F}} Prayed for another son. This was वज्रान्ग who on his birth accord- ing to her orders bound Indra. The latter was released on the mediation of ब्रह्मा and कश्यप. {{F}}9:  M. १४६. १८-55; १७१. २९.{{/F}} Mother of Daityas; a Mother Goddess to be worshipped in house and palace buildings {{F}}१०:  Ib. १७१. ५८; १७९. १५; २५१. २९; २५३. २७; २६८. १९.{{/F}} योगनिद्रा addressed as; {{F}}११:  Vi V. 2. 9.{{/F}} sons of, in the seventh तलम् or पातालम्. {{F}}१२:  वा. ५०. ४३.{{/F}}(II)--a Mauneya. वा. ६९. 2.--(दिवार्क ब्र्। प्।)--son of भानु and father of Sahadeva; leader of an army. भा. IX. १२. १०-11.(I)--the Sun god, king of the planets; {{F}}1:  M. १५०. १५१; २६५. ३८ and ४१. २६६. ३८. २८१. १२. वा. २८. ३२.{{/F}} is Agni; {{F}}2:  Ib. ५३. २९, ३०.{{/F}} different positions of, in the sky in different lands; {{F}}3:  Br. II. २१. ३७-43.{{/F}} struck by स्वभानु, fell on the earth; {{F}}4:  Br. II. २२. १२; III. 3. ११०; 8. ७६.{{/F}} addressed by कार्त्तिकेय to whom he went as a Brahmana; {{F}}5:  Ib. III. ७०. 4.{{/F}} at a distance of १०००×100 yojanas from the earth. {{F}}6:  वा. १०१. १२९.{{/F}}(II)--a son of Prativyoma (प्रतिव्यूह वा। प्।); his capital अयोध्या; (वा। प्।)। {{F}}1:  M. २७१. 5; वा. ९९. २८२.{{/F}} Father of Sahadeva. {{F}}2:  Vi. IV. २२. 3.{{/F}}(III)--divided the earth into ten political divisions and distributed them among इक्स्वाकु and other [page२-091+ २८] cognates. Sudyumna in woman's disguise did not get any share; वसिष्ठ got him प्रतिष्टा and he in turn offered it to Pururavas. वा. ८५. २०-23.--a class of पितृस् propitiated on every New- Moon Day; {{F}}1:  Br. II. २८. २३, ९३; वा. ५६. २१; ७३. ६२.{{/F}} to them कृष्णपक्ष is day and शुक्लपक्ष is night. {{F}}2:  वा. ५६. ८७.{{/F}}--a class of Gods performing श्राद्ध. Br. III. १०. ११०.--Mt. a hill of क्रौञ्चद्वीप. Br. II. १९. ६७; 