rtune. Br. III. ६९. ५४; M. ४३. ४९; वा. ९४. ५३.--a son of Dana. भा. VI. 6. ३१.(I)--a companion of पुरञ्जन, allegori- cally उपस्थ। भा. IV. २५. ५२; २९. १४.(II)--a son of Bhadrasenaka (or Bhadra- sena) and father of Dhanaka. (Kanaka-ब्र्। प्।). भा. IX. २३. २३; Br. III. ६७. ६६; ६९. 7.(III)--(see Durdama) a son of रोहिणी and Vasudeva. भा. IX. २४. ४६-47.(IV)--a son of Vasudeva and पौरवी. भा. IX. २४. ४७. [page२-103+ २६](V)--an Asura commander of ten अक्षौ- हिणिस् was sent against ललिता accompanied by noisy पटह; rode on the camel, succeeded in taking a jewel from the crown of सम्पत्करी-Sarasvati, who being enraged struck him at the breast; he fell dead and his followers were mas- sacred. The rest fled to the सून्यक city in fear. Br. IV. २२. १९, २८, ४७.(VI)--a name of विघ्नेश्वर. Br. IV. ४४. ६८.(VII)--a son of भद्रश्रेणि; (see Dur- dama). वा. ९४. 7.(VIII)--of the रोहिणि family; see also Dur- dama; a son of रोहिणि and आनकदुन्दुभि. वा. ९६. १६९; Vi. १५. १९.--the son of धृत and father of Pracetas. भा. IX. २३. १५.--fought with कामदेव in the देवासुर war. भा. VIII. १०. ३३.--a son of शृञ्जय and राष्ट्रपालि. भा. IX. २४. ४२.--the son of पुष्पमिष्ट. भा. XII. 1. ३४.(I)--a राक्षस killed in the लङ्का war. भा. IX. १०. १८. [page२-104+ ४८](II)--a काद्रवेय Na1ga. Br. III. 7. ३५; M. 6. ४१; वा. ६९. ७१.(III)--a son of खश and a राक्षस. Br. III. 7. १३६; वा. ६९. १६७.(IV)--a विघ्ननायक. Br. IV. २७. ८१.(V)--a son of सुहोत्री, the अवतार् of the Lord. वा. २३. १२७.--born of Krodha and हिम्सा; sister and also wife of Kali. भा. IV. 8. 3-4.--see दुरितक्षय. According to मत्स्य पुराण the name is उरुक्षय. Vi. IV. १९. २४. [page२-100+ ३५]--(दूर्वाक्षी-ब्र्। प्।) the queen of वृक. भा. IX. २४. ४३.(I)--a son of Atri and an younger brother of दत्तात्रेय; {{F}}1:  भा. IV. 1. १५; Br. III. 8. ८२; वा. ७०. ७६.{{/F}} an अम्श of शिव; {{F}}2:  भा. IV. 1. ३३.{{/F}} appeared before अम्बरीष who was about to break his द्वादसि fast; agreed to accept his hospitality, went to the river for bath and tarried there; finding the मुहूर्त for पारण (break-fast) drawing to a close, the king broke his fast with some water. Coming to know of this on his return, the sage produced a flaming spirit to attack him. But Hari's चक्र burnt it down and turned towards the sage, who ran for succour to ब्रह्मा, शिव and विष्णु. All of them were unable to help; but Hari advised him to meet अम्बरीष and apologise to him. {{F}}3:  Ib. IX. 4. ३५-71.{{/F}} This he did and was set at liberty. After partaking the meals with him, he returned to Brahmaloka; {{F}}4:  Ib. IX. 5. 1-२२.{{/F}} blessed पृथ with secret मन्त्रस् to summon gods. {{F}}5:  Ib. IX. २४. ३२; XI. 1. १२.{{/F}} Through him Duryodhana planned to destroy the पाण्डवस् by inciting him to go to them and ask for a feast. But कृष्ण protected them on the occasion. {{F}}6:  Ib. I. १५. ११.{{/F}} In the course of his sojourn he met a विद्या- [page२-106+ २३] dhara maid with a garland given to her by the देवी; took it from her and presented it to Indra who put it on his elephant, who in turn threw it on the ground and trampled upon it. Enraged at this, the sage cursed him to be lost to all fortune. {{F}}7:  Ib. VIII. 5. १६; Br. IV. 5. १६-20; 9. ३१; ४०. १२०.{{/F}}(II)--a Siddha. भा. VI. १५. १३.(III)--one of the Sages who left for पिण्डा- raka. भा. XI. 1. १२.--a son of देवयानि; cursed by his father for refusing to part with his youth. {{F}}1:  Vi. IV. १०. 6, १३.{{/F}} Viceroy of south-east king- dom; {{F}}2:  Ib. IV. १०. ३१.{{/F}} line of; father of Vanhi; got merged into Puru's line ultimately. {{F}}3:  Ib. IV. १६. 2-6.{{/F}}--a commander of भण्ड. Br. IV. २१. ८७.--the eldest of the hundred sons of धृत- राष्ट्र and गान्धारि; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २२. २६; X. ६४. [4]; M. ५०. ४८; वा. ९९. २४३; Vi. IV. २०. ३९.{{/F}} सुभद्रा was intended by राम to be given in marriage to him; {{F}}2:  भा. X. ८६. 3.{{/F}} was met by कृतवर्मन् and taken leave of; {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ५२. (५६. V. १२).{{/F}} went from Balabhadra and learnt गदा from बलराम at मिथिला; {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ५७. २६; Br. III. ७१. ८४; वा. ९६. ८३.{{/F}} mistook the colour of the flooring of the पाण्डव's सभा (built by Maya) for a sheet of water and had a nasty fall at which भीम and the ladies laughed. This enraged Duryodhana who was conciliated by युधिष्ठिर who sent clothes to him through कृष्ण. He did not accept them, but went home downcast; {{F}}5:  भा. X. ५८. २७; ७५. ३४-39.{{/F}} kept under influence Vinda and Anuvinda of Avanti; {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ५८. ३०.{{/F}} banished the पाण्डवस् and द्रौपदी to the forest for defeat in the game of dice; {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ६४. [4].{{/F}} resented साम्ब's action in taking away his daughter लक्ष्मणा in स्वयम्वर and wanted to punish him; heard of राम's arrival and extended welcome to him; afraid of राम's prowess agreed to the marriage of his daughter to साम्ब and gave a rich dowry; {{F}}8:  Ib. X. ६८. (whole); Vi. V. ३५. 4-5, ११.{{/F}} did not feel happy over the success of the राजसूय, where he was in charge of the treasury; {{F}}9:  भा. X. ७४. ५३; ७५. 2 and 4.{{/F}} failed to hit the fish mark in लक्ष्मणा's स्वयम्वर; {{F}}१०:  Ib. X. ८३. २३.{{/F}} Jealous of कृष्ण and द्रौपदी, his mind set on the latter; {{F}}११:  Ib. X. ७५. ३१-32.{{/F}} ordered Vidura's banishment for offering good counsel, and insulted him as the son of a दासि; {{F}}१२:  Ib. I. 7. १४; III. 1. १४-15.{{/F}} met the पाण्डवस् in war at कुरुक्षेत्र; arranged in व्यूह at Syamanta- [page२-105+ ३९] पञ्चक; fought with भीमसेन who killed him with his गद; lay in the battlefield with his thigh fractured, along with eleven अक्षौहिणिस्. {{F}}१३:  Ib. X. ७८ (१६ (V) १५, १८-19), ३९; ७९. २३; ८० [1]; III. 3. १३; M. १०३. 3-5.{{/F}} Built a house of lac to get the पाण्डवस् consumed by flames. {{F}}१४:  Vi. IV. १३. ७०.{{/F}}--of the Paurava line, adopted as son by Marutta; father of सरूप्य. Br. III. ७४. 3-5.(पूरण); one of the १६ classes of पिशाचस्. Br. III. 7. ३७७.--a son of धृतराष्ट्र, gave evil advice to Duryodhana. भा. III. 3. १३; Vi. IV. २०. ३९; V. ३५. २७. [page२-107+ ३३]--a daughter of धृतराष्ट्र. भा. IX. २२. २६.--a commander of भण्ड. Br. IV. २१. ८७.--an Asura; created by भण्ड. Br. IV. १०. ८१.(I)--a son of Raibhya and उपदानवी; a king; while out for hunting came to कण्व's hermitage, saw the beautiful शकुन्तला, married her by the गान्धर्वविधि and left for his capital the next day. A son Bharata was born to शकुन्तला and he was brought up by कण्व. शकुन्तला came to his palace with the boy but दुष्यन्त had forgotten her. A voice from the air asked him to accept them, his wife and son, which he did; {{F}}1:  भा. I. १२. २०; IX. २०. 7-२२ [1-2]; M. ४९. १०-11; Br. III. 6. २५; वा. ६८. २४; ९९. १३३-6.{{/F}} removed from hell by the son. {{F}}2:  Vi. IV. १९. 9-१०.{{/F}}(II)--of Puru's line, was adopted by Marut(t)a as his son; returned to the line of Yadu, the eldest son of ययाति; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २३. १७-18; वा. ९९. 3; वी. IV. १६. 5-6.{{/F}} through ययाति's curse the Turvasu and the Paurava dynasties became commingled. {{F}}2:  M. ४८. 2-3.{{/F}}(I)--a plant sacred to Hari; {{F}}1:  भा. V. 3. 6.{{/F}} from this दूर्वञ्- janam, being an auspicious thing to be looked at in the morning. {{F}}2:  Br. III. २८. १०.{{/F}}(II)--a son of नृपञ्जय: his son Timi. भा. IX. २२. ४२.(I)--an Asura; was killed by राम. भा. IX. १०. 9.(II)--a son of विश्रवस् and वाका. Br. III. 8. ५६. वा. ७०. ५०.--the queen of Bhauvana and mother of त्वष्टा. भा. V. १५. १५.--a messenger: to report as he has been told and to be skilled in languages of different countries; one who can adjust according to time and place; {{F}}1:  M. २१५. १२-4; २५४. २४.{{/F}} of Indra to तारक [page२-108+ २६] to get him ready for war after the birth of कार्त्तिकेय; {{F}}2:  M. ३८. १९; १५९. २४.{{/F}} of पौण्ड्रक. {{F}}3:  Vi. V. ३४. 6.{{/F}}(I)--an अक्षर devi1. Br. IV. १९. ५८; ३७. ३४.(II)--a Mind-born mother. M. १७९. १०.--Those who medidate on the १२ letters are not re-born. Vi. I. 6. ४०; १२. ९७.--an epithet of the Sun god. Br. III. ५९. ७६; IV. ३४. ७५.--the day of the birth of वामन--Hari. भा. VIII. १८. 6.--अम्बरीष observed this vow for a year and ended it in