e performed every year; for this only three पिण्डस् are prescribed; details of ritual. M. १८. 1 & २५; Vi. III. १३. २३, ४०.--a reptile of पाताल. M. १६३. ५६. [page१-280+ ३०](I)--a १००० headed नाग; living with the sun for a part of the year; in the month of नभ। भा. XII. ११. ३७; Br. II. २३. 9; M. 6. ४०; १२६. १०; Vi. II. १०. 9.--the नाग with the sun in नभ and नभ- स्य (आवणि and पुरट्टाशि). वा. ५२. १०.(II)--a काद्रवेय Na1ga. Br. III. 7. ३४.--a तीर्थम् sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ५०.--heard the विष्णु पुराण from Kambala and narrated it to वेदशिरस् who went to पाताल. Vi. VI. 8. ४७-8.--a तीर्थम् sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ५३.--the grass growing on the seashore, supposed to be grown out of the particles of the मुसल given birth to [page१-279+ २०] by साम्ब and thrown into the sea by the order of the यादव king. भा. XI. 1. २२.(I)--a daughter of काकुस्थ, and wife of Yati. Br. III. ६८. १३: वा. ९३. १४.(II)--a name of सरस्वती. वा. २३. 5, ५५.--see विश्वामित्र. M. १४५. १११.--(कौशिक) a royal sage who knew the yoga powers of Hari; {{F}}1:  भा. I. १९. 9: II. 7. ४४. वा. ९१. ६५-6.{{/F}} the son of कुशाम्बु(a) (कुशनाभ- वा। प्।) Indra incarnate. His daughter was सत्यवती whom the ब्राह्मण R2ci1ka wanted to marry. गाधि thought him unsuitable and asked for a bride-fee of a thousand horses white like the moon and with one ear black. This condition was satisfied with the help of वरुण, and ऋचीक got her married. गाधि's wife took the consecrated चरु intended for her daughter and became the mother of a Brahmavit, by name विश्वामीत्र. {{F}}2:  भा. IX. १५. 4-१०: १६. २८ and ३२. Vi. IV. 7. ११-16.{{/F}} He was desirous of more territory on the earth. {{F}}3:  भा. XII. 3. 9.{{/F}} Son of कुशिक, wife Paurukutsi. {{F}}4:  Br. III. ६६. ३५. ५८.{{/F}}--a name of अक्रूर. वा. ९६. ८०. [page१-527+ ३०](I)--a sage of the VIIIth manvantara, a sage of सावर्णि epoch; a भार्गव gotrakara and a pravara sage. भा. VIII. १३. १५. Br. III. ६६-72; IV. 1. १०. M. 9. ३२; १९५. २२; १९६. ३१. Vi. III. 2. १७. [page१-533+ २४](II)--a sage who ca