. 8. 9.{{/F}} He held कृष्ण and राम to be divine incarnations. {{F}}2:  भा. X. ४६. २३.{{/F}} He informed Nanda that कृष्ण was the son of Vasudeva and an अम्श of नारायण. {{F}}3:  Ib. २६. १५-23.{{/F}} He officiated at उपनयन सम्स्कारस् of the two brothers. {{F}}4:  Ib. ४५. २६-29.{{/F}} He had also informed Mucukunda that नारायण was to be born on [page१-521+ २६] the earth as कृष्ण. {{F}}5:  Ib. ५१. ४५.{{/F}} He was invited for the राजसूय of युधिष्ठिर. {{F}}6:  Ib. ७४. 8.{{/F}}(III)--an Angirasa and a मन्त्रकृत्. Br. II. ३२. १०७: M. १४५. १०१.(IV)--the Purohita of Haiha. Br. III. २८. ३९.(V)--a son of Pratardana. Br. III. ६७. ६९: वा. ९२. ६५.(VI)--the preceptor of the seven sons of कौशिक who tended his cow, killed and made a meal of it in a famine. For this sin they were cursed to have five rebirths; no mar- riage alliance with बृहस्पति. M. २०. 3: १९६. २४.(VII)--an author of architecture. M. २५२. 3.(VIII)--a ऋत्विक् at ब्रह्मा's sacrifice. वा. १०६. ३५.--the son of गार्ग्य; of Vatsa line. Br. III. ६७. ७८.--a तीर्थम् on the नर्मदा. M. १९१. ८२. 3.--a सिद्धिदेवी. Br. IV. १९. 4: ३६. ५१.--a दानव. Br. III. 6. १६.--a तीर्थम् near यन्त्रेश्वर on the Nar- मदा. M. १९०. 3. [page१-522+ ३१]--a वर्ण s4akti. Br. IV. ४४. ६०.--a son of वसिष्ठ and ऊर्जा. Br. II. ११. ४१.(II)--a son of विश्वेशा. M. १७१. ५०.(I)--a son of तार्क्ष्य (काश्यप) and विनता (सुपर्णा), and vehicle of Hari. {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 6. २२: III. १९. ११. Br. III. 7. २९: 8. ११. M. 6. ३४: १४६. २२. वा. ४९. १०; ६९. ६६: ७०. ११: ७२. ४५. Vi. I. २१. १८.{{/F}} Has abode in शाल्मलिद्वीप. {{F}}2:  भा. V. २०. 8.{{/F}} Took कृष्ण to Madhuvana; {{F}}3:  Ib. IV. 9. 1.{{/F}} Identified with Hari, and regarded as the embodiment of the Vedas. {{F}}4:  Ib. VI 8. २९. VIII. 3. ३१.{{/F}} Attacked Asura followers of Bali, and knowing Hari's mind, he bound Bali with cords of वरुण. {{F}}5:  Ib. VIII. २१. १६ and २६.{{/F}} Serves as a watch for क्षीरोद. When he saw Bali carrying away Hari's crown-jewel, he pursued him and recovered it after a fight. When he saw on his return from Gomanta, he placed it on His [page१-519+ ४६] head and belauded him, requesting him for opportunities of service to Him, who ordered him to go back and come whenever He thought of him. {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ५३ (V) १०-19.{{/F}} His winning nectar is com- pared to कृष्ण winning वैदर्भी in स्वयम्वर। {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ५२. १७.{{/F}} कालीय, the enemy of snakes, freed from fear of; entered into an agreement with snakes of रमणक to give him बलि every fortnight. कालीय failed to do this, and after a fight escaped to the river कालिन्दी where गरुड could not go, as he was under a curse. It happened once that गरुड took a king- fish from the river against the wish of the sage Saubhari who cursed that गरुड's coming again there would mean the end of his life. {{F}}8:  Ib. १६. ६३; १७. 1-११. Vi. V. 7. ७८.{{/F}} Attacked by Mura, {{F}}9:  भा. X. ५९. 7-8.{{/F}} killed all elephants of Naraka, {{F}}१०:  Ib. ५९. १९. Vi. V. २९. १४.{{/F}} carried कृष्ण to Indra's city. Defeated वरुण attacking कृष्ण, flung शिव and his bull to a distance of a hundred धनुस्। Discomfited ऐरावत of Indra, and took कृष्ण and सत्यभामा safely to द्वारका. {{F}}११:  भा. ६५ (V) 1: ६६ (V) २२-25, ४८; ६७ (V) ११-14, ३८-39, M. १५०. २१९ Vi. V. ३०. ६४-70. XI. ३०. ४४.{{/F}} गरुड standard of Hari. {{F}}१२:  Br. III. ७१. २४८.{{/F}} Praise of Hari. {{F}}१३:  भा. IV. ३०. 6. XI. २७. २८.{{/F}} Took nectar for mother's sake to Somaka hill of प्लक्ष; married five daughters of ताम्र and became father of birds in all the world. {{F}}१४:  Br. II. १९. ११-12: III. 7. ४४८-51: M. १२२. १५.{{/F}} Younger brother of अरुण. {{F}}१५:  M. १५०-53.{{/F}} Worship of, on the भी- मद्वादशि, and in the लक्ष homa of Grahabali. Icon of. {{F}}१६:  M. ५३. ४१; ६९. २६; ९३. ९९: २५८. ११ and १२.{{/F}} In the तारकामय: in the war with कालनेमी: performed tapas at Kanakhala. {{F}}१७:  M. १५२. 6-7, ३६: १५३. १८१: १७१. ५०: १७८. ३२ and ५०: १९३. ७०: २४९. ३५{{/F}} had a number of wives, sons and grandsons; the eater of all cruel snakes--his descendants spread over largely the whole of शाल्मलिद्वीप, and the mountains देवकूट, मणिमन्त, सहस्रशिखर, Parna- mala, सुकेश, and सतश्रुग, the five-peaked Kauraja, हेमकूट etc. {{F}}१८:  वा. ६९. ३२८-335.{{/F}} [page१-520+ ३०]--a महापुराण comprising १९००० s4lokas. भा. XII. 7. २३: १३. 8: Vi. IV. 6. २३.--विष्णु (कृष्ण). M. १५०. २११: १५२. २१: १६३. १०६-7. वा. २४. ९०: ९६. २३९.--see गरुड. भा. III. २१. ११. Br. II. १९. ११. वा. ६९. ३२८, ३३५: Vi. V. ३०. ६४: ३४, १३ and २३.--a goddess following भवमालिनी. M. १७९. ७१.--a सुधर्मान god. Br. IV. 1. ६०.--one of the six sons of पुरूरवस्. वा. ९१. ५२.--same as जलधारवर्षम्. M. १२२. २०-1.--a daughter of Kardama, married to Pulaha. Had three sons--कर्मश्रेष्ट, वरीयस् and सहिस्णु. भा. III. २४. २३: IV. 1. ३८.--not to marry with विश्वामित्रस्, etc. M. १९८. १९.(I)--the mind-born daughter of पितृस् and wife of शुक्र. Br. III. 1. ७७; M. १५. १५; वा. ७३. ३६. [page१-556+ २५](II)--technical name of the Earth first milked by पृथु, and then by others to get the essence each wanted. M. १०. 2-२८.(III)--another name for कृत्वी, a daughter of शुक. M. १५. १०.--noted for श्रावस्ति. M. १२. ३०.--an एकार्षेय sage. M. २००. 5.--an एकार्षेय. M. २००. 3. [page१-559+ २७](I)--a वैकुण्ठ god. Br. II. ३६. ५१.(II)--a son of शुक and पीवरी. Br. III. 8. ९३; १०. ८१; M. १५. १०; वा. ७०. ८५; ७३. ३०.(III)--a Mt. of gold to the north of the कैलास; with हरिताल trees; celebrated for golden crests; at its foot was lake Bindusaras where भगीरथ was engaged in austerities. Here Indra performed a number of sacrifices. Br. II. १८. २४-8; M. १२१. २४; वा. ४७. २३-5.--आत्रेय gotrakaras. M. १९७. 2.--आत्रेय gotrakaras. M. १९७. 2.--a पारशर branch. वा. ७०. ८७.--a sage not to have marriage alliances with Angiras and सम्कृति. M. १९६. ३२.(IV)--good to marry; for a son of such marriage would purify twenty-one generations of his and six on his mother's side. वा. ८३. १२, ४४.(I)--is पार्वती; {{F}}1:  भा. X. ५३. २५; Br. II. २५. १८; वा. ४३. ३८; १०६. ५८; Vi. V. ३२. १२.{{/F}} a शक्ति; {{F}}2:  Br. IV. ४४. ५८.{{/F}} the goddess ensh