 of a parrot and drank of His वीर्य; {{F}}4:  Ib. १५८. ३२.{{/F}} burnt with काम and reattained godhood. {{F}}5:  Ib. १९१. ११२.{{/F}}(I)--as विष्णु and स्वाहा as श्री. Vi. I. 8. २२; 9. ३४.--a son of Dhara (Dharma-वि। प्।) Br. III. 3. २२; वा. ६६. २१; Vi. I. १५. ११३.(I)--a Sukha god. Br. IV. 1. १९. [page३-776+ ३२](II)--a mukhya गण. वा. १००. १८.--a hill tribe. Br. II. १६. ६७; वा. ४७. ५६.--a Gandharva in Brahmaloka who entertains ब्रह्मा with music; {{F}}1:  Vi. IV. 1. ६८.{{/F}} cursed by sage Devala to become a cro- codile; caught hold of Gajendra and was released from his curse; {{F}}2:  भा. X. ५२. १५[4]; VIII. 4. 3-5.{{/F}} with the sun in the months of शुचि and शुक्र. {{F}}3:  Ib. XII. ११. ३६; Br. II. २३. 7; III. 7. 8; वा. ६९. ४६.{{/F}}--a Mother goddess. M. १७९. ३१.--an eastern country. Br. II. १६. ५२.--a tribe defeated by Bharata; purified of their sin by the worship of Hari; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २०. ३०; II. 4. १८.{{/F}} specially created in the war of ललिता with भण्ड; {{F}}2:  Br. IV. २९. १३१.{{/F}} nineteen in number; {{F}}3:  M. २७३. १९.{{/F}} the country of the. {{F}}4:  वा. ४५. १३६; Vi. II. 3. १७.{{/F}}--a Marut गण. M. १७१. ५४.--one of the उत्तम सिद्धिस्। Br. IV. ३६. ५१.(I)--see इला। Br. III. ६०. ११; वा. ८५. 7.(II)--a शक्ति of मारुत. Br. IV. ३३. ७०. [page१-185+ ३८]--the third year of a five year yuga. Also इद्वत्सर; {{F}}1:  भा. III. ११. १४; V. २२. 7; Vi. II. 8. ७२; १३. ११५; वा. ५०. १८३.{{/F}} is Soma or moon. {{F}}2:  Br. II. १३. ११८; १२९; २१. १३२; २८. २२. M. १४१. १८. वा. ३१. ३०; ५६. २०.{{/F}}(I)--a son of दक्षिणा and a तुषित god. भा. IV. 1. 7-8.(II)--a name of Hari; पुरुष. भा. IX. 2. ३५.--son of शतरथ; married the daughter of विश्वसहस्र. Br. III. ६३. १८०.--the daughter of तृणबिन्दु: a queen of विश्र- vas, and mother of Kubera. भा. IV. 1. ३७; १२. 9.--a son of Priyavrata and बर्हिष्मती. Appointed lord of प्लक्षद्वीप, which he divided into seven parts among his seven sons, and retired to practise auste- rities. भा. V. 1. २५ and ३३; २०. 2.(I)--the son of दृढच्युत and