to, by Arjuna, fearing erosion of the sea. See also हस्तिनापुरम्; {{F}}1:  भा. X. ५८. 1; XI. ३०. ४८; ३१. २५.{{/F}} after Indra who performed penance here in honour of परा- शक्ति to vanquish भण्ड. {{F}}2:  Br. IV. १२. ४४.{{/F}} Arjuna had Vajra crowned here. {{F}}3:  Vi. V. ३८. ३४.{{/F}}--a वासिष्थ and a ब्रह्मवादिन्; {{F}}1:  M. १४५. ११०.{{/F}} a name of कुशि, son of वसिष्ठ. {{F}}2:  वा. ७०. ८८.{{/F}}--Manu the fourteenth. Uru and others were his sons. During his period शुचि was Indra, while अग्निबाहु and others were sages. बृहद्भानु was a mani- festation of Hari. भा. VIII. १३. ३३-35.--the assembly of Indra. वा. 2. २९.(I)--a boundary hill in प्लक्षद्वीप. भा. V. २०. 4.(II)--a son of देवऋषभ. भा. VI. 6. 5.(III)--a son of कूर्च (पूर्व-Burnouf) and father of वीतिहोत्र. भा. IX. 2. १९-20. [page१-198+ ३३](IV)--previously Bali. Received कृष्ण and राम with due honours to his region Sutala, and praised their glory; gave them back their brothers killed by कंस. भा. X. ८५. ३५-46, ५२.(V)--a son of ब्रह्मिष्ठ and father of विन्ध्याश्व. M. ५०. 6.--the wife of Mudgola and mother of बध्यश्व. वा. ९९. २००.--(Mt.) a hill north of महाभद्र lake. वा. ३६. ३१.--one of भण्ड's councillors. Br. IV. १२. १२.--a son of ऋषभ and जयन्ती. भा. V. 4. १०.--to be uttered in founding a temple. M. २६५. २५.--a दानव, in the सभा of हिरण्यकशिपु. Br. III. 6. 8; M. १६१. ८१.--Indrahood, attained by Heti. वा. १०९. 9.--see Puramjaya. भा. IX. 6. १२.--of a king; to create prosperity in the country, as Indra gives rains; {{F}}1:  M. २२६. १०.{{/F}} leads to the world of Indra. {{F}}2:  Ib. १०१. ६९.{{/F}}--performed every year by Nanda and other gopas to please Indra, the Lord of rains and hence conducive to त्रिवर्ग। कृष्ण explained that rain was the work of nature, and that no credit went to Indra. So he persuaded them to worship cows, ब्राह्मणस् and hills. So it hap- pened. Indra who was thus deprived of his बलि grew wrath- ful and sent down a continuous heavy downpour of rain creating panic in the minds of gopas. कृष्