r. II. 1. १०-11; ३५. १२४.{{/F}} a वेदव्यास; {{F}}2:  भा. III. ७३. ९३; वा. २३. २१४.{{/F}} a contemporary of वेद्व्यास; {{F}}3:  Br. IV. 4. ६६.{{/F}} exclusion of mutual alliances among जातुकर्णि, वसिष्ठ and Atri. {{F}}4:  M. ४७. २४६; २००. १९.{{/F}}(I)--the name of व्यास of the २७थ् द्वा- पर; सोमशर्म, the अवतार् of the Lord. (See जातुकर्णि). वा. २३. २१४.(III)--(जातूकर्ण-ब्र्। प्।); see कानीन; a disciple of शाकल्य. Imparted the सम्हिता with nirukta to बलाक, Paija and others. भा. IX. 2. २१; XII. 6. ५८. [page१-647+ ३०]--see Bharata.--a Devi. Br. IV. १२. ५९; ३०. 4 and ४४.--see ललिता. Br. IV. १३. १७, ६३.--an attribute of विष्णु. Vi. V. ३३. ४१.--the universe as issuing from the mind and body of ब्रह्मा; {{F}}1:  भा. III. १२. २७.{{/F}} अग्निषोमात्मकम् {{F}}2:  Br. III. ७२. ५०; वा. ९७. ५१.{{/F}} born of विष्णु and abides in विष्णु. {{F}}3:  Vi. I. 1. 4, ३१.{{/F}} Spatial description of; its relation to ईश्वर and other creations. {{F}}4:  वा. ४९. १५६-86.{{/F}}--Evolution of Tattvas, etc. When the शक्तिस् did not attend to their function of creation, the Lord with शक्तिकाला entered into twenty-three तत्त्वस् by dividing him- self into three parts--अध्यात्म, आधिदैव, and आधिभौम with tenfold प्राण, Agni as his mouth, वरुण as tongue, अश्विन्स् as nostrils, etc. Then came the four वर्णस्। At first five varieties of अज्ञान were created, viz., अन्धतामिस्र, तामिस्र, महामोह, moha, and tamas. Ashamed of these sinful creations, ब्रह्मा created seers like Sanaka, Sananda, etc. They also did not proceed with the work of creation as was desired. So ब्रह्मा grew angry and down came Rudra from the midst of his eye-brows. He was assigned places and women. Finding his creation intolerable, ब्रह्मा sent him away for penance, and produced ten mind-born sons, मरिची, Atri and others, and a daughter सरस्वती. Then came the Vedas and other literature. Further the Creator's body got into two halves--one स्वायम्भुव and the other शतरूप. These were parents of two sons and three daughters. Their descendants filled up the whole of the earth. Another account of creation. भा. III. 5. २७-36; 6. (whole); १२. (whole); २०. १२ ff.--a metre; {{F}}1:  भा. III. १२. ४५; XI. २१. ४१; M. १२५. ४७; वा. 9. ५०; ३१. ४७.{{/F}} a horse of sun's chariot; {{F}}2:  Br. II. २२. ७२; Vi. II. 8. 5.{{/F}} with गायत्रि Tr2s2t2ub; {{F}}3:  वा. ५१. ६४.{{/F}} from the face of ब्रह्मा. {{F}}4:  Br. II. 8. ५२; १३. १४५.{{/F}} [page१-621+ २७]--a son of Kuru. M. ५०. २३.--a son of पुष्पवत्. भा. IX. २२. 7.(I)--Taught योग to विष्वक्सेन; wife अपर्णा, a daughter of मेना; got his सिद्धि at Benares. भा. IX. २१. २६; M. १३. 9; १८०. ५७.(II)--the son of शत्शलाक (शतशिलक) mar- ried एकपाटल, a daughter of हिमवान्; mind-born sons शन्ख and Likhita. Br. III. १०. २०-21; वा. ७२. १८-19.(III)--the अवतार् of the Lord in the 7th द्वा- para with four sons. वा. २३. १३८.(IV)--a ऋत्विक् at the sacrifice of ब्रह्मा. वा. १०६. ३६.--श्वेत Para1s4aras. M. २०१. ३३.--a Pravara of Angiras. M. १९६. १७.(I)--a pupil of व्यास in charge of साम Veda (छन्दोगसम्हिता). Was invited for युधिष्ठिर's राज- सूय. His disciple was हिरण्यनाभ; {{F}}1:  भा. I. 4. २१; IX. १२. 3; X. ७४. 8; XII. 6. ५३ and ७५. वा. ६०. १३, १८; ६१. २६; Vi. III. 4. 9.{{/F}} a श्रुतऋषि who taught his son Sumantu; {{F}}2:  Br. II. 1. १३; ३४. 4 and १३; ३५. ४८; III. ३३. 7; ३५. 3; Vi. III. 6. 1-2.{{/F}} an authority on Yoga. {{F}}3:  वा. ८८. २०७; Vi. IV. 4. १०७.{{/F}}(II)--a लान्गल. वा. ६१. ४२. [page१-654+ ३०](I)--a servant of कृष्ण. भा. X. ७१. १२.(II)--the chariot of कृष्ण, that entered the sea before he left for Heaven. Vi. V. ३७. ५१.--a Pravara of Angiras. M. १९६. १७.--an अर्षेय pravara of भार्गवस्. M. १९५. ३७.--a Mt. of शाकद्वीप; perhaps जलधार (s.v.). Vi. II. 4. ६२.--see Jalam; to be worshipped in house- building. M. २५३. २६.--was मानवी. Br. II. ३३. १७.--a son of स्वाहा. Vi. I. १०. १५.(I)--a son of Havya, after whom came Jalada- वर्ष. Br. II. १४. १७-18; वा. ३३. १६.(II)--an आत्रेय gotrakara. M. १९७. 4.(III)--a son of Bhavya of शाकद्वीप. Vi. II. 4. ६०. [page१-642+ २८]--after the name of जलदा; {{F}}1:  Br. II. १४. १७-18. वा. ३३. १७.{{/F}} centring round the Udaya hill in शाकद्वीपम्. {{F}}2:  Br. II. १९. ९१; वा. ४९. ८५.{{/F}}(I)--a Mt. of शाकद्वीप from वासव; draws water always from rain. Br. II. १९. ८५-86; M. १२२. 9; वा. ४९. ७९.(II)--a continent of Udaya hill. M. १२२. २०.--see वरुण, who gave garland to देवी on the eve of her war campaign. Br. IV. २९. ८४.--as a deity with its अधीदेवत Bhava; worship- ped in founding a new temple. M. २६५. ३९ and ४१.--a son of कृष्ण and सत्यभामा. See जरन्धम। M. ४७. १७.--a Pravara sage. M. १९९. १५.--a मागध measure of १३ palas; four of these water measures equal to one नालिकोच्चय or घट; peculiar to the मागध country. Br. IV. 1. २१७; वा. १००. २२०; Vi. VI. 3. 8.--a goddess enshrined at शिवलिन्ग. M. १३. ३३.--a sage. M. १९६. २६.--an epithet of Hari. M. २८५. 5. [page१-643+ २६]--is वरुण. Vi. II. 8-9.--a son of रौद्राश्व. Vi. IV. १९. 2.--a तीर्थम् in the अमरकण्टक hill of Kalinga, fit for पिण्डतर्पणम्। When शिव was burning Tripura ruthlessly, बाण appeared with a लिन्ग on his head when the Lord blessed him with life. Hence the sanctity of the place. M. १८६. १५-38; १८७. 3-५२; Ch. १८८ (whole).--one of the ten sons of रौद्राश्व. भा. IX. २०. 4; वा. ९९. १२४.--a sage of the तामस epoch. M. 9. १६. [page१-644+ २७](I)--a sage of the Vaivasvata epoch; (भार्गव); a son of ऋचीक and सत्यवती; to attain a son for himself and for गाधि, he made a चरु to be taken both by his wife and mother-in-law, the latter to get a क्षत्रिय and the former a ब्राह्मण; then he entered the forest for penance; by mistake the चरु intended for the mother was taken by the daughter and vice-versa; ऋचीक understood the mistake and told his wife that a cruel son would be born to her; she implored him to give her a good son; Jamadagni, born to her; produced by eating (जम) the वैष्णवाग्नि. {{F}}1:  भा. VIII. १३. 5; Br. II. ३२. १०५; ३८. २७; M. 9. २८; १२६. २१; वा. ३२. ४६; ६५. ९३; ९१. ६७ and ८५-86. Vi. IV. 7. ३२-6.{{/F}} Entertained Arjuna (Haihaya) with the help of his काम- dhenu. The king desired to own her; but on being refused, he took her away by force. She was recovered by his son परशुराम who killed Arjuna. Regretted his son's action in killing the king and found fault with रेणुका his wife who saw Citraratha. He asked his other sons to kill their mother but they declined. परशुराम killed them and his mother to please his father but he requested that they might come back to life to which the sage agreed. But the sons of Arjuna took vengeance and slew the sage in the presence of रेणुका. Through the prowess of his son, Jamadagni got back his body and became the seventh in the ऋषिमण्- डल {{F}}2:  भा. IX. chh. १५ and १६.{{/F}} Married रेणुका, daughter of रेणु the youngest son was राम. According to the वायु पुराण रेणुक is also known as कामलि and is said to be the daughter of the इक्ष्वाकु, सुवेणु. Vasumat and others were elders to राम. {{F}}3:  Ib. IX. १५. ११-13; वा. ९१. ८६.{{/F}} Officiated in ब्रह्मा's place in the sacrifice of हरिश्चन्द्र; {{F}}4:  भा. IX. 7. २३.{{/F}} a मन्त्रकृत्; {{F}}5:  Br. III. २१ 1; M. १४५. ९९.{{/F}} a भार्गव gotrakara. {{F}}6:  M. १९५. १५ and २९.{{/F}}(II)--a मन्त्रकृत् and a sage; with the sun in माघ and फाल्गुन. {{F}}2:  Ib. ५२. २०; Vi. II. १०. १६; III. 1. ३२.{{/F}} ^1 वा. ५९. ९६. [page१-629+ ३१](III)--a son of ऊरु and of भृगु gotra; {{F}}1:  वा. ६४. २५.{{/F}} Jamadagni भार्गव, one of the seven sages. {{F}}2:  Ib. १००. १०.{{/F}}--a सुधर्मान God. Br. IV. 1. ६०.(II)--a son of भाष्कल. Br. III. 5. ३८.(III)--a son of Virocana, and father of four sons. वा. ६७. ७६.(IV)--a नाग. वा. ६९. ६९.(I)--father of कयाधू, and chief of Asuras. Took part in the 6th देवासुर war between Bali and Indra. Fought with वृषा-Kapi. Hearing that Bali had fallen dead Jambha riding on a lion attacked Indra and dis- abled his elephant. He then turned towards मातलि who brought a chariot to Indra's aid. But his head was cut off by Indra's वज्र। {{F}}1:  भा. VI. १८. १२; VIII. १०. २१-32; ११. १३-18; Br. III. 6. १०; ७२. ८१ and १०५; वा. ९७. १०३.{{/F}} Led तारक's army in a chariot of १०० lions; fought with Yama, Kubera, जनार्दन and others but was finally killed. {{F}}2:  M. ४७. ७२; १४८. ४२-54; chh १५०-53; २४५. १२. Vi. IV. 6. १४; V. १४. १४.{{/F}} [page१-631+ २७]--also जृम्भण; a commander to aid विषङ्ग was killed by विजया. Br. IV. २५. २९.--the tree at इलावृतम् in the हिमालयस्. Br. II. १७. १२; १९. २९; III. २२. ३७; २७. १७; IV. ४३. १७.--a son of आप. वा. ६९. ३०.--a commander of भण्ड to aid विषङ्ग; was killed by नीलपताका. Br. IV. २१. ८०; २५. २९, ९८.--a R. of the भारतवर्ष. वा. ४५. १००.--(जाम्बूनदम्) a river of juice of celestial roseapple tree flowing from the top of Merumandara into इलावृत. The earth on its two banks yields fine gold जाम्बू- nada from which jewels are made in heaven; source of जम्बु; {{F}}1:  भा. V. १६. १९-20; वा. ३५. २६-30.{{/F}} R. from Candraprabha {{F}}2:  Br. II. १८. ६९.{{/F}} in colour like a butterfly. {{F}}3:  वा. ४६. ३०.{{/F}}--occupies the central position of the globe in the form of a lotus leaf, in extent a १००,000 yojanas. There are nine continents demarcated by moun- tain ranges. In the middle is situated इलावृत, at whose middle portion stands Meru. Some say that eight extra [page१-630+ ३८] countries were attached to it by the sons of Sagara who dug into the earth on all sides in search of sacrificial horse. This द्वीप is surrounded by salt sea. {{F}}1:  भा. I. १२. 5; V. 1. ३२; १६. 5-7; १९. २९-30; २०. 2; M. ८३. ३२; ११३. 7; १२२. 2; २८४. 2; वा. ११. ८४; ३३. ११ and ४५; ch. ३४. Vi. II. 3. २८.{{/F}} Contains many जनपदस्, cities, mountains, rivers, nine भुवनस्, salt ocean, six वर्षपर्वतस् and two oceans--east and west. Divided into nine parts among the sons of आग्नीध्र; {{F}}2:  Br. II. १७. २४, ३०; १५. 8 to the end; १४. ११, ४३ and ५२; Vi. II. 1. १२; 2. २३-25.{{/F}} from the जम्बु tree. {{F}}3:  वा. ४६. २५.{{/F}}--people of, described. See जम्बू. वा. ४६. २५-37.--a तीर्थ with forest near चित्रकूट; {{F}}1:  Br. III. १३. ३८.{{/F}} sacred to पितृस्, {{F}}2:  M. २२. २१.{{/F}} fit for श्राद्ध; {{F}}3:  वा. ७७. ३८.{{/F}} here was born Bharata. {{F}}4:  Vi. II. १३. ३३.{{/F}}--R. of honey, containing gold. वा. ३५. २९; ४७. ६६.--R. in इलवृतम्. (perhaps जम्बू, s.v.). Br. II. १७. २२.--a शक्ति. Br. IV. ४४. ८७.--the fifth लोक from where are born people; from root जनन; {{F}}1:  Br. II. १९. १५६; २१. २२; ३५. १५३ and २०६; III. 1. १५-16; M. ६१. 1; १८४. २३; वा. १००. १२७; १०१. १७.{{/F}} two crores of yojanas from Maharloka. {{F}}2:  वा. १०१. १४०, २०८.{{/F}}--a divine world, {{F}}1:  भा. VIII. २०. ३४.{{/F}} the world of वरुणा {{F}}1: a)वा. 7. २८; २३. ८४; २४. 3; ४९. १४९; ६१. १२९; ६५. १७.{{/F}} as the face of विराट्, {{F}}2:  भा. II. 1. २८.{{/F}} and a part of पुरुष्. {{F}}3:  Ib. 5. ३९.{{/F}} Its inhabitants. {{F}}4:  Ib. III. ११. २९.{{/F}} Here was in ancient times a discussion about ब्रह्मवाद, on the occasion of a sacrifice performed by ब्रह्मा; {{F}}5:  X. ८७. 8-9.{{/F}} at a distance of 2 crores of yojanas from Maharlokam; {{F}}6:  Br. IV. I. १२३; 2. १३-15, १३९. Vi. II. 7. १३-14.{{/F}} during Pralaya the Devas go from Maharloka to this. {{F}}7:  Br. I. 6. २८. Vi. VI. 3. २९.{{/F}} (See also Jana).--a son of शरूथ; had four sons, पाण्ड्य, केरऌअ, Cola, and Kulya. वा. ९९. 5-6.--a name of वासुदेव; {{F}}1:  वा. ९६. ५१; १०६. ५४.{{/F}} विष्णु who took the form of हयग्रीव and appeared before Agastya at काञ्ची; {{F}}2:  Br. II. १९. १८०; २५. ५६-7; III. ७१. ७८ and ९३; ७३. ८७; IV. 5. 8, १४; 9. २८, ४७, ६४; १२. २१; १५. १४.{{/F}} as brother of देवी put down the हिरण्यस् in the भण्ड-Lalita1 war; {{F}}3:  Br. II. २९. १०३, १३३.{{/F}} as Kalki put down the हूणस्, Yava- nas, etc; {{F}}4:  Br. II. ३९. ४९.{{/F}} in the form of पितृस् in गया; {{F}}5:  वा. १०८. ८५, ८९; १०९. २४ and ३४.{{/F}} became black due to poison; {{F}}6:  वा. ५४. ५९.{{/F}} becomes ब्रह्मा, विष्णु and शिव affected by the qualities of सत्व, रजस् and तमस्; {{F}}7:  Vi. I. 2. ६१-7.{{/F}} manifestation and forms described. {{F}}8:  Vi. I. २२. २३-72; III. 8. ११; १८. ३५.{{/F}}(I)--(king of मिथीला) one of the twelve sages who knew the nature of the धर्म ordained by Hari. Son of Nimi, born by churning his dead body and hence known Mithila. He was Vaideha, born of a विदेह। He founded the city of मिथिला. His son was उदावसु. Father of सीता. {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 3. २०; IX. १३. १३-14; X. ७१. 9; वा. ८९. 2; Vi. IV. 5. २२-4; १३. १०३.{{/F}} In his sacrifice याज्ञवल्क्य won a prize for learning while शाकल्य was humbled for pretended superiority. Father-in- law of राम. {{F}}2:  Br. II. ३४. ३३-68; III. ३७. २२; ६४. 2;{{/F}} In the अश्वमेध Yajn5a of his, साकल्य was [page१-623+ ३५] ruined on account of his conceit by taking part in a disputa- tion; Janaka wanted to know the best among the learned assembled and set apart ११,000 crores, much gold, villages and servants to be given as present to him; in the disputa- tion each took part but याज्ञवल्क्य ultimately threw out the challenge. साकल्य questioned this and put to him a number of questions which were all answered. याज्ञवल्क्य in his turn put him a single question, a wrong reply to it inviting instantaneous death; साकल्य agreed, and unable to answer his question, was gathered to his ancestors; {{F}}3:  वा. ६०. ३२-62; ८९. 5; Vi. III. १८. ८५-90.{{/F}} told by the sage Asita what the Earth narrated to him about the ignorance of kings who without subduing themselves, try to subdue others. {{F}}4:  Vi. IV. २४. १२७-136.{{/F}}(II)--king of Videhas, and an ally of बलराम. Welcomed बलराम to his capital. भा. X. ५७. २४-26.(III)--a son of विशाखयूप and father of Nan- divardhana. Vi. IV. २४. 5-6.(I)--the first of the four sons of परीक्षित् and इरावती. {{F}}1:  भा. I. १६. 2; Br. III. ६८. २०.{{/F}} Father of शतानीक. {{F}}2:  Vi. IV. २०. 1; २१. 2-3.{{/F}} Finding that the death of his father was predicted to be by the snake तक्षक, he per- formed a सर्प याग to destroy all snakes. All except Tak- [page१-624+ ३२] षक came, the latter being sheltered by Indra. At this Tak- षक and Indra were invoked together. Advised by बृहस्- pati to refrain from the cruel याग, Janamejaya agreed; with the aid of Tura, the priest, he performed अश्वमेध and other sacrifices; {{F}}3:  भा. IX. २२. ३५-38; XII. 6. १६-28; M. 6. ४२.{{/F}} cursed by वैशम्पायन he made याज्ञ- valkya his ब्रह्मा in a sacrifice. {{F}}4:  M. ५०. ५७-60.{{/F}} Introduced वाजसने- yaka and became known as Trikharvi. {{F}}5:  वा. ९९. २२९, २५०-4.{{/F}} Put to trouble Loha- gandha, the son of गार्ग्य out for mischief and was cursed by गार्ग्य. {{F}}6:  Ib. ९३. २१.{{/F}} King of सुदेश and a Kaurava; highly righte- ous. After anointing his son on the throne he went into the woods for penance. {{F}}7:  M. ५०. ६१-5.{{/F}}(II)--the son of Sumati; with him ended the वैशाल line. भा. IX. 2. ३६.(III)--a son of पूरु and father of Pra- चीन्वत्. भा. IX. २०. 2; M. ४९. 1; वा. ९९. १२०. Vi. IV. १९. 1.(IV)--the son of सृञ्जय, and father of महामनस् (महाशिल-ब्। प्।). भा. IX. २३. 2.(V)--the son of Somadatta, and father of Sumati (Prumati-ब्र्। प्।). Br. III. ६१. १६; Vi. IV. 1. ५७-8.(VI)--a son of Puramjaya and a राजऋषि; {{F}}1:  M. ४८. १२-3; वा. ९९. १५.{{/F}} father of महाशाल. {{F}}2:  Vi. IV. १८. 5-6.{{/F}} [page१-625+ ३८](VII)--a son of बृहद्रथ, entitled विश्- vajit. M. ४८. १०२.(VIII)--a son of भल्लाट; served उग्रा- yudha in his तपस्; saved नीपस् when they were led by Yama at the behest of उग्रायुध by fighting Yama, and earned his appreciation and मुक्तिज्ञान from him as a result. Wife धूमिनी and son यवीनर. M. ४९. ५९-70; वा. ९९. १८२.--१०० in number; according to the म्। प्। and वा। प्। ८० in number. Br. III. ६८. २०-26; ७४. २६७; M. २७३. ७१-3; वा. ९९. ४५४.(I)--get deserted and desolate in Kali; {{F}}1:  वा. ८८. १८७.{{/F}} are left in a state of अराजक। {{F}}2:  Br. II. ३१. ५०, ९७; III. ५०. 5; IV. 5. 4.{{/F}}(II)--the seven of क्रौञ्चद्वीप viz., उष्ण, पीवर, अन्धकार, Muni, Dundubhi, कुशल and Manuja. वा. ३३. २३.(I)--the son of शान्तिदेवा and Vasudeva. Br. III. ७१. १८०.(II)--a son of Tumba. वा. ९६. २४९.--here राम vanquished a host of राक्- षसस्; {{F}}1:  Br. III. ६३. १९५.{{/F}} and performed the work of gods. {{F}}2:  वा. ८८. १९४.{{/F}} [page१-626+ ३७]a Janapada of the केतुमाल country. वा. ४४. १४.(I)--a great king, son of Hotraka, (Suhotra- वा। प्।) and केशिनी (कौशिका-वा। प्।); while he was performing a sacrifice the गन्गा flowed through his यज्ञवाट; enraged at it he drank the waters; so गन्गा became his daughter and came to be known as जाह्नवी; married कावेरी, the grand-daughter of युवनाश्व; and had a son Sunaha (Suhotra-वा। प्।) by her; father Puru, Sumantu-वि। प्।). भा. IX. १५. 3; Br. III. ६६. २५-30; वा. 1. १४२; ९१. ५४-60; Vi. IV. 7. 3-7.(II)--eldest son of Somaka. भा. IX. २२. 1; Vi. IV. १९. ७२.(III)--a son (descendant?) of Kuru, and father of Suratha. भा. IX. २२. 4 and 9; वा. ९९. २१७, २३०; Vi. IV. १९. ७८; २०. 2.--originated from the son of अष्टक, son of विश्वामित्र. वा. ९१. १०३.--a Deva. Br. II. १३. ९५.--a दनायुष. वा. ६८. ३०.--birthday as, fit for गयापिण्ड. वा. १०५. १८.--a तीर्थम् sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ४२.(I)--a son of Purudvat and भद्रसेना, the Vai- darbhi. Wife of ऐक्ष्वाकी, and son सात्वत. M. ४४. ४५-6.(II)--a son of Somaka; was killed (before he got an heir? अजमीढ and धूमिनि had to start the line again). M. ५०. १६-19; वा. ९९. २०९.--a daughter of यातुधान, {{F}}1:  Br. III. 7. ८५.{{/F}} married by Aja? (यक्ष्-वा। प्।), one of the sons of खशा; originator of यातुधान clan; hairy in every part. {{F}}2:  वा. ६९. १२४.{{/F}} [page१-627+ २९]--one of the two पिशाचस्, who met यक्ष, the son of खशा. वा. ६९. ११३.--a group of gods of Uttama epoch. Vi. III. 1. 4.--कृष्ण Para1s4aras. M. २०१. ३५.--for Brahmans only; {{F}}1:  वा. ५७. ५०.{{/F}} for the wise. {{F}}2:  Ib. १६. २२.{{/F}} [page१-628+ ४३](I)--a Deva. Br. II. १३. ९५.(II)--a son of Vasudeva. Br. III. ७१. १८७. M. ४६. २२.(III)--a son of मृत्यु. वा. १०. ४१.(IV)--a Gandharva in कैलास. वा. ४१. २१.(V)--a hunter who aimed a shaft at कृष्ण in ignorance. He was awarded heaven. भा. XI. ३०. ३३-38; Vi. V. ३७. ६८-73.(I)--a राक्षसि who picked up the two parts of बृहद्रथ's son and gave them life--the future जरा- sandha (s.v.). भा. IX. २२. 8; X. ५०. २१; ७१. 3; ७२. ४२.--a son of सत्यभामा. वा. ९६. २३९.(III)--of the family of Sahadeva, the बृहद्रथस् known as मागधेयस्. वा. ९९. २९४.(I)--born to बृहद्रथ in two parts and cast away by the mother. जरा (s.v.) joined them together, saying in sport ‘Live, Live’. It was जरासन्ध. He was father of Sahadeva. {{F}}1:  भा. I. १५. 9; IX. २२. 7-8; M. ५०. ३१-32; २७१. १८; Vi. IV. १९. ८३-4; २३. 2-3.{{/F}} King of Magadha and father-in-law of कम्शा who married his daughters Asti and प्राप्ति; acted as कम्शा's guru in his wicked plans. Heard of कम्शा's death from his widowed daughters and resolved to destroy all the यादवस्. He besieged मथुरा with twenty-three अक्षौ- हिनिस्, stationing at the four gates king of Kalinga and others. Drums were sounded as a call to arms. Told कृष्ण that he was a boy unfit to fight him and asked राम to meet him in battle. राम challenged him on the western gate. Finding all his army followers killed, जरासन्ध attacked राम. When the latter was about to bind him with ropes, कृष्ण asked that he be set free. जरासन्ध went home greatly distressed. Three months after, जरासन्ध collected [page१-640+ ४६] another huge army of twenty-three अक्षौहिनिस्, encamped at यमुना banks and slept that night. कृष्ण divided his army into three divisions and attacked the enemy on all sides by surprise. All जरासन्ध's followers took to flight leaving all their belongings which were presented to Ugra- sena. Then he called on बाण at his city शोणितपुर soliciting his help against the Yadus. बाण's welcome and offer to help; with this force he again besieged मथुरा. Fight between him and राम. Defeat of कुम्भाण्ड and retreat of कूप- कर्ण and other soldiers of बाण to their city. जरासन्- dha's return to the city. {{F}}2:  भा. X. ३६. ३५; ५० (whole); also ch. ५० Vijaya (whole); chaps. ५१-52 (V) Vi. V. ४८ (whole).{{/F}} Felt angry at शृगाल's end and led another expedition to मथुरा. Defeat and return. In this way he led seven- teen expeditions. During the eighteenth expedition a cer- tain Yavana sent by नारद besieged the city. {{F}}3:  भा. X. [५३ (v) २२-24]; ५०. ४२-44; Vi. V. ch. २२.{{/F}} जरासन्ध attacked the Yadus going to द्वारका after vanquishing the म्लेच्छस् by the formation of मकरव्यूह when कृष्ण destroyed it by throwing a big tree on it. राम also gave them mighty blows. Then he turned upon two brothers who were unarmed and who ran to प्रवर्षण hill. जरासन्ध followed them and burnt the hill by besieging it from all sides. The brothers leaped into the plains and regained द्वारका, but were taken by their enemies to be burnt dead. His defeat at कृष्ण's hands during the स्वयम्वर of Ruk- मिणी is mentioned. Arrival at कुण्डिन; went to शिशुपाल and comforted him that all was due to fate, and returned to his city. {{F}}4:  भा. X. ५२ (whole); ५३. १७ and [३४], ५७; ५४. 9-१७; [५६ (v) 6]; Vi. २६. 3 and 7; ३७. २६.{{/F}} His defeats were recalled by कृतवर्मन्. {{F}}5:  भा. X. ५७. १३.{{/F}} He had his capital at Girivraja, where thousands of kings were kept imprisoned. {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ६०. १८; ७०. २३-24, २९.{{/F}} A preliminary to युधिष्ठीर's राजसूय was to kill जरासन्ध. Finding him unconquered and also devoted to ब्रह्मणस्, कृष्ण, भीम and Arjuna went to him in Brahmana's guise and asked for meals. जरासन्ध understood them to be क्षत्रियस् and still recalled Bali giv- ing the earth to Hari in a Brahmana's guise. So he offered to give his head. Then कृष्ण and his two friends revealed themselves and invited him to battle. He refused to fight a [page१-641+ २५] coward who left मथुरा for a sea-girt-city, nor with un- equal Arjuna. But he agreed to fight with भीम. Then battle continued for २७ days and भीम felt despondent. कृष्ण gave him a hint by tearing a twig behind. So भीम pulled him down and tore him to two pieces from head to foot. {{F}}7:  Ib. ७१. 2[1], 3-4; ७२. १५-47; ७३. ३१; ७६. 2; वा. ९३. २७.{{/F}} One of those who failed to hit the fish in the स्वयम्- वर of लक्ष्मणा. {{F}}8:  भा. X. ८३. २३; Br. III. ६८. २८; ७४. १०८.{{/F}}(II)--a son of Nabhasa; a powerful con- queror of all क्षत्रियस्. वा. ९९. २२६-7.--a वीथी in the Madhya मार्ग. M. १२४. ५२ and ५७. [page१-639+ ३२]--a son of सत्यभामा. वा. ९६. २३९.--a son of कृष्ण and सत्यभामा. Br. III. ७१. २४७.--a daughter of सत्यभामा. Br. III. ७१. २४८.--a daughter of सत्यभामा. वा. ९६. २४०.--a son of कृष्ण and सत्यभामा. Br. III. ७१. २४७.--the God of Love with fish standard; also जषकेतु, Makaradhvaja. M. १५४. २०९ and २८३.--the अवतार् of the Lord of the १९थ् dva1para in the जटायु hill of the हिमालयस् with four sons, all engaged in महेश्वर योग। वा. २३. १८६-8.(I)--a son of अरुण and गृध्रि (Syeni-वा। प्।) {{F}}1:  Br. III. 7. ४४७-48.{{/F}} brought forth sons Kaka, गृध्र and अश्वकर्णि; king of vultures and younger brother of सम्पाति; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 7. ४४७-48.{{/F}} father of कर्णि- कार and शतगामि; {{F}}2:  M. 6. ३५-6.{{/F}} Dahanakriya of, done by राम; attained release by सत्सन्ग। {{F}}3:  भा. IX. १०. १२; XI. १२. 6; वा. ६९. ३२६-7.{{/F}}(II)--Mt. a hill in हिमालयस्, the birth-place of जटामालि of the १९थ् dva1para. वा. २३. १८६.--a Mt. on the East of Meru; {{F}}1:  भा. V. १६. २७; वा. ३५. 8; ४२. २०.{{/F}} connects नील and नैषध hills. {{F}}2:  Vi. II. 2. ४१.{{/F}}(I)--a group of heretics. Br. III. १४. ४०. [page१-622+ ३२](II)--a name of विघ्नेश्वर. Br. IV. ४४. ७०.--a त्रयार्षेय. M. १९६. ३९.--a son of Sudhanvan (Jantu.). Vi. IV. १९. ८२.--the house of lac arranged by Duryodhana to burn down the पाण्डवस्. Vi. IV. १३. ७०.--the son of a यक्ष and father of मणिवर. वा. ६२. १८३.--a monkey chief. Br. III. 7. ४२.--a भार्गव gotrakara. M. १९५. २०.--a son of भद्राश्व. M. ५०. 3.--a Deva. Br. II. १३. ९५.(I)--an attendant in वैकुण्ठ cursed by Sanaka and others to be born as an Asura. The curse was confirmed by Hari, who, however, consoled him and Vijaya (s.v.). His fall. {{F}}1:  भा. III. १६. 2, २६-37.{{/F}} In the देवासुर war with Bali, he attacked Bali's fol- lowers. {{F}}2:  Ib. VIII. २१. १६.{{/F}}(II)--a son of Vatsara and स्वर्वीथि. भा. IV. १३. १२.(III)--a sage of the epoch of the tenth Manu. भा. VIII. १३. २२; २१. १६.(IV)--a son of श्रुत (सुश्रुत-ब्र्। प्। and वा। प्।), and father of Vijaya. भा. IX. १३. २५; Br. III. ६४. २२; वा. ८९. २१; Vi. IV. 5. ३१.(V)--a son of पुरूरवस् and ऊर्वशी, and father of Amita. भा. IX. १५. 1-2. [page१-632+ २५](VI)--a son of विश्वामित्र. भा. IX. १६. ३६.(VII)--a son of सञ्जय and father of Krta. भा. IX. १७. १६-17; वा. ९३. 8. Vi. IV. 9. २६.(VIII)--a son of सम्कृति and a great warrior. With him came to an end the क्षत्रवृद्ध line. (Burnouf makes क्षत्रधर्मन् his son. The term is only an epithet of Jaya). भा. IX. १७. १८.(IX)--a son of Manyu. भा. IX. २१. 1.(X)--a son of युयुधान and father of कुणि. भा. IX. २४. १४.(XI)--a son of Kanka and कर्णिका. भा. IX. २४. ४४.(XII)--a son of भद्रा. भा. X. ६१. १७.(XIII)--a name of Arjuna (पाण्डव). भा. X. ७२. ४७.(XIV)--a नाग of the fifth or महातलम्. Br. II. २०. ३७; वा. ५०. ३६.(XV)--a वीकुण्ठ God. Br. II. ३६. ५७.(XVI)--a son of जाम्बवान्. Br. III. 7. ३०२. [page१-633+ २६](XVII)--a son of Kali and grandson of वरुण. Br. III. ५९. 7; वा. ८४. 7.(XVIII)--a son of Vijaya; father of हर्यश्वक. Br. III. ६८. 9; वा. ९३. 9.(XIX)--a son of सृञ्जय, and father of Vijaya. Br. III. ६८. 8.(XX)--a son of शिष्ट. M. 4. ३९.(XXI)--a son of भद्राश्व. M. ५०. 3.(XXII)--the वेदव्यास of the १८थ् dva1para. Vi. III. 3. १५.(I)--a mind-born mother. M. १७९. १३.(II)--a moat equal to १२ oceans. वा. ४७. ७०.(III)--a companion of पार्वती. Br. IV. ४०. ३३.(IV)--a वर्ण s4akti. Br. IV. ४४. ६०. [page१-638+ २३](V)--a goddess enshrined at वराहशैल; a mother-goddess; {{F}}1:  M. १३. ३२; १७९. १३ and ७१.{{/F}} Icon of; to be propitiated before building palaces. ^2 Ib. २६०. १९; २६८. १० and २१.--a lake in the Kuru country; sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ४९; १२१. ७०.--a son of Manasyu. वा. ९९. १२१.--are twelve in number created by ब्रह्मा, bodies of मन्त्र used in यज्ञस्; these are दर्श, पौर्ण- मास, बृहद्य, रथन्तरम्, वित्ति, विवित्ति, आकूति, कूति, विज्ञासा, विज्ञात, मनस् and यज्ञ। These were again born as Jitas in the Svayambhuva epoch. ब्रह्मा asked them to observe household duties and यज्ञस्, but they took to ज्ञान। The enraged creator cursed them to undergo seven वृत्तिस्। They were born in turn as Ajitas, तुषितस्, Satyas, Haraya, वैकुण्थस्, साद्यस्, and आदित्यस्. Br. III. 3. 5-7; 4 (whole).--a son of कार्तवीर्य Arjuna and father of तालजन्घ; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २३. २७-28; वा. ९४. ५०; Vi. IV. ११. २१-22.{{/F}} a महारथ who reigned at Avanti; {{F}}2:  Br. III. ४१. १३; ४७. ६६; ६९. ५०.{{/F}} known also as Vaikarta. {{F}}3:  M. ४३. ४६.{{/F}}(I)--the son of बृहद्काय and father of विशद. भा. IX. २१. २२-23.(II)--the son of बृहन्मनस् and father of Vijaya. His wife was सम्भूति. भा. IX. २३. ११-12; वा. ९९. १११; Vi. IV. १८. २२-23.(III)--the king of Sindhu and an ally of जरासन्ध; was stationed at the north gate of मथुरा, and on the east during the siege of Gomanta; served Duryo- dhana's army. भा. X. ५२. ११[6]; ५०. ११[7]; ७८. [९५ (v) १६]; Vi. V. ३८. १६.(IV)--a son of the second सावर्ण Manu. Br. IV. 1. ७२.(V)--a son of बृहद्भानु. M. ४८. १०१. [page१-635+ २८](VI)--a son of बृहदिषु. M. ४९. ४९.(VII)--a son of बृहद्कर्मन् and father of विश्वजित्. Vi. IV. १९. ३४.--a name of ललिता. Br. IV. १३. 2.(I)--a son of Marutvati and Dharma; an अम्श of वासुदेव, otherwise known as Upendra. भा. VI. 6. 8.(II)--a son of Indra and शची; attacked Asura followers of Bali. Identified with Hari. भा. VI. १८. 7; VIII. २१. १७; XI. 5. २६; Br. III. 6. २४; वा. ६८. २४.(III) son of जाम्बवान्. Br. III. 7. ३०२.(IV)--the city founded by Nimi near the आश्रम of Gautama. Br. III. ६४. 1-2; वा. ८९. 2.(V)--one of the eleven Rudras. M. 5. ३०.(VI)--a consort of कीर्ति and who left him for Soma (s.v.). M. २३. २५. [page१-636+ २८](VII)--a son of वृषभ and जयन्ती; father of अक्रूर. M. ४५. २६; भा. I. १४. २८.(VIII)--a विनायक, to be worshipped in house- building. M. १८३. ६३; २५३. २३ and ४०; २५५. 8; २६६. ४३.(IX)--Mt. a कुलपर्वत of the केतुमाल. वा. ४४. 4.--a तीर्थम् sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ७३.(IV)--a goddess enshrined at हस्तिनापुर; a mother-goddess. M. १३. २८; १७९. १३; वा. 1. १५३. [page१-637+ २५](I)--Bestowed by Indra in marriage to ऋ