nour of him; {{F}}3:  Ib. III. 1. ३२; ११. ४३.{{/F}} resides in the sun's chariot in the month of मार्ग- शीर्ष। {{F}}4:  Ib. II. १०. १३.{{/F}}(VII)--a son of Suhotra. Vi. IV. 8. 5.(VIII)--a son of Parvasa. वा. २८. १३.--the lines of kings commencing with Sannuhotra काश, ruled at काशी. Six of them were ब्रह्मवादिन्स्। Among them were ब्राह्मणस् and क्ष- triyas whose sons were righteous, powerful and strong. Br. II. ३२. ११२; III. ६७. ७९; वा. ९२. ७४.--(कालसर्पि): fit for श्राद्ध। वा. ७७. ८७. [page१-376+ ३०]--one of the sages who heard the first part (sarga) of the पुराण asked सूत to speak on प्रतिसन्धि; {{F}}1:  वा. 7. 1.{{/F}} a gotrakara. {{F}}2:  M. १९९. 9.{{/F}}--आर्षेय pravara of the भार्गवस्. M. १९५. ३७.(II)--capital of पौण्ड्रक invaded by कृष्ण; पौण्ड्रक on the S. of the Gomanta hill during the siege by जरासन्ध. {{F}}1:  भा. X. ६६. [१२], १०; ५२. ११ [9].{{/F}} The अभिचार Agni sent by सुदक्षिण returned and killed सुदक्षिण himself, while विष्णु's Cakra burnt down the whole city. {{F}}2:  Ib. X. ६६. ३०-42; ३७. १९.{{/F}} Its king went to स्यमन्तपञ्- caka for solar eclipse having heard that कृष्ण was there. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ८२. २५.{{/F}} When the kingdom had no rains, its king gave his daughter गान्दिनी to श्वफल्क, and this resulted in plenty of showers. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ५७. ३२. Br. III. ७१. १०४.{{/F}} Likened to भागवत पुराण in its importance. {{F}}5:  भा. XII. १३. १७.{{/F}} Sages of, visited द्वारका. {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ९०. २८ [3].{{/F}} Residence of कामाक्षी {{F}}7:  Br. IV. ३७. १५; ४०. १५ and ८०, ९१.{{/F}} the capital of कुशध्वज; {{F}}8:  वा. ८१. १८; ९९. ४०२.{{/F}} in the brows of the Veda. {{F}}9:  Ib. १०४. ७५.{{/F}}--see (काशिराज): king of कासि who went to aid पौण्ड्रक against कृष्ण and who was so struck that his head shot into the city; his son together with the priest prayed to शिव to avenge his father's murder; शिव granted the boon and sent a female created from fire to destroy कृष्ण whose discus was more than a metal; the dead ran to काशि followed by the discus which burnt the whole city. Vi. V. ३४. १४-43.--a sage. M. १९६. २७.--a sage of the तामस epoch. Vi. III. 1. १८.(I)--a ऋत्विक् at ब्रह्मा's यज्ञ। वा. १०६. ३७.(II)--a Pravara. M. १९२. १०; १९६. ३३.--कश्यप gotrakaras. M. १९९. 4.--Image of; ten hands, three eyes, youthful, killing महिषासुर, and riding the lion. M. २६०. ५५-66. [page१-347+ ३३]--was observed by the girls of the व्रज early in the season of हेमन्त। After bathing in the यमुना, they made a figure of the देवी with sand, and worshipped it as the representation of the देवी for a month. Their object was to win कृष्ण as their husband. Prayers were also sent to भद्रकाली by rising early and bathing in the यमुना. To test their sincerity कृष्ण saw them one day playing in the river naked leaving their clothes on the banks. He removed these to the top of a नीप tree near by. The girls asked for the return of their clothes, and threatened to report to the king. कृष्ण asked them to receive their clothes from him. He said that their vow was fruitless as they bathed naked, and he returned their clothes on their saluting him with both their arms. He then blessed them and asked them to go back to the व्रज which they did. भा. X. २२. 1-२७.--a sage. M. १९६. २७.(I)--R. personified as one of the wives of हव्यवाहन (शम्स्य) fire; Sangamam in the नर्मदा, where Kubera attained सिद्धि by penance to शिव. Its great- ness described. Br. II. १२. १४; M. ५१. १३; १६३. ६१; १८९. 2-२०; वा. २९. १३०. [page१-370+ ३८](II)--the grand-daughter of युवनाश्व and wife of Janhu; mother of Suhotra. (Sunaha-ब्र्। प्।); made of one half of गन्गा. Br. III. ६६. २८-30; वा. ९१. ५८.(III)--a R. of the Bhadra country. वा. ४३. २६.(IV)--R. a महानदि (वा। प्।) in भारतवर्ष; {{F}}1:  वा. १०८. ७९.{{/F}} takes its source in the Sahya (ऋष्यवत्) hills noted for Vai- nana elephants in द्राविड des4a (दक्षिण देश); {{F}}2:  भा. V. १९. १८; VII. १३. १२; XI. 5. ४०; Br. II. १६. ३५; III. 7. ३५७; वा. ४५. १०४; ७७. २८.{{/F}} visited by बलराम; {{F}}3:  भा. X. ७९. १४; M. ११४. २३.{{/F}} fit for श्राद्ध offerings, and sacred to पितृस्. {{F}}4:  Br. III. १३. २८; M. २२. २७.{{/F}}(I)--a son of भृगु and दिव्या; also शुक्र, उशन, the आचार्य for devas and asuras; Kavisuta and the name of a planet; wife गोनाम, had four sons, त्वष्ट, वरूत्री, शण्ड, and Marka; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 1. ७६; ६८. ८६; ७२. ९५; ७३. 1, ३७. वा. ५९. ९०; ६२. ४१; ६५. ७४-7.{{/F}} the lord of भृगुस्; {{F}}2:  Vi. ७०. 4.{{/F}} cursed ययाति. {{F}}3:  Vi. IV. १०. 7.{{/F}} Asuras defeated by Indra appealed to काव्य and resolved to go to रसातल; काव्य encouraged them and said that rains, vegetation, etc., would stand completely with them and only (1/4) with the devas; at that time the devas appealed to him for help; but काव्य went to महादेव and learnt the मन्त्र for their success; in the meantime he asked them to keep quiet and perform austerities after lay- ing their weapons down. महादेव insisted on कुण्ड- धूम observance for a thousand years with their heads down; while so engaged the asuras got afraid of the devas and appealed to his mother and the wife of भृगु; she offered them shelter but finding them being killed by the devas she resolved to deprive Indra of his place; then Indra appealed to विष्णु whose body he entered; but she set on [page१-371+ ३६] fire the whole world of devas, when out of rage विष्णु killed her; भृगु cursed him to be born seven times among men; then by power of तपस् he restored his wife to life; शुक्र's religious observance so as to please him; penance over, महेश्वर granted him three things: non-defeat by others, lordship over wealth, and eternal life; on this he praised नीललोहित by many names; pleased, शिव disappeared; then शुक्र was attracted towards जयन्ती the daughter of Indra and promised to be with her for ten years unknown to the asuras by means of माया; when काव्य returned the asuras were pleased; but during the ten years बृहस्पति appeared before the asuras in the guise of काव्य and pretended to speak to them the मन्त्र he had heard; the asuras accepted him; ten years were over and a daughter देवयानि was born to शुक्र who appeared before the asuras; finding two काव्यस् the asuras became mystified and काव्य said that he was बृहस्पति in disguise; the asuras did not believe in the real शुक्र who left them in anger; soon they found out the mistake and approached शुक्र through प्रह्लाद and he became pleased; then he approached ब्रह्मा who said that after ten युगस् and in the स्वारोचिष Yuga the asuras would get back their kingdom; saying this he pointed out to two disciples सण्ड and Marka equal to बृहस्पति, and at last the devas were defeated. Seeing the success of the asuras विष्नु took different avatars to put them down. {{F}}4:  वा. ९७. ९४ to end and ch. ९८; Br. III, ७२. ९६ to the end; ७३. 1-६४.{{/F}}(II)--an अङ्गिरस, and one of the seven sages of तामस Manu; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३२. ९८ and १०४; ३३. 7; ३६. ४७.{{/F}} a मन्त्रकृत्। {{F}}2:  वा. ५९. ९६.{{/F}}(III)--a son of सेनाजित्. M. ४९. ५०; वा. ९९. १७३.(IV)--a son of भरताग्नि. वा. २९. 8. [page१-372+ ३२]--a group of पितृस् who drink Soma's स्वधा। Their mind-born daughter is Yogotpatti; other names are सम्वत्सरस्, पञ्चाब्दस्, आज्यपस्, being presiding deities of अष्तकस् and others. They drink ghee. Br. II. २३. ३९ and ७३-5; २८. 4, २३ and ७०; III. १०. ८५; M. १४१. 4-१६; वा. ५६. १३, १६.--a son born to the waiting woman of सुदेष्णा and दीर्घटमस्. By austerities at Girivraja, reached ब्राह्मणहोओद्. Father of १००० sons by name कौष्माण्डस् and Gautamas. M. ४८. ६३, ८४-8.--a son of जटामालि, an अवतार् of the Lord. वा. २३. १८७.--a तीर्थम् sacred to माता, पितृस् and to शिव. M. १३. ४८; २२-30; १८१. २६.--a Pravara of the भार्गवस्. M. १९५. ३१.(I)--killed by श्री Ra1ma; an Asura in Tat- valam. भा. IX. १०. १२; Br. II. २०. १६; Vi. IV. 4. ९६.(II)--a pupil of Sumantu of Atharvan fame. He imparted the Veda to two disciples Pathya and Deva- दर्श (वेदस्पर्श,-वा। प्।) dividing it into two. Br. II. ३५. ५६; वा. ६१. ५०; Vi. III. 6. 9.(III)--an Asura chief in Atalam. वा. ५०. १६.--the son of बृहस्पति; deputed by gods to learn सम्जीविनी विद्या from शुक्राचार्य; offered himself as a disciple and admitted as a pupil by शुक्र; conducted himself to the satisfaction of his teacher and his daughter देवयानी for a period of ५०० years. Once while out in the woods tending शुक्र's cows, the Asuras killed him and left his body to be devoured by dogs and jackals. The cows returned home but not Kaca. देवयानी suspected of foul play and reported his death. शुक्र brought him back to life. {{F}}1:  M. २५. १४-37.{{/F}} On another occasion he went to the woods to gather flowers for देवयानी and this time the Asuras ground him to pieces and mixing them with सुरा offered it to शुक्र who drank it. Again देवयानी persisted wanting him back to life. This meant शुक्र's death for he had to come out by tearing open his belly. So he taught Kaca the सम्जीविनी विद्या so that he might restore him after his revival. Thus he did and so he learnt the विद्या। After a sojourn of ten hundred years he returned with due leave from his teacher. Now देवयानी offered to marry him but he pointed out that it was not proper to marry his preceptor's daughter. So [page१-299+ २५] she cursed that he would not get the fruits of his विद्या and he retorted that she would not find a ब्राह्मण husband but only a क्षत्रिय. Returned to the gods who gave him a share in their oblations; put to death by वृषपर्वन्'s men. {{F}}2:  M. २५. ३८-69; chap. २६ whole; भा. IX. १८. २२.{{/F}}--a western country. Br. II. १६. ६२.--the नाग presiding over the month of माधव। भा. XII. ११. ३४.(I)--a son of विश्वामित्र. Br. III. ६६. ६९; वा. ९१. ९७; Vi. IV. 7. ३८.(II)--a नाग. वा. ६९. ७३.(III)--one of the eight निधिस् of Kubera. वा. ४१. १०.--the सर्प who resides in the sun's chariot during the month of माधव। Vi. II. १०. 5.--a western country. Br. II. १६. ६२.--of the south. वा. ४५. १३१. [page१-300+ २४]--a brother of Vasudeva. वा. ९६. १४८.--a R. sacred to पितृस्. Once राम resided on her banks. M. २२. ५२.--a name of ललिता. Br. IV. १७. ३४; २८. ६७.--a name of ललिता. Br. IV. १७. ३४.--sons of Dullola. Br. III. 7. ४४३.--a daughter of दक्ष, wife of तार्क्ष्या, and mother of नागस्, including कालिय: {{F}}1:  भा. V. २४. 8; VI. 6. २१-2; X. १७. 4, ७३.{{/F}} according to बृअह्माण्ड वि।, वा।, and मस्त्य प्। Consort of काश्यप; {{F}}2:  Br. III. 3. ५७; 7. ३१, ४६७; M. 6. 2 & ३८; १४६. १९ & २२; १७१. २९ & ६३; वा. ६६. ५५; Vi. I. १५. १२५.{{/F}} known for anger. {{F}}3:  वा. ६९. ९४.{{/F}}--Reference to तक्षक in Sutalam. Br. II. २०. २४.--a son of Ugrasena. वा. ९६. १३२. [page१-305+ २६]--a मध्यमाध्वर्यु। Br. II. ३३. १६.--कश्यप gotrakaras. M. १९९. 7.--Daughter of मालिन्. Mother of रावण and others. {{F}}1:  Br. III. 8. ४० and ४७.{{/F}} केकसी (रामायण) one of the four wives of विश्- ravas, and mother of three sons, रावण, कुम्भकर्ण and विभीषण and a daughter शूर्पणखा. {{F}}2:  वा. ७०. ३४, ४१.{{/F}} [page१-463+ २५]--the husband of श्रुतकीर्ति. Br. III. ७१. १५७.--Five in number born of धृष्टकेतु and and श्रुतकीर्ति. Its king was vanquished by कृष्ण. See केकयस्। भा. IX. २४. ३८; II. 7. ३५.--a son of शिबि. His ten daughters were queens of सत्राजित्. भा. IX. २३. 3; M. ४५. १९.--a tribe. M. ११४. ४२.--surname of भद्रा, a wife of कृष्ण. भा. X. ५७. ५६.--sacred to लिलिता. Br. IV. ४४. ९७.--a form of temple with 9 storeys and a तोरण with ४० हस्तस्। M. २६९. २८-31, ४७.--the abode of शिव seated on a bani- yan tree and of यक्षस्, full of different plants, trees and flowers, birds and beasts. Here are the city of अलका, and the forest Saugandhika. {{F}}1:  भा. IV. 5. २६; VI. 8. ३३; IX. 4. ५५; X. १०. 2; ५५ [1]; M. ५४. 3; ६२. 2; वा. ३०. ८५; ३५. 9; ३६. २४; ३८. ३३; ४१. 1; ४२. ३२; ४७. 1; ५०. ४८; ५४. ३५-6; १०१. ३०३.{{/F}} It is located on the south of Meru, {{F}}2:  भा. V. १६. २७; Vi. II. 2. ४२.{{/F}} on the Himalayan slopes; the residence of Kubera. Describ- ed. {{F}}3:  Br. II. १८. 1-4; २०. ५०, २५. २४-40; III. १३. ३६; २२. ५६; २५. 9; ४१. १८; IV. 9. ३०; १०. २७.{{/F}} North of Atri's hermitage. {{F}}4:  M. १२१. 2-5; १६३. ८५; १८३. 1.{{/F}}--the Yavanas; not duly crowned kings, rule after the Maury