ng बलराम whose name was suggested for his daughter's husband. On return he found his country overrun by यक्षस्, and getting his daughter married to बलराम, he retired to Badari to [page१-296+ ३०] perform penance. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. 3. २९-36; M. १२. २३; वा. ८६. २६-30; ८८. 1.{{/F}} Ruled from कुशस्थलि. During his sojourn at ब्रह्मा's residence, the राक्षसस् captured the capital and put to flight his younger brothers who established smaller states then and there. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ६१. २०-27; Vi. IV. 1. ६५-96.{{/F}}--a राक्षस in Sutalam. Br. II. २०. २३.(I)--the son of शशाद; rode on Indra in the form of a bull in the आडीवक युद्ध। Father of Anenas. वा. ८८. २४-25; Br. III. ६३. २५; Vi. IV. 2. ३२-3.(II)--a surname of Puramjaya (s.v.); a son of विकुक्षि; lust of, after more territory; eldest of ११४ ruling south of Meru. भा. IX. 6. १२; XII. 3. १०; M. १२. २०.(I)--a स्वर शक्ति। Br. IV. ४४. ५७.(II)--a daughter of Kardama married to मरीचि; bore two sons, कश्यप and पूर्णिमन्. भा. III. २४. २२; IV. 1. १३.(I)--a deva-gandharva. वा. ६८. ३८.(II)--a forest where इक्ष्वाकु was addressed by पितृस्. Vi. III. १६. १७.--on the East slopes of the Himalayas {{F}}1:  वा. 1. १८९; ४१. ४३-6; ४७, ४७.{{/F}} noted for great sages. {{F}}2:  भा. X. ८७. 7.{{/F}} Residence of Manu. Here देवापि [and Puru (Manu) वि। प्।] continued their योग practice. These yogins would start the course of वर्णाश्रम धर्म again at the end of Kali; {{F}}3:  IX. १२. 6; २२. १७; XII. 2. ३७-38; Br. I. 1. १६४; III. ६३. २१०; ६६. 7; M. १२१. ४९; २७३. ५६.{{/F}} watered by the Ganges. {{F}}4:  Br. II. १८. ५०.{{/F}} देवापि and Manu originate क्षत्रिय clans in कृत युग at; the race of Manu responsible for rulers throughout the three ages, कृत, त्रेता and द्वापर। {{F}}5:  वा. ८८. २१०: ९१. 7: ९९. ४३७; Vi. IV. २४. ११८-121.{{/F}} Manu stands rooted to योग at. {{F}}6:  Vi. IV. 4. १०९.{{/F}} [page१-332+ ३८]--sons of धृतराष्ट्रि and गरुड. Br. III. 7. ४५७.--a door-keeper of महाकाल. Br. IV. ३२. १८.(I)--sixty in number: {{F}}1:  Br. IV. ३४. ७०.{{/F}} a 