p from his long sleep. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ५२. 2.{{/F}} Deterioration of Vedic धर्म and rise of पाखण्डस्. Incarnation of Pramati in the form of a horse who puts down all heretics and the unrighteous. {{F}}5:  Br. II. २९. २३-34; ३१. 5-१०२; III. १४. ४६. ७४. २०७-241; M. १४४. ३०-88.{{/F}} Predominance of here- [page१-334+ ३८] tics and शूद्रस् in; {{F}}6:  वा. ७८. ३६.{{/F}} १०६,000 or ३६०,000-duration of; its सन्- ध्याम्श 1,००० years. {{F}}7:  वा. ३२. ६३; ९९. २६४; १०२. 4. M. २७३. २७-33, ४५. ५०.{{/F}} Noted for theft; see तृष्यम्; {{F}}8:  Br. II. 7. ५९.{{/F}} दानम् the chief act and तमस् the chief quality. {{F}}9:  वा. 8. ६६.{{/F}} descrip- tion of the evils of: bad rule and decay of civilization and morality; age of man २३ years; began with परीक्षित् when the two first stars of seven ऋषिस् were in Magha; its duration according to the calculation of men ३६०,800. Then comes कृत। {{F}}१०:  Vi. IV. २४. ७१-96, ९७, १०९. ११४-15.{{/F}}--the २१स्त् (१०थ् वा।) अवतार् of Hari, in कलियुग and emperor of the world by name पाराश्रय with याज्ञ- valkya as Purohita. Born of a ब्राह्मण Vis2n2uyas4as in शम्बलग्राम. His horse would be known as Devadatta. Riding on it, Kalki would rid the earth of the unrighteous and implant धर्म again. {{F}}1:  भा. I. 3. २५; XII. 2. १८-23; M. २७३. २७; २८५. 7; Vi. IV. २४. ९८-101.{{/F}} Invoked; {{F}}2:  भा. VI. 8. १९.{{/F}} destroyer of क्ष- triyas who became म्लेच्छस् by character. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ४०. २२.{{/F}} State of the world then. {{F}}4:  वा. ९९. ३९०-411; ४२४-29.{{/F}} According to the ब्र्। पुराण, his name is विष्नुयाशस्, and son of पराशर: the tenth incarnation of Hari, with Purohita याज्ञवल्क्य. After rooting out [page१-335+ ३६] अधर्म with ब्राह्मण warriors he gives up his ghost at the confluence of the गङ्गा and the यमुना; in the pre- vious birth was Pramiti; would bring round all tribes and wander the world unseen; except vegetation; his life of २५ years' duration and of पराशर gotra; then again अधर्म, disease, etc., at the end of कलि and commence- ment of the कृत युग। {{F}}5:  Br. III. ७३. १०४-24; ७४. २०६; IV. २९. १३३; M. ४७. २४८-62; वा. ९८. १०४-17.{{/F}} Purify the शूद्रस्, cross the ocean and destroy sinners. Then will follow civil strife and the disorder of the world. {{F}}6:  M. ५४. १९.{{/F}}--a commander of भण्ड. Br. IV. २१. ७९.--a son of सरमा, and father of four sons. Br. III. 7. ४४१.--see सौदास। भा. IX. 9. १८.(I)--a king who was cursed by शक्ति in नैमिष which resulted in the enmity between वसिस्ठ and विश्वामित्र. वा. 2. ११; Br. I. 2. ११.(II)--another name is Mitrasaha. See सौदास: son of ऋतुपर्ण. Br. III. ६३. १७६; M. १२. ४६; वा. ८८. १७६; Vi. IV. 4. ५७.--Music; मारुत, the presiding deity. वा. ८६. ५२.(I)--a son of Dhruva and भ्रमी. भा. IV. १०. 1.(II)--a nephew of हिरण्यकशिपु. M. 6. २६.(III)--the period of fourteen Manus or १००० युगस् followed by प्रलय; {{F}}1:  भा. II. 8. १२; IV. 9. १४; XII. 4. 2-3; Br. IV. 1. ११६, १७३ and २१०; Vi. III. 2. ५०-2; VI. 3. १२.{{/F}} in the day ब्रह्मा; in the night नारायण sleeping over his couch शेष the thirty कल्पस् and the thirty days of ब्रह्मा. These are mixed, तामस, राजस and सात्विक {{F}}2:  M. २९०. 1-१६.{{/F}} from क्लिपु, to introduce with intelli- gence; the fourteen सम्स्थस् ब्रह्मा introduced and hence कल्प; {{F}}3:  वा. 7. ७७; २१. २८ff.{{/F}} twenty-eight in number, each of two कल्पार्धस्; {{F}}4:  वा. २१. १७-18; २२. 7; ३०. २३१: ५९. १३८; ६१. ५४ and १०२.{{/F}} the १४ कल्पस् made by ब्रह्मा and hence the name. {{F}}5:  Br. II. 6. ७४.{{/F}}--a door-keeper of महाकाल. Br. IV. ३२. १८. [page१-337+ २६]--a division of श्रीपुरम्. Br. IV. ३१. ६७; ३२. २१ & ६५. [page१-336+ २८]--a gift of ten golden creepers of a कल्प tree, leads one to Heaven. M. २७४. 9; २८६. 1-१७.--ritual literature; part of विष्णु. Vi. V. 1. ३७.--a mindborn mother. M. १७९. २५.--see कल्पवृक्ष। M. २७४. 7.--a part of the पुराणस्। Vi. III. 6. १५.--a branch of Vedic literature, arranged by लोमहर्षण; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३१. १४ & २४; ३४. १६; वा. ५८. १४.{{/F}} begun in द्वापर. {{F}}2:  M. १४४. १३-14.{{/F}}--a son of Vasudeva and उपदेवा. भा. IX. २४. ५१.--leads to the world of ब्रह्मा. M. १०१. ५०.--a divine tree; {{F}}1:  Br. IV. १५. ३७; २८. ७२.{{/F}} gift of a golden tree, leads one to be born राजराज after a sojourn in विष्नुलोक; {{F}}2:  M. २७७. 1-२२.{{/F}} gave clothes, jewels and honey in the कृतयुग। {{F}}3:  वा. 8. ९३; १०६. ७४.{{/F}}--in honour of the Sun for १३ months M. ७४. 2-१६.(I)--the wife of Dhara. M. 5. २४.(II)--the goddess enshrined at Malaya hill: a follower of माया. M. १३. ३६; १७९. ७०.--the vow of; in later कल्प changed into भीमद्वादशी after being observed by भीमसेन, the पाण्डव. M. ६९. ५६-7.(I)--ब्रह्मा's consort; see also लक्ष्मी, श्री। Br. IV. १५. ३७; ३९. ६७. [page१-317+ २३](II)--an Apsaras. वा. ६९. 7.--a Laukikya Apsaras. Br. III. 7. १०.(I)--a तीर्थम् sacred to कमला. M. १३. ३२.(II)--an attribute of श्री. Vi. I. 8. २२.(I)--a श्रुतऋषि. Br. II. ३३. 6.--a name of ब्रह्मा. M. 1. १३; ६०. 4.(I)--a दानव who entered the ocean. M. ६१. 4.(II)--a तीर्थम् sacred to Mahotpala. M. १३. ३४.--a R. in भारतवर्ष. M. १६३. ६२.--A व्रत in honour of the Sun god. M. ७४. 3; ७८ (whole).--a daughter of king रेणुक of इक्ष्वाकु line. Hence रेणुका; wife of Jamadagni; mother of परशुराम. Br. III. ६६. ६१.--is ब्रह्मा; narrated the विष्णु पुराण to ऋभु. Br. III. ५६. ३७; Vi. VI. 8. ४३.--a goddess following माया. M. १७९. ७०. [page१-318+ ३०]--of Budha; {{F}}1:  M. ११. ५५.{{/F}} in possession of Agastya. {{F}}2:  Ib. ६१. ३६.{{/F}} Given to वामन by वसिष्ठ; {{F}}3:  Ib. २४५. ८६.{{/F}} of ब्रह्मा, as the source of गङ्गा; {{F}}4:  वा. ५५. १४; भा. VIII. २१. 4.{{/F}} of शिव. {{F}}5:  वा. १०१. २७३.{{/F}}--is कृष्ण. Br. III. ३६. ३४.--the tortoise अवतार् of Hari, being the eleventh of incarnations. In this form the Mandara hill was supported on his back during the churning of the ocean by gods and Asuras. भा. I. 3. १६; VIII. 7. 8.(I)--a chief of नागस् in पाताल, presides over the month of इष। {{F}}1:  भा. V. २४. ३१; XII. ११. ४३; M. 6. ३९; वा. ५०. २३; ६९. ७०.{{/F}} According to the ब्रह्माङ्द and वायु पुराणस्, he was the resident of Sutalam; {{F}}2:  Br. II. २०. २३; III. 7. ३३.{{/F}} in the प्रजापति- क्षेत्र; used in the chariot of त्रिपुरारी. {{F}}3:  M. १०४. 5; १०६. २७; ११०. 8; १३३. २०.{{/F}} काद्रवेय Na1ga residing in the sun's chariot in the month of माघ; {{F}}4:  Vi. I. २१. २१; II. १०. १६.{{/F}} in the month of तप and तपस्य। {{F}}5:  Br. II. २३. २१.{{/F}}(II)--heard the विष्णु पुराण from अश्वतर and narrated it to एलापुत्र. Vi. VI. 8. ४७.(III)--an यक्ष. वा. ६९. १२.(IV)--(Mt.) a Kulaparvata of the केतुमाल. वा. ४४. 4.--a R. of the केतुमाल continent. वा. ४४. १७.--नाग with the sun in the months of माशि and पङ्गुनि। वा. ५२. २१.(IV)--(Kambalabarhi-वा। प्।). A son of Marutta. M. ४४. २५; वा. ९५. २४.(II)--a son of Satyaka and the daughter of काशिराज. Br. III. ७१. ११६; वा. ९६. ११५.(III)--a son of देवबाहु, (देवार्ह- वा। and मत्स्य प्।) and father of असमञ्जस्; a great scholar. Br. III. ७१. १४२; M. ४४. ८३; वा. ९६. १४०.(I)--a son of Andhaka. भा. IX. २४. १९; M. ४४. ६१; Vi. IV. १४. १२. [page१-319+ २८]Its king was vanquished by कृष्ण. भा. II. 7. ३५.--a son of Raivata Manu. Br. II. ३६. ६४.(I)--a hill of शाल्मलिद्वीप. Br. II. १९. ३९.(II)--a son of Ugrasena. Br. III. ७१. १३३.--a daughter of Ugrasena. Br. III. ७१. १३४.--a श्रुतऋषि. Br. II. ३३. १०.(II)--a name of विष्णु. Br. IV. १२. २०.--also कम्पातरन्गिणी--the sacred waters of काञ्ची. Br. IV. ४०. १७, ४०, ८५, १०२ and ११५.--an यक्ष. वा. ६९. १७७.--a mindborn mother. M. १७९. २४.(I)--the eldest son of Ugrasena {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २४. २४; Br. I. 1. १२५; III. ७१. १३२; वा. 1. १४८; ९६. १३१, १७३, २१६; Vi. IV. १४. २०; M. ४४. ७४; ४६. १३.{{/F}} and brother (cousin-वा। प्।) of देवकी. Took part in the festivities con- nected with the marriage of देवकी and Vasudeva, when he heard a voice from air that her eighth son would kill him. He at once drew his sword to slay देवकी when Vasudeva entreated him to spare her life promising to give him all her sons. To this he agreed. He did not take notice even of the first boy. Subsequently नारद confirmed what he heard from the welkin. So he killed all her sons and put her and Vasudeva in jail. He waited for the seventh and was particularly afraid of the eighth. Being informed of the birth of a girl, and without listening to his sister's appeal to spare the baby, he dashed it against a stone. It flew heavenwards and said that the baby born to vanquish him [page१-293+ ४३] was safe. Disheartened, कंस let Vasudeva and देवकी free. Consulted his ministers who advised him to kill all infants in the kingdom, and to hurt all ब्राह्मणस् and cows, the root cause of Hari's धर्म। Messengers were sent out on this mission. {{F}}2:  भा. X. chap. 1-4; Br. III. ७१. १७५-235; ७३. ९९; वा. ९८. १००; Vi. IV. १५. २६-7; V. 1. 6-११, ६७-69; 3. 2; chap. 4.{{/F}} An incarnation of कालनेमि. Threw his father Ugra- sena in prison and assumed regal administration. {{F}}3:  भा. X. 1. ६८-69.{{/F}} Encouraged by his Asura friends such as Pralamba and Baka, as also by the मागधन् king, he tyrannized the Yadus who left the land for other countries like Kuru, पाञ्- चाल and others. The ब्राह्मणस् were afraid of him. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. 2. 1-4; २३. ५२.{{/F}} Heard from नारद that कृष्ण and बलराम were Vasudeva's sons; when he went to slay Vasudeva, नारद prevented him from it. He then threw Vasudeva and his wife in prison. He summoned his councillors and asked the Mallas, चाणूर and मुष्टिक to get ready for a wrestling match with कृष्ण and राम; ordered his mahout to station the State Elephant at the gate of the enclosure (रङ्ग) and get कृष्ण and राम trampled under its feet; when he was asked why he was out to kill those two boys, he narrated the story of his mother once going in the garden thinking of her husband Ugrasena. Then a Gandharva Drumila per- sonated Ugrasena. Discovering that he was not her hus- band, she asked him in wrath who he was. He tried to console her saying that she would give birth to a heroic son. The chaste lady retorted that he would be cruel and un- righteous. Such being his birth, he hated his kith and kin. Then he commanded to commence the धनुर्याग। अक्रूर was sent for and ordered to take his chariot and bring कृष्ण and राम to the धनुर्याग with all gopas. He proposed to kill all of them and rule the kingdoms with the help of friends like जरासन्ध. Thanked by अक्रूर for an opportunity to visit कृष्ण and राम; अक्रूर reached the Vraja and was welcomed by the brothers and Nanda. Informed of their arrival by अक्रूर. Much concerned to know of the breaking of his bow by कृष्ण and further the killing of his guards. He had no sleep all night and had bad dreams, all in fear of कृष्ण. Next morning he drove [page१-294+ ३६] to the wrestling ground and occupied the royal seat with his ministers; was perturbed to learn of the death of Kuva- लयापीड and its guards. Became furious at the death of his five mallas and the running away of others. Ordered the banishment of the two brothers, robbing the gopas of their belongings, and imprisonment of Nanda, killing of Ugrasena and Vasudeva. कृष्ण attacked him direct, pull- ed him down from his throne and killed him. His eight brothers who offered fight were slain by राम. {{F}}5:  Ib. X. chap. ३६-44; M. ४७. 4, 6; ६९. 8; Vi. V. १२. २१; १५. 2-4; २०. २६, ८२-90.{{/F}} Death welcomed by Gopis and अक्रूर. {{F}}6:  भा. X. ४७. ३९; ४८. १७.{{/F}} Prevented Vasudeva go- ing to करवीरपुर. His oppression. {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ५७. २३; ६६. 9; ८२. २२; ८५. २८, ३३.{{/F}} His queens were Asti and प्राप्ति, daughters of जरा- sandha. {{F}}8:  Ib. X. ५०. 1;{{/F}} His death recalled by कृष्ण to Mucukunda; by कृतवर्मन् to युधिष्ठिर; by कुन्ती. {{F}}9:  Ib. X. ५१. ४२; ५२. [५६ (V) 6]; ५७. १३; I. 8. २३; II. 7. ३४; Vi. V. २९. 5.{{/F}} Attained Hari through fear. {{F}}१०:  भा. VII. 1. ३०.{{/F}} Of the Bhoja family. Funeral rites done by Ugrasena. {{F}}११:  Vi. V. २१. 7-१०; २९. 5.{{/F}}(II)--a दानव king; with the sun for two months--मधु and माधव। Br. II. २३. 3; IV. २९. १२३.--a daughter of Ugrasena; married देवभाग. भा. IX. २४. २५ and ४०; Br. III. ७१. १३४; M. ४४. ७५; Vi. IV. १४. २१.--a daughter of Ugrasena. Married Deva- श्रवस्. भा. IX. २४. २५ & ४१; Br. III. ७१. १३४; M. ४४. ७५; Vi. IV. १४. २१. [page१-295+ २९]--a son of सोमशर्मन्, an अवतार् of the Lord. वा. २३. २१६.(I)--a संहिकेय Asura. Br. III. 6. २०.(II)--a son of Durmada (Durdama-मत्स्य प्।); father of कृतवीर्य and three other sons, कार्तवीर्य, कृत- varma and कृत. Br. III. ६९. 8; M. ४३. १२; वा. ९४. 7-9.(III)--a son of हृदिक. Br. III. ७१. १४१.(IV)--a son of बृहति. Br. III. ७१. २५६.(V)--a king who ruled over स्त्रीराष्ट्र, Bho- jaka and other kingdoms. Br. III. ७४. १९९.--R. a महानदी, remembered by लोमश per- forming penance at the मुण्दपृष्ट hill; fit for performance of श्राद्ध। वा. १०८. ८०.--ruled over स्त्रिराष्ट्र and भक्ष्यकस्. वा. ९९. ३८७.--His wife was met by Agni, and Nala was their son. Br. III. 7. २२९-230.--Raudram metal, dear to पितृस्. Br. III. 1. ६०; ११. 5.--a sacred place (तीर्थ); a bather here goes to heaven, relieved of all three ऋणस्; east of the मुण्डपृष्ट hill. Br. III. १३. ११३-5; वा. ७७. १०५.--(Mt.) from the अण्ड; {{F}}1:  वा. २४. ७५.{{/F}} ten thousand योजनस् in length, containing caves of red arsenic. {{F}}2:  वा. ३५. १०.{{/F}} [page१-306+ २६]--a son of Pulaha and क्षमा; wife यशो- धरा and son सहिष्णु. Br. II. ११. ३१.(I)--enjoy kingdoms of त्रैराज्य and मूषिक. Vi. IV. २४. ६७.(II)--two sons of कृष्ण. वा. ९६. १८९.--one of the forms of ब्रह्मा in the Gaya stone. वा. १०६. ५६; १११. ७२.--a sacred place on the Ganges, where गरुड performed तपस्। Here शिव danced with a योगिनी. Bath here leads to Rudralokam. M. १८६. १०; १९२. ११; १९३. ६९-71; वा. ८३. २१.--a तीर्थ in Gaya; on its right side is Dak- षिणमानस. वा. १११. 7. [page१-307+ २३]--a son of हृदिक. Br. III. ७१. १४१; वा. ९६. १४०.--in the लिङ्ग देश of the personified Veda. वा. १०४. ७६.--a R. of the केतुमाल country. वा. ४४. १८.--in the waist of the personified Veda. वा. १०४. ८०.{{F}}1:  भा. X. ५३. ४१[].{{/F}} --followed रुक्मिणी going to देवी temple; also कञ्चुकधारि। {{F}}2:  Br. IV. ३२. 3; M. २५४. २३.{{/F}}--a chief वानर. Br. III. 7. २३४.--the minister of पञ्चाल Brahmadatta; remembered his previous birth as a son of कौशिक, left for the forest to practise योग with his brother minister. M. २०. २४; २१. ३१.--the name of the 8th कल्प M. २९०. 4.--an attribute of Manmatha. Br. IV. १९. ६७; ३०. ५४ and ८५; M. १५४. २५०.--a वाशिष्ठ and a sage. Br. II. ३२. ११६.(I)--a sage engaged in austerities on the banks of the गोमती; had a daughter through प्रम्लोचा who aban- doned the child in the midst of trees and departed. Soma nourished it with nectar, and trees looked after her as their baby. To get rid of the sin कण्डु entered the temple of पुरुषोत्तम and meditated on केशव. भा. IV. ३०. १३-14; Vi. I. १५. ११-54.(II)--a pupil of लाङ्गलि. Br. II. ३५. ४८.(III)--a लाङ्गल. वा. ६१. ४३.--a game with balls indulged in by girls. मोहिनी played it. भा. VIII. १२. १८ & २३; M. १६०. 4.--father of thousand snakes, moveable and immoveable having a number of heads, and flying in the air and having different names. वा. ६९. ६८.--one of the ten sons of हृदीक. M. ४४. ८२.--one of the five deva-गणस् of the १४थ् epoch of Bhautya Manu. These are the seven सामस् commencing with बृहत्। Br. IV. 1. १०६ & १०८; वा. १००. १११-2; Vi. III. 2. ४३.(II)--a son of देवमीढ अलिअस् शूर, and मारिषा. His queen was कर्णिका and sons were ऋतधामन् and Jaya. भा. IX. २४. २७-9. & ४४.(III)--the अवतार् of the Lord in the fifth द्वापर with four sons, all योगिन्स्। वा. २३. १२९.(IV)--a ऋत्विक् at ब्रह्मा's यज्ञ। वा. १०६. ३६.(V)--(Mt.) a chief hill of the शाल्मलिद्वीप. वा. ४२. ५०; ४९. ३६; Vi. II. 4. २७. [page१-298+ ३५](VI)--a Mt. in कुशद्वीप. M. १२२. ५७.(I)--a son of Ugrasena, and brother of कंस; killed by बलराम. {{F}}1:  भा. IV. २४. २४; X. ४४. ४०-41.{{/F}} His daughter was the queen of Andhaka. {{F}}2:  M. ४४. ६१ & ७४.{{/F}}--a daughter of Ugrasena; wife of आनक and mother of Satyajit and Purujit. भा. IX. २४. २५ and ४१; M. ४४. ७६.(I)--a royal dynasty of sixteen princes noted for their greed. See मौनस्। भा. XII. 1. २९.(II)--a tribe defeated by Bharatas. Purified of sin by devotion to Hari. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २०. ३०; II. 4. १८.{{/F}} Heard of कृष्ण going to मिथिला, and met him there with presents. {{F}}2:  भा. X. ८६. २०.{{/F}}--a northern tribe. M. ११४. ४२.(I)--a son of अजमीढ and केशिनी; father of मेधातिथि. वा. ९९. १६९-170.(II)--a son of Dhurya. वा. ९९. १३०.--(the text is confused). Apparently the four kings beginning with नवकण्ठायान are शुङ्ग- भृत्यस् and were known as कण्टायनद्विजस्। वा. ९९. ३४६-7. [page१-302+ २९]--a श्रुतऋषि। Br. II. ३३. 5.--the Mudgalas belonging to the branch of अङ्गिरस्. वा. ९९. १९९.(I)--a son of Apratiratha and father of मेधा- tithi; शकुन्तला was brought up in his आश्रम; performed birth and other सम्स्कारस् to the son born to her. भा. IX. २०. 6-१२ and १८; Vi. IV. १९. 5-6.(II)--a sage and contemporary of कृष्ण with whom he went to मिथिला. Left द्वारका for पिण्डारक. Invited for युधिष्ठिर's राजसूय। भा. X. ८६. १८; XI. 1. १२; X. ७४. 7; Vi. V. ३७. 6 [page१-303+ २७](III)--the minister of देवभूति S4un3ga, whom he assassinated and usurped the throne. भा. XII. 1. १९.(IV)--An अङ्गिरस and मन्त्रकृत्। A pupil of याज्ञवल्क्य. Br. II. ३२. १०९; ३५. २८; वा. ५९. १००; ६१. २४.(V)--a son of अजामीढ and केशिनी and father of मेधातिथि. M. ४९. ४६; Vi. IV. १९. ३०-31.(V)--a ऋत्विक् at the याग of ब्रह्मा. वा. १०६. ३५; १०८. ४२.--the family of ब्राह्मणस् originally from कण्व and his son मेधातिथि. (See Wilson, Note at p. ३२). Vi. IV. १९. 7.--the predecessors of the आन्ध्र rulers; their reign of 4 kings lasted for ४५ years. Br. III. ७४. १५८ & १५९.--a royal dynasty after शुङ्गस्; four kings in all, ruled for ४५ years. भा. XII. 1. १९; M. २७२. ३६; Vi. IV. २४. ३८, ४२.(I)--राशि and month पुरट्टाशि। वा. १०५. ४७. [page१-308+ २७](II)--daughter of Kardama and wife of Priya- vrata; mother of two daughters and ten sons. Vi. II. 1. 5.(III)--shrine of, south of Malaya {??}ills, visited by बलराम. भा. X. ७९. १७.--the harem of a palace. Vi. V. २९. ३१.--on the नर्मदा. M. १९३. ७६-7.--a son of मणिभद्र. वा. ६९. १५४.--a name of योगमाया. भा. X. 2. १२.--काश्यप gotraka1ras. 