 and राम lived here for four months. Pursued by जरा- sandha, the brothers fled to this city and after taking rest for the night got up the hill before daybreak. Not visited by Vasudeva by order of कंस. भा. X. [५२ (V) २८-42]; [५३. (V) २०-21]; ५२. ११ [1]; ६६. [9]. [page१-323+ २५]--sacred to महालक्ष्मि, and to पितृस्। M. १३. ४१; २२. ७६.(I)--father of कपील. Married देवहूति. {{F}}1:  भा. II. 7. 3; IV. 1. १०.{{/F}} A son of ब्रह्मा born of his shadow. A progenitor and a योगि; {{F}}2:  Ib. III. १२. २७ & ५६; chap. २१ to २४.{{/F}} performed in कृतयुग austerities on the banks of सरस्वती for १०,000 years; when Hari appeared before him, he praised Him and asked for a suitable wife. देवहूति was suggested and the Lord disappeared. Manu came with his wife and daughter to his hermitage, and was suitably received. Kardama agreed to marry his daughter and lead a householder's life until the birth of children. After wed- ding, Manu and his wife returned home. Pleased at his wife's devotion, created an aerial car artistically built and furnished. Took his wife after her bath and dress round the earth for a hundred years. Nine daughters were born when according to original contract he was anxious to leave her for woods to practise योग। Noticing her anxiety at his departure, he consoled her that she would give birth to Hari who would bring solace to her. On the birth of Kapila, ब्रह्मा and other seers called on him; gave his daughters in marriage, took leave of his son and retired to a life of penance. [page१-328+ ३१](II)--a son of Pulaha and क्षमा; married Sruti; son शङ्खपद and daughter काम्या; a प्रजापति; a sage by तपस् and a देवऋषि; {{F}}1:  Br. I. 1. ६५; II. ११. २३ and ३१; ३२. ९९; ३५. ९४; III. 8. १८; १०. ९३; M. १४५. ९३; वा. 1. ८०; 3. 3; २८. २५-29; ३३. 7; ३८. 7; ५९. ९१; ६१. ८४; ६५. ५३; Vi. I. १०. १०.{{/F}} a pravara. {{F}}2:  M. १९९. १६.{{/F}}(III)--a प्रजापति: wife of सिनीवली; had two daughters सम्राट् and कुक्षि, besides ten sons. {{F}}1:  Br. II. १४. 7; III. 1. ५३.{{/F}} His wife left him for Soma. His world that of आज्य पितृस्। {{F}}2:  M. १५. २०; २३. २४.{{/F}}(IV)--also शम्खप; a लोकपाल. Br. II. २१. १५७; M. १२४. ९५; वा. ५०. २०६.--in the navel portion of गया; bath and श्राद्ध here to get rid of the debt to पितृस्. वा. ११२. ५७.--a तीर्थम् sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ७७.--a gotrakara of Atri family. M. १९७. 1.--a daughter of Cedi king; queen of Nakula and mother of Niramitra. भा. IX. २२. ३२; M. ५०. ५५.--the chariot in which ललिता rode at the starting of expedition towards भण्ड. Br. IV. १७. 8.--a sage. M. १९८. २०.--त्रयार्षेय. M. १९८. 4.--a western kingdom. Br. II. १६. ६१.--the performer of, becomes king. M. १०१. ७२.--a ऋत्विक् at the sacrifice of ब्रह्मा. वा. १०६. ३७.--a commander of भण्ड. Br. IV. २१. ७९.--a commander of भण्ड. Br. IV. २१. ७८. [page१-325+ ३९]--Cancer; when the sun enters this it is दक्षिणायन. Vi. II. 8. ३१.--the नाग presiding over the month of पुष्य। {{F}}1:  भा. XII. ११. ४२; M. १२६. १८; वा. ५२. १७; ६९. ७०.{{/F}} A काद्रवेय Na1ga. {{F}}2:  Br. II. २३. १७; III. 7. ३४; IV. २०. ५३; ३३. ३६; M. 6. ३९; Vi. I. २१. २२.{{/F}} The सभा of, in माहिषमति. His son defeated by कार्तवीर्य Arjuna; {{F}}3:  Br. III. ६९. २६; M. ४३. २९.{{/F}} used for त्रिपुरारी's chariot. {{F}}4:  M. १३३. ३३; १६३. ५६.{{/F}} The assembly of, conquered by कार्तवीर्य Arjuna. {{F}}5:  वा. ९४. २६.{{/F}}--a तीर्थम् on the नर्मदा. M. १९१. ३६.(I)--two-fold; प्रवृत्ति and निवृत्ति; {{F}}1:  Vi. I. 1. २७; VI. 4. ४१.{{/F}} importance of; {{F}}2:  Vi. I. १८. ३२.{{/F}} that which consists of यज्ञ is best. {{F}}3:  Vi. II. १४. १४.{{/F}}(II)--(Vedic) two-fold; प्रवृत्त and निवृत्त। {{F}}1:  भा. VII. १५. ४७-49.{{/F}} There is another classification of Karma: वैदिक, तान्त्रिक, [page१-329+ ३६] and मिश्र (mixed). {{F}}2:  Ib. XI. २७. 7.{{/F}} कृष्ण advised Uddhava to pursue निवृत्त and abandon प्रवृत्त path. {{F}}3:  Ib. XI. १०. 4.{{/F}} Karma exalted as the source of all good and evil, and appropriate to four castes: is done due to मायामोहन्; {{F}}4:  Ib. X. २३. ५०; २४. १३-14 & १८-20.{