ructed and after the penance, केशिध्वज called over again to pay the precep- tor's fee; खाण्डिक्य who had no more concerns in this life asked for instruction on the doctrine of the soul; heard of the nature of योग from केशिध्वज; making his son master of his belongings went to the woods for penance. {{F}}2:  Ib. VI. 6. 5-५०; 7. १०२-03.{{/F}} [page१-500+ २६]--rhinoceros; flesh very good for श्राद्ध, but horn to be thrown away. वा. ८०. ५१.--a योग सिद्धि। Br. IV. ३६. ५२.--a name of गणेश. Br. IV. ४४. ७०.--a stage in which ईश्वर roamed like insect during night of ब्रह्मा. Br. II. २४. 9; ३२. ७८.--one of the Eastern entrances of the city of पुरञ्जन, allegorically the left eye. भा. IV. २५. ४७; २९. १०.--the son of वज्रनाभ and father of विधृति. भा. IX. १२. 3.(I)--a daughter of भद्राश्व and घृताचि. वा. ७०. ६९. [page१-498+ ३४](II)--one of the ten daughters of रौद्राश्व. वा. ९९. १२६.--(खालिय-Va1. P.). a pupil of शाकल्य. Br. II. ३५. 2; वा. ६०. ६४.--धूम्र Para1s4aras. M. २०१. ३८.--born of Anga and father of Diviratha. भा. IX. २३. 6.--the son of Jambha. वा. ६७. ७८.--the son of Rambha, (विवीम्श-Va1. P., Vi. P.) and a righteous king; father of Karamdhama (in Tre- तामुख-वा। प्।), (अतिविभूति-वि। प्।). भा. IX. 2. २५; वा. ८६. 7; Vi. IV. 1. २८.--the son of Pramati, (प्रजापति-वि। प्।) and father of चाक्षुष (क्षुप-वा। प्।) (चक्षुष-वि। प्।). भा. IX. 2. २४; वा. ८६. 5; Vi. IV. 1. २४.(I)--vanquished by कृष्ण. भा. II. 7. ३४. [page१-497+ ३२](II)--शिव cursed to become Khara by the sages of दारुवन inadvertently--described. {{F}}1:  Br. II. २७. 5-२०.{{/F}} Donkey born of सुग्रीवि. {{F}}2:  M. 6. ३३.{{/F}}(III)--a son of Vijvara. Br. III. 6. ३३.(IV)--a son of विश्रवस् and पुष्पोत्कट; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 8. ५५; वा. ७०. ४९; ९९. ४०६.{{/F}} a राक्- षस in the third talam (Vitalam); {{F}}2:  भा. IX. १०. 9; वा. ५०. २७.{{/F}} in the तारकमाय; {{F}}3:  M. १७३. १७; १७७. 7.{{/F}} killed by राम. {{F}}4:  Br. II. २०. २८; Vi. IV. 4. ९६.{{/F}}--a region through which पावनी flows; a kingdom. Br. II. १८. ५७; M. १२१. ५६; व