त। A राजऋषि who sought refuge in Hari towards the end of his life. His son was दीर्गबाहु. भा. IX. 9. ४१-49; II. 1. १३; XI. २३. ३०; IX. १०. 1; Vi. IV. 4. ७६-83.(II)--a son of यशोदा, {{F}}1:  Br. III. १०. ९०.{{/F}} a राजऋषि. {{F}}2:  वा. ७३. ४१.{{/F}}(III)--A daitya. भा. XII. 3. 9. [page१-496+ २६]--the son of दिलीप; descended from heaven and lived here for a मुहूर्त. वा. ८८. १८२.--presented dance, song and music to पृथु. भा. IV. १५. १९.--a वर्ण शक्ति; a मुद्रा देवी। Br. IV. ३७. १०; ४२. १४; ४४. ५९ and ८६. ११४.--a small village. वा. ९१. ३०.--a smaller division than a खर्वट. Vi. V. 2. १३.--a mind-born mother. M. १७९. १७.--a rural territorial division. M. २८३. 3; वा. 8. ९९, ११६; Br. II. 7. ९३ and १११.--not to have marital relations with विश्वा- mitra, etc. M. १९८. २१.--a daughter of दक्ष and mother of राक्षसस् as पिशाचस् and others; {{F}}1:  M. १७१. २९ and ६१; Vi. I. २१. २४.{{/F}} Her twelve daughters married Pulaha. {{F}}2:  वा. ६९. २०४.{{/F}}--नील Para1s4aras. M. २०१. ३४.(II)--a son of तामस Manu. भा. VIII. 1. २७; Br. II. ३६. ४९; Vi. III. 1. १९.(III)--a son of ऊरु (Kuru-वि। प्।) and आग्नेयि. Br. II. ३६. १०८; M. 4. ४३; Vi. I. १३. 6.(IV)--a daughter of Kardama, (दक्ष-वा। प्।, वि। प्।) married to भृगु. Mother of sons धातृ and विधातृ and daughter of श्रि. भा. III. २४. २३; IV. 1. ४३; Br. I. 9. ५२. ५४; ११. 1; III. २५. ७७; वा. १०. २७, ३०; ६२. ४३; Vi. I. 7. 7, २५. [page१-501+ ३८](V)--a daughter of भृगु; same as श्री; wife of नारायण; sons, Bala and उत्साह by him; others मानस, mind-born. See श्री. वा. २८. 1-3.(VII)--(एत्य्।) knowledge; all known. वा. 4. ३५.(I)--a son of Ulmuka and पुष्करिणी. भा. IV. १३. 7.(VI)--a R. in क्रौञ्चद्वीप. Br. II. १९. ७५; M. १२२. ८८; वा. ४९. ६९.--the mother of बलाहक and seven other sons, all commanders of भण्ड. Br. IV. २४. 6.(I)--a son of ऋषभ. भा. V. 4. १०. [page१-381+ २५](II)--a son of संकट. His sons were god- lings, being the presiding deities of fortresses. भा. VI. 6. 6.(III) (च्)--the land in which the Buddha was born; its people became purified by t