 ११.(II)--one of the seven sons of कौशिक. M. २०. 3.--श्याम Para1saras. M. २०१. ३७.--a mother goddess. M. १७९. २९.--a daughter of दक्ष and one of कश्य- pa's wives, and mother of दन्दशूक and other serpents. {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 6. २६ and २८; वा. ६६. ५४.{{/F}} Her twelve daughters were married to Pulaha. भूतस्, पिशाचस्, Kinnaras, वानरस् and others belonged to her line. {{F}}2:  Br. III. 3. ५६; 7. १७१, ४४४ and ४६७; 8. ७२; Vi. I. १५. १२५.{{/F}} Some of her sons fell a prey to भीमसेन's sword. {{F}}3:  M. 6. 2 and ४३; १४६. १८.{{/F}}--a गण of कार्दवेय Na1gas inhabiting महातल, afraid only of गरुड. Fought with Rudras in देवासुर battle. भा. V. २४-29; VIII. १०. ३४. [page१-483+ २९]--a sage. M. २००-7.--a deity. Br. IV. २०. २५.--sages. M. २००. १०.--आर्षेय pravara (अङ्गिरस्). M. १९६. 8.--a son of Yadu, and father of वृजिनवत्. भा. IX. २३. २० and ३०.--आर्षेय pravara of अङ्गिरस्. M. १९६. २२.(I)--a son of Yadu and father of द्वजिनीवन्. Br. III. ६९. 2; M. ४३. 7; Vi. IV. ११. 5; १२. 1.(II)--a son of कार्तवीर्य Arjun3a and राजऋषि; father of वृजिनीवत्. In this line was born वृष्णि. Br. III. ७०. १४-15; M. ४३. ४६; ४४. १४-5. [page१-484+ ४१](I)--(कृपशारद्वत) the son of सत्यधृति (शरद्वत्-ब्र्। प्।), found in a forest by शन्तनु with the twin कृपी. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २१. ३६; X. ८२. २४; वा. ९९. २०४; १००. ११; १०६. ३४; Vi. IV. १९. ६८.{{/F}} Met by कृतवर्मन्, राम and कृष्ण; {{F}}2:  भा. X. ५२. [५६ (V) 4, १२]; ५७. 2.{{/F}} invited for the राजसूय of युधिष्ठिर. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ७४. १०.{{/F}} Joined Duryodhana's camp and survived the कुरुक्षेत्र war. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ७८. [९५ (V) १६]; ८०. [2].{{/F}} Went to स्यमन्तपाञ्- caka for solar eclipse. {{F}}5:  Ib. ८२. २४.{{/F}} Supplied arms to शतानीक. {{F}}6:  Vi. IV. २१. 4.{{/F}}(II)--a son of शिष्ट and सुच्चाया. M. 4. ३९.(III)--a sage of the eighth epoch of Manu. Vi. III. 2. १७.--a R. from the शुक्तिमत् (शुक्तिमन्त-म्। प्।). Br. II. १६. ३८; M. ११४. ३२.--a deity. Br. IV. २७. ३८.--one of the ten branches of the Sukarma clan of devas. वा. १००. ९२.--(गौतमी) the wife of द्रोण, and daughter of सत्यधृति, found by शन्तनु in the forest. Mother of अश्वत्थाम. भा. I. 7. ४५; १३. 4; IX. २१. ३६; वा. ९९. २०४; Vi. IV. १९. ६८. [page१-433+ २८](I)--a वैकुण्ठ god. Br. II. ३६. ५७. [page१-434+ ३१](II)--a son of कृशा and उशीनर; capital was वृषला. M. ४८. १८ and २१.--the son of इड्विड, and father of दिलीप Khatva1n3ga. Br. III. ६३. १८१.--one of the five queens of उशीनर. Mother of कृश. M. ४८. १६, १८.--a daughter of सुयशा. वा. ६९. १४.--an indefinite Agni in the second Vedi of the north. See सम्राडग्नि। Br. II. १२. २१; वा. २९. १९.(I)--a son of संयम; married two daughters of दक्ष, Arcis and धिषना; and father of Somadatta and the देवप्रहरणस् are created and destroyed in every कल्प and मन्वन्तर। {{F}}3:  M. 6. 6-7.{{/F}} ^1 भा. VI. 6. 2 and २०; IX. 2. ३४-35; M. 5. १४; १४६. १७; वा. ६३. ४२; ८६. २०; Vi. I. १५. १०४; IV. 1. ५५-6. ^2 वा. ६६. ७९.(II)--the son of बर्हणाश्व, and father of सेनाजित्. भा. IX. 6. २५.(III)--a चरकाध्वर्यु; married a daughter of दक्ष. Br. II. ३३. १३; ३७. ४६.(IV)--a son of तामर Manu. Br. II. ३६. ५०.(V)--a son of Sahadeva and highly righteous. Br. III. ६१. १५. [page१-435+ ३२](VI)--a son of सम्हताश्व. Br. III. ६३. ६५; वा. ८८. ६३.(VII)--father of देवप्रहरण. Vi. I. १५. १३७.(VIII)--a son of अमिताश्व and father of Pra- senajit. Vi. IV. 2. ४६-7.--the pursuit of agriculture, a duty of the वैश्य; introduced by पृथु. Br. II. 7. १६२; वा. ७९. ७१; Vi. I. १३. ८४.(I)--twenty-three अवतार् of Hari; according to one version, the twentieth अवतार्। Went to द्वारका, bowed to his parents and entered the palace. {{F}}1:  भा. I. 2. १७; 3. २३; Chaps. १० and ११; M. 7. ६०.{{/F}} His boyhood sports--sucked उलूकिक's life, kicked शकट to pieces and uprooted two Arjuna trees; brought solace to the Gopas of Vraja by expelling the serpent कालिय from the pool near by and protected their cattle from forest fire. In his mouth यशोदा saw the fourteen worlds. Rescued Nanda from fear of वरुण's noose and recovered the Gopas imprisoned by Vyoma Asura. Shielded the Gokulam from rains by holding up Govardhana Mt. as an umbrella; cut off the head of Kubera's attendant who tried to seize the Gopis engaged in रासकृईडा with कृष्ण. Vanquished several daityas and their wicked kings; manifested Himself through सत्यवती and divided the Vedas into many branches; {{F}}2:  भा. II. 7. २६-36.{{/F}} Lord and goal of Andhakas, वृष्णिस्, सात्वतस्, etc. Supreme Brahman. {{F}}3:  भा. II. 4. २०; VII. १५. ७६-79.{{/F}} [page१-436+ ४३] Just on the eve of the अवतार्, ब्रह्मा and other gods pray to him in the womb of देवकी. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. Chaps. 1-3; M. ४६. १४; वा. ९६. १७४.{{/F}} Birth at the time of constellation रोहिणि, first new moon in winter, Abhijit Nak- षत्र, Jayanti night, Vijaya-मुहूर्त and festivities con- nected with it; enjoyed by Vasudeva and देवकी. Their prayer, and कृष्ण recalled their previous births. Taken to यशोदा's delivery room at Nandavraja, stupifying the guardsmen of the jail and crossing यमुना in floods at dead of night; योगमाया born to यशोदा taken back to the jail ward. {{F}}5:  भा. X. Chaps. (whole); Br. III. ७१. १९६-263; ७२. 7-१३; Vi. V. 1. ९८; 3. 1-२९.{{/F}} योगमाया announced her birth to कंसा, {{F}}6:  भा. X. Chap. 4, वा. ९६. १९९. २१५.{{/F}} His जातकर्मा. {{F}}7:  भा. X. 5. 1-१६.{{/F}} Killed पूतना, when at कम्सा's instance, she attempted to poison him by nursing him; यशोदा warded off evil, (रक्षा) to कृष्ण by waving cow's tail round him, by placing cow's dung on the twelve points of his body and by purifying him with cow's urine, with prayers to Hari to protect him from evil spirits. {{F}}8:  Ib. X. 6; Vi. V. 5. १२-31.{{/F}} The first turning in bed was celebrated with festivity. कृष्ण slept under cradle beneath the cart when he kicked the cart which capsized. This roused suspicion of गृहपीड in यशोदा's mind. शान्ति done when cows, food, etc., were given to Brahmanas. Once the demon तृणावर्त created a whirlwind which swept away all व्रज and took up baby कृष्ण high up in the sky to the embarassment of यशोदा and others. At that time कृष्ण took hold of his neck and strangled him. He fell dead. The child कृष्ण opened his mouth and showed his mother the whole universe. {{F}}9:  भा. X. 7; Vi. V. 6. 1-7.{{/F}}(II) (दवैपायन)--व्यास (s.v.) of the current द्वापर, the son of पराशर and सत्यवती (कालि, वा। प्।): a मुनी; {{F}}1:  भा. I. 4. 3 and ३२; IX. २२. २१; XII. 4. ४०; 6. ३५; वा. 1. १०; २३. २२६; ७०. ५४; Vi. III. 3. १९.{{/F}} wife अरणि and son शुक; author of the पुराण शास्त्र; {{F}}2:  Br. III. 8. ९२; IV. 4. ५०.{{/F}} father of धृतराष्ट्र, वीदुर and पाण्डु by the widows of विचित्रवीर्य and their female servant. Another wife पीवरि, by whom he got five sons and one daughter. {{F}}3:  M. ५०. ४६; १८५. ३०; वा. ९९. २४१; Vi. IV. २०. ३८; VI. 2. ३२.{{/F}} Divided the Vedas into four parts: an अवतार् of नारायण; {{F}}4:  Vi. III. 4. 3-१०.{{/F}} the compiler of the महाभारत।(III)--a son of हविर्धान and हविर्धानी. भा. IV. २४. 8; Br. II. ३७. २४; वा. ६३. २३; Vi. I. १४. 2.(IV)--a brother of the Andhra servant Balin (Balipuccaka-वि। प्।) who killed his master काण्व Sus4ar- man and usurped the throne. After him, his brother कृष्ण became king. His son was श्री S4a1ntakarn2a, {{F}}1:  भा. XII. 1. २३; Br. III. ७४. १६२; Vi. IV. २४. ४४-5.{{/F}} who ruled for १८ years. {{F}}2:  M. २७३. 3.{{/F}} [page१-451+ २४](V)--a name of Arjuna. भा. XII, ११. २५.(VI)--a name of ब्रह्मा. Br. II. ३४. 7.(VII)--a pupil of Sumantu of Atharva Veda fame. Br. II. ३५. ५६.(VIII)--a son of Dullola. Br. III. 7. ४४३.(IX)--a son of शुक and पीवरी. Br. III. 8. ९३; १०. ८१; M. १५. १०. वा. ७०. ८५; ७३, ३०, ६२.(X)--an Andhaka. Br. III. ७१. १४३; M. ४४. ८४.(XI)--the asura of second tala, the Sutala. वा. ५०. २१.(XII)--an adopted son of Asamaujasa. वा. ९६. १४१.(XIII)--a name of व्यास. Vi. V. ३८. ५२.(XIV)--(Mt.) a kulaparvata of the केतुमाल; residence of Gandharvas. वा. ३८. ४९; ३९. ५९; ४२. ५२; ४४. 4.(XV)--a Mt. to the west of the शितोद lake. वा. ३६. २८; ३८. ४९. [page१-452+ २५](XVI)--a hell; illegal intercourse, trespass on others’ lands and living on magic are offences leading to this hell. Vi. II. 6. 3 and २५.(I)--a name of द्रौपदी. भा. I. 7. १४.(II)--a name of योगमाया. भा. X. 2. १२. [page१-454+ २८](III)--a name of यमुना. भा. X. ३२. १२.(IV)--a daughter of खश. वा. ६९. १७०.(V)--a R. of the Sahya hills of the दक्षिणापथ. वा. ४५. १०४.--a R. in भारतवर्ष (कृष्णवेणी-ब्र्। प्।). भा. V. १९. १८.--as clothing of तपस्विन्स्; used for ritual purposes; a good article for gift. {{F}}1:  M. ४७. ८९; ८२. 3; २०४. ११; २०६. 1-४१; २४५. ८५; २७९. 5; वा. २५. ३४ and ८१; ३०. २२१; ७४. 4; ९९. ४१०; Vi. I. ११. ३१.{{/F}} Also used by religious students as when केशिध्वज had it when he visited खाण्- डिक्य for instruction. {{F}}2:  Vi. VI. 6. २०. and २२.{{/F}}--a Janapada of the केतुमाल. वा. ४४. १०.of विरूपाक्ष on the 4th inner slope of Meru; the lord of the s. w. direction. वा. ३४. ८७.--a Janapada of the केतुमाल. वा. ४४. ११.--a vrata; a special prayer to शन्कर on the 8th dy of the dark half of every month; other details follow. {{F}}1:  M. ५६. 1-११.{{/F}} the अष्टमि day on which कृष्ण was born. {{F}}2:  Vi. V. 1. ७८.{{/F}} [page१-455+ ३७]--a caste in Tatvalam. Br. II. २०. १३ and २०.--a Janapada of the Bhadra. वा. ४३. २३.--a Mt. in भारतवर्ष. Br. II. १६. २२; वा. ४५. ९१.--of कृष्ण colour; शिव, कालरूप and Aghora. वा. २३. ७४-76.--a measure of weight mentioned in Vedic literature. M. २२७. 9, ८१; ९३. १५२.--as a shield against all dangers; com- bined with वैष्णवतेजस् and शिव-शक्ति। Br. III. ३१. ३७-8.(I)--the day for the पितृस्. वा. ५२. ३७; ५७. 9; ८३. ८०.(II)--a शक्ति। Br. IV. ३२. १५.--the मन्त्र sacred to कृष्ण (s.v.) given by शेष in the midst of seers, consisting of १०८ names --also क्षृणामृतम्। It gave परशुराम the final success. Br. III. ३४. ५० and ५३; ३६, १०, ४३, ५४-59; ३७. १०. [page१-453+ २५](I)--a class of gods; a पराशर clan. Br. III. 8. ९५; १०. १०९; वा. ७०. ८७.(II)--the शूद्र caste of शाल्मलिद्वीप. Vi. II. 4. ३०.--sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ३८.--a R. of the Bhadra country. वा. ४३. २८.--another name for the शूद्र caste. Br. III. १५. ४४.--R. A महानदि from the Sahya hills --sacred to पितृस्; {{F}}1:  Br. II. १२. १४; १६. ३४; M. ५१. १३; वा. १०८. ८१; Vi. II. 3. १२.{{/F}} personified as a wife of हव्यवाहन fire. {{F}}2:  M. २२. ४६; ११४. २९; १६३. ६१; वा. २९. १३.{{/F}}--in honour of विष्णु, leads to his abode; consists of the gift of a gold चक्र। M. १०१. ५८.--a hell--perhaps कालसूत्र. Br. IV. 2. १५०; वा. १०१. १४९.--a daughter of मरीची. Br. II. ११. १२.(I)--the son of Jaya and father of Haryavana. भा. IX. १७. १७.(II)--a son of Vasudeva and रोहिणी. भा. IX. २४. ४६.(III)--a son of Sannati (म्।प्।); a pupil of Hira- ण्यनाभ; in yoga imparted twenty-four सम्हितस् to his disciples; {{F}}1:  भा. XII. 6. ८०; Br. II. ३५. ४९ and ५५; वा. ९९. १८९-90; Vi. III. १६. 7.{{/F}} chief among the सामयस् by arranging साम वेद in २४ parts. {{F}}2:  M. ४९. ७५-6.{{/F}} Father of उग्रायुध. {{F}}3:  Vi. IV. १९. ५०-3.{{/F}} [page१-424+ २१](IV)--an यक्ष and a son of देवयानि. Br. III. 7. १३०.(V)--married श्रुतदेवी; father of सुग्रीव. M. ४६. 5.(VI)--a son of विश्वामित्र. वा. ९१. ९६.(VII)--a son of Kanaka. वा. ९४. 8.(VIII)--a son of हृदिक. वा. ९६. १३९.(IX)--a son of Cyavana. वा. ९९. २१९.(X)--a son of Vijaya; father of Haryadhana. Vi. IV. 9. २६-7.--a son of Dhanaka (Kanaka-ब्र्। प्।, म्। प्।). भा. IX. २३. २३; Br. III. ६९. 8; M. ४३. १३; Vi. IV. ११. १०-11. [page१-429+ २३]--a वानर chieftain, and son of श्वेत. Br. III. 7. १८०.(I)--a son of स्वारोचिष Manu. Br. II. ३६. १९; वा. ६२. १८.(II)--a name of Yama. M. १४८. ३०.--a son of तामस Manu. Br. II. ३६. ५०.--a son (?) of विश्वामित्र. Br. III. ६६. ६८; Vi. IV. 7. ३८.(I)--a son of सम्कृति and a righteous man. Br. III. ६८-11; वा. ९३. ११.(II)--a son of Dhanaka. Vi. IV. ११. १०.--a son of Dharmadhvaja (Janaka-वि। प्।) and father of केशिध्वज. भा. IX. १३. १९-20; Vi. 6. 7-8. [page१-426+ ३९]--the senior queen of Citraketu who got a son through the blessings of अङ्गिरस्. When the child died of poison, she lamented deeply. भा. VI. १४. २८-48.(I)--a son of मदिरा and Vasudeva. भा. IX. २४. ४८; Br. III. ७१. १७२; Vi. IV. १५. २३.(II)--a son of Cyavana and father of Uparicara- Vasu. Vi. IV. १९. ७९-80.--a वानर chief. Br. III. 7. २४१. [page१-425+ २५]--a son of माद्री and वृष्णि. M. ४५. 2.--sets in when the sun, moon, तिष्य and बृहस्- pati (Planet Jupiter) are in the same mansion. Vi. IV. २४. १०२.--a R. of द्राविड from Malaya hills in भा- रतवर्ष. In this Satyavrata offered water-rites to his पितृस्. Visited by बलराम. भा. V. १९. १८; VIII. २४. १२; XI 5. ३९; X. ७९. १६; Br. II. १६. ३६; III. ३५. १७; M. ११४. ३०; वा. ४५. १०५; Vi. II. 3. 13(II)--the eighteenth वेदव्यास. Heard the ब्र्। पुराण from Dhanamjaya and narrated it to तृणम्- jaya; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३५. १२१; IV. 4. ६३.{{/F}} heard the वायु पुराण from Dhanamjaya. {{F}}2:  वा. १०३. ६२.{{/F}}(III)--the son of Dharmi, {{F}}1:  वा. ९९. २८७.{{/F}} and father of रणम्जय. {{F}}2:  Vi. IV. २२. 6-7.{{/F}}(I)--son of Barhi, and father of रणम्जय. भा. IX. १२. १३.--a god of सुतार group. Br. IV. 1. ९०.--the son of महाधृति and father of महा- roma. Vi. IV. 5. २७.--the son of Pratika and father of देवमीढ. Vi. IV. 5. २७.--a son of इडिविड. वा. ८८. १८१.--the sacred spot where नृसिम्ह blessed the Mother Goddess: Here Rudra established his Raudri body in the midst of ‘seven mothers’. Here is अर्धनारीश्वर praying to नृसिम्ह; {{F}}1:  M. १७९. ८७-90.{{/F}} a तीर्थम् sacred to सुङ्हिका। {{F}}2:  Ib. १३. ४५.{{/F}}--the Apsaras who presides over the month of मधु; {{F}}1:  भा. XII. ११-33.{{/F}} coupled with घृताची. {{F}}2:  Br. III. 7. १५; IV. ३३. १९.{{/F}}--a son of Dhanaka (Kanaka-ब्र्। प्।, म्। प्।). भा. IX. २३. २३; Br. III. ६९. 8; M. ४३. १३; Vi. IV. ११. १०.--a मन्त्रकृत्। M. १४५. १०१.(I)--the eldest son of हृदीक. भा. I. १४. २८; IX. २४. २७; Br. III. ७१. १४०; M. ४४. ८१; वा. ९६. १३९; Vi. १४. २४.(II)--a son of Dhanaka. भा. IX. २३. २३.(III)--was stationed to defend the East gate of मथुरा by कृष्ण. Defeated कूपकर्ण, a minis- ter of बाण; was sent to हास्तिनपुर by कृष्ण to find out whether पान्डवस् had captured Drupada. He went and met द्रोण, Vidura and others, when युधिष्ठीर made enquiries of कृष्ण. He returned to द्वारका after taking leave of them and narrated to कृष्ण as he saw and heard; joined with अक्रूर to set up शतधन्वन् to kill सत्राजित् and take the jewel Syamantaka (s.v.) as he did not give his daughter in marriage as promised. Refused to help शत- dhanvan who solicited for it. {{F}}1:  भा. X. ५०. २०[2]; [५१ (V) २५], [३०-31 and ६४]; [५६ (V) 2-१५]; ५७. 3-१८; Vi. IV. १३. ६७-83.{{/F}} Was sent with the sacrificial horse of कृष्ण. {{F}}2:  भा. X. 8-9. २२ [2].{{/F}} After the राजसूय, he was sent to द्वा- रका for its defence. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ७६. 7[5].{{/F}} Went to उपलाव्य to see the पाण्ड- vas, and to स्यमन्तपञ्चक for solar eclipse. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ७८ [९५ (V) 3]; ८२. 7.{{/F}} His son was married to चारुमती, a daughter of रुक्मिनी. {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ६१. २४.{{/F}} Survived कुरुक्षेत्र war; {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ८०. [2].{{/F}} Heard of शतधन्व's death at कृष्ण's hands, and left द्वारका in fear. {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ५७, २९.{{/F}} Got killed in the general यादव contest. {{F}}8:  Vi. V. ३७. ४६.{{/F}} [page१-428+ २९](IV)--a son of Kanaka. Br. III. ६९. 8; M. ४३. १३; वा. ९४. 8.(I)--a son of Dhanaka (Kanaka-ब्र्। प्।, म्।प्। and वा। प्।) of Arjuna (कार्तवीर्य): {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २३. २३-4; Br. III. ६९. 8; M. ४३. १३; वा. ९४. 8; Vi. IV. ११. १०-11.{{/F}} A king of the Hai- haya clan born in the कृतयुग of Vaivasvata epoch, वराह kalpa. His hundred sons died on account of a curse by Cyavana. He prayed to Sun god who taught him a व्रतम्, by observing which he got a long lived child. {{F}}2:  M. ६८. 6-१२.{{/F}}(II)--a Deva-gandharva. वा. ६८. ३८.(also कृत)--commences when the sun, moon and बृहस्पति are in one, and the same राशी। Its cha- racteristic features. {{F}}1:  भा. XII. 2. २४; 3. १८-19, २७.{{/F}} Form of Hari as worshipped in this युग, and worship by contemplation. {{F}}2:  Ib. XI. 5. २१-23; IX. १०. ५२; XII. 3. ५२.{{/F}} Etymologically people in this age are कृतकृत्यस्। Hari took the form of a वृष (bull) for the manifestation of धर्म। Hamsa was the caste name of men. {{F}}3:  Ib. XI. १७. १०-11.{{/F}} Its duration; repeats at the end of Kaliyuga. पितृस् are worshipped. {{F}}4:  Br. II. १६. ६९; २९. २४-31; ३१. १०३. ११; III. १४. ४६-7; ७४. २२५; M. 1. ३४; १४२. १९ and २४; १४४. ९०; १४५. 6-7; १६५. 1.{{/F}} Physical and moral state of world in; duration ४००० divine years; सन्ध्य, and सन्ध्याम्श १०८ years; ध्यान important in; सन्ध्याम्श ४०० = प्रक्रीयापाद; {{F}}5:  वा. 8. ३२-67.{{/F}} after Kali with seven sages; at the beginning man in Kalinga; {{F}}6:  Ib. ५८. १०३, ११०.{{/F}} pertain- ing to the Brahmanas; Vedas honoured. {{F}}7:  Ib. ७८. ३६-7.{{/F}} People with no restrictions lived on roots and fruits enjoying sexual bliss; ज्ञानम्। {{F}}8:  Ib. ९९. ४१३. Br. II. 7. २१, ४५-59.{{/F}} [page१-427+ ४१]--one of the ten sons of रौद्राश्व. वा. ९९. १२४.(I)--a son of बहुलाश्व, and father of the great वशिन्--the last of the Maithilas (of the Janaka line). भा. IX. १३. २६; Br. III. ६४. २३; वा. ८९. २३; Vi. IV. 5. ३१-2.(II)--a son of नहुष. भा. IX. १८. 1; Br. III. ६८. १२; Vi. IV. १०. 1.(III)--a son of Babhru and father of उशिक. भा. IX. २४. 2.(IV)--a son of चाक्षुष Manu. Br. II. ३६. ७९ and १०६.(V)--a वानर chief. Br. III. 7. २४१.(VI)--a Sutapa god. Br. IV. 1. १४.(VII)--a son of Bhautya Manu. Br. IV. 1. ११४.(VIII)--one of the two best सामगस्. वा. ६१. ४८; ६२. ६७. [page१-430+ २३](IX)--a son of मणिवर. वा. ६९. १६१.(X)--a son of वसिष्ठ, one of the seven sages of ऋतु सावर्ण. वा. १००. ९६.(XI)--a son of शतध्वज and father of अञ्जन. Vi. IV. 5. ३१.(I)--(आकूति-ब्र्। प्।) the wife of विश्वकर्मन्. भा. VI. 6. १५. [page१-431+ ३०](II)--the queen of सम्ह्राद and mother of पञ्- cajana. भा. VI. १८. १४.--a son of यवीनर and father of सत्यधृति. भा. IX. २१. २७.(I)--a son of सन्नतीमत्. Learnt योग from हिरण्यनाभ, and sang the six early साम सम्हितस्। Father of नीप. भा. IX. २१. २८-29.(II)--a son of Cyavana and father of Vasu Upa- ricara. भा. IX. २२. 5.--a son of महाधृति and father of महारोमन्. भा. IX. १३. १७.--(कृतरथ-ब्र्। प्।) the son of प्रतीपक and father of देवमीढ. भा. IX. १३. १६.--see धिष्णि। Br. II. १२. १७.--The Pleidas; a lunar mansion; personified. Six in number, nursed कुमार: wives of Soma, childless due to दक्ष's curse. {{F}}1:  भा. IV. 7. ६४; VI. 6. १४ and २३; Br. IV. ३०. १००; M. 5. २७; ५४. ११; ५५. १२; १५८. ४१; वा. ७२. ४३; Vi. I. १५. ११५; II. 8. ७६.{{/F}} An important day for the श्राड्ध offerings, sacred to moon. {{F}}2:  Br. II. २१. ७७ and १४५; २४. १३०; III. १०. ४४; १८. 2.{{/F}} A constellation containing six stars. {{F}}3:  वा. ६६. ४८. ८२. 2.{{/F}}--a पर्व; when the sun goes to the first अम्श, the moon is in the fourth अम्श of विशाख. वा. २३. १०७; ५०. ९६; ५३. १०५.--a name of शिव. सती who was created by ब्रह्मा was given to him and a number of sons were born who were of all shapes and crude forms and called generally Rudras; they were partakers of the offerings in शतरुद्र। On ब्रह्मा's request he did not procreate but became स्थाणु and महादेव। Br. II. 9. ६९; III. २५. १४: ७२. १८४; M. १८१. १४ ch. वा. २१. ५१. [page१-432+ ३२]--a daughter of शुक and पीवरी, and mother of Brahmadatta; married the पाञ्चाल king अणुह; known also as Gau. भा. IX. २१. २५; M. १५. 8-9; ४९. ५७.--a son of पौरुषेय Ra1ks2asa. Br. III. 7. ९३.--Killed Dundhu, the son of अरूरु, on the advice of Uttanka. वा. ६८. ३१.(I)--the son of विश्रवस् (वैश्रावण) and इडविडा. His father initiated him into a great विद्या। Father of three sons--विशाल and others. Lord of यक्षस्, and brother of शिव; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. 2. ३२-33; IV. 1. ३७; ११. ३३. वा. ४०. 8; ४७. 1; ७०. ३८. ९७. 2.{{/F}} was pleased with Dhruva and blessed him though he killed his followers. {{F}}2:  भा. IV. १२. 1-9.{{/F}} Presented a golden throne to पृथु. {{F}}3:  Ib. १५. १४.{{/F}} With his नरवाहन attacked कृष्ण taking पारिजात, but defeated by सत्यभामा, retreated in fear. Presented to कृष्ण eight treasures and his new city. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. [६५ (V) ४५], [६६ (V) 4-२१]; ५०. ५६.{{/F}} Attended by Guhyakas, he is compared to युधिष्ठिर attended by पाण्डवस्, कृष्ण and sages. {{F}}5:  Ib. I. 9. 3.{{/F}} Lord of Alaka and son of Pulastya and resident of Kai- लास; {{F