hool days, and their loyalty to Guru सान्दीपनि, and how he recipro- cated it. Once when they went out and were caught in storm and rains, the Guru came in search of them with great anxiety. Kucaila gave कृष्ण the पृथुकतण्डुल which कृष्ण shared with रुक्मिनी and heartily ate of it. After spending a jolly night, the ब्राह्मण took leave of his friend and went home, ruminating on the way why कृष्ण did not offer any riches to him. When he neared his place, he found tall mansions lavishly built and furnished. His wife extended him welcome with servants. He knew it was all the work of his friend कृष्ण. Spent a righteous life ever meditating on Hari's lotus feet. भा. X. ८०. 6-४५; ८१ (whole).--a Janapada of the केतुमाल. वा. ४४. ११.--a son of Vasu. Vi. IV. १९. ८१.--a R. sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ४६.--a chief of the क्रोधवश group of serpents (नागस्). भा. V. २४. २९.--a sacred place in Meru where व्यास per- formed austerities. वा. १०४. ६१.--people of the kingdom watered by the Sindhu. Br. II. १८. ४७. [page१-419+ २७](VIII)--the kingdom of. M. १२१. ४६.(I)--a daughter of अङ्गिरस् and श्रद्धा. (स्मृति- वि। प्।). Wife of धात्री and mother of साय. भा. IV. 1. ३४; VI. १८. 3; Br. II. ११. १८; वा. २८. १५; ५०. २०१; ५५. ४२; ५६. 9, ४५ and ५३; Vi. I. १०. 7.(II)--one of the nine devis serving Soma. Br. III. ६५. २६; वा. ९०. २५.(III)--a शक्ति। Br. IV. ३२. १३.(IV)--a daughter of Maya; wife of हविष्मन्त, left him for Soma. M. 6. २१; २३. २५.(V)--the last phase of the new moon. It is the digit that disappears, and not the moon in कुहू, as seen from राम's words to रुक्मिणी fit for giving gifts; {{F}}1:  भा. X. ५४. ४७; Br. II. २६. ४४; २८. ११ and ५९; M. १३३. ३६; १४१. ४९, ५१; Vi. II. 8. ८०.{{/F}} served by Aila. एत्य्। {{F}}2:  M. १४१. 9 and ४३, ४९, ५१; वा. ५६. ५३.{{/F}}(VI)--a R. from the Himalayas; of the भारत- वर्ष. Br. II. १६. २५; M. ११४. २१; वा. ४५. ९५. [page१-420+ २५](VII)--a R. of शाल्मलिद्वीप. भा. V. २०. १०.--the hour in which the moon is not visible. In the same way infancy and boyhood, the eleve