ा country. वा. ४४. २२.--one of the Marut गणस्. वा. ६७. १२९.--next to मुक्ताशाला of ललिता--Palmyra juice is used here: nearby in a grove lives the creator: Fourteen विद्यस्, उपविद्यस् ६४ कलस् all reside here: a little away is विष्णुलोक with a १००० pillars: beyond that is शिव- loka. Br. IV. ३४. ५४. [page२-691+ २६]--a ब्रह्मवादिन्. Br. II. ३३. १९.--a Goddess enshrined at केदार. M. १३. ३०.--a भार्गव. M. १९५. ३३.--highways and byways; दिशामार्ग, ग्राम- मार्ग, राजपथ, साखरथ्यस्, गृहरथ्यस्, uparathyas, घण्टापथ, ग्रहान्तरम्, वृत्तिमार्ग and प्राग्वम्श with their respective measurements. Avaskaram and परीवाहम् are other dispositions of open spaces. {{F}}1:  वा. 7. ११८-22.{{/F}} 1. dik--२० dhanus in breadth. 2. ग्राम 20 dhanus in breadth. 3. सीम 10 dhanus in breadth. 4. राजपथ 10 dhanus in breadth. 5. शाखारत्यस् or streets 4 dhanus. 6. Rathyoparathyas 3 dhanus. 7. उपारथ्य rathas 2 dhanus. [page२-696+ २७] 8. जन्घापथ 4 feet 9. गृहान्तरम् (lanes) 3 feet. १०. धृतिमार्ग 6 feet and more. ११. अवस्कारपरीवार 1 ft. all round. {{F}}2:  Br. II. 7. ११२-16.{{/F}}--month of, good for the gift of the अग्नि पुराण; {{F}}1:  M. ५३. २९.{{/F}} best for military expedition. {{F}}2:  Ib. ५६. 2; ६०. ३५; २४०. 5.{{/F}}--a भार्गव gotraka1ra. M. १९५. २०.--a mind-born mother. M. १७९. १५.(I)--a son of Sunda and ताडक; set up by रावण to take the form of a golden deer in order to secure सीता: killed by राम. भा. IX. १०. 5, १०; Br. III. 5. ३५-6; वा. ६२. ७२; Vi. IV. 4. ८९.(II)--the author of a पुराण: married पुलोमा and कालका, daughters of वैश्वानर: These had १००० sons besides the fourteen who lived in हिरण्यपुर. Br. II. ३८. 5; III. 6. २६; 7. ४६४; ४७. ६०.(III)--(मारीचकश्यप): a son of अन्तर्धान and grandson of पृथु; {{F}}1:  M. 4. ४५.{{/F}} his wife Vasu abandoned him for Soma; {{F}}2:  Ib. २३. २५.{{/F}} his sons are said to reside in the Somapatha worlds of the पितृस्. {{F}}3:  Ib. १४. 1.{{/F}}(I)--a देवगण. Br. III. 1. ५०.(II)--कश्यप gotraka1ras. M. १९९. 9. [page२-692+ ३१]--the world created with moveables and imm