 १७९. २६.(II)--an Apsarasa. वा. ६९. 6.(I)--the सभा of ब्रह्मा on the first inner- slope of Meru in which reside ईशान and Indra besides sages and seers. वा. ३४. ७२-7.(II)--a daughter of Tumburu. वा. ६९. ४९.--a son of वीरव्रत and भोजा; his wife was सत्या, and son Bhauvana. भा. V. १५. १५.--also मन्त्रिणी, {{F}}1:  Br. IV. १७. २२, २७; २७, ५८; १९. ६१.{{/F}} and मन्त्रिणीश्यामा; war master of ललिता; residence at कदम्बवनवाटिका; {{F}}2:  Ib. IV. ३१. ८२, ८९.{{/F}} helped कुमारी in vanquishing भण्ड's sons; rode on Kiri- cakra; consulted दण्डनाथा; {{F}}3:  Ib. IV. २६. 2, ८३, ११३; २७. ५८.{{/F}} invoked मदीरासिन्धु (s.v.). {{F}}4:  Ib. IV. २८. १४, ४८, ९२, १०३.{{/F}}--see मन्त्रनाथा. Br. IV. १७. ३१, ३३, ४०.--a वर्ण s4akti. Br. IV. ४४. ५८.--a branch of Vedic literature; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३१. १२; ३३. ५४; वा. ५९. १३८.{{/F}} ety. of. {{F}}2:  Ib. ५०. १४१; ६१. १०२.{{/F}} [page२-627+ ३८]--Indra of the चाक्षुष epoch. भा. VIII. 5. 8.(I)--(also मन्त्रस्थानम्, Council Cham- ber) consultation to be held with many and individually and with people in whom the king has confidence; at least one expert must be consulted; generally with people learned in the three Vedas, elders who have the ability to correct the erring king; {{F}}1:  M. २१५. ४८-52.{{/F}} kingdom rests on mantra; {{F}}2:  Ib. २२०. ३३.{{/F}} king not to decide alone nor to consult too many; {{F}}3:  Ib. २२०. ३७.{{/F}} भण्ड's War Council. {{F}}4:  Br. IV. २१. २१; २५. 3{{/F}}(II)--a portion of the पूर्व samhita1. वा. ६१. ६५.--a R. in कुशद्वीप. भा. V. २०. १५.--a branch of the Vedic literature. वा. ५८. १४.--take the food offered in sacrifices to the पितृस् as the calf finds out its mother among the lost cows; {{F}}1:  Br. II. २८. ९१; वा. ५९. ६१.{{/F}} came out of discontent, fear, difficulties, happiness and misery of ऋषिस्; later put into form and order by sages; differences in मन्त्रस् as many as twenty-four; {{F}}2:  Br. II. ३२. ६८; ३३. ४२; वा. ५९. ३५-61; M. १४५. ६२-3.{{/F}} the two major divisions --ग्राम्यम् and आरण्यकम्; {{F}}3: 