या and विवस्वान्. Father of Nirmoka and other sons. In this epoch Sutapas, Virajas अमिताभस्, Mukhyas were the gods. Bali was Indra. गालव, कृप, राम and others were the sages. Hari manifested himself as सार्वभौम। {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 6. ४१; VIII. १३. ११-7; २२. ३१; Vi. III. 2. 4; १३-19.{{/F}} Ini- tiated in the mystery of Lord's glories by नारद, worship- ping नरनारायण; {{F}}2:  भा. V. १९. १०.{{/F}} originally श्रुतश्रवस्; performs aus- terities on the slopes of Meru even to-day. {{F}}3:  Br. IV. 1. २८; III. ५९. ४९ and ८०.{{/F}}(XII) (स्वायम्भुव)--the first son of ब्रह्मा and the first king (सम्राट्) also विराट्. Ruled the earth, girt by seven seas, occupying ब्रह्मावर्त with बर्हिष्मती as capital. A विप्रराजऋषि. Learnt the Veda from his father, who asked him to rule according to Dharma. Wife शत- रूपा; sons Priyavrata and उत्तानपाद besides eight more through अनन्ता and a daughter, देवहूती. Other daughters were आकूति and प्रसूति {{F}}1:  भा. VIII. 1. 1, 5 and 7, XI. १४. 4; III. २०. 1 and १०; २१. 1-3, २५-26; २२. २६-9; VI. 1. 1; 8. 6; Br. II. १३. १०५; M. 3. ४४-5; 4. ३४; १४५, ९०; वा. 3. 2, ३६; २३. ४७; ५९. ५६-7; Vi. I. 7. १४-19; III. 1. 6.{{/F}} who married दक्ष and Ruci res- pectively. Met Kardama on the सरस्वती, spoke of inter- dependence of the क्षत्रिय and the Brahmana, and offered his daughter देवहूती in marriage to that sage. {{F}}2:  भा. III. २१. ४५; २२. 3-१४.{{/F}} Another daughter धन्या became the wife of Dhruva. Seeing Dhruva fighting with the यक्षस् in utter wrath, Manu asked him to cease slaughtering the innocents and to ask pardon of Kubera, their chief. {{F}}3:  Ib. IV. ११. 6-३४; M. 4. ३८.{{/F}} Appointed Priyavrata in charge of the kingdom and retired to तपस्। Spent ७१ yugas meditating on विष्णु, and gave Him the name, Hari. Did not take objection to Hara's violation of धर्म, though he was one of the twelve who knew the धर्म ordained by Hari. {{F}}4:  भा. V. 1. २१-2; XI. 2. १५; III. २२. ३१-6; II. 7. 2; VI. १७. १२; 3. २०; IV. २१. २८.{{/F}} Served as calf for पृथु to milk the earth. {{F}}5:  Ib. IV. १८. १२; २९. ४२.{{/F}} Formed one half of the Creator [page२-620+ ३८] and the other was शतरूपा. Asked ब्रह्मा for the earth being lifted out of the waters to form an abode for him and his subjects, when a वराह issued from ब्रह्मा's nostrils to do the work. {{F}}6:  Ib. III. १२. ५३-4; १३. 3-१८.{{/F}} Renouncing the world, Manu stood on one leg medi- tating on the glory of Hari on the bank of the सुनन्दा for a hundred years; when the Asuras tried to attack and devour him, Hari in the form of यज्ञ slew them. {{F}}7:  भा. VIII. 1. 7-१०.{{/F}} The first to give out स्मार्त धर्म, वर्णाश्रम धर्म and the first to practice शिष्टाचार; requested by Brahma to protect the वेदस् and consequently the यज्ञस्। Divided the Vedas into four sections. {{F}}8:  Br. II. २९. ४६, ६१-4; ३०. ३४; ३२. ३५-8, ९६; ३४. 2-8; ३५. १७५; ३६. 3; ३७. १४; IV. 1. ३२ and १०९; M. १४२. ४२.{{/F}} An आदिपुरुष. From him were born वैराजस्. {{F}}9:  Ib. 3. ४५-6; १७१. २७; १९२. १०; २२७. ३२.{{/F}}(XIII)--(स्वारोचिष)--the second Manu, and son of Agni. Father of Dyumat and others. In this epoch Rocana was Indra, तुषित and others were gods, ऊर्ज्जस्तम्ब and six others were the seven sages. भा. VIII. 1. १९-20; Br. II. ३६. 3, २३; ३७. १५.(XIV)--(वैवस्वत)--the seventh Manu, also known as ‘श्राद्धदेव’. {{F}}1:  भा. VIII. १३. 1-9; Br. II. ३६. 4, ८१; III. ५९. २२ and ३८; ६३. २१५; IV. 1. 6-२८; वा. ८४. २२; Vi. IV. 1. 6-7.{{/F}} Son of सम्ज्ञा and Vivasvat (सुरेणु and विवस्वान् वा। प्।): wife श्रद्धा: father of ten sons of whom इक्ष्वाकु was the eldest; {{F}}2:  Br. II. ३८. 1.{{/F}} in this epoch Puran- dara was Indra: कश्यप, Atri and others were sages: आदित्- yas and Vasus were gods: वामन was the manifestation of Hari; {{F}}3:  भा. VIII. १३. 1-9.{{/F}} a क्षत्रिय मन्त्रवादिन्: His sacrifice was disturbed by sons of वरूत्रि who were burnt by Indra in the वेदि: [page२-621+ ४१] a प्रजापति: king and दण्डधर. {{F}}4:  Br. II. ३२. १२०; ३८. २६ and ३२; III. 1. 3 and 6; 8. २१; १०. ९८; ६०. 7; M. १४५. ११५; २४८. १५.{{/F}} Saved by the Matsya Hari during the deluge. After anointing his son on the throne, M. performed penance on the Malaya Mt. for a lac of years when ब्रह्मा blessed him as protector of the universe after the प्रलय। Once in making a water oblation to his manes, a fish fell into his hand which he put into his water vessel. Finding its rapid growth he placed it in a well, tank, Ganges and the sea respectively. From its abnormal growth he suspected it to be an asura or वासुदेव; on questioning it he found it to be the Lord and was asked to use it (the fish) as the life boat when the whole world went down in the deluge, saving at the same time some lives; {{F}}5:  Ib. 1. ११ to the end; 2. १६; 9. 1; १६. 1; ५२. 3.{{/F}} performed तपस् on the यमुना for one hundred years with a view to get progeny; {{F}}6:  भा. I. 3. १५; VIII. २४. ५०; IX. 1. 3-१२; 2. 1; 6. 4.{{/F}} see Satyavrata; celebrated an अश्वमेध in honour of Mitra and वरुण; out came इला who went to them; {{F}}7:  Br. III. ६०. 1-१०.{{/F}} the Lord of men, and seven worlds with towns; {{F}}8:  वा. ७०. १८.{{/F}} divided the Vedas into four for the pro- gress of the world; {{F}}9:  Ib. ६०. 8.{{/F}} in order to get sons he performed the मित्रावरुण ritual; owing to the होत'स् carelessness a daughter इला came out; she became again a male Sudyumna by name; by an imprecation of शिव he again became a woman near Budha's hermitage. Budha got by her a son by name पुरूरवस्; {{F}}१०:  Vi. IV. 1. 8-१२.{{/F}} interpretation of शब्दब्रह्म by. {{F}}११:  Ib. VI. 5. ६४.{{/F}}(XV) (दक्ष सावर्णी)--the ninth Manu. Born of वरुण; father of भूतकेतु and other sons. पारस् and others were gods of his epoch, and Adbhuta was Indra; Dyu- timat and others were sages. During this period Hari mani- fested himself as ऋषभ. भा. VIII. १३. १८-20. [page२-622+ ३५](XVI) (रुद्रसावर्णि)--the twelfth Manu; father of देववान् and other sons. ऋतधामन् was Indra. हारित and others were gods. तपोमूर्ति and others were sages. स्वधाम was Hari manifesting in this epoch; {{F}}1:  भा. VIII. १३. २७-29.{{/F}} the fourth सावर्ण Manu in the १२थ् पर्याय। {{F}}2:  Br. IV. 1. ८२-93.{{/F}}(XVII) सावर्ण(इ)--the second Manu in the epoch of the Vaivasvata Manvantara; son of सावर्ण; {{F}}1:  Br. IV. 1. ५१-5, ७३-81.{{/F}} in his age Bali was to reign over the whole world. {{F}}2:  Ib. II. ३६. 4; III. ७३. ५२.{{/F}}(XVIII) (रौच्य)--a सावर्ण Manu of the XIII पर्याय; three groups of gods, all addicted to Soma and ghee through यज्ञस्। Br. IV. 1. ९५-116.(XIX)--(चाक्षुषान्तरम्)--भृगु and other sages lived in this epoch. {{F}}1:  M. 2. १४; 6. 3; 8. १२.{{/F}} There were five classes of devas, Lekha, ऋभव, ऋभाद्य, वारिमूल, and Divaukasa; चाक्- षुष had ten sons commencing with Ruru; {{F}}2:  Ib. 9. २२, २५.{{/F}} King पुरूरवस् flourished in the same line in this epoch. {{F}}3:  Ib. ११५. 7-8.{{/F}}(XX) (औत्तम)--the third Manu; {{F}}1:  M. 3. ४७.{{/F}} father of ten sons; the devas of the epoch are भावनस् and there were also seven sages, कौकुरुण्डि, etc., all engaged in yoga. {{F}}2:  Ib. 9. ११.{{/F}}(XXI) (चाक्षुष) (VI)--the son of चक्षु and वीरिणी; married a royal princess नड्वला and had ten sons. M. 4. ४०; Vi. I. १३. 4.(XXII)--the son of हर्यश्व and father of Pra- tika. Vi. IV. 5. २७. [page२-623+ २९]--a son of द्युतिमान् after whose name is a Janapada. वा. ३३. २१.--a विश्वेदेव. M. २०३. १३.--the whole period of the fourteen Manus covering a कल्प of one thousand yugas--the fourteen man- vantaras. भा. VIII. १३. ३६; १४. ११.--worshipped with Devas for kingdom; their duties in different epochs described. {{F}}1:  भा. II. 3. 9; VIII. १४. 2-१०{{/F}} Fourteen in number; went to Maharloka when their duties were over; {{F}}2:  Br. IV. 2. 2 nad 5.{{/F}} in order: स्वायम्भुव, स्वारोचिष, Auttama, तामस, Raivata, चाक्- षुष; these six are past ones; the future are eight; सावर्ण, पञ्चरौच्यस्, Bhautya and Vaivasvata. {{F}}3:  वा. ६२. 3-4.{{/F}}--are Laukikas (s.v.). Br. II. २८. ७१, ७८, ९५.--created out of the रजस् element; {{F}}1:  Vi. I. 5. २३, ३७-8; 6. 1.{{/F}} four वर्णस् of. {{F}}2:  Ib. I. 6. 5.{{/F}}--a तीर्थ visited by बलराम. भा. X. ७९. २१.(मनुत्त or मरुत्त)--a king equal to a cakravartin, went to heaven with Samvarta, a sage; father of नरिष्यन्त. वा. ८६. 9.--an अवतार् of Hari. भा. II. 7. २०. [page२-624+ २३]--a daughter of Tumburu. Br. III. 7. १३.--a son of Madhu. वा. ९५. ४५.--the Gods of three worlds, sages, पितृस्, and people help him; but finding the diminished powers, go to Maharloka. वा. ६१. १४९-51. [page२-634+ ३७]--periods of Manus; seven in number and seven to come, of स्वायम्भुव, स्वारोचिष, Auttama, तामस, Raivata, चाक्षुष, सावर्णि (after Vaivasvata in म्। प्।), रौच्य (ब्र्। प्।); Vaivasvata present according to the म्। प्।) Ruci, Bhautya, मेरुसावर्णि, Rta, ऋतधामान् and विष्वक्सेन; the last seven are future Manus; {{F}}1:  Br. II. 6. 6, २०; ३६. 1-4; M. 2. २२; 9. 2-३६; वा. २१. ११, १४, १९, ३८, ४४; ५७. ३३-6; Vi. I. 3. १८.{{/F}} one of the five characteristics of the पुराण; {{F}}2:  M. ५३. ६५; Br. I. 1. ३७; वा. 4. १०.{{/F}} calculation of the duration of the epochs of Manus; {{F}}3:  M. १४२. ३०.{{/F}} constitutes ७१ yugas at the end of which comes क्षय {{F}}4:  वा. १०. १२; ३२. ४१.{{/F}} according to मानुष and Divyavat- sara. {{F}}5:  Ib. ६१. १३८-144; १५०. १७६.{{/F}}(I)--a name of a Rudra. भा. III. १२. १२.(II)--the son of Vitatha (भरद्वाज); father of बृहद्क्षत्र and four other sons. भा. IX. २१. 1; Vi. IV. १९. २०, २१.--the son of जाठराग्नि; see विद्वानग्नि. Br. II. १२. ३४; वा. २९. ३२.--war musical instruments. M. १४०. ४३; वा. ५४. ३७. [page२-643+ २७]--a प्रजापति; husband of अदिती and father of the आदित्यस्. वा. ३०. ७२; ५०. १६८; ५२. ९५; ६७. ४३; १००. २०; १०१. ३५ and ४९.--a son of Bhavya of शकद्वीप. Vi. II. 4. ६०.(I)--a mind-born son of ब्रह्मा born with नारद at the beginning of creation; {{F}}1:  भा. I. 6. ३१; III. १२. २२; IX. 1. १०; Br. II. ३२. ९६; III. 1. २१, ४३-4; M. 3. 6; 4. २६; १९५. 9.{{/F}} married कला a daughter of Kardama; {{F}}2:  भा. III. २४. २२; IV. 1. १३.{{/F}} father of कश्यप; {{F}}3:  Ib. III. १४. 7; २०. १०.{{/F}} came with ब्रह्मा to see Kapila born to Kardama; {{F}}4:  Ib. III. २४. 9.{{/F}} was present in दक्ष's यज्ञ; {{F}}5:  Ib. IV. 7. ४३; २९. ४३.{{/F}} directed the अश्वमेध of Indra; {{F}}6:  Ib. VI. १३. २१.{{/F}} came to see the Trivikrama अवतार् of the Lord; {{F}}7:  Ib. VIII. २१. 1.{{/F}} did not comprehend Hari's माय। {{F}}8:  Ib. IX. 4. ५८.{{/F}} The chief sage of Vena's reign responsible for punishing him. A sage in दारुवन; {{F}}9:  Br. II. २१. ११५; २७. १०४; ३६. १३३; III. १०. ५२; M. १४५. ९०; १५४. ३५२; १७१. २७.{{/F}} one of the seven sages of स्वायम्भुव epoch: instructed by ब्रह्मा on the eighteen पुराणस्; praised शिव, out to destroy Tripuram; {{F}}१०:  Ib. 9. 4; ५३. १२; १०२. १९; १२७. २४; १३३. ६७.{{/F}} had a daughter सुरूपा, whom Angiras got married. {{F}}११:  Ib. १९६. 1; २४५. ८६; २५०. 4.{{/F}} [page२-637+ ३१](II)--a son of सम्राट् and उत्कला. Father of बिन्दुमती. भा. V. १५. १५.(III)--His wife was ऊर्णा; had six sons in the first antara; then Gods laughed at ब्रह्मा seeking connec- tion with his daughter; these were born of हिरण्यकशिपु as Asuras, but were taken away by योगमाया; then they were born of देवकी and killed by Kamsa. भा. X. ८५. ४७-49.(IV)--created from the eyes; one of the Nine ब्राह्मणस् alluded to in the पुराणस्। Br. I. 5; II. 9. १८ and २२; ११. १०; १३. ५४.(V)--a sage of the स्वायम्भुव epoch; {{F}}1:  वा. 3. 2; ३१. १६; ६२. ११३; ६५. ४४.{{/F}} son-in- law of दक्ष; {{F}}2:  Ib. ३०. ४८.{{/F}} married सम्भूती; {{F}}3:  Br. II. 9. ५५; वा. २८. 8; Vi. I. १०. 6; ११. ४३.{{/F}} advised Dhruva to pray to विष्णु. {{F}}4:  Ib. I. १२. 6.{{/F}}(VI)--a son of ब्रह्मा married धर्मव्रता, the daughter of Dharma whom he cursed for dereliction of duty, to become a stone; got one hundred sons through her; in turn cursed by her for the unjust curse. वा. १०७. 7, २६; ११२. ३६.(VII)--a mind-born son of ब्रह्मा; married सन्नती. Vi. I. 7. 5, 7, ३७.(I)--the gods of the ninth Manvantara; a गण of १२ gods. भा. VIII. १३. १९; Br. IV. 1. ५५, ५८-9; Vi. III. 2. २१. [page२-638+ २३](II)--the w