 the Asuras of the other world, and a past master in the practice of माया। Served as calf for the मायिन्स् to derive माया from Earth. Built aerial cities, three in number, of gold, silver and iron for the pro- tection of the Asuras, and constructed the divine सभा। The cities were well equipped and furnished, with paintings and drawings of couples of नागस् and Asuras, pigeons, parrots and शारिकस्, interspersed by charming gardens of flowers and fruits with lakes of crystal waters. Being the Lord of Tripura which he built, he took part with Bali in the देवासुर war, and also fought with विश्वकर्- man; {{F}}1:  भा. I. १५. 8; II. 7. ३७; IV. १८. २०; V. २४. 9-१०; VII. १०. २२ and २९, ५१-60.{{/F}} son of विश्वकर्मन्; सुरेणु was his sister; {{F}}2:  Br. III. ५९. २१; IV. १२. 3; २०. ४६; ३१. 7; वा. ८४. २०-1.{{/F}} had an evil dream that a naked lady and a man of three eye burning the city: reported it to the सभा: was explained by नारद: precautions for defence: army stationed at respec- tive places of vantage; विद्युन्मालि was over-powered; Maya constructed a tank of medicinal waters to make the dead live and restored विद्युन्मालि. Knowing this immortalising fluid, ब्रह्मा and Hari drank the whole of it; fierce war; शिव directed his arrows against the three cities and killed the Asuras by destroying their cities. Maya's address to the Asuras for a bold stand. विद्युन्मालि and तारक were killed. Maya was let off and asked to live in a special house [page२-635+ ३२] after burning the city. In the तारकामय it is said he rode on a golden chariot with arms and weapons. {{F}}3:  M. ch. १२९; १३१. २५-30; १३४. 9-३०; chh. १३५-140. १७३. 2-१३; १७७. 3-6.{{/F}}(II)--the Asura architect and a contemporary of कृष्ण. His son enslaved the gopas and hid them in a cave. कृष्ण recovered them; {{F}}1:  भा. II. 7. ३१.{{/F}} freed from the forest fire of काण्- डव by Arjuna, he erected a सभा for the use of the पाण्- डवस्. Once Duryodhana (s.v.) mistook a floor of this for a sheet of water and had a nasty fall; {{F}}2:  Ib. X. ५५. २१; ७१. ४५; ५८. २७; ७५. ३४ and ३७.{{/F}} Supplied a magic car to शाल्व under orders of शिव. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ७६. 7; ७७. २८.{{/F}}(III)--an Asura; Lord of तलातल region, won the grace of शिव and attained मोक्ष by सत्सन्ग। A follower of वृत्र in his battle with Indra; {{F}}1:  भा. V. २४. २८; XI. १२. 5; VI. १०. ३१.{{/F}} wife रम्भा and father of six sons; {{F}}2:  Br. III. 6. 5 and २८; वा. ६८. २८-9.{{/F}} had daughters like उपदानवी. {{F}}3:  M. 6. २१.{{/F}}(IV)--father of माया. Br. II. 9. ६४.(V)--an author on architecture. M. २५२. 2.--a शक्ति created from the heart of नृसिम्ह. M. १७९. ६४.--of the Agastya family. M. २०२. 2.(I)--the riding animal of कार्त्तिकेय; several on the हिमालयस्; {{F}}1:  Br. II. २५. १६, २७; III. १०. ४७. M. १६०. २१. वा. ३६. 2; ५४. १९.{{/F}} a banner of Skanda presented to वायु. {{F}}2:  Ib. ७२. ४६.{{/F}} [page२-636+ ३९](II)--a peak on the वराह hill. वा. ४२. ७०.--बाण with the peacock standard; the breaking of the flag was a sign of impending war. Vi. V. ३३. 3.--a son of पौरुषेय, a राक्सस. Br. III. 7. ९४.--a son of पुरीमन्, and father of शिवस्- kandha. भा. XII. 1. २७.(I)--a daughter of दक्ष and a wife of Dharma: Mother of स्मृति [श्रुत वा। and वि। प्।]. भा. IV. 1. ५०-52; Br. II. 9. ४९, ५९; वा. १०. २५. ३४; ५५. ४३; Vi. I. 7. २३. २९.(II)--a कला of ब्रह्मा. Br. II. २६. ४५; IV. ३५. ९४.(III)--a शक्ति; {{F}}1:  Br. IV. ४४. ७२.{{/F}} the goddess enshrined at काश्मीरमण्डल. {{F}}2:  M. १३. ४७; २४६. ६२.{{/F}}(II)--a son of Priyavrata, and appointed lord of the शाकद्वीप (प्लक्षद्वीप-वि। प्।). He divided it among his seven sons and retired to a hermitage. भा. V. 1. २५ and ३३; २०. २५; Vi. II. 1. 7, १२.(III)--a son of कण्व. From him came प्रस्कण्व and other Brahmanas; ancestor of the काण्वायन द्विजस्। भा. IX. २०. 7; M. ४९. ४७; Vi. IV. १९. 6-7, ३१-2. [page२-734+ २९](IV)--one of the ten sons of स्वायम्भुव Manu; attained heaven by तपस्; {{F}}1:  Br. II. १३. १०४; M. 9. 5; १४३. ३८; वा. ३१. १७.{{/F}} consecrated for प्लक्ष- द्वीप; {{F}}2:  Ib. ३३. 