ack to heaven; {{F}}२३:  Ib. I. 9. 6.{{/F}} came to see परीक्षित् practising प्रायोपवेश; {{F}}२४:  Ib. I. १३. ३७-59.{{/F}} welcomed by कृष्ण, युधिष्ठिर and others, नारद, drew the attention of कृष्ण to the necessity of vanquishing शाल्व who was out to cut the root of the यादवस्; knew of कृष्ण's glory and greatness and told लक्ष्मणा of it; praised Vasudeva for his question on Karma; left for Sya- मन्तपञ्चक; {{F}}२५:  Ib. I. १९. १०.{{/F}} went with कृष्ण to मिथिला, heard स्रुतिगीता from नारायण at नारायणाश्रम; visited श्वेतद्वीप during Brahmasatra; called upon व्यास and communicated to him what he heard from नारायण; advised by वृत्र to worship शिव as the most easily pleased among the Gods; {{F}}२६:  Ib. X. ७६. 2 [2-१०]; 3-7 [1-4]; ८३. १७; ८४. 3, ३०-33, ५७.{{/F}} left with other sages for पिण्डारक; visited द्वारका and met Vasudeva; questioned by him on भागवत धर्म, he related the conversation that took place between Nimi, the Videha King, and the nine sages, the sons of ऋषभ; {{F}}२७:  Ib. X. ८६. १८; ८७. 4-5, १०, ४७-8; ८८. १४-16.{{/F}} views of, on thirty characteristics of धर्म, on the वर्णस् and women; on a ब्रह्मचारि, वानप्रस्थ, a Yati, and a गृहस्थ; {{F}}२८:  Ib. XI. 1. १२; chh. 2-5 (whole).{{/F}} enquired of ब्रह्मा the knowledge lead- ing to the realisation of आत्मन्; a महाभागवत who attained Hari through devotion. {{F}}२९:  Ib. VII. chh. ११-14 (whole).{{/F}} Sang a गाथ in honour of कार्तवीर्य Arjuna: compiled the नारदीय धर्म; told the रामायण to वाल्मीकि; {{F}}३०:  Ib. II. 4. २५; 5. 1-8; VII. 1. ३०; XI. २७. 2.{{/F}} [page२-229+ २४] learnt the details of the vow नक्षत्रपुरुष from महा- deva and of माहेश्वरव्रतम् from नन्दिकेश; on the lat- ter's advice took a bath at प्रयागा. {{F}}३१:  M. ४३. २३; ४७. ३०; ५३. २३ and ७२.{{/F}} Informed Maya at Tripuram of the preparations of gods to attack his city; visited इलावृतम् sacred to Bali; arranged, at the request of Indra, the marriage of उमा with शिव; {{F}}३२:  Ib. ५४. 2-4; ९५. 4; १०२. १९; ११२. २१.{{/F}} His sister was अरुन्दती,