 in वैकुण्ठ. भा. III. १५. १६.--the place of Kavi Agni (उशीर). वा. २९. २९. [page२-268+ ३६]--a पिशाच clan. वा. ६९. 264--a son of हृदीक. वा. ९६. १४०.--the king after चन्द्राम्शु; the second king of विदिश. Br. III. ७४. १८१; वा. ९९. ३६७.--a son of पृथुसेन (पृथु-ब्र्।, वि।, and वा। प्।) and father of Gaya. भा. V. १५. 6. Br. II. १४. ६८; वा. ३३. ५७; Vi. II. 1. ३८. [page२-191+ ३६]--born to माद्री (माद्रवती) through the favour of the अश्विन्स्: father of शतानीक and Niramitra, the latter by करेणुमती; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २२. २८-9, ३२; Br. III. ७१. १३५; M. ४६. १०; ५०. ५०; वा. ९६. १५४; ९९. २४५; Vi. IV. १४. ३८; २०. ४०.{{/F}} felt joy at कृष्ण's visit to Indra- prastha; was sent to the northern countries, for gathering provisions for युधिष्ठिर's राजसूय; {{F}}2:  भा. X. ७१. २७; ७२. १३; ७५. 4.{{/F}} approved of Drau- पदी's desire to release अश्वथाम; {{F}}3:  Ib. I. 7. ५०; १०. 9.{{/F}} consoled by कृष्ण while in forest; {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ५८. 4; ६४. 9.{{/F}} heard from भिष्म the secret of the cycle of births and deaths. {{F}}5:  Vi. III. 7. 8-१३.{{/F}}--sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ७७.--(नकुलेश्वरी)--Mind-born daughter of ललिता, riding on गरुड to vanquish सर्पिनी, was attacked by the five commanders of भण्ड: नकुली cut off Karanka's head when the army retreated in fear to सून्यक city; {{F}}1:  Br. IV. २३. ५२-93; २८. ३९.{{/F}} an अवतार् of the Lord. {{F}}2:  वा. २३. २२१.{{/F}}(I)--a son of Yadu. भा. IX. २३. २०; Vi. IV. ११. 5.(II)--a Vanara son of Agni born by the wife of Kanakabindu. Br. III. 7. २२९.(III)--a वानर chief. Br. III. 7. २३४.(IV)--a nephew of हिरण्यकशिपु. M. 6. २६.(V)--the son of निषध, hence नैषध; with the son of वीरसेन he made the two Nalas in the कश्यप line; {{F}}1:  M. १२. ५२, ५६; वा. ८८. २०२.{{/F}} taught the game of dice to King ऋतुपर्ण. {{F}}2:  भा. IX. 9; १७; Br. III. ६३. १७३ and २०२, ७४. १९०; वा. ८८. १७४; Vi. IV. 4. ३७.{{/F}} Learned in अश्वविद्या. [page२-213+ २८](VI)--a son of वीरसेन. M. १२. ५६.(VII)--also known as Nandanodaradundubhi, son of Taittiri, performed अश्वमेध, and in the middle of the अतिरात्र rite Punarvasu appeared and became his son. M. ४४. ६३-5.--a people of the southern country. वा. ४५. १२७.--a son of Kubera and ऋद्धि; as an attendant of Rudra became very proud and with his brother मणिग्रीव enjoyed maidens' embrace on the Ganges, all naked. नारद saw this when the ladies put on their dress while नलकूबर and his brother continued to remain nak- ed owing to their drunkenness. The sage cursed them to become trees for a hundred divine years without losing the पूर्ववासन। So they stood till कृष्ण redeemed them by bringing down the trees; their prayer to कृष्ण; set out to the north, permitted by कृष्ण. भा. X. 9. २२. २३; १०. (whole); Br. III. 8. ४६. वा. ७०. ४१.(I)--one of the eastern entrances of the city of पुरञ्जन {{F}}1:  भा. IV. २५. ४८.{{/F}} allegorically the nostrils. {{F}}2:  Ib. २९. ११.{{/F}}(II)--one of the wives of अजमीढ and mother of नील. भा. IX. २१. ३०. Vi. IV. १९. ५६.(III)--a R. in शाकद्वीप. Br. II. १९. ९६; Vi. II. 4. ६५. [page२-214+ ३५](IV)--digging of lakes at the auspicious hour; the same prescription as for the excavation of तदाग; is also पुष्करणि. M. ५८. 1, ५१.(V)--a name for the Ganges; {{F}}1:  M. १०२. 6.{{/F}} a stream of the गन्गा, flows east through the countries of Tomara, Hamsa- मार्ग, Haihaya, कर्णप्रावरण, अश्वमुख, शिकता- parvatamaru, विद्याधर, and नागमण्डल and reaches the salt ocean; {{F}}2:  Br. II. १८. ४०, ५८-61; वा. ४७. ३८ and ५६.{{/F}} one of the seven streams, and one of the three going towards the western direction. {{F}}3:  M. १२१. ४०.{{/F}}--a measurement in connection with the chariot of Maya; {{F}}1:  M. १७३. 2; Br. IV. 2. १२५; ३६. ४९.{{/F}} the seat of हिरण्यकशिपु in his सभा was १० nalvas in measurement; {{F}}2:  M. १६१. ७१.{{/F}} a furlong in distance; ३०० dhanus. {{F}}3:  वा. ८३. ४९; १०१. १२५.{{/F}}--a son of प्रवीर and father of चारुपद. भा. IX. २०. 2.--a son of Vipracitti. Lord of the Asuras, hostile to Indra; {{F}}1:  Vi. I. २१. ११.{{/F}} a resident of the first talam or atala; {{F}}2:  वा. ५०. १५; ९८. ८१.{{/F}} a nephew of हिरण्यकशिपु; married सुप्रभा, the daughter of स्वर्भानु; {{F}}3:  भा. VI. 6. ३२; Br. III. 6. १९; M. 6. २७.{{/F}} followed वृत्र against Indra; {{F}}4:  भा. VI. १०. १९-31; Br. II. २०. १६.{{/F}} took part in the देवासुर war between Bali and Indra; fought with अपराजित; heard of Bali's and Jambha's fall and fought with Indra; resisted with success Vajra on account of the fact that he could not be killed either by a dry or wet thing; Indra who came to know of this by a voice in the air used फेन (foam) and killed him to the satisfaction of all gods; {{F}}5:  भा. VII. 2. 4; VIII. १०. २० to the end; ११. १९, २३, २९-40; M. २२. ६१.{{/F}} entertained desire for more territory; {{F}}6:  भा. XII. 3. ११.{{/F}} taken to पाताल by वामन. {{F}}7:  Br. III. ७३. ८१; M. २४९. ६७.{{/F}}(I)--an attendant on पुरुषोत्तम Vis2n2u (Hari); {{F}}1:  भा. II. 9. १४; X. ३९. ५३; ८९. ५७; VIII. २२. १५.{{/F}} praised Dhruva; {{F}}2:  Ib. IV. १२. २२.{{/F}} went with Hari going to पृथु's sacrifice; {{F}}3:  Ib. IV. १९. 5; VI. 4. ३९.{{/F}} attacked the Asuras, the followers of Bali. {{F}}4:  Ib. VIII. २१. १६.{{/F}}(II)--a Mt. of क्रौञ्चद्वीप. भा. V. २०. २१.(III)--a son of मदिरा and Vasudeva. भा. IX. २४. ४८; Br. III. ७१. १७१; वा. ९६. १६९; Vi. IV. १५. २३.(V)--a king of the Nanda dynasty; {{F}}1:  भा. XII. 1. 9.{{/F}} from परीक्षित् to Nanda the period was १११५ years; At the time of Nanda the सप्तऋषिस् moved from Magha to पूर्वाषाढ. {{F}}2:  Ib. XII. 2. २६-7, ३२.{{/F}}(VI)--the fourth son of मेधातिथि and founder of the Nanda Kingdom. Br. II. १४. ३६-9.(VII)--a वानर chief. Br. III. 7. २३४.(VIII)--a son of शूर and भोजा. M. ४६. 3.(IX) city; Uragapati, in the third Tala or Vitalam. वा. ५०. २९.(X)--an Ajitadeva. वा. ६७. ३४.(IV)--In previous birth the Vasu, द्रोण; {{F}}1:  भा. X. 8. ४८-50; Br. III. ७१. २३९.{{/F}} connected with the Devas, married यशोदा; {{F}}2:  भा. I. 8. २१; X. 1. ६२; 2. 9; Vi. IV. १५. ३१.{{/F}} celebrated the birth of कृष्ण as his son by inviting Brahmanas, Gopas and गोपीस् and making rich presents to them, the Gopas and गोपीस् threw balls of turmeric on the baby and sprinkled butter, curds and milk on one another, a folk custom; {{F}}3:  भा. X. 5. 1-१६; chh. 5. 6, 7 and 8 (whole),{{/F}} went to मथुरा to pay the annual tribute to Kamsa; was met by Vasudeva who advised him to leave at once for his place as he expected some उत्पातस् there: Nanda thinking Vasu- deva's words to be true turned his thoughts on the way to Hari; heard of पूतना, the demon killed by कृष्ण and felt greatly surprised; embraced कृष्ण in joy; performed शान्ति for कृष्ण for kicking the cart; was surprised at कृष्ण's taking the lap of तृणावर्त and believed more and more in Vasudeva's words; welcomed Garga and had नामकरण done to his sons; became pleased at Garga's service; {{F}}3:  भा. X. 5. 1-१६; chh. 5. 6, 7 and 8 (whole),{{/F}} Nanda and his friends bewildered at the fall of the Arjuna trees and released कृष्ण from his fetters; planned to leave Vraja for ब्रिन्दावन; {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ११. 1-2; Vi. V. 5. 1-२१; 6. 6 and २१; 7. २२ and ३४; १०. १८ and २५.{{/F}} his fortune in enjoying Hari at close quarters; {{F}}5:  भा. X. १४. ३२.{{/F}} was much concerned at the bad omens at कृष्ण's fight with कालिय; was stopped by बलराम from entering the port of कालिय; joy at कृष्ण's escape from कालिय; gave presents of gold and cows to Brahmanas on the occasion. {{F}}6:  Ib. X. १६. १२-22; १७. १५-18.{{/F}} [page२-195+ ४३] Prepared for the इन्द्रयाग; but gave it up and prayed to the mountains instead, as advised by कृष्ण; Indra's anger towards Nanda; was surprised at कृष्ण holding the Govar- dhana; when the Gopas wondered at the exploits of the boy, कृष्ण, Nanda said that he heard from Garga that he was Vasudeva's son and an अम्श of नारायण; after fasting on एकादशि, Nanda went to यमुना for bath for the द्वादशि; it was आसुर time and not the time for bath; so an Asura follower of वरुण took hold of him and placed him before वरुण; seeing Nanda missing, the Gopas got frightened and appealed to कृष्ण who went to वरुण; pleased at seeing him वरुण said that it was a mistake committed by his servants in ignorance and set Nanda free; then he returned to Vraja to the great joy of all the Gopas; taken to Brahmah- rada; {{F}}7:  Ib. X. chh. २४, २५, २६, २७ and २८ (whole).{{/F}} when once he went to अम्बिकावन he was seized by a reptile and was released with कृष्ण's help. {{F}}8:  Ib. X. ३४. 4-१८; ३६. २४. (३१).{{/F}} Extended a hearty welcome to अक्रूर and enquired of Kamsa; became afraid of अक्रूर's message; got ready with all the Gopas to start for मथुरा with presents to Kamsa; followed अक्रूर's chariot with all his carts and men; came in advance and waited for कृष्ण's arrival; took his seat along with the other Gopas in the gallery of the wrestling ground; Kamsa desired to imprison him; duly honoured by कृष्ण, Nanda and the Gopas returned to Vraja after Kamsa's death; {{F}}9:  Ib. X. ३८. ४१-43; ३९. १०-12, ३५; ४१. 8; ४२. ३८; ४४. ३२; ४५. २०-25; Vi. V. ११. 3; १५. १८; २०. २८ and ८३.{{/F}} welcomed Uddhava with due honour; exhibited his deep love for कृष्ण; Uddhava revealed the real nature of कृष्ण to him. {{F}}१०:  भा. X. ४६. १४ to the end.{{/F}} Came to स्यमन्तपञ्चक and met कृष्ण and others; embraced and enquired after by Vasudeva and others; {{F}}११:  Ib. X. ५२. ३२-35.{{/F}} was honoured by कृष्ण, राम, Ugrasena and Vasudeva; spent three months unwilling to be away from the Yadus, left for मथुरा; {{F}}१२:  Ib. X. ८४. ५९-69.{{/F}} chief of सात्वतस् and vassal of कृष्ण: went with वृष्णिस् to बाण's city. {{F}}१३:  Ib. I. १४. ३२; II. 7. ३१; X. १३. 3.{{/F}} [page२-196+ २५](I)--a celestial R. of शाल्मलिद्वीप, and sacred to Hari; {{F}}1:  भा. IV. 6. २४-27; V. २०. १०; VII. १४. ३२; VIII. 4. २३.{{/F}} sacred to पितृस्. {{F}}2:  M. २२. १०.{{/F}} [page२-199+ २७](II)--north of Vedi, sacred to महादेव. Br. III. १३. ८२-3.(III)--a शक्ति; a goddess enshrined at the हिमा- layan slopes. Br. IV. ४४. ७२; M. १३. ३०.(IV)--a R. of शाकद्वीप: पार्वती. M. १२२. ३१; वा. ४९. ९२.(V)--a R. in कैलास. वा. ४१. १८.--one of the three disciples of Rathitara. वा. ६१. 3.--the residence of Nanda and other Gopas. भा. X. 2. 7; 3. ४५ [1].--see Nanda. Br. III. ७१. २१२; वा. ९६. २०६.(I)--विष्णु's sword; reached कृष्ण during जरासन्ध's siege of मथुरा. भा. X. ५०. ११. [१४]. [page२-197+ २४](II)--a नाग chief with his city in the third Talam. Br. II. २०. ३०.(III)--a son of वृकदेवी and Vasudeva. M. ४६. १८.(IV)--a disciple of ब्रह्मा. वा. २२. १६.(I)--a यक्ष: a son of पुण्यजनी and मणिभद्र. Br. III. 7. १२२; वा. ६९. १५४.(II)--a son of Madhu. Br. III. ७०. ४६; वा. ९५. ४६.(III)--a son of शिव; father of रन्ती and रन्तिपाल (Tanti and तन्तिपाल-वा। प्।). Br. III. ७१. १४९ and १९२; M. ४६. २७.(IV)--a younger brother of चन्द्रहास. Br. IV. २९. ११३.(V)--a temple with several peaks; the तोरण is of ३० hastas. M. २६९. २९, ३३, ४८. [page२-198+ २९](VI)--a disciple of ब्रह्मा. वा. २२. १६.(VII)--one of the eight निधिस् of Kubera. वा. ४१. १०.(VIII)--a brother of Vasudeva. वा. ९६. १४८.(IX)--a son of Vanga and father of Sunandi. Vi. IV. २४. ५६.--a R. from the पारियात्र hill (ऋष्यवत्). Br. II. १६. २८; M. ११४. २५.--a pleasure garden of gods and Indra, noted for पारिजात; {{F}}1:  भा. III. २३. ४०; V. १६. १४; M. ३८. १८; वा. ३६. ११; ४६. 4; ४७. 3; ६९. १३६; ९१. 6; ९३. ६९.{{/F}} visited by कृष्ण and सत्यभामा; {{F}}2:  भा. X. [६५ (v) १२-21]; [६७ (v) ३४].{{/F}} in the Kai- लास on the north of इलावृत destroyed by Daityas; {{F}}3:  Br. II. १८. 4; III. 7. १०२; ६६. 6; IV. 9. ३९; M. १८३. 2; २१२. 9; Vi. II. 2. २५; V. 7. ६६; ३०. ३०; ३६. १२.{{/F}} on the banks of मन्दाकिनी. ^4 M. १२१. 5; १३१. ४८; १३३. 9.--another name for Nala, son of Taittiri. M. ४४. ६३.--the Royal dynasty preceding the Mauryas; {{F}}1:  भा. XII. 1. 8-१०.{{/F}} commence their line when the Seven ऋषिस् reach पूर्वाषाढ, and after १०६५ years from परीक्षित्. {{F}}2:  Vi. IV. २४. १०४ and ११२.{{/F}}--is Nanda gokula. Br. III. ३६. १३.--ruled for १०० years. वा. ९९. ३३०.(I)--a son of Svarga. भा. VI. 6. 6.(II)--the वाहन of शिव; {{F}}1:  वा. ५४. ७६ and १०८; १०१. २६५.{{/F}} harnessed the steeds of बाण's chariot. {{F}}2:  Vi. V. ३३. २८.{{/F}}(III)--a consort of धृति; was deserted by her for Soma. M. २३. २६.(IV)--a गण attending on महादेव seated on the peak of the हिमालयस्. M. १९२. 6.(V)--a son of Nandivardhana; with him the Pradyota line came to an end; was the fifth of the line. All the five ruled for a period of १३८ years. Vi. IV. २४. 7-8. [page२-200+ २७]--the place where Bharata lived during राम's exile. भा. IX. १०. ३६.--one of the eighteen authors on architecture. M. २५२. 3.--the god attendant on शिव; {{F}}1:  वा. ७७. ६३.{{/F}} the vehicle of Rudra; {{F}}2:  भा. X. ६३. 6.{{/F}} भगवान् with सूल; {{F}}3:  वा. ३०. ९१, ३१५.{{/F}} cursed दक्ष for his hatred of शिव; {{F}}4:  भा. IV. 2. २०-26.{{/F}} caught hold of Bhaga on the occasion of the destruction of Daksa's sacrifice; {{F}}5:  Ib. IV. 5. १७.{{/F}} his permission to see [page२-202+ २९] शिव; temple of, at स्वर्गमार्ग Prasa1da. {{F}}6:  Br. III. ३२. २३; १३. ६३-4; IV. ३०. ७५; ३४. ८९; ४१. २६ and ३०; ४३. ३०.{{/F}} Observed the vow सौभाग्यशयनम्; lord of a गण, versed in महेश्वर dharma; advised नारद to take to प्रयाग; the standard of शिव. {{F}}7:  M. ६०. ४९; ९५. 3; ११२. २१; १३२. १८; १३३. ६०-5.{{/F}} Fought with विद्युन्मालि in Tripuram; {{F}}8:  Ib. १३५. ४८ and ५३; १३६. ६८; १३८. ४४. १४०. २०-1.{{/F}} related to सनत्कुमार about the स्थानुत्वम् of शिव at Benares. {{F}}9:  Ib. १८१. 2; १८३. ६४; २४५. ८०. २६६. ४२. २७८. 9.{{/F}}a तीर्थम् on the Nar- मदा. M. १९१. 6 and ३७.(I)--a शक्ति: the goddess enshrined at देवी- कातट; a Mother-goddess. Br. IV. ४४. ८४; M. १३. ३८; १७९. १४ and २५.(II)--a R. of the केतुमाला continent. वा. ४४. २०.--an उपपुराण; contains the माहात्म्य of Nandi described by कार्त्तिकेय. M. ५३. ६१.(I)--a son of उदावसु and father of Suketu. भा. IX. १३. १४; Br. III. ६४. 7; वा. ८९. 7. Vi. IV. 5. २५.(II)--a son of राजक (विशाखयूप) and the last of the five Pradyotanas, who ruled for १३८ years. भा. XII. 1. 4. [page२-201+ ३३](III)--a son of Ajaya (Ajaka-ब्र्। प्।) and father of महानन्दि; ruled for २० years (४०)? भा. XII. 1. 7. Br. III. ७४. १२६ and १३३.(IV)--a palace with seven storeys; the तोरण is of ३२ hastas. M. २६९. २९, ४८.(V)--a son of सूर्यक: was succeeded by शिशुनाक; ruled for thirty years. M. २७२. 5.(VI)--the son of उदासि, and a शैसु- नाग ruled for ४० years. (४२ years ब्र्। प्।). M. २७२. ११; वा. ९९. ३२०.(VII)--a son of Manivara; a यक्ष and a Guhyaka. वा. ६९. १५८.(VIII)--a son of Janaka and father of Nandi of the Pradyota dynasty. Vi. IV. २४. 6-7.(IX)--a son of Udayana and father of महानन्दि of the शैसनाभ dynasty. Vi. IV. २४. १७-8.(I)--the younger brother of भूतनन्दि (Madhunandi-वा। प्।); a king. Br. III. ७४. १८२.(II)--a son of Nandana and brother of Sunandana. Vi. IV. २४. ५६.(I) (नारायण)--an अवतार् of विष्णु, born of Dharma and मूर्ती, a daughter of दक्ष; आदिशेष form of Hari, distinguished for tapas; {{F}}1:  भा. I. 2. 4; 3. 9; II. 7. 6-7; XII. 8. ३२, ३५. Br. II. ३५-93; M. 1. 2.{{/F}} a friend and associate of नारायण said to have performed tapas at बदरी; {{F}}2:  भा. III. 4. २२; IV. 1. ५२; VII. 6. २७.{{/F}} seeing the sage's penance Indra got afraid and sent the God of Love and the Apsarasas to disturb his contemplation. Nara invited him and was hospitable by creating a number of beautiful women who served them; Nara asked them to choose one among them as an ornament of Heaven. So they took ऊर्वशि and narrated to Indra the superior powers of the sage; {{F}}3:  Ib. XI. 4. 6-१६; 7. १८.{{/F}} was seen with नारायण by मार्कण्डेय and was praised by him. {{F}}4:  Ib. XII. 8. ३२, ३५, ४०-49; 9. 1.{{/F}}(II)--a son of तामस Manu. भा. VIII. I. २७; Br. II. ३६. ४९. Vi. III. 1. १९. [page२-206+ २८](III)--a son of सुधृति and father of Kevala (Candra वि। प्।). भा. IX. 2. २९. ३०; Br. III. 8. ३५; ६१. 9; Vi. IV. 1. ४०-1; वा. ८६. १३-14.(IV)--a son of Manyu and father of सम्कृति. भा. IX. २१. 1.(V)--a son of Gaya and father of विरात्. Br. II. १४. ६८; Vi. II. 1. ३८; वा. ३३. ५८.(VI)--one of the ten horses of the moon's chariot. Br. II. २३. ३५; M. १२६. ५२.(VII)--a साध्य; is satya in the स्वारोचिष epoch. Br. III. 3. १६-7; M. २०३. ११; २५१; २४-5; वा. ६६. १५; Br. II. ३६. ५०.(VIII)--a son of Bhuvamanyu. M. ४९. ३६; वा. ९९. १५९.(IX)--the riding vehicle of नैऋति and drawer of Kubera's chariot. M. २६१. १५ and २२.(X)--a son of तामस Manu. वा. ६२. ४३.(XI)--a देवऋषि. वा. ६१. ८३.--the daughter of सुयग्ञ (श्वफल्क, वा। प्।) and wife of भन्गकार; had two sons शत्रुघ्न and Ban- धुमान्, whom अक्रूर killed. Br. III. ७१. ८७. वा. ९६. ८६.--(एत्य्।) waters. वा. 7. ५६-8; १००. १८३.--a son of कालनेमि; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 5. ३९; वा 67. ८०.{{/F}} was killed in the लन्का war. {{F}}2:  भा. IX. १०. १८.{{/F}}--a वानर chief. Br. III. 7. २४३.--the eighteenth, out of the अवतार्स् of विष्णु; did heroic deeds, subduing the sea and so on. भा. I. 3. २२.--one of the 6 kinds of fortresses. M. २१७. 6.--a son of अनृत; another name of Raurava. Br. II. 9. ६४; वा. १०. ३९.--a nephew of हिरण्यकशिपु and son of the Earth and Vipracitti; lived in प्राग्ज्योतिष; {{F}}1:  M. 6. २७; १६१. ७८; १६३. ८१-2; २४५. १२. Vi. I. २१. १२८; V. 1. २४; १२. २१.{{/F}} took away a [page२-207+ ४१] number of women belonging to sages and kings to his palace, robbed Mandara of its crest jewel, Aditi of her ear- rings and वरुण of his umbrella; demanded the ऐरावत from Indra; at Indra's request was cut in twain by कृष्ण in his own city प्राग्ज्योतिष; {{F}}2:  Ib. V. २९. 8-२१.{{/F}} spoils distributed among his fol- lowers while all women were appropriated to कृष्ण's harem. {{F}}3:  Ib. V. ३१. १४-15.{{/F}} Friend of वानर Dvivida who was killed by Baladeva. {{F}}4:  Ib. V. ३६. 2-२१.{{/F}}--a दानव with मनुष्य धर्म; {{F}}1:  वा. ६८. १५.{{/F}} a Saimhi- keya; {{F}}2:  Ib. ६८. १९.{{/F}} killed by कृष्ण. {{F}}3:  Ib. ९८. १०२.{{/F}}--कृष्ण. Br. III. ३६. ३४.--(Naraka, s.v. Bhauma); Born of Hari in his Boar manifestation when he touched and raised the Earth, {{F}}1:  भा. X. ५९. ३०[1]; [६५ (v) 1].{{/F}} hence son of Earth, {{F}}2:  Ib. X. ५९. ५९. [1] and 2.{{/F}} an asura friend of Kamsa; {{F}}3:  Ib. X. 2. 2; ३६. ३६.{{/F}} a friend of the वानर Dvivida; {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ६७. 2; ६९. [3] 1.{{/F}} ran away with the umbrella of वरुण, कुण्डल of Aditi and contested the position of Indra. {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ५९. [1] and 2.{{/F}} Fought with सनैश्चर in the देवासुर war; {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ७३. २०; ८३. ४०; Br. III. 6. १५; ७३. १०२; IV. २९. १२५.{{/F}} find- [page२-208+ ३३] ing Mura and his sons dead, came out with elephants, which were all killed by गरुड; fought with कृष्ण till his head was cut off and the ladies of his harem married by Him (कृष्ण); {{F}}7:  भा. VIII. १०. ३३.{{/F}} lost his kingdom through pride of power. {{F}}8:  Ib. X. ५९. १४-22; ३७. १६; I. १०. २९.{{/F}}--is bhaumam (earth). M. ३९. 4, 7-8; ४१. 6.--२७ hells under Yama; to them go the un- righteous according to their respective sins; after a certain period they are born as low beings according to their कर्म। {{F}}1:  Br. IV. 2. १४६-150.{{/F}} Seven under the earth below the शेषलोक-- Raurava, शीतस्तप, कालसूतु, अप्रतिष्ठ, अवीची, लोहपृष्ठ, and Avidhya. {{F}}2:  वा. १०१. १४४-92; Vi. II. 6. 1. (whole).{{/F}}--the belly of the personified Veda. वा. १०४. ८४. [page२-209+ २९]--The two sages comprising the fourth अवतार् of विष्णु and born of मूर्ती; universal joy and good omens at their birth; गन्धमादन their abode; {{F}}1:  भा. I. 2. 4, २६; 3. 9; IV. 1. ५२-57; Vi. V. २४. 5; ३७. ३४ and ३७.{{/F}} born later as कृष्ण and अर्जुण; {{F}}2:  Ib. IV. 1. ५९.{{/F}} worshipped by नाभी; {{F}}3:  Ib. V. 4. 4.{{/F}} wor- shipped in भारतवर्ष; {{F}}4:  Ib. V. १९. 9.{{/F}} praised by नारद. {{F}}5:  Ib. V. १९. १२-15.{{/F}} To their आश्रम the sages repaired for a visit; {{F}}6:  Ib. IX. 1. ३१.{{/F}} shrine of, at Badar- याश्रम. {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ५२. 4.{{/F}}--one of the births of the जयादेवस्; these are विपश्चित्, Indra, Satya and Hari. वा. ५४. ७५; ६६. १४.--The अवतार् of Hari to kill हिरण्यकशिपु by the nails neither wet nor dry; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 5. २६-27; ५७. ५७; ७३. ७४; वा. ६७. ६६; ९७. ७३; ९८. ७३; १११. ७२; Vi. I. २०. ३२.{{/F}} on ब्रह्मा granting the request of हिरण्यकशिपु, Narasimha was approached by the gods; Narasimha promised to slay him and left for the सभा of हिरण्यकशिपु; प्रह्लाद alone knew Him to be the Lord; all the Asuras attacked him from all sides; finally Narasimha killed him by tearing him with his teeth. {{F}}2:  M. ५३. ५०. chh. १६१, १६२ and १६३; २८५. 6.{{/F}}--an attribute of Kubera. M. १७४. १८.--is Candragupta Maurya. Br. III. ७४. १४३.(I)--a son of Vaivasvata Manu and father of Citrasena and Suca; his line ends with जातूकर्ण्य. भा. VIII. १३. 2; IX. 1. १२; 2. १९, २२; Br. III. ६०. 3; M. ११. ४१; १२. २०; वा. ६४. २९; ८५. 4; Vi. III. 1. ३३; IV. 1. 7.(II)--(नाभाग) a son of स्वायम्भुव Manu. Br. II. ३८. ३१. वा. ८५ 4. [page२-210+ ४३](III)--a son of Marutta and father of Dama. Br. III. 8. ३५; ६१. 7; वा. ८६. १२; Vi. IV. 1. ३४-5.(I)--a महानदि of the भारतवर्ष; a R. from the ऋक्ष or ऋष्यवत् hills: (Vindhyan ranges) on its northern bank was भृगुकच्छ: a sacred river that sur- vived the अन्तरक्षय, sacred to पितृस् and for श्राद्ध; in the neighbourhood of the Haihaya kingdom. {{F}}1:  भा. V. १९. १८; VIII. १८. २१; Br. II. १२. १४; १६. २९; III. १०. ९७; M. 2. १३-15; २२. २५; ११४. २३; वा. ४५. ९९; ७७. ३२; ९४. २८; १०८. ८२; V. II. 3. ११.{{/F}} The scene of battle between वृत्र and Indra; here Rukmi challenged कृष्ण when the latter was crossing the stream with रुक्मिणी; its current was stopped by कार्त- वीर्य. {{F}}2:  भा. VI. १०. १६; X. ५४. २३[1]; Br. III. १३. 8, ३२; २६. १० and ३८; ३८. 3 and 7; ४१. १५; ४५. 2; ६९. २८; M. ४३. ३१; ४४. ३१; ४४. ३१; १६३. ६३; Vi. IV. ११. १९.{{/F}} The महात्म्य of; just like मार्कण्डेय this river does not get lost in the time of the deluge; in Kalinga, near the अमरकण्टक hill; has a number of तीर्थस् like जलेश्वर, रुद्रकोटि, अम्रकण्टक, Kapila and विशल्य Karan2i. The devotee bathing in any तीर्थ on the नर्मदा gets the benefit of performing an अश्वमेध sacrifice. {{F}}3:  M. ch. १८६.{{/F}} The Lord enshrined here is महेश्वर who devised plans to vanquish बाणासुर of Tripura with the help of नारद. The Lord was much concerned about virtuous ladies in Tripura and नारद undertook to delude them by proclaiming ordinances to ladies to give gifts to poor and deserving Brahmanas. {{F}}4:  Ib. ch. १८७.{{/F}} शिव got ready for war here and attacked Tripura with incendiary materials. Out of the three cities comprising Tripura, (s.v.) two fell down reduced to ashes. The first city became converted into the श्रि S4aila hill, and the second अमरकण्टक hill, both adorned by the Siddhas, Gandharvas and so on. The Lord enshrined at the latter is ज्वालेश्वर. The third city was left unconsumed. {{F}}5:  Ib. ch. १८८.{{/F}} [page२-211+ ३८] It is said that at the confluence of the नर्मदा with कावेरी, Kubera practised tapas in honour of शिव and be- came the Lord of the यक्षस्. A bath here is equal to that at the confluence of the गन्गा and the यमुना. {{F}}6:  Ib. ch. १८९.{{/F}} To the north of the नर्मदा are a number of तीर्थम्स् like मन्त्रेश्वर, गर्जना, अम्रातक, करन्या, कुण्डेश्- vara and others. A bath in each of them rids one of all sins. Then follows other तीर्थस्, all equally sacred, includ- ing रावणेश्वर, the shrines of Kubera, अहल्यातीर्थ, and the shrine of जनार्दन. Here Agni, धर्मराज and वायु practised asceticism and attained emancipation. A visit to शुक्लतीर्थम् sacred to राजऋषि Ca1n2akya washes off all the sins of a life time. Any gift given here bears rich fruits. {{F}}7:  Ib. chh. १९०-192.{{/F}} Among the other sacred places can be mentioned the भृगुतीर्थम्, Kankhala, where गरुड once was in austereties, कन्यातीर्थ, पितामहतीर्थ, and स्वर्गद्वार- तीर्थम्; He who reads or listens to the glory of the नमदा has his wishes fulfilled whatever be his caste. {{F}}8:  Ib. chh. १९३-194.{{/F}} On its banks Purukutsa heard the विष्णु पुराण from the sages. {{F}}9:  Vi. I. 2. 9; IV. 3. 7-१६.{{/F}} Penance here by Asuras, who became converted into Arhats. {{F}}१०:  Ib. III. १८. 1 and १३.{{/F}} मरुभूमीविषय on the N. ruled by शूद्रस् and other castes. {{F}}११:  Ib. IV. २४. ६८.{{/F}}(II)--the मानसकन्या of शुकाला Pitr2s; given in marriage to Purukutsa by her brother Uraga; and mother of Trasadasyu; she took him to रसातल where he killed some bad Gandharvas to the satisfaction of the नागस्: {{F}}1:  भा. IX. 7. 2-3; Br. III. १०. ९७; वा. ७३. ४८; ८८. ७४.{{/F}} Heard the विष्णु पुराण from him and narrated it to धृतराष्ट्र the नाग and आपूरण. {{F}}2:  Vi. VI. 8. ४५.{{/F}} [page२-212+ २७](III)--the wife of युवनाश्व, son of Amba- रीष. Br. III. ६३. ७३.(IV)--a mind-born daughter of Somapa पितृस्: one of the १६ wives of हव्यवाहन: turned into a river of दक्षिणापथ. M. १५. २५, २८; ५१. १३; वा. ७७. ३२.--sages of, visited द्वारका. भा. X. ९०. २८. [5].--on the नर्मदा. M. १९४. 2.--a R. from विष्णुपद lake. वा. ४७. ६५.--the boat in the Ocean; in the river; {{F}}1:  वा. 6. २७; ५२. ८६; १०८. ३७.{{/F}} illustrative of the earth floating on waters. {{F}}2:  Vi. I. 4. ४६.{{/F}}--(महीमयी) the divine boat given to Manu (Vaivasvata) by विष्णु in the shape of a fish to be tied to its horn; {{F}}1:  M. 1. ३०-32; भा. I. 3. १५.{{/F}} in the deluge it rescued the sun, moon, ब्रह्मा, नर्मदा, sage मार्कण्डेय, शिव, the Vedas, पुराणस् and other Vidyas from ruin; {{F}}2:  M. 2. १०-15.{{/F}} Druhyu to ply the ocean with. {{F}}3:  Ib. ३३. २०.{{/F}}(I)--a son of स्वारोचिष Maru. Br. II. ३६. १९.(II)--a son of नवा and उशीनर; chief of Nava- राष्ट्र. Br. III. ७४. १९ and २१; M. ४८. १८ and २१; वा. ९९. २०, २२. Vi. IV. १८. 9.--भृगु, Pulastya, Pulaha, Kratu, आन्गिरस, मरीचि, दक्ष, Atri, and वसिष्ठ; according to the पुराणस्। वा. 9. ६८-69.--one of the five queens of उशीनर and mother of Nava. Br. III. ७४. १८-19; M. ४८. १६. १८; वा. ९९. १९-20.--a वानर chief. Br. III. 7. २४०.--a वानर chief. Br. III. 7. २४४.--one who preaches neo-dharma; applied to Yadu by ययाति. वा. ९३. ३७.--see Ayutahoma: the nine planets are the Sun, Moon, अङ्गारक, Budha, शनैश्चर, शुक्र, Guru, राहु and Ketu: इश्वर, उमा, श्कन्द, Hari, ब्रह्मा, Indra, Yama, काल, and Citragupta are अधिदेवतस्; Agni, Waters, Earth, विष्णु, Indra, Aindri, प्रजापति, नागस् and ब्रह्मणस् ar