ed and cursed that the King be dead by the bite of तक्षक in a week; the sage who came to know of it regretted his son's conduct as it was a great punishment for a small offence; {{F}}5:  Ib. ch. १९. 1-१६, ३२. ३८; II. 8. 1-२६; VIII. 1. ३३.{{/F}} the King regretted his deed, knew that the Brahmana's curse would come true and was in a state of प्रायोपवेश, when he was visited by sages and kings to whom he bowed; thither came शुक whom the king enquired as to the beneficial course to seek मोक्ष; requested शुक to narrate the stories of कृष्ण; {{F}}6:  Ib. XII. 6. 1-7.{{/F}} heard the whole of भागवत पुराण from शुक and thanked him for enlightening him on निर्वाण; {{F}}7:  Ib. II. 4. 2; XII. 6. 9-१५; १२. 5-6.{{/F}} knew of his coming death at the hands of तक्षक and prepared calmly to cast off his body into गन्गा to attain Hari's feet; sat in contemplation in a detatched spirit; bitten by तक्षक, his body was reduc- ed to ashes by the poison; universal surprise and benediction at the occurrence; {{F}}8:  Br. III. ७४. २२७, २३०; M. २७३. ३६; Vi. IV. १९. ७८; २०-1.{{/F}} from P. to Nanda's accession was a period of १५०० years (१०५० years वि। प्।: १०१५ Wilson). Father of Janamejaya and three other sons. {{F}}9:  वा. ९९, २२९, ४२३; Vi. IV, १९. ७८; २०. I.{{/F}} [page२-299+ २९](II)--a son of Kuru, childless. भा. IX. २२. 4, 9; M. ५०. २३; वा. ९९. २१८.(III)--a son of तामस Manu. Br. II. ३६. ४९.--a mind-born mother. M. १७९. २४.--a pupil of कृत. Br. II. ३५. ५२.--a त्रयार्षेय. M. १९८. १०.--a Bhavya God. Br. II. ३६. ७२.--a thousand परार्धस्. वा. १०१. १००.--the son of सुखीनल and father of Sunaya. भा. IX. २२. ४२.--the son of सुखीबल. वा. ९९. २७५.--a son of सुखीबल. M. ५०. ८३.--a son of देवकी killed by Kamsa; taken to द्वारका from Sutala by कृष्ण, and after having been seen by his parents, went to heaven. भा. X. ८५. ५१-6.--a Janapada of the Bhadra country. वा. ४३. २०.(I)--a variety of wind controlling the Parjanya clouds. वा. ५१. ४५.(II)--the sixth of the seven Maruts helping, the Parjanya and Diggaj