ras; {{F}}1:  M. १९६. 2; वा. ६५. १०५.{{/F}} a साध्य; {{F}}2:  Ib. ६६. १५.{{/F}} a तुषित; {{F}}3:  Br. III. 3. १९; वा. ६६. १८.{{/F}} an Ajitadeva. {{F}}4:  Ib. ६७. ३४.{{/F}}(VI)--the अन्तरात्म; it is अन्नम् or food; अन्नम् is ब्रह्मा, etc.; from this grows creatures. (cf. उपनिषद्; also Yajur Veda); {{F}}1:  वा. १५. १४.{{/F}} one of the वायुस् which determine the कर्म of people; {{F}}2:  Ib. २१. ४७; ३१. ४१.{{/F}} is जीव। {{F}}3:  Ib. १०२. १०१.{{/F}}(VII)--a son of धातृ and father of Dyutimat. V. I. १०. 4-5.(VIII)--one of the seven seers of the स्वारोचिष epoch. Vi. III. 1. ११.--the purohita to be consulted by the king. M. २१५. ३५.(I)--a साधन for yoga. Vi. I. २२. ४५; V. १०. १५; VI. 7. ४०. [page२-443+ ३४](II)--three-fold: its utility; a mode of penance. {{F}}1:  भा. IV. 8. ४४; २३. 8; Br. III. २२. ७४; M. २२७. ३७.{{/F}} one of the constituents of महेश्वर yoga; एत्य्।, the control of प्राण or wind; three ways are distinguished; मन्ध, मध्य and उत्तम; the प्रमाण of प्राणायाम is १२ मात्रस्; मन्द is of १२ मात्रस् as also उद्घाता; मध्- यम इस् twice उद्घाता or २४ मात्रस्; उत्तम is three उद्घा- तास् or ३६ मात्रस्; उत्तम produces स्वेद, कम्प and विषाद; प्राण is like the cruel wild animal which if tamed becomes soft; if approached direct by yoga, प्राण becomes disciplined in course of time; having controlled the वायु one can live as he pleases; there is no sin in his body; प्राणायाम is equal to all penances and fruits of यज्ञ; all दोषस् become burnt as it were by this practice. {{F}}2:  वा. १०. ७८-92.{{/F}} fruits of; शान्ति, प्रशान्ति, दीप्ति, and प्रसाद; {{F}}3:  Ib. ११. 4; १८. १७-19.{{/F}} practice of:--द्रw in ॐ, pray to sun and moon, and sit in स्वस्तिक or पद्म posture; half- shut eyes; look at the tip of the nose a little raising the head, neck and the body; hence तमस् and रजस् look on सत्व; attaining this yoga, प्रत्याहार to be begun, मात्र--निमि- षोन्मेष--१२ मात्रस्। {{F}}4:  Ib. ११. १२-29; २२. १९; ११०. १३.{{/F}}(I)--One of the २८ hells where those who indulge in the hunting and killing of animals are punished. भा. V. २६. 7 and २४.(II)--control of the breath, one of the aids to deep meditation. वा. १०४. २४.--a R. sacred to the पितृस्. M. २२. ६५.--the सप्तान्गस् of kings; wife, purohita, सेनानि, charioteer, minister, horse and elephant. Br. II. २९. ७६; वा. ५७. ७०.--noted for horses. Br. IV. १६. १८.--an Asura. Br. III. 6. 7.(I)--a daughter of जरासन्ध and queen of Kamsa. After Kamsa's death she went to her father's house and reported the circumstance under which he was killed. भा. X. ५०. 1-2; Vi. V. २२. 1.(II)--a siddhi devi. Br. IV. १९. 4; ४४. १०८. [page२-445+ २६](III)--one of the eight योगैश्वर्यस् Va1. १३. 3, १३.(IV)--one of the ten branches of the सुपार group of Devas. वा. १००. ९४.--ety. that which pleases the mind; generally a palace. वा. 8. १२७; ३५. 4; ३९. ३६; ४०. 9.--of विष्णु; offering of बलि to deities as a pre- liminary to building; varieties of buildings descrbied--मेरु, मन्दर, कैलाश, कुम्भ, सिम्ह, मृग, विमान, छन्- दक, चतुस्र, अष्टास्र, षोडशास्र, वर्तुल, सर्वभद्रक, सिम्हास्य, नन्दन, नन्दिवर्धनक, हम्स, वृष, सु- वर्णेश, पद्मक and समुद्रक; with तोरणस् and arch- ways of wood, stone or brick. Br. IV. 7. २८; M. chh. २६८-9.--a कश्यप gotrakara. M. १९९. 8.--ब्रह्मा as, in the fights of Madhu and Kai- tabha and विष्णु and जिष्णु. वा. २५. ४१.--a son of उद्गीथ. Vi. II. 1. ३७.(I)--a son of पुष्पार्ण and प्रभा. भा. IV. १३. १३.(II)--morning; born of धात्रि and राका. भा. VI. १८. 3.(III)--a राक्षस with the sun in आवणि and पुरट्टशि (Sep-Oct.). वा. ५२. १०. [page२-444+ २९]--when the sun passes three मुहूर्तस् com- mencing with the लेख, that time is the fifth part of the day; {{F}}1:  वा. ५०. १७०.{{/F}} the first six नालिकस्। {{F}}2:  Ib. ५६. ४६.{{/F}}--a ब्रह्मवादिनि. Br. II. ३३. १९.--Pravara Angiras. M. १९६. १३.--a वर्ष of क्रौञ्चद्वीप. वा. ४९. ६७. [page२-446+ ३०]--Pravara (Angiras). M. १९६. १६.--an eastern country. Br. II. १६. ५४.--expiation: of no use to one not devoted to नारायण. भा. VI. 1. ११, १८.--vow of fasting unto death pratcised by परीक्षित् contemplating on विष्णु; {{F}}1:  भा I. १९. 7.{{/F}} undertaken by सुकर्मा when Indra killed his pupils. {{F}}2:  वा. ६१. २९. Br. II. ३५. ३४.{{/F}}--brought forth १० Deva-gandharvas, all best songsters. वा. ६८. ३७.(I)--an attendent of Hari; attacked the Asura followers of Bali. भा. II. 9. १४; VIII. २१. १६.(II)--a son of कृष्ण and माद्री. भा. X. ६१. १५.(I)--a queen of पुष्पार्ण, and mother of प्रात, माध्यन्दिन, and सायम्. भा. IV. १३. १३.(II)--a daughter of स्वर्भानु; wife of आयु and mother of नहुष and four others; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 6. २३-4; ६७. 1; M. 6. २१; वा. ६८. २२, २४; Vi. I. २१. 7.{{/F}} one of the nine Devis serving Soma; {{F}}2:  वा. ९०. २५.{{/F}} wife of स्वर्भानु. {{F}}3:  Ib. ९२. 1.{{/F}}(III)--one of the three wives of Vivasvat; {{F}}1:  M. ११. 2.{{/F}} mother of प्रभाता; the goddess enshrined in सूर्यबिम्ब; {{F}}2:  Ib. १३. ५२.{{/F}} abandoned her consort for Soma with eight other Devis. {{F}}3:  Ib. २३. २५.{{/F}} [page२-421+ २९](IV)--the wife of Sagara; यादवी and mother of ६०,000 Sagaras. M. १२. ३९, ४२.(I)--a son of ज्योतिष्मत् after whom the वर्ष was named. Br. II. १४. २८-29; वा. ३३. २४. Vi. II. 4. ३६.(II)--the father of Soma through मद्रा. Br. III. 8. ७६.(III)--one of the २० Sutapa गणस्. Br. IV. 1. १४; वा. १००. १४.(IV)--the Sun and consort of प्रभा who left him for Soma; image of; one wheel and seven horses; दण्डि and Pingala are the door-keepers; धाता with the pen in his hand; the charioteer, अरुण. M. २३. २५; २६१. 1-8.(V)--an आत्रेय; when सूर्य was beaten by स्वर्भानु and was falling down to the earth, the whole world became dark when the sage by his words was able to prevent his falling down and thus giving light in the place of darkness. वा. ७०. ७०-4; ९९. १२७.--a kingdom of कुशद्वीपम्. Br. II. १४. २९; १९. ५८; वा. ३३. २६; ४९. ५४.--a son of कृष्ण and सत्यभामा. भा. X. ६१. १०.(I)--a तीर्थ sacred to Hari and famous for the west flowing सरवती. {{F}}1:  भा. VII. १४. ३१; XI. ३०. 6; Br. III. १३. ४०; वा. २३. २१५; ७७. ४०.{{/F}} Sages of this place visited द्वा- रका. {{F}}2:  भा. X. ९०. २८ [5].{{/F}} During his pilgrimage tour Arjuna went to this; {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ८६. 2.{{/F}} was visited by बलराम and revisited by him; {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ७८. १८; ७९. २१.{{/F}} here the Moon God who was struck with consumption (यक्ष्म) by the curse of दक्ष got rid of his disease. {{F}}5:  Ib. XI. 6. ३५-8.{{/F}} Here सान्दिपानि's son was drowned, and Vidura cast off his body. {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ४५. ३७-8; III. 1. २०; I. १५. ४९; Vi. V. २१. २५.{{/F}} To this came once the वृष्णिस्, Bhojas, and Andhakas for sacred ablution when they had been cursed by some मुनिस्, and gave gifts of gold, silver and bed to Brahmanas. {{F}}7:  भा. III 3. २५-8.{{/F}} On कृष्ण's sugges- tion the Yadus left द्वारका for good and went to this place, where they drank heavily induced by कृष्ण, and fighting with one another, all of them died. {{F}}8:  Ib. XI. ३०. १०-19. Vi. V. ३७. ३०, ३८-9.{{/F}} Sacred to पुष्करावति {{F}}9:  M १३. ४३.{{/F}} the intervening space between the cheek and neck of the personified Veda. {{F}}१०:  वा. १०४. ७८.{{/F}}(II)--one of the twenty Sutapa गणस्. Br. IV. 1. १४; वा. १००. १५.(III)--Mt. covering the foot of the शिला of गयासुर; ety. that which shines bright; from the little finger of the शिला came out ईश; in गया. वा. १०८. १३-4; १०९. १४.(IV)--a Vasu; married the sister of बृहस्- pati. Father of विश्वकर्मन्. Vi. I. १५. ११०, ११८-19. [page२-423+ २७]--at sunset the rays of the sun enter fire and hence the latter is seen in the night; when the sun rises in the morning, fire enters the sun's rays and hence the light of fire is not seen in the day; when the sun is in the middle of the earth night enters the waters and hence they are of the copper colour. In the night day enters the waters and hence waters take the white colour. Thus अहोरात्रस् enter waters. वा. ५०. ११२-17.--is शिव, the God who came out as a little finger of the शिला at गया; by cutting through the प्रभास hill. वा. १०८. १४, २३.--the eighth Vasu who had for his wife Yogasiddhi (वरस्त्री) the sister of बृहस्पति; their son was विश्वकर्मन्; [see रामा; बाल्. खान्. २७-35 where he is named सावित्र]. Br. III. 3. २१; ५९. १६; M. 5. २१, २७; २०३. 4; वा. ६१. ८२; ६६. २०, २७-8; ८३. २०; ८४. १६. [page२-422+ ३७]--the performer of it becomes a राजराज. M. १०१. ५४.(I)--God of the wind; {{F}}1:  भा. II. २५. 7.{{/F}} narrator of the वायु पुराण। {{F}}2:  वा. 2. 2.{{/F}}(II)--a monkey chief. Br. III. 7. २३३.--a R. in the केतुमाला continent. वा. ४४. १८.(I)--a son of भृगु and a deva. ^1 Br. III. 1. ९०. ^2 M. १९५. १३.(II)--a साध्य. M. १७१. ४३; वा. ६६. १६.--a विश्वेदेव. वा. ६६. ३२.--is Lord शिव. वा. १०१. २९४.(I)--a son of Bhaga and Siddhi. भा. VI. १८. 2.(II)--a son of शुक and पीवरी; a साध्य. Br, III. 3. १७; 8. ९३; M. १५. १०; २०३. १२; वा. ७०. ८५; ७३. ३०.(III)--see Maru. Br. III. ६३. २११.(IV)--one of the अमिताभ gan2a. Br. IV. 1. १६; वा. १००. १६.--of the king. Br. II. २९. ८२; M. १४२. ६८; वा. ५७. ७५.--a मरीचि God. Br. IV. 1. ५८. [page२-424+ ३७]--a son of ऋषभ; a भागवत; advised Nimi how to get rid of the माया by means of going to a गुरु and following the path of devotion to Hari. भा. V. 4. ११; XI. 2. २१; 3. १८-33. [page२-420+ ३१]--a goddess enshrined at छागलाण्ड. M. १३. ४३.(I)--the son of Durdama; had a hundred sons who went to the North as lords of the म्लेच्छस्। {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २३. १५-16; Br. III. ७४. ११-12; वा. ९९. ११.{{/F}} Father of शतधर्म. {{F}}2:  Vi. IV. १७. 4-5.{{/F}} [page२-402+ २३](II) (प्रशान्ति): a name of शन्ति Agni. Br. II. १२. २९; वा. २९. २७.(III)--a मन्त्रकृत्; see Cyavana. Br. II. ३२. १०४; III. 1. ९२; वा. ६५. ५४, ८८.(IV)--a पारावत god. Br. II. ३६. १३. वा. ६२. १२.(V)--a god of प्रसूत group. Br. II. ३६. ७०.(VI)--a god of the Lekha group. Br. II. ३६. ७५.(VII)--one of the Mind-born sons of ब्रह्मा; a मन्त्रकृत्. M. 3. 7; १०२. १९; १४५. ९८; वा. ५९. ९६.(VIII)--the son of विदुष; had १०० sons, all chieftains of the म्लेच्छ countries of the northern regions. M. ४८. 8-9.(IX)--the father of the यक्षस्. वा. ६९. ११.--a प्रजेश्वर. Br. III. 1. ५४.--the collective name of the ten sons of प्राचीनबर्हिष and सामुद्री; commanded by their father they engaged themselves in penance in the [page२-403+ ३६] midst of the ocean and meditated on the teachings of शिव given to them; leaving their home they proceeded to the west and in a park near a great lake heard the divine music; when listening to it, there appeared शिव who on request initiated them in the meditation on विष्णु (रुद्रगीता); when शिव left they meditated under the waters for १००० years. विष्णु appeared before them and promised them a son by asking them to marry the daughter of कण्डु and प्रम्लोचा; pleased with seeing the God they praised Him; after his disappearance they came out of the waters and seeing the earth filled with wild growth they began to burn the trees by breathing spiritual fire and wind from their mouth. ब्रह्मा (Soma) interceded then and prevented them from further destroying the trees by offering वार्क्षि (मारिषा) the daughter of the trees in marriage to them; they married her and she gave birth to दक्ष on the eve of the चाक्षुष epoch. {{F}}1:  भा. IV. २४ (whole); २५. 1-2; ३० (whole) VI. 4. 4-१७; Br. II. १३. ४०; ३७. २७; M. 4. ४७-9; वा. ६३. २७-9.{{/F}} After a long period of enjoyment of life they placed their wife under their son दक्ष and went away to the western sea where Jajali attained siddhi; seeing them steadfast in devotion नारद came there, and was welcom- ed by them; requested by them to be instructed to get rid of सम्सार, नारद advised them to worship and contemplate on विष्णु directly, and than departed; they did so and attain- ed the world of विष्णु; {{F}}2:  भा. IV. ३१. 1-२५.{{/F}} sacrifice of, when नारद sang praises of Dhruva; {{F}}3:  Ib. IV. १२. ४०; १३. 2.{{/F}} worshipped for treasure. {{F}}4:  Ib. II. 3. 7.{{/F}}--the son of Janamejaya and father of Pra- वीर. Vi. IV. १९. 1.--a measurement; ten अन्गुलस् in length. वा. 8. १०२.--the index finger used for measuring अन्गुलस्। वा. 8. १०३.--an अनन्त and अव्ययात्म; covers the महत्। Br. II. २१. २८; III. ४३. 4; IV. 4. १२ and २०. [page२-419+ २६]--(माया-वा। प्।) a term for प्रकृति; with विकार results in महत्-तत्वम्। Br. I. 1. ८८ and ९३; 3. 9; 5. १०३; वा. १०३. १२, २१, ३६. M. 3. १५, १७; ६०. 3; वा. 4. १९; २३. ५६; २४. ६६. Vi. I. 2. १५-16.and सत्व; प्रधान appears at the time of creation from सदसदात्मकम्. Br. I. 4. 1; वा. 5. 7-8, २२.--a name of ललिता. Br. IV. १७. ३३.--a son of दोष and पुष्पार्ण. भा. IV. १३. १४.--a शक्ति on the सोडशपत्राब्जा. Br. IV. ३२. १२.(I)--a son of शुनक, the minister of पुरञ्- jaya; when पुरञ्जय was killed by शुनक, Pradyota became king; father of पालक; founder of the line of Pra- dyotanas, five in number and who ruled for १३८ years. भा. XII. 1. 3-4.(II)--a यक्ष; a son of पुण्यजनि and मणि- bhadra. Br. III. 7. १२४; वा. ६९. १५६.(III)--the son of Munika, killed his master Ripumjaya and ruled for २३ years; a प्रणतसामन्त, his four successors ruled for १३८ years; शिशुनाक slew him and became king. Father of बलाक. वा. ९९. ३१०-4; Vi. IV. २४. 2-3.--five beginning with Pradyota and end- ing-with Nandivardhana: they ruled the earth for १३८ years. भा. XII. 1. 4.--ruled for २३ years with the सामन्तस् sub- dued. Br. III. ७४. १२३.(I)--the eldest son of कृष्ण by रुक्मिनी; in his previous birth the God of Love (काम, Smara); {{F}}1:  Vi. IV. १५. ३७; V. २६. १२ to the end; ch. २७ (whole); २८. 6-7; ३२. 1 and 6; भा. I. १०. २९; ११. १७; १४. ३०; X. ४०. २१; ६१. 7 and 9; ९०. ३५; Br. III. ७१. २४५; ७२. 1; IV. २९. १२८; वा. ९६. २३७.{{/F}} within ten days of his birth शम्बर stole him and threw the babe into the sea; was swallowed by a fish; fishermen who caught the fish presented it to शम्बर who asked the cooks to cook it; when cut open there was the child inside and नारद asked मायावती in charge of the kitchen to take care of the child after telling her the truth about it; that it was the re-incarnation of her husband काम; she brought up the child more as a lover; asked by Pradyumna why she was not behaving as a mother but as a wife she explained that she was रती and himself काम, and also as to how he came there by शम्बर's act; taught मायावती the विद्या of [page२-417+ ४६] महामाया: he invited शम्बर to battle and cut off his head; then मायावती took him by air to द्वारका the resi- dence of रुक्मिणी and कृष्ण; in कृष्ण's palace, women found the likeness of कृष्ण in him and रुक्मिनी thought of her lost son; to their wonder and joy नारद related the life story of Pradyumna; the couple were embraced by all of them and the whole द्वारका was filled with satisfaction. {{F}}2:  भा. X. ch. ५५ (whole); M. ४७. १५, २३; ९३. ५१; १०१; १०; २४८. ४८.{{/F}} Won his wife रुक्मावती (वैदर्भी) in a स्वयम्वर after vanquishing his rivals; father of Aniruddha; {{F}}3:  भा. X. ६१. १८, २२, २३ [8]; ९०. ३६. Vi. IV. १५. ३९.{{/F}} attended his son's marriage at भोजकट; {{F}}4:  भा. X. ६१. २६.{{/F}} Picture drawn by Citra- lekha; {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ६२. २०; Vi. V. ३२. २४.{{/F}} one among the वृष्णिस् who went to attack बाण's city; {{F}}6:  भा. X. ६३. 3.{{/F}} fought with Guha; {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ६३. 7.{{/F}} went along with his brothers to play and seeing a huge lizard in a well reported the same to कृष्ण; {{F}}8:  Ib. X. ६४. 1-4.{{/F}} defended द्वारका with other Yadus when शाल्व besieged it; defeated शाल्व's commander-in-chief and did other feats of valour; had a hit in the chest by शाल्व's minis- ter Dyumat and was taken out by his charioteer, whom he chided for his action; the charioteer defended his action under the ethics of war; attacked and vanquished Dyumat; {{F}}9:  Ib. X. ७६. १३-33. ७७. 1-3.{{/F}} went to स्यमन्तपञ्चक for the solar eclipse; {{F}}१०:  Ib. X. ८२. 6.{{/F}} went with कृष्ण's sacrificial horse; {{F}}११:  Ib. X. ८९. २२. [2].{{/F}} unable to recover the dead son of the द्वारका Brahmana; {{F}}१२:  Ib. X. ८९. ३१ and ४१; ९०. ३३.{{/F}} fought with साम्ब at प्रभास deluded by कृष्ण; {{F}}१३:  Ib. XI. ३०. १६.{{/F}} at his death his wives burnt themselves in fire. ^१४ Ib. X. ३१. २०; Vi. V. ३३. १२; ३७. ४६.(II)--a son of चाक्षुष Manu. भा. IV. १३. 16(III)--a son of भानुमान्. Br. III. ६४. १९; व