 by कृष्ण who took her away by force and married her, as her brothers wanted to bestow [page३-069+ ३२] her on Duryodhana; {{F}}2:  भा. X. ५८. ३१.{{/F}} according to the भागवत had two sons Vinda and Anuvinda; {{F}}3:  वा. ९६. १४९.{{/F}} mother of two sons. {{F}}4:  Vi. IV. १४. ४३.{{/F}}--a son of शम्भु. Br. III. 5. ४०.--the first kings of the earth were Priyavrata and उत्तानपाद, sons of Manu; wielders of दण्ड; ety. of. वा. ५७. ५८.--police officials; {{F}}1:  वा. १०१. १५४.{{/F}} go to hell. {{F}}2:  Br. IV. 2. १५५.{{/F}}--also क्षत्रधर्म; no sin to kill one in war. M. १०३. २२.--the capital of Malla whom कृष्ण van- quished; the palace of. Br. III. ७३. १००; IV. १४. ११.--a sacred place in कीकट. वा. १०८. ७३.--son of विशाखयूप, and father of Nandivar- dhana, the Magadha king. भा. XII. 1. 3-4.--a sage. M. १९६. २६.--to punish evil doers and to protect the law abiding. M. २११. 9.(also राजपथस्)--royal roads as fre- quented by पिशाचस्; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 7. ४०४; २७. ११.{{/F}} in the city of श्रीपुरम्; {{F}}2:  M. १३०. 3.{{/F}} in the city of मथुरा; {{F}}3:  Vi. V. १९. १२.{{/F}} lighted by lamps during nights; {{F}}4:  M. १३९. १९.{{/F}} persons commit- ting nuisance in public roads were visited by fines and required to clean them. {{F}}5:  Ib. २२७. १७५.{{/F}}--unfit for श्राद्ध. Vi. III. १६. 7.--ety. दण्डधारिन्; crimes escaping his notice are dealt with by Yama. In Kali the king is mostly of the fourth caste and takes the profession of robbery rather than protection. Earth loses its fertility. The wealth and wives of others are coveted; म्लेच्छस् are patronised. Duties-- salutation to cows and Brahmanas, sandhya worship and gifts to the deserving; not to deprive forcibly a Brahmana of his property; {{F}}1:  Br. II. २९. ६३-64; ३१. ४१-156; ३६. १५६; III. २८. १०-74.{{/F}} renowned kings get the title of राजऋषि, gene- rally of the family of Manu, Aila, इक्ष्वाकु. {{F}}2:  Ib. II. ३५. ९०, ९६-102; III. ७१. १९४.{{/F}}--six-fold; learnt by राम and कृष्ण. भा. X. ४५. ३४.--१० dhanus broad; permits of easy move- ment for men, horses, chariots and elephants. वा. 8. ११९.(I)--a name of Budha, the son of राजसोम and the originator of the science of elephantology. M. २४. 3.(II)--prince; special teachers are to be appointed to teach him Dharma, Artha and काम s4a1stras, to train him in elephant riding, chariot riding, and in arts and crafts; he must have his bodyguard so that he may not mix with the undesirables and may control his senses; he [page३-065+ ३५] must live in a private residence, for an ill-disciplined prince will root out the family. {{F}}1:  M. २२०. 1-6{{/F}} A possible internal enemy of the king. {{F}}2:  Ib. २२३. 9.{{/F}}--a work on elephantology by the sage राजपुत्र, identified with Budha. M. २४. 3.--the giver of gift; kalpa tree becomes so in the next birth; {{F}}1:  M. १०१. ३०, ५४, ७१; २७७. २१.{{/F}} for the gift of gosahasra. {{F}}2:  Ib. २७८. २५.{{/F}}--the abode of Kubera. M. ८३. ४५.--the special title awarded by ब्रह्मा to Soma. Br. III. ६५. २०; वा. ९०. २०.--devices for the protection of the king's person; different kinds of mixtures of medicines used for १५ days, one month, etc.; remedies to avert houses being consumed by fire; against snakes by burning their coating; examination of cooked food by giving it to birds or throw- ing it into the fire and then examining the change in colour; [page३-066+ २७] flies would not sit on the poisoned food; its effect on birds and beasts; the same is applicable to drinking water; such protection needed since he is the root of the tree of the people. M. २१९. 1-३४.--a title of पुरूरवस्, ययाति and कार्तवीर्य; {{F}}1:  M. १३. ६२; ४३. २३; वा. ९६. १९०.{{/F}} attained by शमिक. {{F}}2:  M. ४६. २८.{{/F}} For some more names see वा। प्। {{F}}3:  वा. ३२, ३८, ५४; ६१. ८०, ८६-88; ९९. १५, १२७.{{/F}}--otherwise known as केतुमान्, a लोकपाल; {{F}}1:  Br. II. २१. १५७; M. १२४. ९५.{{/F}} attained heaven by तपस्। {{F}}2:  Ib. १४३. ३८.{{/F}}--for wrong entry in, punished with uttama दण्ड. M. २२७. २०२. [page३-067+ ३४]--also प्रजाकरी; this quality possessed by मरीचि Kas4yapa. वा. ६६. ८७, १०४, १०५.--intervening both satva and tama; leads to karma and rebirth and hence duhkha or misery due to ear, eye, tongue, body and smell. वा. १०२. ५४, ६२.--a king of Vidarbha. His daughter was married to Malayadhvaja पाण्ड्य. भा. IV. २८. २८-29.(I)--the conqueror of cardinal points was fit to perform this: युधिष्ठीर on this, to कृष्ण: Done by Soma who conquered the three worlds; {{F}}1:  भा. X. ७१. 2[1]; ७२-3; IX. १४. 4; वा. ९०. २२.{{/F}} युधिष्ठिर's desire to be a पारमेष्ठी. So ऋत्विक्स् were sent for, including भीष्म, Vidura. Even शूद्रस् were invited. After the sacrifice, on the suggestion of Sahadeva, the first honour was given to कृष्ण. शिशुपाल's protest and vilification of कृष्ण who had his head cut off. In the sacrifice each brother was assigned specific functions--Duryodhana in charge of treasury, भीम cooking, Nakula the supply of provisions, etc. The अवभृत bath at गन्गा accompanied by divine music. Every visitor duly honoured, returned back. Jealousy of Duryodhana at the success of the sacrifice. {{F}}2:  भा. VII. 1. १३;; X. ७०. ४१; Chh. ७४-75.{{/F}} The consecration ceremony of a king done by पृथु, वालि and others. {{F}}3:  Br. II. ३६. ११३; III. 7. २६८; 8. २५; ६३. ११६; ७२. २८; वा. ६२. ९५; ७०. २१.{{/F}} [page३-068+ ३४](II)--the head of the Veda. वा. ७१. ७७; ८८. ११८. Ib. १०४. ८४; ११२. ६३.(III)--the fifth गान्धार gra1mika. वा. ८६. ४२.--the gift of ब्रह्माण्ड पुराण equal to the performance of १००० sacrifices. {{F}}1:  M. ५३. ५७.{{/F}} The fruits of this यज्ञ are equal to fasting and praying to विष्णु on the अक्षयतृतीय day; {{F}}2:  Ib. ६५. 7.{{/F}} a plunge in the प्रयागा is equal to this यज्ञ। {{F}}3:  Ib. १०६. २१.{{/F}} Sacrifice performed by Soma when विष्णु was ब्रह्मा, शिव, the protector, Atri, the hota, भृगु, the अध्वर्यु, ब्रह्मा, the उद्गात, Sanaka and others were the Sadasyas, ten विश्वेदेवस् Camasa1dhvaryavas, and the three worlds दक्षिण; after this sacrifice the nine देवीस्, लक्ष्मी, सिनिवाली, कीर्ती, Vasu, धृती and others left their husbands and sported with Soma who acted as their consort; {{F}}4:  Ib. २३. १९-27; ५८. ५४; २३९. ३७; Vi. IV. 6. 8.{{/F}} the title of Soma after the राजसूय. {{F}}5:  वा. ९०. २६.{{/F}}--a दान; also रौप्याचलम्; the best gift is of १०,000 palams of silver; the giver goes to the world of the moon; then of 5,००० and then 2,५०० palams; anything above २० palams. M. ८३. 6; ९१. 1ff. [page३-064+ ३३]--the silver vessel used by पितृस् in milking the cow-earth; {{F}}1:  M. १०. १८.{{/F}} out of शिव's eye; {{F}}2:  Ib. १५. ३१; १७. २०. २३.{{/F}} best for use in श्राद्ध. {{F}}3:  वा. ७३. ५१; ७४. 1.{{/F}}--son of Dyutimat. Vi. I. १०. 5.--son of Dama, and father of Suvrddhi. Vi. IV. 1. ३६-7.--a कश्यप and a त्रयार्षेय. M. १९९. १२.--sacred to ललितापीठ. Br. IV. ४४. ९६.--followed by robbers as the kings themselves begin to rob in the Kali age. वा. ५८. ४२.--smitten by this, Soma was relieved by his father, Atri. Br. III. ६५. ४६-8.--to be worshipped in house-building. M. २५३. ३०, ४२; २६८. २३.--the collective name for the hundred sons of Raji; the latter won over the Asuras and finally established Indra on the throne and retired for penance; his sons deprived Indra of his power when the latter appealed to बृहस्पति; he increased Indra's strength by rituals and made the राजेयस् adopt the जीनधर्म and hence got outside the pale of the Veda, when Indra easily overcame them and got back his kingdom; beginning of जीन dharma and hetu- वाद. M. २४. ३५-49.--a Janapada of the केतुमाला continent. वा. ४४. १४.--a horse of the moon's chariot. वा. ५२. ५३.--a pupil of कृत. Br. II. ३५. ५१; Vi. ६१. ४४.--one of the three wives of विवस्वान्; she was the daughter of Raivata and had a son Revata. M. ११. 2-3.--son of भजमान. वा. ९६. १३५.--a kingdom; if a king has no legitimate suc- cessor, it changes hands; ruled by ministry in the king's absence; is concerned with two main things (बाह्य) or foreign affairs and (abhyantara) or home policy; {{F}}1:  Br. III. ५०. २९-51; वा. ८८. ९४; ११२. १४. ४६.{{/F}} of पृथु, described. {{F}}2:  M. 1. ११; १०. १०-35.{{/F}} [page३-070+ २८]--son of Dama, and father of सुधृति. भा. IX. 2. २९; Br. III. 8. ३५.(I)--a daughter of Angiras and स्म्र्ती; wife of धात्रि, and mother of प्रातस्; {{F}}1:  भा. IV. 1. ३४; VI. १८. 3; वा. २८. १५; Vi. I. १०. 7.{{/F}} a शक्ति. {{F}}2:  Br. IV. ३२. १२.{{/F}}(II)--a R. in शाल्मलिद्वीप. भा. V. २०. १०.(IV)--Two lavas of the afternoon of Pratipada. M. १३३. ३६; १४१. ३३, ४१, ५१. [page३-061+ ३७](III)--the full moon shining resplendent and much pleasing to the eye; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ११. १८; २८. ३८, ४६ and ६०; वा. ५०. २०१; ५६. ३५, ४१ and ५५.{{/F}} a day fit for giving gifts; {{F}}2:  Vi. II. 8. ८०.{{/F}} ety. of. {{F}}3:  वा. ५६. ४१.{{/F}}(I)--Balabhadra of the यादव race and lord of द्वारका. (बलराम): brother of कृष्ण and सुभद्रा; See Baladeva; eldest son of Vasudeva by रोहिनी; father of two sons; welcomed कृष्ण to द्वारका; asked by कृष्ण to take one of the two heavenly chariots and get ready to fight जरासन्ध. राम blew his conch and began fighting [page३-072+ ४४] under his palmyra ensign; defeated the enemies on all sides. Fastened जरासन्ध with ropes but कृष्ण set him free; when जरासन्ध encamped on the यमुना, was consulted by कृष्ण; fought successfully जरासन्ध a third time and defeated बाण's army; when about to give a death-blow to जरासन्ध, a voice from the welkin said “do not kill जरासन्ध; go back.” Thus जरासन्ध was allowed to go back to his city. {{F}}1:  भा. I. ११. १६; X. ५०. १२-32; [५० (v)  8]; [५१ (v)  ३८-58]; [५२ (v) 1-6]; Br. III. ६१. २५; ७१. १६४-8; M. ४६. ११; वा. ८६. ३०; ९६. १६२; Vi. V. 6. 9; १३. १६.{{/F}} Honoured by the याधव sabha, went with कृष्ण to the Gomanta hill; on the way met and bowed to परशुराम; helped कृष्ण in killing शृगाल Vas4udeva and was welcomed by the citizens of करवीरपुर. Stayed in this city for four months and returned to मथुरा with his brother. Attacked by जरासन्ध's army, fled with कृष्ण to Gomanta, pursued by जरासन्ध; reached द्वारका safe. {{F}}2:  भा. X. [५२ (v)  १३-41]; [५३(v) 1-२२]; ५२. 5-6 [5-7]; 7. १४ [1 and 2].{{/F}} Married रेवती before the advent of Kali and hence very tall in appearance; with his plough he brought down her height to his level. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ५२. १५ [११-12].{{/F}} Heard of कृष्ण going alone to कुण्डिन and of the pre- parations of Caidya to fight him; went with his army to कुण्डिन and was welcomed by its king: Attacked Caidya's party pursuing कृष्ण and रुक्मिणी on that account. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ५३. २०-21 and ३२; Ch. ५४ (whole).{{/F}} Went to हास्तिनपुर with कृष्ण after the reported burning of the पाण्डवस् and कुन्ती: Pursued शतधन्वन् with कृष्ण and finding he had not the स्यमन्त in his person, sent कृष्ण back to द्वारका and himself to मिथिला as Janaka's guest; taught the use of the गदा (mace) to Duryodhana. Did not agree with कृष्ण in returning the jewel to अक्रूर. Left for Videha after Satadhanvan's death. {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ५७ (whole) ; ५८. 9 [4 and 5]; ६७ (v) ४२.{{/F}} Attended Aniruddha's marriage at भोजकट where induced by Kalinga and other friends, Rukmin invited राम for a game of dice: in it, राम sometimes lost and sometimes gained. At his loss Kalinga laughed showing his teeth. When Rukmin played false it was referred to [page३-073+ ३८] a mediator who was unfortunately Kalinga and who there- fore maintained that Rukmi was in the right. A voice from the air said: “Rukmi tells an untruth”. Without heeding to this Rukmi insulted राम as a forester and herdsman and new to the art of dice. राम got enraged, took the mace and vanquished Rukmi: next he pulled out the teeth of Kalinga making fun of him all the time: others fled in fear; returned to द्वारका. {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ६१. २६-40.{{/F}} His picture was among those drawn by चित्रालेखा: In- vaded बाण's city, fought with कुम्भाण्ड and कूप- कर्ण. Once drove to Vraja and spent two months there. During nights he sported and sang with Gopis on the यमुना drinking वारुणी and playing in the waters: changed the course of the river by his plough: {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ६२. २०; ६३. 3-8.{{/F}} यमुना (s.v.) presented him with clothes, and ornaments with which he shone brighter than ever. {{F}}8:  Ib. X. Ch. ६५ (whole).{{/F}} Desire for more territory. {{F}}9:  Ib. XII. 3. 9.{{/F}} Wanted to give सुभद्रा in marriage to Duryodhana but कृष्ण was for her marriage with Arjuna. The latter went to द्वारका as an ascetic when राम one day invited him for भिक्ष। It was an opportunity for Arjuna and सुभद्रा to see each other. Arjuna carried her away on a festive occasion with कृष्ण's consent. राम's wrath was pacified by कृष्ण. Then he approved of the marriage and sent him presents. {{F}}१०:  Ib. X. ८६. 1-१२, १८.{{/F}} Unable to recover the dead son of the द्वा- रका Bra1hman2a. {{F}}११:  Ib. X. ८९, ३१ and ४१.{{/F}} Founded the city of Govardhana on the upper regions of the गोदावरी in the northern part of the Sahya mountain. {{F}}१२:  Br. II. १६. ४४.{{/F}} The God of Love cursed to be born as the brother of कृष्ण at द्वारका. {{F}}१३:  M. 4. १७-21.{{/F}} [page३-074+ ४७](II)--a son of दशरथ known for his righteous- ness and truth: परिक्षित् compared to him: An अवतार् of Hari born in the इक्ष्वाकु line; killed रावण; His fame equalled that of पृथु. {{F}}1:  भा. I. १२. १९; II. 7. २३-25; IV. २२. ६३; IX. १०. 3; M. १२. ५०-51.{{/F}} King of the कोशल country and brother of लक्ष्मण, Bharata, and शत्रुघ्न: Disfigured सूर्पणका; killed मारीच (सुबाहु?) and other राक्षसस् in the यज्ञ of विश्वामित्र, bent and broke the bow of शिव and married सीता, put down the pride of परशुराम, spent a forest life with his wife in obedience to his father's command, killed Khara, त्रिशिरस् and १४,000 राक्षसस्; performed the funeral rites to जटायु, and Kabandha, killed वालि for the sake of सुग्रीव, put up a bridge across the sea, welcomed by the Lord of the seas; killed रावण and कुम्भकर्ण in their capital, ordered विभीषण to perform funeral rites to his dead kith and kin; recovered सीता; enthroned विभी- षण; left in an aerial chariot to अयोध्या, embraced Bharata, paid respects to Brahmanas, Gurus, elders and was crowned by वसिष्ठ just like Indra. In his period which was the त्रेतायुग, it looked like कृतयुग; sons, कुश and Lava; ruled for १०१० years; {{F}}2:  भा. V. १९. 1; VII. 1. ४४; १०. ३६; IX. १०. 3-५२; X. ४०. २०; XI. 4. २१; Br. III. 7. २०३; 8. ५४; ३७. ३०; ६३. १८५-193; ६४. १६; ७३. ९१; वा. ८८. १९२-4; Vi. IV. 4. ८७-102, १०४.{{/F}} led an exemplary household life, by his loyalty to his wedded wife; performed sacrifices by giv- ing all his kingdom as दक्षिण, retaining only the ornaments and dress, and for सीता, her सौमान्गल्य। The Brahmanas returned the kingdom as they had no use for it and praised him. {{F}}3:  भा. IX. १०. ५३-6; ११. 1-7; वा. ७०. ४८; ८८, १८४, १९१-7.{{/F}} One night he went about to know what people talked of his rule. He heard a person saying that राम was mad after सीता, taking her back though she was at another's house for long. Next day he abandoned her and left her at वाल्- मीकि's abode. Here were born his two sons--कुश and Lava. When सीता entered the bowels of the earth, राम led a life of celibacy for १३,000 years giving joy and happiness to the people of कोशल. Sent his brothers on दिग्विजय and him- self resided at the capital. {{F}}4:  भा. IX. ११. 8-३५.{{/F}} Hearing of the रामचरित of वाल्- मीकि, rids one of कर्मबन्धस्; {{F}}5:  Ib. IX. ११. २३; M. १२. ५०-51.{{/F}} resided on the banks of the कदली river; {{F}}6:  Ib. २२. ५३.{{/F}} the २४थ् in the त्रेतायुग; 7th incarnation [page३-075+ ४१] with वसिष्ठ as Purohita; {{F}}7:  Ib. ४७. २४५; ११४. ३८; वा. ९८. ९२; १०८. १६, २४-5.{{/F}} image of, generally ten तलस् in measurement; {{F}}8:  M. २५९. 1.{{/F}} an earthly paradise created by राम in the upper regions of गोदावरी in Govardhana; {{F}}9:  वा. ४५. ११३.{{/F}} performed श्राद्- dha at Rudrapada and दशरथ took the पिण्ड and went to Rudraloka blessing his son to go to विष्णुलोक; {{F}}१०:  Ib. १११, ६४.{{/F}} an incarna- tion of नारायण. {{F}}११:  Vi. IV. १३. ५३.{{/F}}(III) (परशुराम)--a son of Jamadagni and रेणुका; an अम्श of Hari. Heard from his father that Arjuna-Haihaya had taken कामधेनु against his wish, and getting angry went to Haihaya's capital, cut off the king's head and took back the cow. In order to get rid of the sin of killing a king, he went on तीर्थयात्र for a year. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. १५. १३ to the end. Br. III. 1. ९८; ६६. ६३; ६९. ४८; M. ४३. ४०; २८५. 7.{{/F}} In obedience to his father's command he killed his mother and brothers. This pleased the father and by his boon to his son, they all came back to life. During his absence, the sons of Haihaya killed his father, and on his return, found his mother crying over the death of Jamadagni. He took his axe, ran to माहिष्मती, rooted out all the क्षत्रियस् by defeating them twenty-one times; with their blood he made nine pools at स्यमन्तपञ्चक, where he worshipped his father's dead body and distributed the various regions to the priests; ended it with अवभृत in the सरस्वती। {{F}}2:  भा. IX. १६. 1-२३; M. २७३. ६६.{{/F}} He would be a great sage in the forthcoming मन्वन्तर। A sage of the 8th मन्वन्तर। Even today resides in Mahen- dra contemplating on Hari; {{F}}3:  भा. VIII. १३. १५; IX. १६. २५-7.{{/F}} was invited for the राजसूय of युधिष्ठिर and came to see कृष्ण at स्यमन्तपञ्चक. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ७४. 9; ८४. 4.{{/F}} In his early years, with the leave of his parents, he visited his grand parents ऋचीक and सत्यवती; and after some stay there, called on his great grandfather भृगु, who advised [page३-076+ ३४] him to do तपस् in the हिमालयस् in honour of शिव. Engaged in तपस् by standing in water in the winter and on the fire in summer, by means of पद्मासन; शिव in hunter's guise visited him and asked him to quit his place. Suspecting him to be god, राम, appealed to him when शिव showed his true form. Instructed by शिव, he went round the earth on a pilgrimage tour. Helped the Devas in routing the Asuras; continued his तपस् by worshipping शिव as मृग- व्याध. Pleased, the Lord instructed him in the अस्त्र- ग्राम in its four aspects; went to ब्रह्मा for advice before he started on his crusade against the क्षत्रियस्. Advised to meet शिव and to get initiated into कृष्णमन्त्र कवचम्; शिव instructed him with त्रैलोक्य विजयम् मन्त्रम्। On his way back he stayed at पुष्कर and heard a male deer narrating the story of परशुराम and अकृतव्रण to the female deer, adding that his was not the उत्तम भक्ति but the मध्यम। He took the hint from that conversation that he would achieve his end by Agastya's grace. राम repaired to the hermitage of Agastya, followed by the deer. {{F}}5:  Br. III. Chh. २१-35.{{/F}} मूलक afraid of; {{F}}6:  Ib. III. ६३. १७९; ७४. २६२.{{/F}} a ब्राह्मण; {{F}}7:  वा. ९४. ४६; ९९. ४४९.{{/F}} a slayer of the क्षत्रियस्; versed in Dhanurveda; {{F}}8:  Ib. ९१. ९१.{{/F}} equal in prowess to Indra resplend- ent and a mixture of Brahma and क्षत्र; {{F}}9:  Ib. ६५. ९४.{{/F}} consort धरनी. {{F}}१०:  Vi. I. 9. १४३.{{/F}}(IV)--a son of शिवदत्त. Br. III. ३५. १२.(V)--a sage of the सावर्णि epoch. (eighth epoch वि। प्।). M. 9. ३२; Vi. III. 2. १७. [page३-077+ ३१](VI)--son of सेनाजित्. वा. ९९. १७३.--son of Puramjaya; and father of Dhar- मवर्मा. Vi. IV. २४. ५६.--the nineteenth अवतार् of Hari born among the वृष्णिस्. भा. I. 3. २३.--a son of सारण. वा. ९६. १६५.--a northern tribe. M. ११४. ४२.--a R.; the महानदी touching the hill of प्रभास where राम bathed with his wife; all sins com- mitted in a hundred generations vanish as a result of a bath in this तीर्थ; {{F}}1:  वा. १०८. १६-18.{{/F}} the मन्त्र for bathing in; {{F}}2:  Ib. १०८. २०.{{/F}} sacred to रमना and the पितृस् {{F}}3:  M. १३. ४०; २२. ७०.{{/F}} in अयोध्या. {{F}}4:  Ib. १९१. ९३.{{/F}}--is कृष्ण. Br. III. ३३. १२.--a तीर्थ sacred to पितृस्; one visiting it after bath at गया has no rebirth. वा. १०८. २७.--narrated by वाल्मीकि; originally nar- rated by ब्रह्मा in a hundred crore of verses to नारद who gave it to वाल्मीकि. M. ५३. ७१-2. [page३-078+ ४१]--a composer of साम Veda; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३५. ४४.{{/F}} a Kauthuka and a disciple of लोकाक्षि. {{F}}2:  वा. ६१. ३७-39.{{/F}}--is कृष्ण. Br. III. ३३. २१.--created by ब्रह्मा from his feet. Vi. I. 5. ४९.(also रासगोष्ठि)--in this was seen the same कृष्ण between every two गोपीस्, his hands over the shoulder of each गोपी engaged in dancing and singing, until all of them were tired. भा. X. Ch. २९ (whole); ३३. 2-२२; ३९. २९; ४७. ४३ and ६०, ६२.--three-fold, as ब्रह्मा, Rudra and विष्णु; (four- fold, according to another reading; see Wilson's translation). Vi. VI. 8. 7.--son of काशि (काशेय वि। प्।) and father of दीर्- ghatamas (tapas वि। प्।). भा. IX. १७. 4; Vi. IV. 8. 7.--a son of Bharata. भा. V. 7. 3.--one of the nine sons of Ugrasena. भा. IX. २४. २४; Br. III. ७१. १३३; M. ४४. ७५; वा. ९६. १३२; Vi. IV. १४. २०. [page३-079+ २८]--a daughter of Ugrasena, and wife of सृञ्जय. भा. IX. २४. २५ and ४२; Br. III. ७१. १३४; M. ४४. ७६; वा. ९६. १३३; Vi. IV. १४. २१.--an आर्षेयप्रवर (अङ्गिरस्). M. १९६. २१.--son of Dama. Br. III. ६१. 8.--the 4th kalpa. M. २९०. 3.(I)--a R. in क्रौञ्चद्वीप. Br. II. १९. ७५; M. १२२. ८८; वा. ४९. ६९; Vi. II. 4. ५५.(II)--a शक्ति. Br. IV. ४४. ७५.(III)--पारमेश्वर; pralaya or destruction at the end of which recurs the creation of the universe. वा. 5. 2 and 6.(IV)--when the Asuras were born to प्रजापति night came into being; ety.; three यामस् of the night are full of darkness--त्रियामिका; then प्रजापति took another guise and created the devas; आसुरि of tamas quality; {{F}}1:  वा. 9. 6-१५; Br. II. १३. १४.{{/F}} no [page३-071+ ३०] night for the region to the north of Meru and south of लोका- loka as the sun is far removed and the earth is surrounded by the lekha; {{F}}2:  वा. ५०. १०८.{{/F}}  for the पितृस् is सुक्लपक्ष; {{F}}3:  Ib. ५१. ११; ५७. 9.{{/F}} enters water in the morning. {{F}}4:  Ib. ५३. १४.{{/F}}--a मन्त्र of the ऋग् Vedins to be recited in tank ritual. M. ५८. ३४; ९३. १३१.--a son of विश्रवस् and केशिनी; {{F}}1:  भा. VII. 1. ४३; IV. 1. ३७; Br. III. 8. ४७; वा. ७०. ४१-8.{{/F}} pleased शिव by his praises; {{F}}2:  भा. X. ८८. १६.{{/F}} afraid of मान्धात; {{F}}3:  Ib. IX. 6. ३३.{{/F}} heard of शीता's beauty and set up मारीच to display himself as a golden deer and entice राम away; {{F}}4:  Ib. IX. १०. १०{{/F}} resented Arjuna-Haihaya's action in ruining his camp by blocking a river and was overpowered by him in the presence of women and imprisoned in his capital माहिष्मती; {{F}}5:  Ib. IX. १५. २१-2; Br. III. ३२. ५०; ६९. ३५-7.{{/F}} pursued by the king of kites, compared to Indra being pursued by वीर; {{F}}6:  भा. IV. १९. १६-17.{{/F}} killed by राम; {{F}}7:  Ib. VII. 1. ४४; १०. ३६; X. ४०. २०; Br. III. 8. ५४; M. १२. ५०; ४७. २४५; वा. ८८. १९७; ९४. ३५; ९८. ९२.{{/F}} lost his king- dom through pride of power; desire for more territory. {{F}}8:  भा. X. ७३. २०; XII. 3. ११.{{/F}} Vanquished by वालि at पुष्कर, agreed to be his ally. {{F}}9:  Br. III. 7. २४८-67.{{/F}} A description of: {{F}}१०:  Ib. III. 8. ४८-50.{{/F}} Killed अनरण्य; {{F}}११:  Ib. III. ६३. ७४; वा. ८८. ७५; Vi. IV. 3. १७; १५. 1.{{/F}} also दशग्रीव; defeated by कार्तवीर्य and released at the request of Pulastya. {{F}}१२:  M. ४३. ३७-9.{{/F}}--a तीर्थ on the नर्मदा. M. १९१. २६.--a form of marriage by which कृष्ण married रुक्मिणी. But Rukmi objected to this form of marriage. भा. X. ५२. १८ and ४१; ५४. १८; Vi. III. १०. २४.--a son of जाम्बवन्. Br. III. 7. ३०३.--eight in number: perhaps the seven daughters of खश and नीला; create fear and disease among children (human beings- वा। प्।). Br. III. 7. १५६-61; वा. ६९. १८८.(I)--see रक्षस्: semi-divine beings; {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 8. २४; Br. II. ३२. 1 and 2; ३५. १९१.{{/F}} different clans--देवराक्षसस् like नैरृतस्, भूमिराक्षसस्, Guhya- राक्षसस् Daityara1ks2asas like कापिलेयस्; Another classifica- tion is दीवाचरस् (यज्ञमुखस्) (यातुधान, Brahma- धान, and वार्त्त) and निशाचरस् (Paulastya, नैरृत, आगस्त्य, and विश्वामीत्र) who ruin the श्राद्ध, but wor- ship पितृस्; {{F}}2:  Ib. III. 7. १३२- १६७; 8. ६०-65; १०. १११; ११. ८१; IV. 1. १५५; 2. २६; २०. ४७; वा. ७०. ५४-7.{{/F}} of sharp teeth, reside in Bhaumanarakam; {{F}}3:  M. ३९. 8-9.{{/F}} sons of यातुधान; {{F}}4:  वा. ६९. १२८.{{/F}} description of their forms and features; {{F}}5:  Ib. ७०. ५४-63.{{/F}} mother, स्वसा; {{F}}6:  Vi. I. २१. २५.{{/F}} both दानवस् and Daityas live in पाताल. {{F}}7:  Ib. II. 5-4.{{/F}}(II)--एत्य्: (see also यक्ष, निशाचर). When out of hunger the first created beings began to swallow water, the राक्षसस् tried to protect the waters; then the hairs of प्रजापति stood on end with anger; out of this came snakes of all sorts; {{F}}1:  Br. II. 8. ३२; वा. 9. ३०-5; Vi. I. 5. ४३.{{/F}} occupy Vajraka hill. {{F}}2:  वा. ३०. ९०; ३१. १२; ३४. ५५; ३९. ३६; १००. १५९; १०१. 3, २८.{{/F}}--a mind-born mother. M. १७९. १६. [page३-062+ ३३]--when no ceremonies are to be performed; the first three मुहूर्तस् or नालिकस् of the morning, सङ्घव (8-३० to ११ A.M.) of noon, afternoon and evening. M. २२. ८२-83.--a chief doorkeeper in Geyacakraratha. Br. IV. १९. ८८.--a son of Rambha, and father of गम्भीर. भा. IX. १७. १०.--a mind-born mother. M. १७९. २६.--a Daitya lady and queen of त्वष्ट. भा. VI. 6. ४४.(I)--a son of दीर्घबाहु, and a man of ever- lasting glory. His son was Aja. Lust after more territory: knew the power of विष्णु's योगमाया. भा. IX. १०. 1; XII. 3. 9; II. 7. ४४; Br. III. ६३. १८३; वा. ८८. १८३; Vi. IV. 4. ८४-5.(II)--a son of Nighna. M. १२. ४७.--an epithet of विष्णु. M. ५४. १८.--a son of सम्पाति. M. ४९. 4.--a group of deities. Br. IV. १९. ४६.--the king of Sindhu--सौवीर kingdom: employed जड-Bharata as his palanquin bearer, and found fault with him for not bearing it properly: He understood that he was a Brahmana, felt remorse and enquired who he was. Heard precepts on आत्मविद्या from Bharata and became devoted to Hari in a spirit of detachment. भा. V. १०. 1-२५; १३. २५.(I)--a son of Sumati, and father of दुष्यन्त. भा. IX. २०. 7.(II)--a son of वत्सार; his children, Raibhyas. वा. ७०. २५-6.(III)--a son of Rebhya and a ब्रह्मवादिन्. Br. II. ३२. ११२; III. 8. ३०; वा. ५९. १०३.--one of the three belonging to कश्यप group. Br. III. 8. ३३.--a Pravara of the भार्गवस्. M. १९५. ३९.(I)--a Rudra and a son of भूत and सरूपा. भा. VI. 6. १७; M. 5. २९; VI. I. १५. १२२. [page३-100+ २९](II)--a son of Reva (known also as Kakud- min); king of आनर्त्तस्; had a daughter रेवती (s.v.) whom he took to ब्रह्मा to consult him as to a suitable bride- groom. The music of हाह and हूहु was going on, and when it was finished, there was a different कल्प in the earth; was advised to give her to बलराम, and so he did. भा. X. ५२. १५ [1-११]; Br. III. ६१. २०; M. १२. २३; वा. ८६. २५.(III)--the fifth Manu; during his epoch were देवबाहु and six other sages, Gods named आभूतर- jasas. {{F}}1:  M. 9. १९-22; वा. ६२. 3.{{/F}} Vibhu was Indra; अमिताभ and other three गणस् of gods each १४ in number; हिरण्यरोम and other six formed the सप्तऋषिस्; Balabandhu and others were his sons; of the Priyavrata line. {{F}}2:  Vi. III. 1. 6, २०-4.{{/F}}(IV)--a class of reptiles, as arrows of Tripu- रारि. M. १३३. २५.(V)--a king and father-in-law of Baladeva. Vi. V. २५. १९.(VI)--a प्रसूत god. वा. ६२. ६०.(I)--Mt. in शाकद्वीप. Here रेवती nak- षत्र stops always, and hence sacred to it. Br. II. १९. ८७; वा. ४९. ८१; Vi. II. 4. ६२.(II)--(Mt.) in भारतवर्ष; {{F}}1:  वा. ४५. ९२; भा. V. १९. १६; Br. II. १६. २२.{{/F}} here Dvivida met राम and provoked him to a battle and in it was killed. {{F}}2:  भा. X. ६७. 8-२५.{{/F}} [page३-101+ २५]--a तीर्थ sacred to the पितृस्. M. २२. ७४.(I)--son of Viraja and father of Ketuman (शत- jit, वि। प्।). Br. II. १४. ७०; III. 8. १९; Vi. II. 1. ४०.(II)--son of Dhara. Br. III. 3. २२.(III)--is राजसीवृत्ति: Leads to duhkha and तृष. Br. IV. 3. ३२-41.(IV)--one of the seven sons of वसिष्ठ and ऊर्जा; wife मार्कण्डेयी and son Ketuman. वा. २८. ३६-37; Vi. I. १०. १३.(V)--the quality present both in तमस् and सत्व as oil in the oil-seed and ghee in milk; it is the result of agitation in the प्रधान। वा. 3. 2; 5. १०, १२.(VI)--son of Arija; a राजऋषि and tapassiddha. वा. ३३. ६०; ५७. १२२.(VII)--one of the ten branches of the Rohita clan of devas. वा. १००. ९०. [page३-045+ ३०]--a washerman; {{F}}1:  M. १९२. २०.{{/F}} शुक्लतीर्थम्, compared to, in washing sins; to be fined a माष of gold by the king for not properly washing. {{F}}2:  Ib. २२७. १५५.{{/F}} the washerman of Kamsa was killed on his refusing cloths to कृष्ण and राम. {{F}}3:  Vi. V. १९. १४-17.{{/F}}--a R. in शाल्मलिद्वीप. भा. V. २०. १०.--son of Varatri. Br. III. 1. ७९.--silver, came out of शिव's eyes; hence dear to पितृस्; but inauspicious and to be avoided in देवकार्यस्. M. १७. २२-3.(I)--the milkman of the यक्षस् on the earth and father of मणिधर. Born of यक्ष and apsaras क्रतुस्थला. Br. II. ३६. २१६; III. 7. १११.(II)--the grandfather of the यक्षस्, mar- ried भद्रा, the daughter of अनुह्राद, the Daitya; father of मणिभद्र and मणिवर; wives of these two become the aunts of सम्सिद्धकरण. वा. ६९. १५१-2.--one of the ten sons of रौद्राश्व. वा. ९९. १२४.--son of आयु and father of five hundred (hundred म्।प्।) sons known as Rajeyas; a devotee of नारायण; was invested with conquering powers; fearing प्रह्लाद and other enemies, Indra gave his kingdom to Raji; once when the देवासुर (कोलाहल) war broke out between प्रह्लाद and Indra extending for ३०० years both parties invoked his assistance; he joined the Devas who unlike the Asuras [page३-046+ २९] accepted him as their Lord and he vanquished the Asuras; Indra became thus his adopted son to whom he gave back his kingdom and returned to forest for penance. Indra, however, returned the kingdom to Raji; after Raji's death his sons appropriated the kingdom and refused to give it to Indra; the latter therefore killed all of them with the help of बृहस्पति. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. १७. 1-१६; Br. III. ६७. 2, ७९-105; ७२. ८६; M. २४. ३५-42; वा. ९७. ८६; Vi. IV. 8. 3, २१; 9. 1-२३.{{/F}} It is said where Raji is, there लक्ष्मी finds her abode; where लक्ष्मी is there धृति lives; where धृति resides, धाम lives; where धाम lives, there is Jaya. {{F}}2:  वा. ९२. ७४-99.{{/F}}--the thirtieth Kalpa; ब्रह्मा got a son red in colour, dress and eyes; finding him to be महादेव, ब्रह्मा bowed to him and contemplated upon वामदेव; शर्व appeared to him and made अट्टहास when were born four sons beginning with Viraja. वा. २२. २१-30.--a mind-born mother. M. १७९. १२.--an attendant on शिव. Br. III. ४१. २६.--an Asura killed by दुर्गा. Br. IV. २९. ७६.--a mind-born mother. M. १७९. २६.--a ब्रह्मराक्षसी. वा. ६९. १३४. Br. III. 7. ९९.--one of the six charioteers of ललिता. Br. IV. २०. ९२.--a शक्ति. Br. IV. ४४. ९०.--a son of Dhara. M. 5. २४.--the Goddess enshrined at रामतीर्थ. M. १३. ४०. [page३-055+ २८](I)--An उपद्वीप to जम्बूद्वीप: a terri- torial division of शाल्मलिद्वीप: {{F}}1:  भा. V. १९. ३०; २०. 9.{{/F}} The island where कालीय originally lived. Here the serpents agreed to give बलि every fortnight to गरुड, except कालीय. {{F}}2:  Ib. X. १६. ६३; १७. 1-4.{{/F}} South of श्वेत and north of नील. People live here for thousands of years (१०१५० years वा। प्।) by drinking the juice of the fruit of the banyan tree, रोहण in the island; people living there, pleasant to look at, devoid of disease and difficulties. {{F}}3:  Br. II. १५ 62-5; M. ११३. ६१; वा. ४५. 2-5.{{/F}}(II)--son of वीतिहोत्र of पुष्करद्वीप. भा. V. २०. ३१.--a daughter of the वालेयस्; originator of the कम्बलेयगण. वा. ६९. २१.(I)--a son of विविम्शति, and father of Khani- netra. भा. IX. 2. २५.(II)--a son of आयु, and father of Rabhasa: known for his valour; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. १७. 1 and १०; Br. III. ६७. 2.{{/F}} had no son. {{F}}2:  Vi. IV. 8. 3; 9. २४.{{/F}}(III)--the fifth Kalpa. वा. २१. ३०.(I)--the Apsaras presiding over the month of शुचि; {{F}}1:  भा. XII. ११. ३६.{{/F}} wife of Maya; {{F}}2:  Br. III. 6. २८; 7. 7.{{/F}} presiding over the month of ऊर्ज. {{F}}3:  Ib. II. २३. २२; IV. ३३. १८; भा. XII. ११. ४४.{{/F}}(II)--the goddess enshrined at Malaya hills: a mother goddess. M. १३. २९; १७९. २०. [page३-056+ ३३](III)--An Apsaras versed in dancing; {{F}}1:  M. २४. २८; वा. ६९. 6.{{/F}} created by ब्रह्मा; {{F}}2:  M. १३६. ११.{{/F}} going with the sun sometime; {{F}}3:  Ib. १२६. २३.{{/F}} seized by the Asuras; {{F}}4:  Ib. १२६. 7; १३३. 9.{{/F}} in the सभा of हिरण्यकशिपु. {{F}}5:  Ib. १६१. ७५.{{/F}}(IV)--a snake with the sun in summer. वा. ५२. 6.(V)--with the sun during फाल्गुन month; शुक्र or आषाढ; {{F}}1:  Vi. II. १०. १८.{{/F}} along with other Apsaras cursed by अष्तावक्र. {{F}}2:  Ib. V. ३८. ७३. ७७.{{/F}}--with the sun in the months of शुचि and शुक्र. Br. II. २३. 8.--आर्षेयप्रवरस् (भार्गवस्). M. १९५. ३९.(I)--son of आग्नीध्र, and Lord of नीलम् (नीलवर्ष-वा। प्।); {{F}}1:  Br. II. १४. ४६-50; वा. ३३. ३९, ४२.{{/F}} placed in charge of the kingdom bordering on नीलाचल. {{F}}2:  Vi. II. 1. १७ and २०.{{/F}}(II)--(केशरि s.v.) Mt. in शाकद्वीपम्. वा. ४९. ८४.--a daughter of Meru, and wife of Ramyaka. भा. V. 2. २३.(I)--son of आग्नीध्र. भा. V. 2. १९.(II)--(नीलवर्ष) a continent bounded by नील on one side: Here विष्णु in the form of Matsya is worshipped by Manu. भा. V. १६. 8; १८. २४-28. M. ११३. ३०; वा. ३४. ३०. Vi. II. 2. १४.--a son of सम्हताश्व. M. १२. ३४.--born of Pulaha. Br. III. 7. १७८.--a son of धृष्ट. M. १२. २१. [page३-047+ ३०]--son of क्षुद्रक, and father of Suratha. भा. IX. १२. १५.(I)--a son of कृतञ्(m)jaya, and father of सम्जाय; of the बृहद्बल (बार्हद्बलायन-भा। प्।) dynasty. भा. IX. १२. १३; Vi. IV. २२. 7-8.(II)--a son of व्रात. वा. ९९. २८७.--a kingdom of the West watered by the Sindhu. Br. II. १८. ४८.--a son of कृतम्जय, the इक्ष्वाकु king. M. २७१. ११.--the wrestling place where separate seats were arranged for judges, nobles, women, cowherds, etc. Women of the palace and the city attended such matches; these women recalled कृष्ण's former exploits. Vi. V. २०. २३-29, ४३, ४५-7. [page३-044+ २३]--professional actors. वा. १०१. १६४.--son of वरूत्रि. वा. ६५. ७८.(I)--a son of Nandana. Br. III. ७१. १९२.(II)--a son of Riveyu, his wife was सरस्वती. वा. ९९. १२८, १२९.--a son of ऋतेयु, and father of Sumati and two other sons. भा. IX. २०. 6.(I)--a son of सम्कृति: attained permanent fame. He performed a sacrifice when he gave up all he had and suffered with his family having nothing to eat for fortyeight days. When he had something to eat, there came a Brahmana guest and a वृषल, and another guest with dogs around him; they all shared it. When he had some- thing to drink, there came a Pulkasa and asked for the drink and got it. To such a high soul, the gods showed दर्शन्. All his followers became Yogins, himself having realised the योगमाया of विष्णु. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २१. 2-१८; X. ७२. २१; II. 7. ४४; Vi. IV. १९. २२.{{/F}} परीक्षित् compared to him for his generosity. {{F}}2:  भा. I. १२. २४; Br. III. ३४. ३८.{{/F}}(II)--a son of महायशस्. M. ४९. ३७.--a son of Nandana. Br. III. ७१. १९२. [page३-054+ २८](I)--a तुषित god. Br. III. 3. १९.(II)--the गुण of waters becomes absorbed in ज्योतिस् or तेजस् and consequently waters reach the verge of destruction. वा. १०१. ४२. १०२. 9.--(also पातालम्) the underworld of rocky soil. Here live पणिस्, नागस्, निवातकवचस् and कालेयस्; all दानवस् of great strength and enterprising spirit and afraid of Hari and Sarama, the messenger of Indra. {{F}}1:  भा. V. २४. 7 and ३०; Br. II. १९. १७१; २०. १० and १२, ३९-40; ३०. ३१; M. ४७. ६३; वा. ४९. १६३; ९७. ९५; १००. १५७; Vi. IV. 3. 4 and 8; V. 1. २८.{{/F}} Visited by Arjuna in search of the dead child of the द्वारका Brahmana; {{F}}2:  भा. X. ८९. ४४.{{/F}} burnt by Pralaya; {{F}}3:  Br. III. ५३. 1; ७२. ९६. ७३. ४६ and ४८; IV. 1. १५३.{{/F}} the Asuras entered it help- less; {{F}}4:  M. ४७. २१२-13, २३३.{{/F}} Vasu, cursed by the sages to live there, for his decision against the killing of पशु in sacrifices; {{F}}5:  Ib. १४३. २४-25; १६६. 3; २४८, 4, ११, ५३, ६७ff; वा. ५७. ११०.{{/F}} of १०,000 Yojanas in extent; other talams are Atala, Sutala, Vitala, Gabhastala, महातल, Sritala, and पताल with the characteristics of black, white, पीतम्, chunam, rocky and gold they are in groups of earth, water and space. {{F}}6:  Ib. 6. २५; ५०. 9-१४.{{/F}} [page३-060+ २८]--fit for gift during the विशोकद्वादशि व्रत। M. ८२. १९.--a companion of Puramjana, allegorically the organ of taste. See मुख्या. भा. IV. २५. ४९; २९. ११.--a व्रत to be performed on the third day of the माघ month; sacred to ललिता; this is continued every month preceded by fasting and followed by gifts to Brahmanas; the person who does this enjoys in the world of गौरी. It is equal to performing १००० यज्ञस्। M. ch. ६३ (whole)--a देवी. Br. IV. १९. १८; ३६. ६९; ४४. ११८.--a R. in कुशद्वीप. भा. V. २०. १५. [page३-059+ ३४]--a son of the राक्षस Vidyuta. Br. III. 7. ९५.--son of Kuthumi. वा. ६१. ३८.--one of the eight सौभाग्यम्स्. M. ६०. 8, २८.--is a yoga siddhi. Br. IV. ३६. ५२; ४४. १०८.--the months of Madhu and माधव. Br. II. १३. 9; वा. ३०. 8.--a son of स्वाहा and father of Citraratha; the best among givers; performed many sacrifices. वा. ९५. १६-17.--one of the २० Sutapa गणस्. वा. १००. १५.--of the moon, description of; sprang out of waters with ten horses, charioteer, etc., has three wheels. वा. ५२. ५०-4.--a kingdom of कुशद्वीप. Br. II. १४. २९; १९. ५८.(I)--a क्षत्रोपेत dvija. Br. III. ६६. ८८.(II)--a disciple of सत्यश्रिय; a शाख प्र- वर्तक, शाखपूर्णरथीतर (?). वा. ६०. २९, ६५.(III)--an elephant. वा. ६९. २१९.--a यक्ष who resides in the sun's chariot in the months of Caitra and Madhu. Vi. II. १०. 3.(I)--with the sun in the months of शुचि and शुक्र (in the month of आषाढ वि। प्।). Br. II. २३. 7; Vi. II. १०. 8.(II)--a ग्रामणि with the sun in summer. वा. ५२. 7. [page३-050+ २९]--a ग्रामणि with the sun in spring. वा. ५२. 4.(I)--the यक्ष presiding over the month of Madhu. भा. XII. ११. ३३; Br. II. २३. 3.(II)--one of the seven प्रानिन्स् of the king. वा. ५७. ७०, Br. II. २९. ७६.--a यक्ष, who resides in the sun's chariot during the month of माधव. Vi. II. १०. 5.--a जयादेव and son of ब्रह्मा; a man- त्रशरीर. Br. III. 3. 6; वा. ६६. 6; ६७. 5.--an account of, in the ब्रह्मवै- वर्त पुराण; {{F}}1:  M. ५३. ३४; ६९. 1, 5.{{/F}} king पुष्पवाहन belonged to this aeon. {{F}}2:  Ib. १००. 1.{{/F}}(I)--the साम sung by Bhauvana; ele- phants, Kapila and पुण्डरीक born of; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 7. ३२४ and ३३५; वा. 9. ४८; २२. 8; ३०. ११९; ६९. २०९.{{/F}} to be heard on the श्राद्ध day; {{F}}2:  M १७. ३८.{{/F}} to be uttered while installing