 ४३ and ५५.(V)--a son of शिष्टि(i1) and सुच्छाया, wife बृहती; his son चाक्षुष. M. 4. ३९; Vi. I. १३. 2.(I)--the son of सुवीर (सुधीर वि। प्।) and father of Bahuratha. भा. IX. २१. २९-30; Vi. IV. १९. ५५. [page३-082+ २६](II)--a son of विश्वजित्--last link of the line; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २२. ४९.{{/F}} with him ends the बृहद्रथ line after ruling for १००० years; {{F}}2:  Vi. IV. २३. १२.{{/F}} his minister Munika murdered him and enthroned his own son Pradyota. {{F}}3:  Ib. IV. २४. 1-2.{{/F}} Ruled for thirty-five years. {{F}}4:  Br. III. ७४. ११४.{{/F}}(III)--a son of Acala, ruled for ५० years. M. २७१. २९.(IV)--a son of वराङ्गी and Divamjaya. वा. ६२. ८७.(V)--a son of मेधावि and father of Urva. Vi. IV. २१. १३.(VI)--a son of शिष्टि and सुच्छाया. Vi. I. १३. 2.--an apsaras; mother of the वेगवती group. Br. III. 7. १२ and २१.--son of मानस. वा. ७०. ३०. [page३-083+ २९]--one of the २० Sutapa गणस्. वा. १००. १४.--a head of a शिव gan2a. Br. III. ४१. २८.--one of the २० Amita1bha गणस्. वा. १००. १६.--a son of अनादृष्ट; a राजऋषि; ज्वलना, daughter of दक्ष was his consort. वा. ९९. १२७-8.--son of पुरुजानु. वा. ९९. १९५. [page३-081+ २६]--a son of देवकी and Vasudeva; killed by कंस. Vi. IV. १५. २६-7.--the १८थ् Vedavya1sa. Br. II. ३५. १२१. भा. IX. २४. ५४.--a son of देवकी killed by कंस. Br. III. ७१. १७५.--a शक्ति। Br. IV. ४४. ७५.--one of the names in the fourth मरुत् गण। वा. ६७. १२७.of the Vedas; {{F}}1:  भा. X. 7. १४; ५३. १२; XII. ११. ४७; १२. ६२.{{/F}} learnt by the Asuras. {{F}}2:  Br. II. ३३. ३६; IV. १२. १७.{{/F}}--8th face of the fourteen-faced god; सावर्णि Manu from. वा. २६. ४०.--is threefold for a द्विज--to gods, to पितृस् and to sages. {{F}}1:  वा. ७७. १०६; १०८. ७६ and ८९; ११०. ६०; १११. २९ and ३१.{{/F}} Vasudeva is asked by sages to perform a sacrifice to please gods. {{F}}2:  भा. X. ८४. ३९-40.{{/F}}--a तीर्थ sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ६७.--a तीर्थ on the north of the यमुना, and south of प्रयाग. M. १०७. २०.--in the नर्मदा. M. १९१. २७. [page१-263+ २५]--a sage, not to have marital alliance with विश्वामित्रस्. M. १९८. १९.(I)--a विश्वेदेव. Br. III. 3. ३१; M. २०३. १३; वा. ६६. ३२.(II)--a son of आनर्त्त and father of Reva. M. १२. २२-23.(III)--a son of उपदेवी and Vasudeva. M. ४६. १७.(I)--a son of दक्षिणा and a तुषित god. भा. IV. 1. 7-8.(II)--the name of Indra of the स्वारोचिष epoch. भा. VIII. 1. २०.(III)--a son of Vasudeva. Br. III. ७१. १८२.(IV)--a son of उपदेवा. वा. ९६. १७९.(I)--one of Vasudeva's wives, and mother of Hasta and other sons. भा. IX. २४. ४५ and ४९.(II)--grand daughter of Rukmi, married to Aniruddha. भा. X. ६१. २५.(III)--a Mind-born mother. M. १७९. २३. [page३-102+ २६]--a son of उषा and विभावसु. भा. VI. 6. १६.--a son of स्वारोचिष Manu. भा. VIII. 1. १९.--the two mothers of the world (Heaven and Earth) worshipped for security of place. भा. II. 3. 5.--a kind of hell; here fall slayers of cows, of phoetus murderers and those who set fire to cities. वा. १०१. १४६, १५२; Vi. II. 6. 2 and 8.--a R. in भारत vars2a. भा. V. १९. १८.--to be worshipped in housebuilding and palace building. M. २५३. २६; २६८. १७.--a kingdom of the West watered by Sindhu. Br. II. १८. ४८; वा. ४७. ४६.(I)--same as Rohita. M. १२२. ९७.(II)--the banyan tree in the रमणक vars2a. वा. ४५. 4.(I)--a daughter of वाल्मीकि; one of Vasudeva's wives, and mother of Gada, बलराम and five other sons besides a daughter, चित्रा. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २४. ४५-6; X. 1. 8; Br. III. ७१. १६१-5; वा. ९६. १६०-3; Vi. V. 1. ७४-6; 2. 2; 5. 5; 6. ११; IV. १५. १८-9.{{/F}} Had her residence at Nanda- gokula. Hari ordered योगमाया to transfer his धाम in the womb of देवकी to that of रोहिणी. This was the future बलराम Sankars2ana. नारद spoke about this to Kamsa. {{F}}2:  भा. X. 2. 7-8, १५.{{/F}} [page३-104+ ३४] Her joy at the birth of कृष्ण, and helped यशोदा in her रक्ष ritual to कृष्ण; joy at his escape from कालीय; intensely attached to राम; surprised at कृष्ण holding the Govardhana; came to see him taking पारिजात from Indra's abode. कृष्ण's respects to; {{F}}3:  Ib. X 5. १७; 6. १९; ११. १२; १५. ४४; १७. १५; २५. ३०; ३६. १७; [६७ (v) ४७-8].{{/F}} went to Syamanta- पञ्चक for the solar eclipse, met यशोदा there and embraced her. Lamented the decease of कृष्ण and राम. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ८२. ३७; XI. ३१. १८.{{/F}} Entered fire after their deceuse; {{F}}5:  Vi. V. ३८. 4.{{/F}} also known as पौरवी. {{F}}6:  M. ४६. ११.{{/F}}(II)--one of कृष्ण's wives; a देवी; mother of दीप्तिमत्, ताम्रपक्ष and other sons. भा. X, ६१. १८; Br. III. ७१. २४२; वा. ९६. २३३. Vi. V. २८. 4; ३२. 2.(III)--a wife of महादेव-Candramatanu of शिव; mother of Budha. Br. I. 2. 9; II. १०. ८४; M. ५५. १२; १३९. २५; वा. २७. ५६; ६६. २२. Vi. I. 8. 8.(IV)--a daughter of सुरभी and कश्यप; a sister of the Rudras; mother of four daughters--सुरूपा, हम्सकाली (कीला), भद्रा and कामदु(a)घा. Br. III. 3. ७३-5; वा. ६६. ७१-72.(V)--a constellation important for श्राद्ध per- formance; {{F}}1:  Br. III. १८. 3; M. १७. 3; ५४. 9; वा. ८२. 3.{{/F}} the worship of, in गो सहस्र दानम्। {{F}}2:  M. १६३. ४१; १७१. ३२; २७८. १४.{{/F}}(VI)--had Saumya as her son. वा. 2. 9.--with which नारायण is wor- shipped with the names of the moon; to be observed on the full moon day when रोहिणी is the नक्षत्र or Monday being [page३-105+ २८] a शुक्लपञ्चमि; even शूद्रस् can observe it; a list of flowers given for worship; it lasts for a year; at the end a furnished bed with looking glass, etc., to be given to a learned श्रोत्रिय; the giver attains the world of Candra; even women may observe it. M. ५७. 3-२७.(I)--a son of हरिश्चन्द्र; knowing that he would be sacrificed, went out of his kingdom. Having heard of the decease of his father, he wanted to return but was prevented by Indra. At the end of the sixth year, he pur- chased सुनश्शेप and returned home. Father of Harita. भा. IX. 7. 9-२१; 8. 1; Br. III. ६३. ११७; M. १२. ३८; वा. ८८. ११९.(II)--a son of वपुष्मती, after whom came the kingdom of Rohita. Br. II. १४. ३२-3; वा. ३३. २८-29; Vi. II. 4. २३, २९.(III)--a son of सत्यभामा and कृष्ण. Br. III. ७१. २४७; M. ४७. १७; वा. ९६. २३८.(IV)--a progenitor and a son of दक्ष; परा, मरीचि, and सुधर्मान gan2as, all of १२ gods each are from him. Br. IV. 1. ५६-61; वा. १००. ६०.(V)--a Mt. a hill of शाल्मलिद्वीप. M. १२२. ९६.(I)--a son of शठ. Br. III. ७१. १७०.(II)--of the रोहिणि family. वा. ९६. १६८.(III)--son of हरिश्चन्द्र and father of Harita. Vi. IV. 3. २५.--one of the five deva गणस् of the 4th ऋतु Sa1varn2a Manu; of ten gods; mind-born sons of Budha with ten branches; {{F}}1:  Br. IV. 1. ८३-6; वा. १००. ८७.{{/F}} of the XII epoch of Manu. {{F}}2:  Vi. III. 2. ३४.{{/F}} [page३-106+ २७]--a tribe of the Vindhyas. वा. ४५. १३२.--a pupil of व्यास in charge of इतिहास- पुराण, and father of सूत. Himself a sage and सूत. Adopted as ब्रह्मा by the sages in their यज्ञ at नैमिष; also लोमहर्षण (s.v.); killed by बलराम for his failure to honour him by rising from his seat. {{F}}1:  भा. I. 4. २२; X. ७८. २२-30, ३६; Br. I. 1. १८. II. १६. 3; २२. 2; २४. 1; वा. ६७. 2-3; Vi. III. 4. १०.{{/F}} His was the मूल- सम्हिता; adept in आख्यान narrated royal genealogies. {{F}}2:  Br. I. 1. १४; II. ३४. १३-16; ३५. ६८; III. ५९. 3; IV. 4. 8.{{/F}} Had six disciples. {{F}}3:  Vi. III. 6. १६.{{/F}}--the पुराण (मूल) सम्हिता compiled by रोमहर्षण. Vi. III. 6. १८.(I)--see Citraratha. भा. IX. २३. 7; Vi. IV. १८. १६.(II)--the famous son of Vidarbha and father of Babhru; attained wisdom from नारद. भा. IX. २४. 1-2; Vi. IV. १२. ३८-9.(I)--a siddha. भा. VI. १५. १४.(II)--a विद्याधर chief in वेणुमन्त hill. वा. ३९. ३८.--fourteen गणस् of gods; live in मह, तप and जन lokas. वा. २४. 2. [page३-103+ ३४]--a daughter of क्रोधवशा, and a wife of Pulaha. Had five daughters after whom came the मैन गण। Br. III. 7. १७२ & ४१३; वा. ६९. २८९-291. [page१-272+ ४२](I)--a sage about whose welfare Arjuna is asked by युधिष्ठिर. भा. I. १४. ३१.(II)--a follower of वृत्र in his battle with Indra. भा. VI. १०. १९.(III)--a son of Indra and पौलोमी. भा. VI. १८. 7.(IV)--a manifestation of Hari in दक्षसावर्णि epoch. Born of आयुष्मत् and अम्बुधारा; engaged in ध्यानमार्ग। भा. VIII. १३. २०; वा. २३. १४३, १४६.(V)--a son of कुशाग्र, and father of Satyahita. भा. IX. २२. 6-7. वा. ९९. २२३.(VI)--a playmate of कृष्ण. भा. X. २२. ३१.(VII)--identified with the sun. भा. XII. 6. ६८.(VIII)--the son of नाभि and सुदेवी (Meru- देवी according to वि।, वा। & ब्र्। प्।) An अवतार् of विष्णु, eldest of all क्षत्र. A परमहम्स। Had a hundred sons of whom Bharata was the eldest. {{F}}1:  Br. II. १४. ६०-62; भा. II. 7. १०; XI. 4. १७; Vi. II. 1. २७; वा. ३३. ५०-51.{{/F}} Nine of these became rulers of the nine द्वीपस् of the world. Eightyone [page१-270+ ३३] of them became addicted to कर्म तन्त्र, and the remain- der nine became sages. {{F}}2:  भा. XI. 2. १५-20.{{/F}} Indra grew jealous of him and stopped rains in his kingdom अजनाभ. But ऋषभ, in- voked rains by yogic powers. {{F}}3:  Ib. V. 3 (whole); 4. 1-3.{{/F}} As king, married जयन्ती, bestowed on him by Indra, who gave birth to १०० sons. Under ऋषभ, his kingdom flowed with milk and honey. Once he went to control ब्रह्मावर्त and proclaimed the importance of self-control and discipline to his sons and to the world at large. Installed Bharata on the throne, renounced life and became a wandering mendicant. Finding the world opposed to his yoga practice he adopted the vow of a python (आजगरम्) by which he ate, chewed, drank and passed water all lying down. By his yogic powers he wandered through कोङ्क, वेङ्क, कुटक, S. कर्नाट, and was consumed by forest- fire. By listening to his story, devotion to Hari was in- creased. His path was followed by Sumati; {{F}}4:  Ib. V. 4. 8-१९; chap. 5 (whole); 6. 6-१९; १५. 1; वा. ३३. ५१.{{/F}} took to the third आश्रम at Pulaha's hermitage and lived there until his death. {{F}}5:  Vi. II. 1. २८-31.{{/F}}(IX)--a son of अङ्गिरस्, and a sage of the स्वा- रोचिष epoch; a मन्त्रकृत्। Br. III. ३६. १७; वा. ५९. १००.(X)--a son of Sudhanvan. वा. ६५. १०२.(XI)--a दानव with मनुष्य dharma. वा. ६८. १५.(XII)--a ऋत्विक् at ब्रह्मा's याज्ञ। वा. १०६. ३७. [page१-271+ २७](XIII)--a mountain on the north base of Meru but in भारतवर्ष; sacred to Hari and visited by Bala- राम; {{F}}1:  भा. V. १६. २६; १९. १६; X. ७९. १५; M. १६३. ७८; Vi. II. 2. ३०.{{/F}} entered the sea. {{F}}2:  M. १२१. ७२; Br. II. १८. ७५.{{/F}}(XIV)--an elephant at one of the four cardinal points to maintain the balance of the worlds. भा. V. २०. ३९.(XV)--स्वर (auspicious), when heard by a king starting on an expedition; the second of the seven notes of the Hindu gamut. M. २४३. २१; वा. २१. ३४; ८६. ३७.(XVI)--the fifteenth कल्प; here came into being ऋषभस्वर। वा. २१. ३३-34.(XVII)--another name for the सुमना hill of प्लक्षद्वीप. वा. ४२. १९; ४९. ११.(I)--a R. from Vindhya hills. M. ११४. २७.(II)--a R. from the केतुमाल country. वा. ४४. १९.--a class of people in क्रौञ्चद्वीप. भा. V. २०. २२.-- (ety.) got the मन्त्रस् by the pupil of the eye, by observation, by accident and by past and future events. Five groups are distinguished: अव्यक्तात्मा, महानात्मा, (also महात्मा), अहम्कारात्मा, भूतात्मा and इन्द्रियात्मा; also ब्रह्मऋषिस्, देवऋषिस्, राजऋषिस्, महऋषिस्, सप्तऋषिस्, ऋषिकस्--all मन्त्रवित्स्। {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३२. ७०-95; ३३. ३२, ३४; ३५. ८९ & ९५; M. १२३. २९; १४५. ८१-89. वा. ५९-87.{{/F}} Milked the cow Earth when Soma acted as calf; बृहस्- pati was the milkman, the vessel being the Vedas and the essence तपस्; {{F}}2:  M. १०. १६-7.{{/F}} cursed by महादेव in the स्वायम्भुव epoch and freed from it in the Vaivasvata. {{F}}3:  M. १९५. 3.{{/F}}(I)--a kingdom watered by ह्लादिनी. ^1 Br. II. १८. ५४; M. १२१. ५३. [page१-273+ २८](II)--(see ऋषिकस्). {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३२. ९१ & १०३; ३३. २७; वा. ४७. ५१.{{/F}} Sons of sages by several union. {{F}}2:  M. १४५. ८६; वा. ५९. ८४-94.{{/F}}and ऋषिजाति, ety. of. वा. ५९. ७९-87.--पञ्चार्षेय. M. १९६. ५०.--a मन्त्रकृत्; son of सुरूपा and a गोत्रकार. M. १४५. १०५; १९६. 4.--a R. originating from the शुक्तिमती. वा. ४५. १०७.--a तीर्थम् on the नर्मदा. M. १९४. १४.--a R. in भारतवर्ष from the शुक्तिमत् hill. (Mahendra--ब्र्।, म्। and वि। प्।). भा. V. १९. १८; Br. II. १६. ३७-38: M. ११४. ३१; Vi. II. 3. १३-14.--three, ब्रह्मऋषि, देवऋषि and राजऋषि। वा. ६१. ८०; Vi. III. 6. २९. [page१-274+ ३१]--sons of र्षिकस्--composers of ब्राह्मणस् and the कल्प; authors of धर्मशास्त्रस्; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३२. ९३; ३१. १२, २२; M. १४५. ८७.{{/F}} modify the Vedic texts by introducing changes. {{F}}2:  वा. ५८. १२; ५९. ८४-86.{{/F}}--rearrange the Vedas as मन्त्रस् and ब्राह्मणस्, and स्वर and वर्ण। वा. ५८. १२: ५९. ८४ and ८६.--blessed पृथु. {{F}}1:  भा. IV. १५. १९; १९. १८.{{/F}} Divine ascetics. {{F}}2:  Ib. III. २०. ५२-3; VII. 8. ३७ and ४३; VIII. 5. ३९; १४. 8; X. ७२. 8; ७४. ३७.{{/F}} Went to द्वा- रका to see कृष्ण. {{F}}3:  Ib. XI. 6. 3.{{/F}} Sing in praise of the sun. {{F}}4:  Ib. XII. ११. ४७.{{/F}} Born in the form of cows when Hari manifested himself as कृष्ण. {{F}}5:  Ib. X. 1. २३ [1].{{/F}} (See ऋषि). The seven of the Vaivasvata epoch were विश्वामित्र, Jamadagni, भरद्वाज, शरद्वान्, Atri, वसुमान्, वत्सार- कश्यप. {{F}}6:  वा. ६४. २४-28.{{/F}} Relations of, with gods and पितृस्. {{F}}7:  Ib. ६२. २१.{{/F}}--a place on the नर्मदा. Here तृणबिन्दु got rid of his curse. M. १९१. २२; १९३. १३-4.--a son of देवकी and Vasudeva; killed by कंस. M. ४६. १३.--the son of देवातिथि, and father of दिलीप. भा. IX. २२. ११.--a hill in भारतवर्ष. भा. V. १९. १६.--the son of उपदानवी. M. ४९. १०.(I)--a sage of the eighth मन्वन्तर। भा. VIII. १३. १५; Vi. III. 2. १७.(II)--married शान्ता, the adopted daughter of रोमपाद. Superintended the इष्टि of दश- ratha to propitiate Indra and blessed दशरथ with issue. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २३. 8-१०.{{/F}} The son of a deer, became the plaything of dance, song, etc. {{F}}2:  Ib. XI. 8. १८.{{/F}} Gave son चतुरङ्ग to लोम्पाद-Das4a- ratha. {{F}}3:  M. ४८. ९६.{{/F}} Blessed his son with a son; {{F}}4:  वा. ९९. १०४.{{/F}} one of the seven sages. {{F}}5:  वा. १००. ११.{{/F}}--a mt. from which several rivers originate. M. ११४. २३-26.(I)--a son of चाक्षुष Manu and नड्वला. भा. IV. १३. १६.(II)--the son of Vijaya and father of Sunaka (Sunaya-वि। प्।). भा. IX. १३. २५-26; वा. ८९. २२. Vi. IV. 5. ३१.(III)--a तुषित god. Br. II. ३६. १२.(IV)--a Sukha god. Br. IV. 1. १८.(V)--the १२थ् Manu of the future. M. 9. ३६.(VI)--