7:  Ib XI. 1. १३-23; Vi. V. ३७. 7-१०.{{/F}} Adopted by गण्डूष; had five sons, all warriors, through काशी; one of the five वम्शवीरस्; {{F}}8:  Br. III. ७१. १९१ and २६०; ७२ 1.{{/F}} married कश्या, daughter of सुपार्श्व, and mother of पञ्चवीरस् and a number of sons, all with divine sparks; {{F}}9:  M. ४७. २४.{{/F}} was looked upon with love by the १६००० [page३-587+ २५] women of कृष्ण and hence they were cursed by कृष्ण to be robbed and dishonoured by robbers. They were rid of the curse by observing अनङ्गदान व्रतम् as prescribed by दाल्भ्य, the sage. {{F}}१०:  Ib ७०. 5-१०, १७-19, ६२.{{/F}} Got killed in the यादव struggle at Pra- भास. {{F}}११:  Vi. V. ३७. ४६.{{/F}}(II)--a son of Tarasvin. वा. ९६. २५२.(III)--a वम्शवीर. वा. ९७. 1.--the उपपुराण containing legends connected with साम्ब. M. ५३. ६२.--a portion of the पूर्वसम्हिता. वा. ६१. ५७. [page३-586+ ४३]--शिव. वा. ३०. २२०. ९७. १७५.--of कौशिक gotra. वा. ९१. १००.--the क्षेरोपेत Brahmans; of Angirasa line. वा. ९९. १६४.--a son of Nara. वा. ९९. १६०.--a भार्गव gotraka1ra; a श्रुत r2s2i. Br. II. ३३. 2; M. १९५. २३. [page३-578+ ४९]--a name of ललिता. Br. IV. १८. १५.--see samudra. Br. II. १९. १२८, १३१-5.--a wife of प्राचीनबर्हिष (सावर्णि-वा। प्।) (प्राचीनबर्हि-म्। प्।); mother of ten प्राचीनबर्हिषस्. Br. II. ३७. २७; M. 4. ४७; वा. ३०. ३६.--वास्तु in house buildings. M. २५३. १५.--the प्रलय fire remembered by those who witnessed the fight between Arjuna and अश्वत्थामन्. भा. I. 7. ३१.--the musala or club of Hari. Vi. V. २२. 7. [page३-583+ २९]--one who has a knowledge of षाड्- गुण्य, knows the language of countries and is skilled in policy. M. २१५. १६.--(also सान्दीपन); of काशी, and a resident of Avanti; was the preceptor of कृष्ण and बलराम. Taught them all branches of learning in ६४ days; got back his dead son recovered from the world of Yama (from the sea वि। प्।) by his pupils as गुरुदक्षिण; acted as purohita in the यज्ञस् performed by कृष्ण at कुरुक्षेत्र; {{F}}1:  भा III. 3. 2; X. ४५. ३१-49; ९०. ४६. Vi. V. २१, १९-31. [2] वा. ९८. ९९.{{/F}} his concern when कृष्ण and Kucela were caught once in storm and rain. {{F}}2:  भा X. ८०. ३९-40; Br. III. ७३-79.{{/F}}--the capital of कुशध्वज; {{F}}1:  Br. III. ६४. १९.{{/F}} also the name of the kingdom. {{F}}2:  Vi. IV. 5. २९.{{/F}}--Revealed by विष्णु: taught by Kapila to आसुरि. {{F}}1:  भा. I. 3. १०; II. 1. 6; V. १८. ३३; M. 3. २९; वा. ३०. २९३.{{/F}} Here tattvas or first principles are taught. पुरुष the eternal, acts as agent to get things done by the गुणस् of प्रकृति. Its relation to Bhaktiyoga. {{F}}2:  भा. III. २४. १७; २५. ३१; ch. २६ (whole); २९ 2; वा. ६१. १११.{{/F}} Its principles are differently enumerated as eleven, five, three and so on; ac- cording to one's युक्ती or reason. Creation of universe ac- cording to सान्ख्य, and the place of प्रकृति and पुरुष therein. {{F}}3:  भा. XI. २२. 1-२५; भा 24 (whole).{{/F}} Followed by कृष्ण while ruling from द्वारका and by नारद in his worship of नरनारायण. {{F}}4:  ch. III. 3. १९; V. १९. १०; IX. 8. १४; X. 8. ४५; XI. १४. २०.{{/F}} Practised by वैराजसस्; {{F}}5:  M. १३. 5.{{/F}} is itself a kind of yoga; {{F}}6:  Ib. ५२. 3; ११०; १९; १८२. १८; १८३. ४४; वा. ६६. ११०.{{/F}} born out of the creator. {{F}}7:  M. १८३. ५०; १८४. २४; २४५. ८७; २४७. 9; २४८. १७; २९१. 2.{{/F}}--sages of rigid vows: learnt the भाग- वत from कुमार and imparted it to पराशर and बृहस्पति. भा. III. 8. 7-8; M. २००. ११.--the devas known as वैराजस् live in. वा. ७१. ५२.--an expiation ceremony for ascetics guilty of sexual act. वा. १८. 8.--a son of सत्यभामा and कृष्ण. Br. III. ७१. २४७; वा. ९६. २३८.--a pupil of याञवल्क्य. Br. II. ३५. २८.--extends to several generations. M. १८. २९.--the गोत्रकारस् of Atri family. M. १९७. 1.--a son of श्वफल्क. भा. IX. २४. १६.--one of the twenty-eight hells; contains ७२० hounds of adamantine teeth; setting fire, administering poison, plundering of villages or caravans are punished here. भा. V. २६. 7 and २७.--lineal descendants of सरमा's two sons. Br. III. 7. ३१३.(I)--a son of Vasudeva (आनकदुन्दुभि) and रोहिणी and father of सार्ष्