eographical knowledge of the country, able to calculate the strength or weakness of the army corps; loyal, etc. M. २१५. २०-21.--belonging to आर्षेय Pravara of Angiras. M. १९६. 6.--one of the eight मुहूर्तस् of the afternoon. Br. III. 3. ३९.--a भार्गव gotraka1ra. M. १९५. २३.--a son of सारण. Vi. IV. १५. २१.--a particular period of the day. वा. ६६. ४०.(I)--a manifestation of Hari in the सावर्णि epoch as the son of Devaguhya and सरस्वती. He deprived Purandara of Indrahood and made Bali Indra. भा. VIII. १३. १७. [page३-591+ २५](II)--a son of वीदूरथ, and father of Jayasena. (Jayatsena-वि। प्।). भा. IX. २२. १०; M. ५०. ३५; वा. ९९. २३१. Vi. IV. २०. 4.(III)--a son of Sudha(va)rma; an एकराट्. M. ४९. ७१-2; वा. ९९. १८६.--a देवी and wife of कृष्ण. वा. ९६. २३३.--that which is above and divine; {{F}}1:  वा. १०२. ५४.{{/F}} the mind becomes clean and the truth is open to him and leads to ज्ञानम् or knowledge; {{F}}2:  Ib. ७४. ७६.{{/F}} of विष्णु. {{F}}3:  Ib. ६६. ८७, १०४-6.{{/F}}--married कीर्तिमती. वा. ७०. ८६; ७३. ३१.(I)--a son of आयु, and father of भजमान and six other sons. Attacked the Asura followers of Bali. भा. VIII. २१. १७; IX. २४. 6-7.(II)--the son of Satva (Janhu म्। प्।); wife, कौसल्या; father of four sons, भजमान, Bhaji etc., who founded four different dynasties. Br. III. ७०. ४८; ७१. 1, 2; M. ४४. ४६-8; वा. ९५. ४७.the भागवतम् a means to bhakti (see सात्वति s4ruti). भा. I. 7. 6-7.--(सात्वत s4a1stra) is पाञ्चरात्र? Propounded by विशोक, a means of obtaining mukti for women, शूद्रस् and slaves by the साम्प्रदाय given here; {{F}}1:  भा. X. ९०. ३४ [2]; VI. १६. ३३.{{/F}} taught by नारद. {{F}}2:  Ib. I. 3. 8.{{/F}}--is भागवत: a discourse between शुक and परीक्षित् at हास्तिनपुर. भा. I. 4. 7.--the followers of सात्वततन्त्र. भा. V. २५. 1.--a यादव tribe related to the पाण्डवस्. Their overlord was कृष्ण; {{F}}1:  भा. 1. 4. 7; १४. २५; II. 4. २०.{{/F}} knew how to read [page३-580+ २८] others' minds and possessed high understanding and culture; {{F}}2:  Ib. III. 2. 9.{{/F}} ended their lives