g through the head of ब्रह्मा. {{F}}3:  वा. २३. ७८, ९१.{{/F}}(V)--the Goddess worshipped by King अश्वपति. M. २०८. 6.(VI)--the daughter of अश्वपति and मालती, mar- ried सत्यवान्. नारद spoke to her of his short life: Followed him to the forest knowing that his end was nearing. Enjoyed his company seeing the fauna and flora there: saw him un- conscious when cutting fuel, {{F}}1:  M. Chh. २०८-9.{{/F}} saw the Lord of death and begged him on her knees to let him live. Yama granted her a boon which she would desire. Her first was that her father-in-law should get back his sight and his kingdom. Though granted, she pursued Yama to free her husband and praised the god's glory. She was asked to name another boon and that was to bless her father with a number of sons. It was granted. Yama asked her to get back. She did not feel weary and pursued him. Her third request was to grant her one hundred sons. Her continuous praise and earnest- ness pleased the god who restored her husband back to life. She returned to the place where the body of सत्यवान् lay, with him she went home, found Dyumatsena enjoying his regained eye-sight and people requesting him to take up the kingship again. Lived long and happy. {{F}}2:  Ib. Chh. २१०-4.{{/F}}--the २४थ् kalpa. M. २९०. 9. [page३-596+ २४](I)--in the नर्मदा. (गया-वा। प्।), auspicious for bath and the offering of मध्यान्ह sandhya or noon prayers. M. १९४. 6. वा. ११२, २२.--witness; the Devas as witnesses to पिण्डदान. वा. ११०. ५९ and ६०.--one of the names in the third मरुत्गण. वा. ६७. १२६.--a son of प्रभा. भा. IV. १३. १३.--(Evening); born of धात्री and कुहू Bha1. VI. १८. 3; Br. II. २१. १२१.--an आर्षेय Pravara of Angiras. M. १९६. २१. [page३-588+ ३१]--a lake on the slopes of the हेमकूट hill. वा. ४७. ६३.--a Durbar; of the king, {{F}}1:  Br. II. २५. १०१: वा. ३०. २७९; ५४. १०५; ९६. ९२.{{/F}} a description of Sagara's assembly; composed of Brahmans, क्षत्रियस्, पौरजानपद, relatives and friends; {{F}}2:  Br. III. ४९. ३१; ५०. १६, १७-20: ५४. २४: ५५. २०.{{/F}} of कृष्ण where there were readings of sacred texts and the पुराणस्; {{F}}3:  M. ६९. १०-11.{{/F}} public halls of Tripuram; {{F}}4:  Ib. १३०. 5.{{/F}} of Maya; respective seats for members; the address of the chief; {{F}}5:  Ib. १३१. २०f.{{/F}} of Indra; {{F}}6:  Ib. १४८. ६१: वा. 1. ९२.{{/F}} of तारक; servants with canes illtreated the devas where the seasons served him as also Siddhas, Kin- naras and Gandharvas the latter by music; {{F}}7:  M. १५४. ३९.{{/F}} of हिरण्य- कशिपु; here were all trees plants and birds, animals, Apsaras and other ladies, Asuras of distinction full of splendour and wealth, the equal of which has neither been heard of nor seen. {{F}}8:  Ib. १६१. ३८-89.{{/F}} [page३-536+ २६]--a son of Anu (4th son of ययाति) and father of कालनर (कालानल ब्र्। and वि। प्।). भा. IX. २३. 1: Br. III. ७४. १३. M. ४८. १०: वा. ९९. १३: Br. IV. १८. 1-2.--members of the assembly; {{F}}1:  वा. १०१. २८३.{{/F}} residence of. {{F}}2:  M. २१५. २५: २४६. ३८: २५४. २६.{{/F}}--a son of शम्स्य agni. वा. २९. १२.--members of the assembly, punished for con- scious misdirection of justice. M. २२७. २११-3.--in गया; श्राद्ध here leads to the fruit of ज्योतिष्टोम. वा. १११. ५१.--a Mt. to the east of अरुणोद. वा. ३६. १९.--इन्द्राणी, took सत्यभामा as a human being and did not accord her due treatment; did not wish to part with पारिजात which Satya wanted; induced Indra to fight कृष्ण who was taking the पारिजात. Vi. V. ३०. २९ and ५२.--see Indra; got कृष्ण's promise of protection to Arjuna. Vi. V. १२. १५; १२. १६-20, २४. [page३-507+ २९]--ministers, consulted by तारक before his war with the devas; {{F}}1:  M. १४८. ३१.{{/F}} of a State. {{F}}2:  Ib. २१६. २५.{{/F}}(I)--a son of Angirasa. M. १९६. 2.(II)--one of Danu's sons. वा. ६८. 9.(I)--the king after Bhoga. Br. III. ७१. १८१.(II)--the first king of विदिश. वा. ९९. ३६७.--a mind-born mother. M. १७९. २२.--a son of अक्रूर. M. ४५. २९. [page३-524+ २६]--is ललिता. Br. IV. १७. ३४.--a R. from the पारियात्र hill. Br. II. १६. २८.--a son of अक्रूर. M. ४५. २९.(I)--the Lord at गोकर्णम् worshipped by भगीरथ. Br. III. ५६, १७, ३९; IV. 8. ३३; ३९. १२०.(II)--a name of विघ्नेश्वर. Br. IV. ४४. ६७; वा. ६२. ३२.--one of the ११ Rudras. वा. ६६. ६९.--is ललिता. Br. IV. १५. 7.--a tribe. M. ११४. ४३. [page३-523+ २५](I)--a Satya god. Br. II. ३६. ३५.(II)--a son of Samara. M. ४९. ५४: Vi. IV. १९. ४१.--the father of उपदानवी. Br. III. 6. २३.--for a sacrifice; members of a sacrificial meet- ing; Sanaka and other sages formed the Sadasyas for Soma's राजसूय; {{F}}1:  वा. 1. २१; ९७. २९.{{/F}} in the army of the Devas at the तारकामय. {{F}}2:  M. २३. २१. Ib. १७४. 5: २४६. ४२.{{/F}}--a मन्त्रकृत्। M. १४५. १०२.--not to marry with Angiras, Kutsas, etc. M. १९६. ३७.--a मन्त्रकृत् and of Angirasa branch. वा. ५९. ९९.--a वानर chief. Br. III. 7. २३२.--a wife of Dharma; sons known as साध्यस्, participators in यज्ञ। वा. ६६. 2, १२.--a son of Kali and a cannibal; wife तामसी, also known as पूतना; had one hand. वा. ८४. १०-2.--a daughter of प्रीती and Pulastya; wife of Bha- रताग्नि and mother of Parjanya. वा. ११. १९, २७; २८. १६.--the 9th kalpa. M. २९०. 5.--a son of बाहु, (Phalgutantra) born with गर (poison) administered to his mother by the co-wives of her husband and after 7 years' stay in his mother's womb; brought up by sage Aurva; केशिनी was one of his queens and सुमती was another. प्रभा, and भानुमती, mother of Asamanjasa were also his queens. Father of Asamanjasa who was abandoned by his father for misconduct. A Cakravarti. His sons ६०,000 in number by Sumati, excavated the sea and dug all over the earth in their search for the consecrated horse. Helped by Aurva, he propi- tiated Hari with sacrifices. Once Indra stole his sacrificial horse, and this was discovered near Kapila's hermitage in the N. E. by his sons who imputed the theft to the sage. The latter burnt them to ashes. But अम्शुमत्, son of Asaman- jasa got back the horse, and enabled his grandfather to com- plete the sacrifice. Anointed अम्शुमत् on the throne in the [page३-502+ ३८] presence of पौरजानपद and devoted himself to attaining salvation through the path prescribed by Aurva. Greed for more territory; conquered तालजन्घस्, Yavanas, शकस्, Haihayas and Barbaras. On the advice of his guru, वसिष्ठ, he spared their lives but punished them by disfiguring them-- some wholly shaven, and some half-shaven. They became ancestors of Mlecchas and व्रात्यस्. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. 8 (whole); X. ४१. १५: XII. 3. 9: Br. III. ५२. ३७ Chh. ५३ and ५४ (whole) ५५. २२: ५८. ३७. Vi. III. 8. 3: १७. 1: वी. IV. 3. ३५-41: 4. 1-२९, ३२. ६३. १२१-151: M. १२. ३९-43.{{/F}} Realised the yoga power of Hari. {{F}}2:  भा. II. 7. ४४.{{/F}} Addressed by him वसिष्ठ narrated the story of परशुराम. In the case of Haihayas, he conquered the king and burnt the city. When he invaded the Vidarbhas, its king sought alliance by offering his daughter in marriage; was honoured by शुरसेनस् and यादवस्. {{F}}3:  Br. III. ३१. 1: ४७. ९३-100: Chh. ४८ (whole).{{/F}} During his rule, nowhere was heard राज s4abdha; ruled like Dharma himself, maintained castes and orders, earned the title of अष्टमण्डल्- आधिपति; had an erudite assembly. {{F}}4:  Ib. III. Chh. ४९-51.{{/F}} The jewel of the solar race. सुमती brought forth a mass of flesh which ulti- mately through the blessings of Aurva was converted into ६०,000 sons.--the sons of Sagara who created eight extra countries (उपद्वीपस्) near जम्बूद्वीप, when they dug up the earth in search of their father's sacrificial horse; {{F}}1:  भा. V. १९-29-३०.{{/F}} purified by the Ganges. {{F}}2:  Vi. II. 8. ११५.{{/F}}(I)--a son of प्राण, and a Vasu. भा. VI. 6. १२.(II)--a son of कृष्ण and माद्री. भा. X. ६१. १५.(III)--month (Tamil-मार्गलि); {{F}}1:  Br. II. १३. १०; वा. ३०. 9; ५०. २०१; ५२. १९; ६२. ४९.{{/F}} sacred to अम्शु. {{F}}2:  भा. XII. ११. ४१.{{/F}}(IV)--a god of the आभूतरय group. Br. II. ३६. ५६.(V)--one of the ten sons of स्वायम्भुव Manu. M. 9. 4.(VI)--the last and tenth son of Auttama Manu, generous and much reputed. M. 9. १३.--(महानन्दी?) ruled for ४३ years; father of महापद्म born of a शूद्र woman. Br. III. ७४. १३४.--king's advisers and servants; a cammander- in-chief either a Brahman or a क्षत्रिय; प्रतीहार, दूत, रक्षिण्स् or bodyguards; a नारी or nurse; a साङ्धिविग्रहिक; देसरक्षित; a revenue minister; swordsmen and other soldiers; a charioteer; सूदाद्यक्ष; judges; members of assembly; Lekhaka; दौवारिक; धनाध्यक्ष; vaidya; आचार्य; गजाध्यक्ष; अश्वाध्यक्ष; दुर्गाध्यक्ष; sthapati; अस्त्राचार्य; पुराध्यक्ष; आयूधागाराध्यक्ष; mantrins; उपधास्; चारास्. M. ch. २१५.(I)--a son of दिवा(r)ka(ra) and a hero: father of बृहदश्व. भा. IX. १२. ११; M. २७१. 6; वा. ९९. २८३; Vi. IV. २२. 4.(II)--a son of जरासन्ध of the मागध line; father of सोमापि(a) and मार्जास्पि; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २२. 9 and ४६; M. ५०. ३३. Vi. IV. १९. ८४; २३. 4.{{/F}} enthroned by कृष्ण; commanded by कृष्ण, he arranged for the bath, dress and meals of the released kings; honoured कृष्ण when he left the capital. {{F}}2:  भा. X. ७२. ४८; ७३. २४-6, and ३१; वा. ९९. २२७.{{/F}} Killed in भारत battle; his son सोमापि (सोमाधि-म्। प्।) ruled for ५८ years, at Girivraja. The latter's son was श्रुतश्रवस्. {{F}}3:  Br. III. ७४. १०९-11. M. २७१. १८.{{/F}}(III)--a son of Havyavana, and father of हीन. भा. IX. १७. १७.(IV)--a son of सुदास, (सन्दास-वि। प्।), and father of Somaka. भा. IX. २२. 1; वा. ९९. २०७; Vi. IV. १९. ७१.(V)--a son of माद्री (माद्रवती-ब्र्। प्।), born through the grace of the अश्विन्स्. Father of श्रुतकर्मन्. His other son was Suhotra by विजया; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २२. २८-31; Br. III. ७१. १५५; M. ४६. १०; ५०. ५०; वा. ९६. १५४; ९९. २४५. Vi. IV. १४. ३८; २०. ४०.{{/F}} joy at कृष्ण's visit to Indraprastha; paid his respects to him; was consoled by [page३-571+ २४] कृष्ण when banished to the forest; {{F}}2:  भा. X. ७१. २७. ५८. 4; ६४. 9.{{/F}} was sent to southern countries with सृञ्जयस्. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ७२. १३; ७४. १८-25; ७५. 4.{{/F}} His suggestion that कृष्ण should be accorded the first honour among the Sadasyas in the राजसूय of युधिष्ठिर was accepted. Entertained guests in that sacrifice. Approved of द्रौपदी's desire 