ined बृहस्पति in the तार- कामय; {{F}}4:  Ib. IV. 6. १६.{{/F}} father of Arjuna. {{F}}5:  Ib. IV. २०. ४०.{{/F}}(I)--a son of Nighna; to him the sun was a great companion; once he visited him and wanted to see his form; for this the sun handed over Syamantaka the best of gems wearing which he saw his form distinctly; it was so beautiful that he desired to keep the gem himself to which the sun agreed; then he returned to his city with the jewel; he shone like the sun himself and entered the harem to the wonderment of his people. {{F}}1:  वा. ९६. २०-9.{{/F}} शक्रजित् received back the मणि from वासुदेव; he had १०० sons by his ten wives; of these three were famous, भन्गकार, Vratapati and अपस्वान्. {{F}}2:  वा. ९६. ५०, ५३.{{/F}} [page३-361+ २९](II)--a son of शूर. वा. ९६. १३७.--a distance equal to १००० yojanas. Br. IV. 2. १२७; वा. १०१. १२७.--a सुधर्माण god. Br. IV. 1. ६०.--(शक्रपूज) a festival in honour of Indra; {{F}}1:  Vi. V. १०. १८ and २५.{{/F}} being the Lord of rains he was expected to shower seasonal rains. {{F}}2:  Ib. V. १०. २३.{{/F}}--in गया. वा. १११. ५२.--is Indraprastha. भा. X. ७१. २२.--on the southern bank of the नर्मदा; sacred to the पितृस्. M. १९१. २०; २२. ७३.--of कश्यपगोत्र. M. १९९. 4.--a देवगण, mind-born sons of ब्रह्मा, in the स्वायम्भुव epoch. Br. II. १३. ९०.(I)--(शक्त्रि-ब्र्। प्।) the eldest of the १०० sons of वसिष्ठ and अरुन्धती. Father of पराशर through अदृ- श्यन्ति; {{F}}1:  भा. IV. 1. ४१; Br. I. 1. 9; III. 8. ९१; ३६. 6; M. २०१. ३०; वा. 1. १७४; ७०. ८३.{{/F}} a sage by tapas; a वेदव्यास. Heard the वायु पुराण from दक्ष and narrated it to पराशर in embryo; {{F}}2:  Br. II. ३२; ९९ and ११५; ३५. १२४; IV. 4. ६५; M. १९६. २६; वा. १०३. ६५.{{/F}} a resident of ब्रह्मक्षेत्र; {{F}}3:  वा. ५९. ९१, १०५.{{/F}} cursed king कल्माषपाद in नैमिष. {{F}}4:  Ib. 2. १०-11.{{/F}}(II)--the principle identified with शिव; {{F}}1:  भा. IV. 6. ४३.{{/F}} urges creation by ब्रह्मा. {{F}}2:  Vi. I. 5. ४७.{{/F}}(III)--as a daughter of वसिष्ठ and अरुन्धती. Br. I. 2. १०. [page३-358+ ३५](