erformed अश्वमेधस्. Br. III. ७४. २६९; M. २७३. ७३.(I) (चित्ररथ)--a son of Citraratha; highly learned and a yogin; an emperor of glory; had ten thousand wives and thousands of sons of whom six were distinguished. Possessed fourteen excellent jewels. His daughter Bin- दुमती (चैत्ररथी) had १०० famous sons with names begin- ning with पृथु; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २३. ३१-33; 6. ३८; Br. III. ७०. १९-22; M. ४४. १८-19; वा. ८८. ७०; ९५. १८-21.{{/F}} father-in-law of मान्धाता; heard of the significance of श्राद्ध from Yama. {{F}}2:  Br. III. १८. 1 and १५; ६३. ७०.{{/F}}(II)--the moon. वा. ८२. 1.--the animal fit for श्राद्ध purposes. वा. ८८. १३.(I)--a son of Andhaka. M. ४४. ६१. [page३-396+ २९](II)--moon; {{F}}1:  M. ९३. १३.{{/F}} chariot of, described; relation of, to the sun cosmology; his nectar and its use to gods, ऋषिस् and पितृस्; {{F}}2:  Ib. १२६. ४८-73.{{/F}} his मण्डल twice that of the sun; {{F}}3:  Ib. १२४. 8.{{/F}} van- quished by रावण. {{F}}4:  Br. II. २१. 8; २४. ६७; III. 7. २५४.{{/F}}--a son of Citraratha; lord of १४ maha1ratnas and cakravarti; had १००,000 wives and ten lakhs of sons, among whom the chief were पृथुश्रव, पृथुकर्म and four others; (see शशबिन्दु). Vi. IV. १२. 3-6.--the region of the moon, १००,000 yoja- nas from that of the sun; above it is the नक्षत्र man2d2alam. Vi. II. 7. 5-6.--a कला of the moon. Br. IV. ३५. ९२.--a शक्ति. Br. IV. ४४. ७५.--one-sixth of their merit the Brahmans give to righteous kings. भा. V. १५. ११.--sacred to ललिता pi1t2ha. Br. IV. ४४. ९८.--a शक्ति. Br. IV. ४४. ९१.--a दानव. Br. III. 6. 9.--a son of Jambha. वा. ६७. ७८.--a तीर्थ sacred to the पितृस्. M. २२. ३५.--a दानव. Br. III. 6. 6.--a son of भजमान. भा. IX. २४. 8.--a daughter of Ugrasena. वा. ९६. १३३. [page३-378+ २५](I)--a son of अहल्या and Gautama, (शरद्- वान्-म्। प्।). Father of सत्यधृति. भा. IX. २१. ३४-35; M. ५०. 8; Vi. IV. १९. ६३.(II)--came to see कृष्ण at Syamanta- पञ्चक. भा. X. ८४. 3.(III)--a sage of the period of सावर्णि. M. 9. ३२. [page३-377+ २८](IV)--a son of शारद्वत, a great seer. वा