s a wolf; again the daughter of the king of काशी met him; remembering his former state he was born as a vulture, crow and a peacock; when she bathed him during the sacrificial bath of Janaka he was born as the son of Janaka. Then a svayamvara was held, she married him, lived as his queen and attained heaven. See शैव्या. Vi. III. १८. ५३-95.(I)--the wicked; of the race of Bhojas, and king of मिथिला; set up अक्रूर and कृतवर्मन् who were displeased with सत्राजित for not giving his daughter in marriage to them; शतधन्वन् killed सत्राजित while asleep, and walked away with the jewel; when कृष्ण heard of this from सत्यभामा, he came back to द्वारका from हास्तिन- pura to kill शतधन्वन्. Knowing this, the latter requested कृतवर्मन् and अक्रूर for help and they refused; placing the jewel under अक्रूर's custody he rode one hundred yojanas and on reaching मिथिला, his horse fell tired. Then he ran on foot pursued by कृष्ण. कृष्ण got his head cut off but found no jewel. His death was known in द्वारका; knew the yoga power of Hari. भा. X. ch. ५७ (whole); ५८. 9 [4]; II. 7. ४४; वा. ९६. ५६-74; Vi. IV. १३. ६७-100. [page३-373+ २७](II)--the son of सोमशर्मन् and father of बृहद्रथ. भा. XII. 1. १५; Vi. IV. २४. ३०-1.(III)--the fifth son of हृदीक; {{F}}1:  Br. III. ७१. १४०; वा. ९६. १३९.{{/F}} the middle (second ?) among the ten sons of हृदीक; {{F}}2:  M. ४४. ८१.{{/F}} performed sau- भाग्यशयनम्. {{F}}3:  Ib. ६०. ४९.{{/F}}(IV)--a Maurya king, ruled for six years. M. २७२. २३.(V)--a son of Pracetas; overlord of nume- rous Mlecchas of the north. Vi. IV. १७. 5.--a son of Devavarma, ruled for eight years. वा. ९९. ३३५.(I)--a name of Indra. भा. IX. १०. ३४.(II)--a name of ब्रह्मा. भा. XI. 4. 5.(I)--of दाशार्णस्; was stationed by जरा- sandha on the west of Gomanta fort during its siege. भा. X. ५२. ११[12].(II)--a son of ऊर्ज and father of कृति. Vi. IV. 5. ३१.--a R. in भारतवर्ष, flows from the हिमा- layas. भा. V. १९. १८; Br. II. १२. १५; १६. २५; वा. ४५. ९५; Vi. II. 3. १०; III. १४. १८.--Indra of १००० eyes; adop