e ४०० pour [page३-446+ २४] out rain, ३०० dew, ३०० heat--all for the benefit of man and gods. Br. II. २४. ११, २४, ३३; वा. ५३, 7, १७, २०-21; ६२. १८८.(XI)--a ऋषिक who became a sage by satya. Br. II. ३२. १०२.(XII)--a सुधामान god. Br. II. ३६. २७.(XIII)--a वैकुण्ठ god. Br. II. ३६. ५७.(XIV)--a son of Raivata Manu. Br. II. ३६. ६३.(XV)--a son of भृगु, and a deva. Br. III. 1. ८९.(XVI)--a son of Satyaka. Br. III. ७१. ११६.(XVII)--a बृहद्रथ; ruled for ५८ years. Br. III. ७४. ११५; वा. ९९. ३०२.(XVIII)--(Angirasa) a son and sage of the १४थ् epoch of Bhautya Manu. Br. IV. 1. ११३-4; वा. १००. ११६.(XIX)--a daughter of ताम्रा and कश्यप; mother of swans, cranes, ducks, etc.; {{F}}1:  M. 6. ३०; Vi. I. २१. १५, १७.{{/F}} in the chariot of Tripura. {{F}}2:  M. १३३. २७.{{/F}} [page३-447+ २२](XX)--a son of Auttama Manu. M. 9. १२.(XXI)--a son of Vibhu, ruled for ६४ years. M. २७१. २४.(XXII)--a Saimhikeya. वा. ६८. १९.(XXIII)--a son of Manu and नड्वला. Vi. I. १३. 5.--a son of Citraratha. वा. ९९. २७२.--a son of Citraratha. M. ५०. ८०.--a son of पुरूरवस् and ऊर्वशी. M. २४. ३४.--an Apsaras. Br. III. 7. 6.(I)--an ajita deva. Br. II. १३. ९३; वा. ३१. 7.(II)--a प्रजापति. वा. ६५. ५३.--a queen of ग्रीष्म r2tu. Br. IV. ३२. २५. [page३-448+ २६]--a प्रजापति. Br. III. 1. ५४.(I)--a son of Anenas, and father of शुचि. भा. IX. १७. ११.(II)--a son of Bhautya Manu. Br. IV. 1. ११४.(III)--a son of कौशिक in previous birth, born as चक्रवाह in मानस. M. २०. १८.(IV)--a pure man is rid of his bondage by satva; from the state of निरञ्जन or separation, looks upon all equally. वा. १०२. ६६, ८०, ११८.(V)--a sage of the epoch of the fourteenth Manu. भा. VIII. १३. ३४.--a particular मूर्छन having the 4th accent (music) coming out of मरुदेश; presiding deity, Gandharva. वा. ८६. ३८, ५३.--the second stage of कामाक्षी, the first being चित्परा. Br. IV. ३९, १०.--a particular मूर्छन (music); the seventh in addition to षड्ज. वा. ८६. ४०. [page३-449+ २४]--a son of शाक्य. M. २७१. १२.--the goddess enshrined at कपालमोचन. M. १३. ४८.(I)--the sea of fresh water. भा. V. 1. ३३.(II)--a son of शाक्य, and father of लान्गल (राहुल-वि। प्।). भा. IX. १२. १४; वा. ९९. २८८; Vi. IV. २२. 8.(I)--a son of व्यास and अरणी and a great yogin; superior to his father as a yogi; seeing him firm in renuncia- tion, व्यास taught him the भागवत; renounced worldly life before his upanayana. Wandered naked from place to place and reached the country of कुरुजान्गलस्. When at हास्तिनापुर he stopped for a few minutes at the threshold of householders to purify their abode. {{F}}1:  भा. I. 2. 2-3; 4. 2-8; 7. 8; M. १५. 8.{{/F}} सूत's salutation to: called on परीक्षित् doing प्रायोपवेश and imparted know- ledge to him, addressed by the king as to the best way of spending his last moments for attaining मोक्ष। Enlightened [page३-437+ ३४] him by the भागवत episodes; {{F}}2:  Ib. I. १२. 3; १९. २५-39; 1. 3; XII. 6. 8.{{/F}} went with कृष्ण to मिथिला, and to स्यमन्तपञ्चक for the solar eclipse. Took part in defending द्वारका against शाल्व. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ८६. १८; ७६. १४; ८२. 6.{{/F}} On सौर गण as seven for each month. Heard the story of Citraketu from व्यास, नारद and Devala. {{F}}4:  Ib. XII. ११. २७; VI. १४. 9.{{/F}} In the form of a Brahman; one of the twelve who knew the धर्म ordained by Hari. {{F}}5:  Ib. XII. १३. २१; VI. 3. २०.{{/F}} A Madhya- माध्वर्यु; married पीवरी and got by her five sons all योगा- चार्यस् and a daughter कीर्तिमती, a योगिनी; of superior bhakti; (married पीवरी, the mind-born daughter of the बर्हिषद् Manes and had by her a daughter and four sons-म्। प्।) the sons were कृष्ण, Gama, Prabhu, शम्भु and भूरिश्रुत. {{F}}6:  Br. I. 1. १५०; II. ३३. १४; III. 8. ९२-4; १०. ८०-82; ३४. ३८; M. १५. 8; वा. ७०. ८४; ७३. २८; १०८. ४२ and ६०.{{/F}}(II)--a son of गार्हपत्य agni. Br. II. १२. १२.(III)--a son of शरभ and father of ऋक्ष. Br. III. 7. २०७.(IV)--the father-in-law of अणुह. M. ४९. ५७; वा. ९९. १७९.--see कृत्वी. भा. IX. २१. २५.--a Janapada of the केतुमाला continent. वा. ४४. १३.--a R. of the केतुमाला continent. वा. ४४. १८. [page३-438+ २६]--a name of ललिता. Br. IV. १७. ३३ and ४४.--parrots, children of शुकि; {{F}}1:  M. 6. ३१.{{/F}} cry in the presence of poisoned food; {{F}}2:  Ib. २१९. २०.{{/F}} of the Tamra line. {{F}}3:  Vi. I. २१. १६.{{/F}}(I)--loved by अग्नी. भा. IV. २४. ११.(II)--a daughter of ताम्रा and कश्यप; married Garutmat and had six sons त्रिशिर, Sumukha, Bala, पृष्ट, त्रिशन्कुनेत्र and Surasa who had in their turn a number of sons and grandsons; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 7. 8-9, ४४६; वा. ६९. ३२८-30.{{/F}} brought forth parrots and owls; gave birth to parrots, owls, and crows (वि। प्।) {{F}}2:  M. 6. ३०-31; Vi. I. २१. १५-16.{{/F}}(I)--a name of Hari. भा. III. २१. ३५. [page३-443+ २८](II)--a son of हविर्धान. भा. IV. २४. 8; Br. II. ३७. २४.(III)--a Mt. in क्रौञ्चद्वीप. भा. V. २०. २१.(V)--one of the seven sons of वसिष्ठ. वा. २८. ३६.(IV)--the first of पक्षस्; {{F}}1:  M. २३. १४; वा. ५३. ११४; ८३. ८०.{{/F}} the night of the पितृस्; {{F}}2:  Ib. ५२. ५९; ५७. 9.{{/F}} the ocean rises and falls in. {{F}}3:  Ib. ४९. २७.{{/F}}(II)--same as Vidyut. M. १२२. ७३.--on account of the distance of the rising sun the reflection of agni and waters is white, and of earth dark and red when there is no ray; and hot owing to this reddishness. वा. ५०. ११०.(I)--a son of बलराम. Br. III. ७१. १६७.(II)--a son of सारण. वा. ९६. १६५.--the two ayanams. वा. ३१. ३०.--near Benares. M. १८३. ६२.--a group of नाडीस् of the sun emitting heat. Br. II. २४. ३०.--sacred to शिव; merits of expounded to शिव to मार्कण्डेय; attached to the नर्मदा; here चाणक्य a राजऋषि attained siddhi; destroys the sin of brahmicide and infanticide; the lord lives here with उमा on the fourteenth day of the dark half of वैशाख and Caitra months. Prayers [page३-444+ २८] on the fourteenth day of the कृत्तिका month takes one to the abode of शिव. M. १९२. 3, १२-38.(I)--(alias उशनस्) a son of Kavi (हविर्धान and दिव्या, hence काव्य); married ऊर्जस्वती, and father of [page३-439+ ४९] देवयानी through जयन्ती. {{F}}1:  भा. III. 1. २२; IV. 1. ४५; V. 1. ३५; VI. 7. १८; वा. ६३. २३; ६५. ७४; ९३. ८५; १०१. ३३; Vi. I, १४. 2.{{/F}} The Purohita of हिरण्यकशिपु. Father of शण्ड and Marka, tutors of प्रह्लाद. Took part in प्रह्लाद's coronation. A ब्रह्मऋषि: Heard of the in- sult offered to his daughter by शर्मिष्ठा, the daughter of the ruler वृषपर्वन् and left the capital. The Purohita of वृषपर्वन्, the latter made him stay offering to make his daughter a slave of देवयाणी. In offering the latter to ययाति, he asked him not to share his bed with शर्मिष्ठा, cursed ययाति to become aged for having shared his bed with शर्मिष्ठा, and on an appeal mitigated it by saying that he could exchange his old age with youth of another if he found one to accept the exchange; {{F}}2:  भा. IX. Ch. १८ (whole); VII. 5. 1-2 १०. ३३; Br. III. ६८. १५; M. २५. 4, १६; २७. २६, ३७; ३०. ३०-36; ३२. २३, २६; ३३. 2 and २६.{{/F}} joined Soma in तारकामय war: blessed the Asuras in this war: fought with बृहस्पति in a देवासुर battle. {{F}}3:  भा. IX. १४. 6; VIII. १०. ३३.{{/F}} Brought back to life the unconscious Bali by सञ्जीविनी Vidya. Presented Bali with an unfading garland of flowers; knowing वामन to be Hari, warned Bali from agreeing to his request. Bali would not hear, and शुक्र cursed him to lose all श्री. At the bidding of Hari com- pleted the यज्ञ begun by Bali. {{F}}4:  Ib. VIII. ११. ४७-8; १५. 6; १९. ३०-43; २०. 1-१५; २३. १८; Br. III. ३०. ५४; ६५. ३१; M. १९२. १०; २४६. 1.{{/F}} The third वेदव्यास. Heard the पुराण from वायु and told it to बृहस्पति; {{F}}5:  Br. III. 1. ७६ and ८६; १०. १८; II. ३५. ११७; IV. 4. ५९.{{/F}} wor- shipped स्थानु with severe penance; born in तिष्यनक्षत्र: married mind-born daughter of पितृस् (Somapas) and father of 4 sons, त्वष्ट्रि, Varatri, शण्ड and Marka; {{F}}6:  Ib. I. 1. १२७-9; II. २४. ५०-51 and १३१; ३३. ३२; III. 1. ७५-8; १०. ८६-7; ६८. १५, ८६-7.{{/F}} cursed the Asuras when they lost their empire, and यज्ञ came to the side of Devas. Asura's appeal and शुक्र's penance to शिव. Finding the Asuras having no आचार्य, the Devas attacked them who appealed to शुक्र's mother. विष्णु at the instance of Indra slew her, a woman and a wife of भृगु, for which विष्णु was cursed to be born on earth as man seven times. Indra then set up his daughter जयन्ती to serve शुक्र and earn his goodwill. Pleased with her service, शुक्र agreed to live with her as husband for ten years. After this period, बृहस्पति assumed his form and deluded the Asuras. शुक्र who grew angry cursed the Asuras at which बृहस्पति felt happy and threw off his disguise. They appealed to शुक्र for help once again or threatened to leave for रसातलम्. He managed to get back their kingdom in the epoch of सावर्णि [page३-440+ ४८] when Bali was emperor; {{F}}7:  Ib. III. ७२. ९३-195; ७३. 2, ५८; M. ४७. ८६-111, १७२-202.{{/F}} lives in Bhuvarlokam; आश्रम of, located below the सहस्रशिखर and Kumuda hills; {{F}}8:  Br. IV. 2. ३०; वा. ३८. ६०-2;{{/F}} consecrated भण्ड on the throne; {{F}}9:  Br. IV. १२ 2-6; १७. ५६.{{/F}} revealed अन्गारकव्रत to विऋओचन; {{F}}१०:  M. ६२. 6, २७-40.{{/F}} preached peace between the devas and asuras after seeing the destruction of twelve wars: wanted to excel बृहस्पति in मन्त्र by the grace of शिव and learnt नीति from शिव; {{F}}११:  Ib. ४७. ६१-84.{{/F}} encouraged Asuras by giving them his pupils शण्ड and Marka for assistance. But his curse tells when the pupils desert them. Both were bought off by gods who offered them a status in sacrifices. This resulted in the helplessness of Asuras who entered रसातलम्; {{F}}१२:  Ib. ४७. २१०-233; ४८. ९३; ९३. १४.{{/F}} appointed Purohita of the Asuras; expert in सञ्जीविनी vidya1, revived the dead back to life; {{F}}१३:  Ib. २५. 9.{{/F}} taught Kaca, son of बृहस्पति; {{F}}१४:  Ib. २५. ४७.{{/F}} has ruled that the son of the king who pleases his father best is entitled to the throne; {{F}}१५:  Ib. ३४. २४-5.{{/F}} a ऋषि; {{F}}१६:  Ib. ४७. ६२ and ११४; १२६. ६९; १४५. ९२.{{/F}} a मन्त्रकृत्; {{F}}१७:  Ib. १४५. १०३.{{/F}} asked Bali to treat वामन with choice gift. ^१८ Ib. २४६. 3.(II)--goes round Dhruva, and is believed to cause rain by his rapid marches, before or after or along with the sun; {{F}}1:  भा. IV. 9. २१; V. २२. १२.{{/F}} the planet above Budha; {{F}}2:  Br. IV. 2. १३२; वा. १०१. १३२.{{/F}} fed by the विश्वश्रव ray of the sun: of १६ rays of white watery region: 1/१६ in size to the moon; {{F}}3:  Ib. II. २४. ६९. ९५ and १०४.{{/F}} to be worshipped when it begins to rise or is opposite or at the commencement or end of a journey; {{F}}4:  M. ७३. 1.{{/F}} gifts to be given to a सामग; {{F}}5:  Ib. १६३. ३९.{{/F}} on the left, a bad omen; an auspicious planet. {{F}}6:  Ib. १६४. 8.{{/F}} car of, drawn by earth-born horses armed with arrows and adorned with pennon. {{F}}7:  वा. ५२. ७४-5; Vi. II. १२. १७.{{/F}} [page३-441+ २५](III)--the month sacred to मीत्र. भा. XII. ११. ३५; Br. II. १३. 9; वा. ३०. 8.(IV)--the नाग presiding over the month of शुचि. भा. XII. ११. ३६.(V)--a son of ऊरु and आग्नेयी. Br. II. ३६. १०८.(VI)--a name of शिव. Br. III. ७२. १८३.(VII)--one of the twenty Sutapa गणस्. Br. IV. 1. १४; वा. १००. १४.(VIII)--a son of ऊर्जा and वसिष्ठ: a sage of the epoch of Bhautya Manu; of the XIV epoch of Manu. Br. IV. 1. ११३; Vi. I. १०. १३; III. 2. ४४.(IX)--a son of हविर्धान. M. 4. ४६.(X)--a son of Auttama Manu; married गौट् the mind-born daughter of the मानस Pitr2s. M. 9. २०; १५. १५.(XI)--a son of सावर्णि Manu; the hero. M. 9. ३३.(XII)--a son of प्रजापति and overlord of Daityas; {{F}}1:  वा. १०. ७२; ३८. ६२; ५३. ३३.{{/F}} mother of, brought back to life by भृगु. {{F}}2:  Ib. 1. १५०.{{/F}} [page३-442+ २४](XIII)--the शुक्ल Paks2a. वा. ५२. ३७.(XIV)--a son of Jala or waters. Vi. I. 8. ११.(XV)--a son of Nandana. Vi. IV. २४. ५६.--the second son of गार्हपत्य. वा. २९. ११.--a R. in शाल्मलिद्वीप. Br. II. १९. ४६; वा. ४९. ४२.--the mind-born sons of स्वायम्भुव Manu; १२ in number, all सोमपायिन्स्--a गण. Br. II. 9. ४६; १२. ४७; वा. ३१. 4. 8-9.--a queen of ग्रीष्म r2tu. Br. IV. ३२. २५.--on the south bank of the नर्मदा; sacred to the पितृस्. M. २२. २९; १९१. २०-21.--a portion of the Vedic literature, the Yajur Veda; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३