 eastern country and tribe; a Janapada of the east. {{F}}2:  Br. II. १८. ५१; III. ७४. १९७; M. ११४. ४५; १२१. ५०; १६३. ७२; वा. ४५. १२३; ९९. ३८५.{{/F}}--(ताम्रम्) copper vessel for ceremo- nial purposes; fit for gifts. M. 7. १२; ५८. १३; ५९. 8; ६१. ४५; २०६. १५; २७९. 7; २८८. ११; वा. ७४. 1. [page२-017+ ३२](I)--the elephant of the साम fold. Br. III. 7. ३३७.(II)--one of the nine divisions of भारत- वर्ष. M. ११४. 8; Vi. II. 3. 6.(I)--a R. of the कुलाचल hill in भारत- वर्ष, {{F}}1:  भा. IV. २८. ३५; V. १९. १८.{{/F}} and in द्राविड. {{F}}2:  Ib. XI. 5. ३९.{{/F}} Visited by बलराम; {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ७९. १६.{{/F}} from the Malaya Hills flowing through sandal wood regions; famous for pearls and conch; fit for श्राद्ध offerings; {{F}}4:  Br. II. १६. ३६; III. १३. २४-7; IV. ३३. ५२; Vi. II. 3. १३.{{/F}} sacred to पितृस्; {{F}}5:  M. २२. ४९; ११४. ३०.{{/F}} flows towards the southern ocean; at its confluence with the ocean are produced conches, shells and pearls. {{F}}6:  वा. ७७. २४-5.{{/F}}(II)--a daughter of सत्यभामा. Br. III. ७१. २४८; वा. ९६. २४०.--a son of रोहिणि and कृष्ण. Vi. V. ३२. 2.--a daughter of रौद्राश्व. वा. ९९. १२६.--copper hall; of Lalita's श्रीपुर--square in shape spreading to seven yojanas. There was कल्पकवा- टिक between this and काम्श्यशाल full of beautiful and fragrant trees. Br. IV. ३१. ६६.--a son of कृष्ण and रोहिणी. भा. X. ६१. १८.--a Mt. near Patanga in the southern direction. वा. ३८. 8.(I)--a division of the भारतवर्ष. Br. II. १६. 9; वा. ४५. ७९.(III)--name of an elephant; son of पुष्प- danta. वा. ६९. २२१.(II)--a R. of the Malaya hills. वा. ४५. १०५.--a son of सत्यभामा. वा. ९६. २३९.--exclusion of marriage alliances among Angiras and Maudgalyas. M. १९६. ४४.--a mode of worship but different from the Vaidika or Vedic path; {{F}}1:  भा. VIII. 6. 9.{{/F}} the तान्त्रिक concept of Hari. {{F}}2:  Ib. XII. ११ (whole); Br. IV. 2. १०८.{{/F}}--as different from the Vaidika, in the mode of prayer to Hari. भा. XI. ११. ३७; २७. 7. [page२-013+ २६]--a western country. Br. II. १६. ६०.--a pupil of याज्ञवल्क्य. Br. II. ३५. २९.--a southern tribe. M. ११४. ४९; वा. ४५. १२९.--Here to the wonderment of a hunter, a deer which fell in water due to dread was taken to the world above. M. १९१. १०२-4.--three pains; आध्यात्मिक (bodily and mental pain), आधिभौतिक (natural but incidental pain) and आधिदैविक (superhuman); each is multiplied in thousands. Vi. VI. 5. 1-9.(I)--a R. in भारतवर्ष rising in the Vin- dhyas; {{F}}1:  भा. V. १९. १८; Br. II. १६. ३२; M. ११४. २७.{{/F}} visited by बलराम. {{F}}2:  वा. ४५. १०२; भा. X. ७९. २०.{{/F}}(II)--a R. rises from the ऋक्ष hill. Vi. II. 3. ११.--one of Danu's sons. वा. ६८. 8.(I)--a monkey chief. Br. III. 7. २३१.(II)--a God of the Harita गण. Br. IV. 1. ८५.(I)--the wife of बृहस्पति, and abducted by Soma. Of this union was born Budha. Through ब्रह्मा's influ- ence she was restored to her husband; (came back to बृहस्- pati after a battle between the Devas and the दानवस्). भा. IX. १४. 4-8, १३-14; Br. III. ६५. २९; M. २३. ३०-47; २४. 3; वा. ९०. २८-35, ४३. Vi. IV. 6. १०-33.(II)--a ब्रह्मवादिनी. Br. II. ३३. १८.(III)--a daughter of सुषेण and queen of वालि; her son was अङ्गद. Br. III. 7. २१९. [page२-021+ ३१](IV)--also तोरणेश्वरि and ताराम्बिका; a शक्ति living in the midst of waters that could be crossed only by boats of different sizes. Br. IV. ३५. १२-24, ५८; ३६. १६; ४४. ८०.(V)--the goddess enshrined at किष्किन्धपर्वत. M. १३. ४६.(VI)--one of the ten branches of the Harita group of Devas. वा. १००. ८९.--Lord of the stars; the moon. वा. ४१. ५८.--a son of चन्द्रावलोक of the सूर्यवम्श. M. १२. ५४.--above नक्षत्रमण्डल; below this Budha moves. वा. १०१. ३१, १३२.(I)--an Asura; took part in a देवासुर battle between Bali and Indra. {{F}}1:  भा. VIII. १०. २१.{{/F}} Fought with Guha in a देवासुर war. {{F}}2:  Ib. VIII. १०. २८; M. ६१. ३८.{{/F}} Lust after more territory. {{F}}3:  भा. XII. 3. ११.{{/F}} Escaped to the ocean and gave trouble by coming out often. {{F}}4:  M. ६१. 4; १२९. 5; १३१. २२; १३६. ३४ and ६७.{{/F}} Slain by Nandin. {{F}}5:  M. १३८. ४३-4.{{/F}} City in the third तल named after him. {{F}}6:  Br. II. २०. २६.{{/F}}(II)--a son of Danu, {{F}}1:  Br. III. 6. 7; M. 6. १९; वा. ५०. २६; ६८. 7; Vi. I. २१. 5.{{/F}} and a friend of भण्ड. {{F}}2:  Br. IV. ३०. ३९.{{/F}}(III)--from तारण or that which takes good men across to next world. M. १२८. ३४ and ५६. [page२-019+ ३३](IV)--a son of वज्रान्ग and वरान्गी who troubled the Devas and destined to be killed by a baby of seven days; relieved his mother (तारक) from sorrows and hence the name; एत्य्। was crowned king of the Asura world; did penance at the पारियात्र cave when ब्रह्मा granted his wish to be killed by a lad of seven days. All लोकपालस् served him. He wanted to vanquish Hari and set out with Grasana as commander. The flag of मकर was hoisted. Indra's report to बृहस्पति. {{F}}1:  M. Chh. १४६-149; १६०. २५-6; Br. IV. ११. 7.{{/F}} The war in which he was killed by कुमार. {{F}}2:  Br. III. १०. ४९; IV. ३०. १०३; वा. ७२. ४७.{{/F}}(V)--of कौशिक gotra. वा. ९१. ९८.--सुनीती, the mother of Dhruva, known as. Vi. I. १२. ९४.(I)--A देवासुर battle in कृत yuga; तारा's (तारका, बृहस्पति's wife) abduction by Soma, was the ground for war between the Asuras and the Suras. शुक्र joined Soma while शिव and Indra took up बृहस्- pati's cause. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. १४. 4-7; Br. III. 5. ३२; M. १२९. १६; १७२. १०; वा. ६७. ६९; ७०. ८१; ९०. ३३.{{/F}} Here विष्णु killed कालनेमि, and Indra, Viro- cana, son of प्रह्लाद; (Virocana was killed by विष्णु in the [page२-020+ २९] guise of Indra-वा। प्।). After the war there was a famine when वसिष्ठ helped the people with fruits and roots; {{F}}2:  Br. III. 8. ८८; ६५. ३४; ७२. २०-21, ७४; M. Chh. १७३- १७८.{{/F}} the fifth battle in which Virocana was blessed with eternal life by शिव; {{F}}3:  वा. ९७. २१, ७४ and ८०.{{/F}} ended with the intervention of ब्रह्मा who gave तारा back to बृहस्पति. {{F}}4:  Vi. IV. 6. १६-19.{{/F}}(II)--the fifth of the twelve कोलाहलस्. Indra killed Virocana, son of प्रह्लाद. M. ४७. ४३-9.--extent of, west to east five thousand yojanas; above i