; ७७. ५७-64. [page२-042+ २६]--the son of शुचि; also known as Dharma- सारथि. Father of शान्तरय. भा. IX. १७. ११-12.--(त्रिकर्णक ?) a commander of भण्ड to aid विषङ्ग; {{F}}1:  Br. IV. २५. २९.{{/F}} was killed by ज्वाला ma1linika1. {{F}}2:  Ib. IV. २५. ९८.{{/F}}--a name of शिव. वा. ३०. २१७.--a प्रकटशक्ति. Br. IV. १९. १५; ४२. 2; ४४. ११५.--one of the ten पीठस् for images, in the shape of a trident. M. २६२. 7, १२, १८.--the whole universe is said to be pervaded by the three daughters of हिमवान्, अपर्णा, Eka- पर्णा and एकपाटला, all eternal youths and ब्रह्मवादिनीस्. Br. III. १०. १४; वा. ७२. १३-5.(I)--a mountain on the base of the Meru, in भारतवर्ष; {{F}}1:  भा. V. १६. २६; १९. १६.{{/F}} surrounded by क्षीरोद, and १०००० yojanas high with three shining crests of silver, iron and gold; served by Siddhas, चारणस् and others. In its valley was ऋतुमत्, the pleasure garden of goddesses, full of varied trees. {{F}}2:  Ib. VIII. 2. 1-१९.{{/F}}(II)--Here is लन्का in मलयद्वीप. वा. ४८. २६.(I)--शिव known in Trayambaka क्षेत्र; meditation of. M. २२. ४७; १३१. ३५; २६६. ३६; Vi. V. ३३. 1.(II)--a name of विघ्नेश्वर. Br. IV. ४४. ६७.--progress of, depends on the sun without which there would be no reckoning of time and nothing would go on. वा. ५०. ६०; ५३. ३४-41. [page२-049+ ३७]--a Pravara. M. १९६. ३०.--is Om; प्रणव constituted by वैद्युती, तामसी and निर्गुणि Ma1tras. वा. २०. 1.--the Brahmanas of the साम Veda fit for feeding on the श्राद्ध occasions. Vi. III. १५. 2.--a horse of the Moon's chariot. वा. ५२. ५३.--a son of खश, and a राक्षस. Br. III. 7. १३५.(त्रिणाचिकेत-वा। प्।) the Brahmanas of the Yajur Veda, fit for श्राद्ध feeding. Vi. III. १५. 2; वा 79. ५८; ८३. ५३.(I)--see शिव; {{F}}1:  Br. II. २७. ६९; III. २३. ३१; २४. ७९; २५. 2; ३२. १८.{{/F}} constructed the पुष्पकम्. {{F}}2:  M. १२९. ३६; १३०. १२.{{/F}}(II)--the son of निर्वृति; ruled for २८ years. M. २७१. २७.--the name of a horse of the Moon's chariot. M. १२६. ५२. [page२-046+ ३८]--गन्गा (s.v.) descended at the Gaura hill; {{F}}1:  Br. II. १८. २७, २९, ३०.{{/F}} fell on शिव's head; {{F}}2:  Ib. III. १३. ११८; २५. ११.{{/F}} originating from the foot of Soma; {{F}}3:  M. १०२. 8; १०६. ५१; १२१. २८-9; १८३. 7.{{/F}} came to be divided into seven streams; flows in अन्तरिक्ष, Divam and भूमि; शिव prevented her course by yoga, when she grew angry and on account of which drops of water fell on the ground and collected themselves into a lake, Bindusaras; she resisted this and wanted to enter the पाताल when ब्रह्मा consoled her and let her flow in seven directions, three to the east, three to the west and the seventh to the south; the last one is भा- गीरथी. {{F}}4:  वा. ४७. २६-41.{{/F}} Stopped in the sky above मानस. {{F}}5:  Ib. ७७. १११.{{/F}}(I)--near the दृषद्वती; {{F}}1:  Br. III. १३. ६९.{{/F}} like श्यामक and इक्षु being created by Gods; {{F}}2:  Ib. १४. 8.{{/F}} to be propitiated at the Parva and at the Tithis. {{F}}3:  Ib. १७. 6.{{/F}} [page२-048+ २४]--a mark on the forehead. Br. IV. ३८. २२.(I)--a city built by माया, of gold, silver and iron fortifications for the sake of Asuras. {{F}}1:  भा. IV. १७. १३; V. २४. २८; VII. १०. ५४ and ६८. VIII. 6. ३१; XI. १६. २०; Br. III. ७२. ८२. वा. ९७. ८२.{{/F}} Really three towns under तारक, Maya and विद्युन्मालि; city described. Battle of Tripuram; march of शिव's army. First battle at तारकाख्यपुरम्; non-combatants visiting it; fight be- tween Nandi and विद्युन्मालि; तारक's fight with the गणस्; actual battle on the shores of the western sea, described; battle in the air and under water; तारक slain by Nandi, as also विद्युन्मालि; burning the city including women and children by शिव. {{F}}2:  M. Chh. १२९-130; Chh. १३५-140; १८७. 8, १४-6; १८८. 9-१०.{{/F}}(II)--an Asura having his city in the third Talam. Br. II. २०. २७; III. ३८. 4.--a name of ललिता; worship of. Br. IV. 5. ३१.--a mother Goddess, see ललिता. Br. IV. 7. ७२; ११. 1.--(Tripuradhvamsa): see शिव. Br. III. २३. ३२; २५. १३.--an epithet of Rudra; शिव with १६ hands danced in joy at the ruin of the city, Tripuram (s.v.). M. १७९. ३८; २५९. ११.--the second charioteer of ललिता. Br. IV. २०. ९१. [page२-047+ २८]--a तीर्थम् sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ४३.--is ललिता. Br. IV. १८. १४; ३९. ७६, ९६ ff; ४०. 1, ४३ ff.--a Guptayogini. Br. IV. ३६. ७२.--deals with the construction of Tri- pura by Maya; trouble to the world by the Asuras; Gods wait on Rudra; the war chariot of शिव; नारद's mediation; Maya gets ready for war; the war; the efforts of गणस्, especially Nandi's part in the battle; death of तारक; the second day of the battle; शिव's victory by burning the city. M. Chh. १२९-141.--a R. in भारतवर्ष, from the Mahendra hill. भा. V. १९. १८; Br. II. १६. ३७; वा. ४५. १०६; Vi. II. 3. १३.--the son of गोभानु, and father of Karan- dhama. Br. III. ७४. 1; वा. ९९. 1.--a son of गोभानु. M. ४८. 1.(I)--The goddess enshrined at गोदाश्रम. M. १३. ३७.(II)--a तीर्थम् sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ४६. [page२-053+ ३१]--also known as धान्यकम्. M. २५३. ५१; २५४. 4-7.--Satyavrata (s.v): the son of Tribandhana and father of हरिश्चन्द्र; became a चण्डाल by the curse of his Guru; three spikes meant for him by वसिष्ठ. Result of his three sins--displeasing his father, killing the Guru's cow and eating unconsecrated flesh; banished from the kingdom; seeing this विश्वामित्र consoled him and agreed to be his Guru; the latter had him crowned after a purifica- tion bath in the river, कर्मनाशा near the Vindhyas; this enabled him to go to heaven bodily and get a place among [page२-051+ ३१] the planets all in the presence of वसिष्ठ; though thrust down headlong from heaven, he was stopped and given a place in the sky. भा. IX. 7. 5-7; Br. III. ६३. १०८; वा. ८८. १०८-13. Vi. IV. 3. २१.--the territory north of the महा- नदी and south of वैकट (कैकट-वा। प्।) unfit for श्राद्ध. Br. III. १४. ३१-2; M. १६. १६; वा. ७८. २१. 2.--the planet त्रिशङ्कु or Satyavrata in the moon's sphere, Cf. रामा. Yud., IV. ९०. वा. ८८. ११५-6.--one who performs the three ablutions, at dawn, noon and sunset; fit for performing श्राद्ध. वा. ७४. १२.(I)--was Indra of the तामस epoch. भा. VIII. 1. २८.(II)--the Veda-व्यास of the eleventh द्वापर, see त्रिवर्ष. Vi. III. 3. १४.--a Mt. sacred to शिव. M. १८३. 2.--a hill. वा. ४२. २८.(I)--a son of त्वष्ट and यशोधरा; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 1. ८६; वा. ६५. ८५.{{/F}} his mother was a sister of Virocana; {{F}}2:  वा. ८४. १९.{{/F}} a राक्षस killed by राम. {{F}}3:  भा. IX. १०. 9; वा. ६९. १६७.{{/F}} His city was in the third Talam. {{F}}4:  Br. II. २०. २६; वा. ५०. २६.{{/F}} [page२-052+ ३०](II)--a son of खश and a राक्षस. Br. III. 7. १३५.(III)--a son of विश्रवस् and वाका. Br. III. 8. ५६; वा. ७०. ५०.(IV)--a son of प्रह्रादि and त्वष्टा ?. Br. III. ५९. १९-20.--a Mt. on the north of Meru; {{F}}1:  भा. V. १६. २७; M. १६३. ८६; Vi. II. 2. ४४.{{/F}} west of the शितोद. {{F}}2:  वा. ३६. २९; ४२. ७२.{{/F}}--a poetic metre; {{F}}1:  भा. III. १२. ४५; XI. २१. ४१; M. १२५. ४७.{{/F}} a Chandas serving as a horse in the Sun's chariot, {{F}}2:  Br. II. २२. ७२; वा. ५१. ६४; Vi. II. 8. 5.{{/F}} with गायत्रि and Jagati forms the Tri- वर्णम् or प्रणव. {{F}}3:  Br. II. १३. १४५; वा. ३१. ४७.{{/F}}--the trident of शिव; {{F}}1:  Br. III. ३२. १४; IV. १९. 6, ८५; २०. ८१; वा. १०१. २७१.{{/F}} made from the वैष्- णव तेजस् of the sun filed off by त्वष्ट. {{F}}2:  M. 5. ३१; ११. २९; २१७. ३१ Vi. III. 2. ११.{{/F}}--of the lord--Divya, आन्तरिक्ष and Bhauma. वा. २३. १०४, १०७.--the Brahmanas versed in सुपर्ण sec- tions; {{F}}1:  वा. ८३. ५३.{{/F}} eligible for पार्वण S4ra1ddha. {{F}}2:  M. १६. 7; Vi. III. १५. 2.{{/F}}(I)--a sage who called on the dying भीष्म; was invited for the राजसूय of युधिष्ठिर; came to Syamanta- पञ्चक to see कृष्ण. भा. I. 9. 7; X. ७४. 7; ८४. 5.(II)--a son of चाक्षुष Manu. A place sacred to him on the सरस्वती; a मन्त्रकृत्. भा. IV. १३. १६; III. 1. २२; M. १४५. १०१. [page२-044+ २६]--a तीर्थ visited by बलराम. भा. X. ७८. १९.--a group of mountains round मेरुमूल. वा. ३५. 7.--a hunchback maid who supplied unguents to Kamsa. For the mere asking she gave them away to कृष्ण and his brother. Pleased at this, कृष्ण converted her into a beautiful maid. She requested him to go to her house and honour her with his company. He promised to do so after his other engagements were over. {{F}}1:  भा. X. ४२. 1-१२.{{/F}} Visited by कृष्ण with Uddhava. Her house was found filled with pictures drawn according to the कामशास्त्र. After spend- ing some time there, कृष्ण left. {{F}}2:  Ib. X. ४८. 1-१०.{{/F}} Her son was विशोक. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ९०. ३४[1].{{/F}} Came to see कृष्ण and सत्यभामा returning from Indra's abode. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. [६७ (V) ५०].{{/F}}--(Cyavana?) son of अन्तिनार. M. ४९. 8.--three ends of human endeavour, Dharma, Artha and काम; was taught to प्रह्लाद by his tutors. This did not appeal to him. It should be a means to realise Hari, according to प्रह्लाद. {{F}}1:  भा. VII. 5. ५२-53; 6. २६.{{/F}} Even the householder, it is said, should not exert himself too much for Trivarga. But it is generally observed by householders. {{F}}2:  Ib. VII. १४. १०; VIII. १६. ११. Vi. III. ११. 6.{{/F}} A भिक्षु is expected to discard it. {{F}}3:  भा. VII. १५. ३६; Br. III. ५०. ५२; ५१. १५.{{/F}} To one devoid of Dharma, the other two, काम and Artha, are of one use. {{F}}4:  M. २९. 3; ५३. 4, ४५; २१२. 3-9.{{/F}} [page२-050+ २९]--the eleventh Veda-व्यास. Br. II. ३५. ११९.--an अवतार् of विष्णु who conquered the three worlds with three steps; the lustrous God with sword as weapon; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 3. ११८; IV. ३४. ७९; M. १७६. ५९; Vi. V. 5. १७.{{/F}} महात्म्यम् of; in the वामन पुराण; icon of; {{F}}2:  M. ५३. ४५; २६०. ३६.{{/F}} Brahma-पुरुषोत्तम. {{F}}3:  वा. १०८. ३८.{{/F}}--heard the ब्रह्माण्ड and वायु पुरणस् from शरद्वान् (शरद्वत) and narrated the former to अन्तरिक्ष. Br. IV. 4. ६१; वा. १०३. ६१.--a साम; {{F}}1:  वा. 9. ४८.{{/F}} created from ब्रह्मा's face. {{F}}2:  Br. II. 8. ५०.{{/F}}--from the first face of ब्रह्मा. Vi. I. 5. ५३.--(नियामिका) night, so called. Br. II. 8. 6, २३.--an Asura friend of Kamsa; created a whirl- wind which covered all Gokulam with dust and took the baby कृष्ण high in the sky. कृष्ण caught hold of his neck and the demon, unable to bear his weight, fell down dead to the wonder of all Gopas and गोपीस्. भा. X. 2. 1; 7. २०-32; २६. 6; ४६. २६; Br. IV. २९. १२४. [page२-035+ २८](I)--a king and the son of Bandhu. (Budha- वि। प्।). His queen was अलम्बुषा. Father of a number of sons and a daughter चेडवीडा. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. 2. ३०-31; Br. III. 8. ३६-7; ६१. १०; Vi. IV. 1. ४६-7.{{/F}} (इलविला-वि। प्।). Lust after more territory. {{F}}2:  भा. XII. 3. १०.{{/F}} Lived at the commencement of the third [page२-034+ २९] त्रेतायुग. His daughter was द्रविडा. Many kings of विशाल ruled by his grace. {{F}}3:  वा 86. १५-16, २२.{{/F}} Begot an Apsaras, आलम्बुषा, a son विशाल who began the वैशाल line of kings which ended with Sumati. {{F}}4:  Vi. IV. 1. ४८-9, ५९.{{/F}}(II)--the २७थ् Veda व्यास, learnt the ब्र्। पुराण and the वायु पुराण from सोमशुष्म and narrated the former to दक्ष. Br. II. ३५. १२३; IV. 4. ६४-65; वा. १०३. ६४.(III)--a sage who got freed from a curse at ऋसितीर्थम् on the नर्मदा. M. १९३. १३.(IV)--the Veda-व्यास of the २३र्द् (२४थ्- वि। प्।) द्वापर; श्वेत, the अवतार् of the Lord. वा. २३. २०३; Vi. III. 3. १७.(V)--the son of Dama and a king at the beginning of the third त्रेतायुग in the ११थ् Manvantara; had a daughter इडिविला, who was married to पौलश्त्य. वा. ७०. ३०-1.--A pravara of Angiras. M. १९६. १३.--heard the ब्र्। and वायु पुराणस् from कृतम्जय and narrated the former to भरद्वाज. Br. IV. 4. ६३; वा. १०३. ६३.--a Mauneya. वा. ६९. 2.also तृषा--implications of, with regard to life and death; {{F}}1:  Br. III. ६८. १०१; IV. 3. ४२, ५९.{{/F}} annihilation of, leads to मोक्ष; {{F}}2:  Ib. IV. 3. ७१.{{/F}} no end of. {{F}}3:  Vi. IV. १०. २४.{{/F}}--a शक्ति resident of षोडशपत्राब्ज. Br. IV. ३२. १४.--an Asura. भा. VII. 2. 4.--a forest tribe of the Vindhyas; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३६. १४५.{{/F}} to be conquer- ed by Kalki. {{F}}2:  Ib. III. ७३. १०८.{{/F}}--a Vindhya tribe. Br. II. १६. ६५.--equinox. वा. ५०. १९५.--Weighing in balance; one of the १६ maha1- दानस्; rules detailed. The gift takes one to the world of विष्णु or Indra. M. २७४. (whole); २७५. 2.--sacred to Hari; {{F}}1:  भा. I. १९. 6; V. 3. 6; X. ३०. 7; XI. ३०. ४१.{{/F}} on the chest of विष्णु. {{F}}2:  Br. IV. 9. ८०-2; १७. ७४.{{/F}}--कृष्ण. Br. III. ३६. ३२.--a son of लान्गली of the २२न्द् Dva1para. वा. २३. २००.--a son of Tumba; had two sons. Br. III. ७१. २५८.--a son of Tumba. Br. III. ७१. २५८.--a son of Tumba. वा. ९६. २४९. [page२-029+ ३६]--a Vindhyan tribe. M. ११४. ५३.--a निषाद tribe; on the other side of the Vindhyas. वा. ६२. १२४; ४५. १३३.(I)--an expert in divine music; had two daughters मनोवती and सुकेशा; {{F}}1:  वा. ६९. ४७, ४९.{{/F}} a friend of Candrodaka दुन्दुभी. {{F}}2:  Ib. ९६. ११७.{{/F}} A Gandharva disciple of नारद, came with the sage to see युधिष्ठिर, and returned to heaven with him; {{F}}3:  भा. I. १३. ३७ and ५९.{{/F}} sang with नारद the glories of Ananta; {{F}}4:  Ib. V. २५. 8.{{/F}} praised हिरण्यकशिपु when he became the overlord of all worlds. {{F}}5:  Ib. VII. 4. १४.{{/F}} Sang the praise of कृष्ण when he held the Govardhana; {{F}}6:  Ib. X. २५. ३२; २७. २४.{{/F}} presiding over the months of Madhu and माधव. {{F}}7:  Ib. XII. ११. ३३; Br. II. २३. 4.{{/F}} His two daughters were celebrated as पञ्चचूडस्; {{F}}8:  Ib. III. 7. 9; IV. २०. ५० and १०१.{{/F}} residing in the Sun's chariot in the months of Caitra and Madhu. {{F}}9:  वा. ५२. 3; ३६. ४७; Vi. II. १०. 3.{{/F}}(II)--a friend of Anu, son of Kapotaroma. भा. IX. २४. २०.(III)--a friend of Andhaka. Br. III. ७१. ११८.--a tribe, on the other side of the Vindhyas. M. ११४. ५३; वा. ४५. १३३.--(तुण्डकेश-वा। प्।); a राक्षस; son of खश. Br. III. 7. १३५; वा. ६९. १६७.--a Vindhya tribe; one of the five classes (गणस्) of the Haihayas; {{F}}1:  Br. II. १६. ६५; III. ६९. ५३; वा. ९४. ५२.{{/F}} on the other side of the Vindhyas. {{F}}2:  वा. ४५. १३४.{{/F}}--a R. in भारतवर्ष from the Sahya hill; sacred to पितृस्. भा. V. १९. १८; Br. II. १६. ३५; वा. ४५. १०४; M. २२. ४५; ११४. २९.--Mt. a hill. Br. II. १६. २२.--the son of कावष, and Purohita of Janamejaya. भा. IX. २२. ३७.--a तीर्थम् on the नर्मदा. M. १९१. २९.--a white horse came out of the churning of the ocean; claimed by the Sun god. M. २५०. 3; २५१. 3. [page२-030+ ३०]--a horse of the Moon's chariot. वा. ५२. ५३.--a people of the नर्मदा region. वा. ४५. १२९.(I)--a name of ब्रह्मा (s.v.). भा. XI. १५. १६.(II)--(Turiya Indrayuk?-ब्र्। प्।); a Deva (a- jita). Br. II. १३. ९४; वा. ३१. 8.--frank incense of white colour for धूप of the पितृस्. Br. III. ११. ६९.--(तुष्करस्-ब्र्। प्।; तुरुष्कार-वा। प्।)-- Fourteen kings among them, see Maunas. भा. XII. 1. ३०; Vi. IV. २४. ५३.(I)--a son of ययाति and देवयानी; refused to part with his youth to his father; he was therefore cursed to have no issue and to live a king among the wicked and low tribes and Mlecchas; became overlord of the Mlecchas in the western part of the kingdom. His son was Vahni. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. १८. ३३ and ४१; १९. २२; २३. १६; M. २४. ५३; वा. ९३. १६.{{/F}} His line became merged with the Paurava line, during the time of Marutta. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ६८. १६, ४०, ५०; ७३. १२६; ७४. 1 and 4; M. ३३. 9-११; वा. ९९. 1-4.{{/F}} Equal to विष्णु; father of Garbha; Yavanas take their origin from him, {{F}}3:  M. ३२. 9; ३४. ३०; ४८. 1.{{/F}} got the south-east of the kingdom, when his father retired to the forest. {{F}}4:  वा. ९३. ३९-44, ८९.{{/F}} [page२-031+ २९](II)--a son of देवयानी and Yadu? Br. I. 1. १३२; वा. 1. १४१.(I)--a dynasty of १४ rulers, ruled for १०५ years [५०० years (वा। प्।)] after the Yavanas; reigned for ७००० years? Br. III. ७४. १७२-6; M. २७३. १९, २१; वा. ४५. ११८; ४७. ४४; ५८. ८३; ९८. १०८; ९९. ३६०. ३६२.(II) (च्)--a northern kingdom; {{F}}1:  Br. II. १६. ४७; १८. ४६; ३१. ८३.{{/F}} १४ kings of it ruled for १०५ years after the Yavanas. {{F}}2:  M. १२१. ४५; १४४. ५७.{{/F}}(I)--the wife of वेदशिरस् and mother of Vibhu. भा. VIII. 1. २१.(II)--the wife of Kratu and mother of the तुषित gods in the स्वारोचिष epoch; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३६. 8; वा. ६२. 8; ६७. ३५.{{/F}} gave birth to विष्णु by name Ajita in that epoch. {{F}}2:  Br. III. 3. ११-15.{{/F}}(III)--the mother of यजिष in the 