--a वाजिन्. वा. ६१. २५.(I)--a pupil of बृहस्पति, a friend of कृष्ण, and a minister of वृष्णिस्. Requested by कृष्ण, he took a mes- sage to Nanda and Gopis of Vraja, where he was duly wel- comed by Nanda. The latter said that he believed with Garga, कृष्ण and राम to be gods when यशोदा narrated कृष्ण's exploits as a child. The conversation lasted all night. After his morning prayers Gopis surrounded him and asked whether कृष्ण was well and remembered them. Uddhava was struck with their devotion and told them of कृष्ण's promised visit in the near future. After spending some months when Gopis entertained him on कृष्णलीला, Uddhava left for मथुरा. {{F}}1:  भा. X. ४६ (whole); ४७ (whole).{{/F}} Went with कृष्ण to Sairan- dhri's house, and to अक्रूर's and returned home. {{F}}2:  Ib. X. ४८. 4, १२ and ३६.{{/F}} Heard the secrets of कृष्ण's self from him and was a हरिदास। {{F}}3:  Ib. IX. २४. ६७; X. ४७. ५६.{{/F}} Went with कृष्ण to द्वारका, and respected him by holding चामर। कृष्ण playing dice with. {{F}}4:  Ib. I. 8. 7; १०. १८; १३. १६ [1]; १४. ३२; X. ६९. २०.{{/F}} Consulted by him as to the method to be adopted in vanquishing जरासन्ध; sug- gested the performance of राजसूय by युधिष्ठिर and the [page१-227+ ४७] defeat of जरासन्ध resulting in the release of imprisoned kings; {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ६९. २७; ७०. १५, ४५-7; ७१. 1-११; ७२. १५.{{/F}} was sent in advance by राम to the Kurus to inform them of his visit. {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ६८. १६.{{/F}} Went to see the पाण्डवस् at उपप्ला- vyam. {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ७८. [९५ (V) 3].{{/F}} Honoured Nanda. {{F}}8:  Ib. X. ८४. ६८.{{/F}} A member of the यादव सभा। Was stationed to defend the E. gate of मथुरा when it was beseiged by जरासन्ध. Consulted by कृष्ण on the right detachment of the army. {{F}}9:  Ib. X. [५२ (V) १५]; ५०. २० [2]; [५० (V) 8 & १२];{{/F}} Met Vidura on the यमुना and was asked about the welfare of his kinsmen. Touched deeply by Vidura's query, Uddhava described how the Lord spent eleven years with बलराम, Gopas and Gopis, doing miracles and how he persuaded Nanda to perform गोसव। He narrated the heroic deeds of कृष्ण and the destruction of the wicked. Concluded by saying that he would reside at Badari after the यादवस् as it was the Lord's wish adding that Maitreya had been asked to be the गुरु of Vidura. {{F}}१०:  Ib. III. ch. 1-4 (whole); XII. १२. 8; Vi. V. ३७. ३१-37.{{/F}} Narrated to Maitreya the story of शिव destroying दक्ष's sacrifice. {{F}}११:  भा. IV. 7. ६०.{{/F}} Joined Yadus in defeating पौण्ड्रक. {{F}}१२:  Ib. X. ६६. [2].{{/F}} Saw Yadus leaving for प्रभास, and understanding कृष्ण's mind, requested him to take him also to His eternal abode. कृष्ण warned him of the advent of Kali and asked him to go about always meditating on Hari. In the course of the dialogue कृष्ण related the conversation between a Yadu and a ब्राह्- मण ascetic, laying emphasis on how the ब्राह्मण learnt lessons from earth, hill, air, sea, archer, pigeon and others and regulated life by cultivating detachment. Listened to the Lord's discourses on various spiritual topics. After being thus well instructed he made Badari his home to spend the evening of his life. {{F}}१३:  Ib. XI. 6. ४०-49; XI. 7. 1-२९; ३०. 1.{{/F}} As a lad of five he worshipped Hari without caring even for breakfast. {{F}}१४:  Ib. III. 2. 2.{{/F}} He knew the योग power of Hari. {{F}}१५:  Ib. II. 7. ४५; Br. III. ३४. ४०.{{/F}} Of superior भक्ति। [page१-228+ २५](II)--a son of देवभाग. M. ४६. २३.--a hell. M. १४१. ७०.--sages. M. २००. १२. [page१-226+ ३६]--a sacrificial priest; created by विष्णु, {{F}}1:  भा. IX. १६. २१; Br. III. ७२. २९.{{/F}} issued from the mouth of Hamsa नारायण; a सामग. {{F}}2:  M. १६७. 7; २४६. १२; वा. ६०. १७.{{/F}}--a कौशिक and sage. Br. II. ३२. ११७.(I)--the son of भूमन् and ऋषिकुल्या: Begot प्रस्ताव on देवकुल्या. भा. V. १५. 6; Br. II. १४. ६७; वा. ३३. ५६.(II)--the son of Bhava. Vi. II. 1. ३७.(III)--a son of Devaki, killed by कंस. Taken back by कृष्ण to द्वारका; after being seen by his parents went to heaven. भा. X. ८५. ५१-56.--R. a महानदि. वा. १०८. ८०.--next to दक्षिणमानस in गया. वा. १११. 6.--pupils of पौष्पिञ्जि. Vi. III. 6. 4.--an eastern tribe which Kalki was to conquer. Br. III. ७३. १०७; वा. ५८. ८१; ९८. १०६.--sacred to ललितापीठ। Br. IV. ४४. ९८.--one of the ten सुपार devas. वा. १००. ९४. [page१-225+ २६]--a त्रयार्षेय. M. १९८. २०.--belong to कौशिकगोत्र. Br. III. ६६. ७०; वा. ९१. ९८.--between शिशिर and पतङ्ग hills- the आश्रम of Kardama प्रजापति. वा. ३८. 2-7.--belonging to कौशिक gotra. वा. ९१. ९८.(I)--a pravara (अङ्गिरस्). M. १९६. १४.(II)--a surname of Soma. Vi. IV. 6. ३३.--a surname of Soma. Br. III. ५१. ३६. [page१-213+ २८]--Four kinds of marriage mentioned: कालक्रीता, क्रयक्रीता, पितृदत्ता, स्वयम्युता। The first is वेश्या, the second is दासिका, the third is पत्नी, and the fourth गान्- धर्व। Br. IV. १५. 4.--marriage dowry sent by Duryodhana as his daughter's marriage with साम्ब was approved. Vi. V. ३५. ३८.--the chief of the third वातस्कन्ध, situated between the sun and the moon. Br. III. 5. ८४; वा. ६७. ११६.--on the left foot of the शिला; founded by Agastya; ब्रह्मा and विष्णु performed severe austerities at the place; offering of पिण्ड at, leads पितृस् to Brahmapura. वा. १०८. ३९, ४३, ४४.(I)--a Rudra; son of भूत and सरूपा; {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 6. १७; Br. IV. ३४. ४१; Vi. I. 8. 6.{{/F}} an अमिताभ deva. {{F}}2:  Br. II. ३६. ५३.{{/F}}(II)--a Marut of the third गण। Br. III. 5. ९४; वा. ६७. १२६.(III)--a son of यातुधान; father of वज्रहा. Br. III. 7. ८९ and ९२.(IV)--a manifestation of शिव, and the presiding deity of यजमान (अधिवास): {{F}}1:  M. २६५. ४१; वा. २७. १५.{{/F}} wife दीक्षा and son San- तान; {{F}}2:  वा. २७. ५५; Br. II. १०. ८३.{{/F}} the seventh name of महादेव. {{F}}3:  Br. II. १०. १६.{{/F}} [page१-209+ २१](V)--an अवतार् of the lord in the गङ्गाद्वार in the eleventh द्वापर with four sons. वा. २३. १५२.(VI)--an Asura. Vi. V. 1. २४.(I)--a शक्ति। Br. IV. ४४. ७३.(II)--a पिशाच kanya1. वा. ६९. १२७.(I)--the son of नीप, and father of क्षेम. भा. IX. २१. २९.(II)--the son of कृत (कार्ता the सामग- वा। प्।) of Paurava dynasty. Father of क्षेम; slew father of पृथुक, the पाञ्चाल Ni1la: Conqueror of नीपस्: was engaged in severe austerities for १८,000 years. Was served by Janamejaya, son of भल्लाट. They were both attacked by नीपस् who were unmoved by उग्रायुध's appeals for peace and protection; then उग्रा- yudha asked Lord of Death to destroy them. Soon he took pity and asked Yama to save them; and this led to a scuffle between Yama and the king who got salvation. M. ४९. ५९-78; वा. ९९. १८२, १९१; Vi. IV. १९. ५३-55. [page१-212+ २५]--a daughter of Meru, wife of Harivarsa. भा. V. 2. २३.--one of भण्ड's councillors. Br. IV. १२. १२.--a deva (Ajita). वा. ३१. 7; Br. II. १३. ९३.--a councillor of भण्ड. Br. IV. १२. १२.--a name of Rudra. भा. III. १२. १२.(I)--A son of आहुक of the Kukura family, father of Kamsa and other eight sons. Father of five daughters who were all married to the younger brothers of Vasudeva. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २४. २१, २४-5; X. 1. ३०; Br. III. ७१. १२९-134, २१२-3, २३०; M. ४४. ७१-74; वा. ९६. २०६; Vi. IV. १४. १६-21.{{/F}} King of सात्वतस्, वृष्णिस्, Bhojas, and दाशार्हस्. {{F}}2:  भा. III. 1. २९.{{/F}} Hated by his son Kamsa who desired even to kill him and who eventually threw him into prison. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ४४. ३३; 1. ६९; ३६. ३४; Vi. V. १५. १८; १८. 6.{{/F}} Enthroned by कृष्ण, after performing Kamsa's funeral rites; {{F}}4: Ib. X. ४५. १२; Vi. V. २१. 9-१२.{{/F}} got helpful service from कृष्ण and welcomed him to द्वारका. {{F}}5:  भा. III. 2. २२; I. ११. १६; Vi. V. २४. 7.{{/F}} In कृष्ण's opinion Ugrasena was the proper person to wear the jewel Syamantaka; did not press it lest there should be a family feud. {{F}}6:  Vi. IV. १३. २७-28, १०७.{{/F}} When जरासन्ध beseiged मथुरा, कृष्ण stationed Ugrasena to defend the northern gate; was pre- sented with spoils of war including jewels and ornaments. His part in defence against जरासन्ध's third attack on मथुरा. A member of the यादव सभा; was consulted by कृष्ण as to failure of rains in द्वारका. {{F}}7:  भा. X. ५०. २०[3] and ४१; [५० (V) ३२-33]; [५१ (V) २५]; [५२ (V) १५]; ५७. ३०[1].{{/F}} वायु fetched from Indra the hall सुधर्मा for Ugrasena's use; {{F}}8:  Vi. V. २१. १३-17, ३२.{{/F}} attacked पौण्ड्रक and laughed at his message. Heard of साम्ब's imprisonment and urged war on the Kurus, order being communicated through बलराम. According to the Kurus, a king only by sufferance. {{F}}9:  भा. X. ६६ [3]; ६८. १३, २१ and ३४; Vi. V. ३५. १०. १४, २३.{{/F}} Ordered the मुसल born to साम्ब to be powdered and thrown into the sea. {{F}}१०:  Vi. V. ३७. ११-12.{{/F}} Sent to द्वारका for defence after the राजसूय। {{F}}११:  भा. X. ७६. 7[5].{{/F}} Welcomed बलराम on his return after a pilgrimage tour. {{F}}१२:  Ib. X. ७९. २९.{{/F}} Went to स्यमन्तपञ्चक for solar eclipse. {{F}}१३:  Ib. X. ८२. २३.{{/F}} Honoured Nanda. {{F}}१४:  Ib. X. ८४. ५९ and ६८.{{/F}} Heard of वृष्णिस् killing one another and of the decease of राम and कृष्ण and bemoaned their loss. {{F}}१५:  Ib. XI. ३१. १५; Vi. V. ३७. ५७.{{/F}} Entered fire. {{F}}१६:  Vi. V. ३८. 4.{{/F}}(II)--a son of परीक्षित्. भा. IX. २२. ३५. [page१-211+ ३१](III)--a Gandharva, presiding over the month of नभस्य; आवणि and पुरट्टाशि (वा। प्।) {{F}}1:  भा. XII. ११. ३८; Br. II. २३. १०; वा. ५२. १०.{{/F}} A Mauneya Gandharva; {{F}}2:  Br. III. 7. 1; वा. ६९. 1.{{/F}} in the sun's chariot in the भाद्र- पद month. {{F}}3:  Vi. II. १०. १०.{{/F}}--a wife of अक्रूर, and mother of देववान् and Upadeva. M. ४५. ३१.--a daughter of Ugrasena and wife of अक्रूर (s.v.). वा. ९६. ११२.--surname of सूत. His discourse on crea- tion to sages of नैमिष. भा. III. २०. 7. [page१-210+ ५१]--a son of Gautama; an अवतार् of the १४थ् द्वापर। वा. २३. १६४.--a class of sages. M. २००. 9. [page१-252+ २४]--a portion of साम वेद। Br. II. ३५. ७२. [page१-259+ २६]--a hill in भारतवर्ष. Br. II. १६. २२; वा. ४५. ९२.--the kingdom of. M. १२१. ५६.--(Mt.) a mountain in which are the temple of योगेश्वरि and the अश्रम of वसिष्ठ. वा. ७७. ५२.--sacred to ललितापीठ। Br. IV. ४४. ९७.--the fifth face of the fourteen faced god, चरिष्- णव Manu of the पीत colour. वा. २६. ३७.--the fourth face of ब्रह्मा whence came तामस Manu of copper colour. वा. २६. ३६.वा. २०. 8-9.--the son of Nemicakra and father of Citraratha. भा. IX. २२. ४०.--born from the eastern face of ब्रह्मा. भा. III. १२. ४०.--an यज्ञ from the south face of ब्रह्मा. (उक्तम्-ब्र्। प्।)। वा. 9. ५०; Br. II. 8. ५१; Vi. I. 5. ५४.--womb of the अण्ड; became cloud. M. 2. ३३.--one of the seven sons of वसिष्ठ and ऊर्जा. भा. IV. 1. ४१.--a राक्षस having his city in the third talam. (Vitalam-वा। प्।) Br. II. २०. २९; वा. ५०. २८.--a mindborn mother. M. १७९. २४.--a daughter of खशा and a राक्षसी. Br. III. 7. १३८.--thrice for पितृस् and once for gods. वा. ७५. १६.(II)--a friend of जरासन्ध, who was station- ed at the eastern gate of मथुरा when it was beseiged. भा. X. ५०. ११[2].(III)--a son of बलराम (Baladeva) and रेवती; fought with his kinsmen at प्रभास, deluded by कृष्ण. भा. XI. ३०. १७; Br. III. ७१. १६६; Vi. IV. १५. २०; V. २५. १९. [page१-247+ ३२](I)--a son of चाक्षुस Manu and नड्वला. His queen was पुष्करिणी. Father of six sons. भा. IV. १३. १६-17.(I)--the son of Bala, and a righteous person; Father of वज्रनाभ. Br. III. ६३. २०५.(II)--a son of हिरण्याक्ष. M. 6. १४.(III)--a son of सहिष्णु of the २६थ् द्वपर। वा. २३. २१३.(IV)--a son of सोमशर्म; an अवतार् of the Lord. वा. २३. २१६.(V)--a विद्याधर chief in the वेणुमन्त hill. वा. ३९. ३८.--a son of धूमिनी, sister of भण्ड; served as a commander भण्ड, and killed by a देवी of ललिता. Br. IV. २१. ८४; २८. 6, ३८ and १००.--son of भासि, owls as children of शुकी; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 7. ४५५; M. 6. ३१; २३७. १२; २४०. १८.{{/F}} of ताम्रा line. {{F}}2:  Vi. I. २१. १६.{{/F}} [page१-245+ २७](I)--the mortar; pregnant Diti not to sit on; {{F}}1:  M. 7. ३८.{{/F}} child कृष्ण tied to by यशोदा. {{F}}2:  Vi. V. 6. १४ and १६.{{/F}}(II)--a लेख on this wooden mortar and the honouring of उदपात्र are details of the श्राद्ध connected with the आश्वलायनिन्स्. वा. ७५. २८.--a pupil of कृत. Br. II. ३५. ५२.a group of पिशाचस् (also उलू- खलिकस्)--Hidden eyes and long tongues; wearing उलूखल for ornaments. Br. III. 7. ३७८ and ३९३; वा. ६१. ४६; ६९. २७४.--see उलूखलस्। Br. III. 7. ३८२.--a mindborn mother. M. १७९. १५.--Life sucked out by infant कृष्ण. भा. II. 7. २७.--त्रयार्षेयस्. M. १९८. 5. [page१-246+ २५]--the queen of Arjuna and mother of इरावान्. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २२. ३२.{{/F}} A नागकन्या. {{F}}2:  Vi. IV. २०. ४९.{{/F}}--a northern kingdom. Br. II. १६. ४८.(I)--worshipped for a happy family. {{F}}1:  भा. II. 3. 7.{{/F}} Her splen- dour. {{F}}2:  Ib. VIII. 7. ३३; VI. १७. ३६.{{/F}} Also known as अम्बिका; also रुद्राणी. {{F}}3:  Ib. VIII. १८. १७; III. १२. १३.{{/F}} In the forest of सुकुमार. {{F}}4:  Ib. IX. 1. २५; XII. १०. 4.{{/F}} Consort of शिव, also गौरी; originally दाक्षायनी, daughter of मेना and हिमवान्. Original name अपर्णा. Her garden: a शक्ति: {{F}}5:  Br. II. २५. १७; २६. ४४; III 9. 1; १०. १३ and २६; ४१. १७ and ५५; ६०. २४ and २७; IV. ४४ 84; M. १३. १८-9; २३. 5; वा. ७१. 2-5.{{/F}} The world of: अधिदेवता for the planet Soma. {{F}}6:  M. ८४. 9; ९३. १३; १३२. १८.{{/F}} Festivities at her birth. {{F}}7:  M. १५४. ९३-108.{{/F}} Going with her father to शिव's house, they met Rati weeping on the way. She said that शिव had burnt down her husband. On this उमा's father did not like the idea of giving his daughter to such an ill-tempered person. उमा requested permis- sion to do penance and was allowed. Indra at this time thought of the seven sages to bring about शिव's marriage with उमा. The sages were satisfied of her steadfast love to शिव and had his consent for the marriage; celestial women dressed उमा, as also the god शिव; amidst divine music, the couple went to the city of महागिरिनगर and ब्रह्मा officiated as priest: After the marriage they left for Mandaragiri. {{F}}8:  M. १५४. २७६-496.{{/F}} Once उमा made a doll with elephant face and dropped it in the Ganges. It became a huge figure and was claimed as son by उमा and the Ganges respectively. {{F}}9:  M. १५४. ५०२-505.{{/F}} Then उमा [page१-239+ ४१] grew a tender अशोक plant when बृहस्पति and others told her that she would have a real son and that trees and dolls were no satisfaction; {{F}}१०:  M. १५४. ५०६-510.{{/F}} once she heard a yell of noise and was told of the play engaged in by गणस्, and then her eyes attracted वीरक. She expressed to शिव for a son like वीरक. शिव asked her to have him as her child. He was sent for and nursed by उमा. {{F}}११:  M. १५४. ५२२-555.{{/F}} Touched by Goddess of Night, she became black in colour. शिव found fault with her and after reproaching him with his past deeds, she left him for penance. वीरक appealed to her when she said she would return as गौरी. She asked वीरक to see that no lady entered her harem. Meanwhile आडि, son of अन्धकासुर entered शिव's abode in the guise of उमा but was slain by शिव. Hearing from वायु that a lady entered her home, she cursed वीरक to be born on the earth; out of her rage came out a lion which ब्रह्मा gave to the Goddess of Night, who was asked to leave उमा for the Vindhya hills. Now उमा became गौरी and entered शिव's abode when वीरक stopped her, as he did not at first recognise her. Convinced of his mother's identity, he requested her to recall her curse and was assured of a place in देवगण. {{F}}१२:  M. १५४. ५८८; chap. १५५- ५८.{{/F}} While उमा was sporting with शिव, Agni entered the harem in the form of a parrot. Noticing this उमा left the bed and शिव made Agni drink his वीर्य। Out of the scat- tered वीर्य, there sprang up a beautiful pond where the six Pleiades bathed and took water in a lotus leaf. Blessed by them the देवी got the गर्भ and out of her left side came out सुब्रह्मण्य. {{F}}१३:  M. १५८. २४-48; वा. ७२ (whole).{{/F}} Going through the उद्यानम् again शिव spoke to her of the greatness of Benares. {{F}}१४:  M. १८०. २०-79; १८१. 6-8; १९१. ११३; १९३. ४६.{{/F}} सती in previous birth. {{F}}१५:  वा. ३०. ७१; ५४. २०; ५५. ४२; Br. II. १३. ७७.{{/F}}(II)--the goddess enshrined at विङायक. M. १३. ४१. [page१-240+ ३३]--to be worshipped in आदित्यशयनम्: Image of; worship of; either four or two hands; three eyes; clad in e