IX. १४. १६-42; १५. 1; XI. २६. 4-5 and २५; Br. III. ६५. ४६; ६६. 4-5; वा. 2. १६; ९१. 4; Vi. IV. 6. ३५-78.{{/F}} Returned to Heaven. {{F}}5:  भा. XI. 4. १५; Br. IV. ३३. १८.{{/F}} The Goddess enshrined at Badari. {{F}}6:  M. १३. ४९.{{/F}} When she danced before Indra, she forgot her अभिनय and was cursed by Bharata to become an invisible creeper for ५५ years on the earth. During that time पुरूरवस् was in the guise of पैशाच. After the lapse of the period she bore him 8 sons. {{F}}7:  Ib. २४. १२-33.{{/F}} In the सभा of हिरण्यकशिपु. {{F}}8:  Ib. १६१. २५.{{/F}} Mother of six sons by Aila. {{F}}9:  वा. ९०. ४५.{{/F}} Also ऊर्वशी (s.v.).(II)--The Apsaras presiding over the month of सह। {{F}}1:  भा. XII. ११. ४१; Br. II. २३. १८.{{/F}} With the sun in the हेमन्त; {{F}}2:  Br. I. 2. १६; वा. ५२. १८; M. १२६. १९.{{/F}} in the sun's chariot in the मार्गशीर्ष month; {{F}}3:  Vi. II. १०. १३.{{/F}} a ब्रह्मवादिनी। {{F}}4:  Br. II. ३३. १८.{{/F}}(III)--An आभीर कन्या who observed the भीमद्वादशी, and became उर्वशी. M. ६९. ५९. [page१-244+ २६]--A तीर्थ sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ६६.--a क्षेत्रम् in प्रयाग. M. १०६. ३४.--see भूमी or पृथ्वी; extent ५०० million योजनस्; foremost of all elements and mother of all beings; depth below the surface is ७०,000 योजनस् consisting of the seven regions of पाताल. Vi. II. 4. ९६-7; 5. 1-2.--भारभूति; a वरमूर्ति. Br. IV. ४४. ४९.--(also उषा, s.v.) Daughter of बाण. Her compa- nion was चित्रलेखा. Dreamt one night that she was sleeping with Aniruddha. Informed her friend of the dream but could not give Aniruddha's name. चित्रलेखा drew pencil sketches of all gods and men and showed them to her one by one. Seeing Aniruddha's she identified him. At this, चित्रलेखा flew through air and brought Aniruddha to her room unnoticed by others. ऊषा was enjoying his company. The guards who got scent of this reported to बाण who imprisoned Aniruddha. In course of time she married Ani- ruddha and went to his home with the approval of बाण. भा. X. ६१. २३ [9]; ६२. 1-३५; ६३. ५०.--the daughter of बाण and granddaughter of Bali got enamoured of Aniruddha whom she saw in a picture and requested her maid to arrange for her marriage with him; she saw उमा dallying with शिव and asked of her marriage which उमा said will be to him whom she would see in a dream. So she saw Aniruddha in a dream on a वैशाख शुक्ल द्वादशी; by the aid of चित्रलेखा, he was taken to her chamber in secret. Also ऊषा (s.v.). Vi. V. ३२. 7-३०.--the son of तितिक्षु, a famous king of the east. Br. III. ७४. २५; वा. ९९. २५.(रुशना-Burnouf)--one of the queens of Rudra. भा. III. १२. १३.(I)--a son of Dharma. Performed a hundred अश्वमेध sacrifices. Father of Rucaka. भा. IX. २३. ३४.(II)--the son of Bhava and धात्री (ओषा-वा। प्।). Br. II. १०. ७७; वा. २७. ५०.(III)--a son of सुयज्ञ, and a performer of १०० अश्वमेधस्; father of Marutta. Br. III. ७०. २३-4; M. ४४. २३.(IV)--The preceptor of the Daityas and Asuras; {{F}}1:  वा. 3. 5; ६२. ८०; वा. ६५. ७४.{{/F}} on शिशुमारचक्र; {{F}}2:  भा. V. २३. 7.{{/F}} disciple of the father of बृहस्पति and leader of a side of Soma (पार्ष्णि); {{F}}3:  वा. ९०. ३०.{{/F}} father of देवयानी; by his curse ययाती could not enjoy his youth to the full and hence requested his sons to give their youth in exchange for his old age. {{F}}4:  ६५. ८४; ९३. ३०; १०३. ५९.{{/F}} Praised अमरकण्टकक्षेत्र; {{F}}5:  वा. ७७. १४.{{/F}} a sage; {{F}}6:  वा. ३०. ८५; ५९. ९०.{{/F}} see शुक्र।(V)--a son of गोकर्ण, the अवतार् of the १६थ् द्वापर। वा. २३. १७३.(VI)--the son of पृथुश्रवस्, performed १०० अश्वमेधस्। वा. ९५. २३. [page१-248+ ३१](VII)--the planet Venus above Budha; above is अङ्गारक. Vi. II. 7. 7-8.(VIII)--the वेदव्यास of the third द्वापर; {{F}}1:  Vi. III. 3. १२.{{/F}} an author on नीतिशास्त्र; {{F}}2:  Vi. I. १९. २६.{{/F}} on the efficacy of तपस्; {{F}}3:  Vi. I. १२. ९८-103.{{/F}} jealous of बृहस्पति joined Candra in the तारकामय war and acted as पार्ष्णिग्राह. {{F}}4:  Vi. IV. 6. १२.{{/F}}(IX)--the son of पृथुतम; he performed १०० अश्वमेधस्; father of शितपु. Vi. IV. १२. 8-9.(I)--the wife of विभावसु; mother of व्युष्ट and two other sons. भा. VI. 6. १६.(II)--Night: a mind-born mother. M. १७९. २०; वा. ५०. १६१.(III)--created by ब्रह्मा from his feet; {{F}}1:  Vi. I. 5. ४९.{{/F}} camels belonging to the ताम्र line. {{F}}2:  Vi. I. २१. १७.{{/F}} [page१-250+ २८]--a name of Kavi located at नैष्- थीय. (उशीराग्नि-वा। प्।). Br. II. १२. ३०; वा. २९. २९.--Had शिबि, grandson of ययाति for son. A son of महामन; had five queens of राजऋषि families, each of whom bore a son; (four sons, शिबि and others, ब्र्। प्।). भा. I. १२. २०; IX. २३. 2-3; Br. III. ७४. १७; M. ४२. १९; ४८. १५-18; वा. ९९. १८-19; Vi. IV. १८. 8-9.(I)--a sage who went to स्यमन्तपञ्चक for solar eclipse. भा. X. ८२. १३.(II)--a tribe of which सुयज्ञ was a king. भा. VII. 2. २८; X. ८२. १३.--a mt. near Mandara hill; people here felt the influence of हिरण्यकशिपु. M. १६३. ८७.(I)--a sage by तपस्; elder brother of बृहस्पति who had sexual intercourse by force with उशिज's wife when pregnant. Hence बृहस्पति cursed that son to be perpe- tually ignorant (दीर्घतमस्); {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३२. ९९; III. ७४. ३६-46; M. ४९. १७.{{/F}} ममता was his wife. {{F}}2:  M. ४८. ३२; १९६. ११.{{/F}} A pravara of अङ्गिरस्. [page१-249+ २७](II)--a son of अङ्गिरस; hence a branch of अङ्गिरस. वा. ६५. १००, १०६.(I)--the son of कृति, and father of Cedi. भा. IX. २४. 2.(II)--the twelfth कल्प। वा. २१. ३२.--and thirty-two other devas from the Sumanasa group. वा. १००. ९१-2.--a son of Atharvan अङ्गिरस्. Br. III. 1. १०५.--a पराशर clan. Br. III. 8. ९५.(I)--a पाराशार clan. वा. ७०. ८७.(II)--a class of पितृस्. Br. II. २७. १११; २८. ९३. [page१-258+ 8]--a class of पितृस् to be given oblation after bath; {{F}}1:  M. १०२. २०; १४१. २०; वा. ३०. १००.{{/F}} propitiated every new moon; to them कृष्णपक्ष a day and शुक्लपक्ष a night. {{F}}2:  वा. ५६. २१. ८७.{{/F}}--a class of पितृस्. Br. II. २८. २३.(I)--a son of Dyutimat, with his kingdom by name उष्ण. Br. II. १४. २२ and २५; वा. ३३. २१-22; Vi. II. 4. ४८.(II)--a region of क्रौञ्चद्वीप. Br. II. १९. ७२; M. १२२. ८५; वा. ४९. ६६.(III)--the son