t of the recovered earth came mountains and seven worlds; creation of human beings; {{F}}3:  Ib. I. 5. १९.{{/F}} where ब्रह्मा is said to assume this form. {{F}}4:  Ib. II. 7. 7-9.{{/F}}(II)--a Mt. afraid of हिरण्यकशिपु's arms. M. १६३. ८१.(III)--the २६थ् kalpa. M. २९०. 9.(IV)--the present kalpa; fourteen Manus be- ginning with स्वायम्भुव; name and features explained. वा. २१. १२, २३, २६ f. Vi. I. 3. २८; II. 1. ४३.--in this aeon, Hari took the incarnation of a boar; see वराह. भा. III. ११. ३६.--a महापुराण, comprising २४,000 श्लोकस्; {{F}}1:  भा. XII. 7. २४; १३. 7; Vi. III. 6. २३.{{/F}} narrated by विष्णु to क्षोणि containing the माहात्म्य of [page३-200+ २६] महावाराह; he who gives it with a golden eagle on the Full Moon day of Madhu reaches oneness with विष्णु. {{F}}2:  M. ५३. ३९-41.{{/F}}--a शक्ति. Br. IV. २०. ३७.--a Janapada of the भद्रा continent. वा. ४३. २२.--a Pravara (Angiras). M. १९६. १२, १३.(I)--a surname of ललिता. Br. IV. १७. १९.(II)--a शक्ति; a mind-born mother. {{F}}1:  Br. IV. १९. 7; २०. ३७; M. १७९. ११.{{/F}} Icon of, with buffalo mount. {{F}}2:  Ib. २६१. ३०.{{/F}}(III)--a R. of the वराहद्वीपम्. वा. ४८. ३९.--काशी: sacred to Hari; {{F}}1:  भा. VII. १४. ३१; X. ६६. ४०.{{/F}} fit for श्राद्ध offer- ing, and sacred to ललिता; {{F}}2:  Br. III. १३. १०१; IV. ४४. ९३.{{/F}} the capital of दिवोदास devastated by the राक्षस Ks2emaka, resulting in the change of capital to गोमती. The abode of शिव and उमा after their marriage, and hence the name Avimuktam क्षेत्रम्; {{F}}3:  Ib. III. ६७. २६-62.{{/F}} the goddess enshrined here is विशालाक्षी: a place of pilgrimage; {{F}}4:  M. १३. २६; २२. 7.{{/F}} capital of रुद्रशृएण्य of the Yadu race: city where मार्कण्डेय lived. {{F}}5:  Ib. ४३. ११; १०३. १३.{{/F}} Lord became क्षेत्रपाल: the यक्ष Harikes4a per- formed penance here; {{F}}6:  Ib. १८०. 1-5, १५ and ५४.{{/F}} the place of Yogis and Siddhas: death here is release from rebirth; {{F}}7:  Ib. १८०. ७२-79.{{/F}} a siddha क्षेत्र where शिव and His consort live all the three yugas and make Avi- muktam गृहम् in Kaliyuga; {{F}}8:  वा. ७७. ९३; ९२. २७, ५८-59; ९९. ३१५.{{/F}} अवतार् of लान्गलि at, in the २२न्द् dva1para; {{F}}9:  Ib. २३. १९८.{{/F}} cursed by Nikumbha to become deserted for 1,००० years; {{F}}१०:  ९२. २३-28.{{/F}} burnt down by कृष्ण. {{F}}११:  Vi. V. ३४. 3, ३९-41.{{/F}}--शिव addresses पार्वती on, in taking her out and showing the grandeur and majesty of the forest and garden round about काशी; the place of विद्या- [page३-198+ ४१] dharas, Siddhas and चारणस्. Here भगवान् Pin3gala became गणेश्वर and क्षेत्रपाल and distributor of food to the residents in the city. He was originally a यक्ष, son of पूर्णभद्र. He devoted himself to severe austerities and was blessed by शिव to be a गणपति. {{F}}1:  M. ch. १८०.{{/F}} It is अविमुक्त तीर्थ for here शिव is omnipresent and is never absent from there. All sinners who die here become Rudras in time. शिव stands here like a pillar, motionless till the deluge. Every part of the city is holy. {{F}}2:  Ib. ch. १८१.{{/F}} He who remains here for a month gets the benefit of observ- ing the पाशुपत vow. By living permanently one gets true emancipation. By giving up life at the मणिकर्णिका ghat one secures the desired goal. Perpetual life in काशी leads one to union with शिव. {{F}}3:  Ib. ch. १८२.{{/F}} काशी's importance on account of its sacred stream, the Ganges; survives all deluge; शिव addresses पार्- वती on the great glory of the क्षेत्रम् in terms of Parama- yoga, Paramagati and परममोक्ष. It is a place where people of all वर्णस् attain immortality. Gifts of cow and other things in this city are always beneficial. {{F}}4:  Ib. ch. १८३.{{/F}} It is the place where शिव got rid of the curse of ब्रह्मा to roam about with a skull for having cut off the fifth head of the creator. Through the grace of Hari, the skull fell down in काशी and broke into a thousand pieces. {{F}}5:  Ib. ch. १८४.{{/F}} It is the burial ground of all the gods, the ground being the Avimukta temple. It is the seat of ब्रह्मा. But it deludes non- devotees. Here वेदव्यास resided for १२ years observing the vow of silence. At the end of the vow he felt hungry and asked for alms. None was able to feed him. When he was about to curse the city, शिव and पार्वती took the human form and entertained him to his satisfaction. Then व्यास knew of his guests who remarked that a man of choleric temper like himself should not live in that city. But he was permitted to visit it twice a fortnight on अष्टमि and चतुर्दशी days. {{F}}6:  Ib. ch. १८५.{{/F}} [page३-199+ ३०]--the heavenly animal which came down for Haryanga's help. M. ४८. ९८. [page३-197+ ४०]--the city of हस्तिनापुर; सत्यभामा goes there to complain to कृष्ण often about the death of her father by शतधन्वा; {{F}}1:  वा. ९६. ६१.{{/F}} here कृष्ण went to perform the last obsequies to the पाण्डवस् who were reported to have been burnt down. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ७१. ६३; Vi. IV. १३. ७०.{{/F}}--शिव in काञ्ची. Br. IV. 5. 7.--a money-lender, unfit for पन्क्ति feeding and for श्राद्ध. Br. III. १५. ५३; १९. ३०.--a transformation of तेजस् or fire; has four quali- ties, sound, touch, form and taste (रस)। M. 3. २५.--a Mt. in भारत vars2a. भा. V. १९. १६.--a queen of वर्ष R2tu. Br. IV. ३२. २९.--a son of अक्रूर. M. ४५. २९. [page३-201+ ३०] वारिषेण--a Kinnara with human face. वा. ६९. ३५.--a class of deities of the चाक्षुष epoch. M. 9. २४.--a son of Candragupta Maurya and father of अशोकवर्धन. भा. XII. 1. १३.--a seer. वा. ३४. ६३.(I)--शर्मिष्ठा (s.v.). वा. ६८. २३.(II)--a daughter of स्वर्भानु. Vi. I. २१. 7.--leads to the world of शिव; consists of dedication of a bull in the month of कार्तिक. M. १०१. ६५. [page३-205+ ३६]--धूम्र Para1s4aras. M. २०१. ३८.--(धार्ष्टक) the line of धृष्ट. Vi. IV. 2. 4.--produced by ब्रह्मा; according to प्रह्लाद, should be a means to realise Hari; profession of वैश्यस्. Fourfold--कृषि, वाणिज्यम्, गो-रक्ष, and कुसीद (usury). {{F}}1:  भा. III. १२. ४४; VII. 6. २६; ११. १६; X. २४. २१. Br. I. 1. ९२; वा. ४९. ११७; ५७. ८९; ५८. २५; ५९. ३६; ६१. १६० and १६६.{{/F}} Began in the त