वा. ६२. ९०.{{/F}}(IV)--the २७थ् kalpa;^1 (१९थ् kalpa-वा। प्।); the period of वैराज Manu, son of the Creator. M. २९०. १०; वा. २१. ४०-2; Br. IV. 2. ६५.(V)--is ब्रह्मा. वा. १००. ४३.(VI)--father of नद्वला; a progenitor and father-in-law of sixth Manu. Vi. I. १३. 4.(VII)--also a वीरपुरुष from whom was born शतरूपा and two sons Priyavrata and उत्तानपाद as also two daughters आकूती and प्रसूती. वा. १०. १५-7.(I)--the first gods created by ब्रह्मा to occupy the first worlds by name सम्तानकस्; among them seven groups are distinguished, three formless and four with form; then earth, rains, food, worship of moon for rice; the formless attain absolution through yoga power; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 9. ५२-62; वा. ७१. ५२.{{/F}} the three formless groups are पितृस् engaged in yoga; {{F}}2:  Br. III. १०. 4.{{/F}} ऋभु and Sanat- कुमार come under this class; they attained Brahmaloka or siddhi. {{F}}3:  Ib. IV. 2. ३५, ७० ff.{{/F}}(II)--a class of formless पितृस्: Fallen from Yoga, they attain eternal worlds (लोकान् sana1tana1n) and are reborn as ब्रह्मवादिन्स् at the end of a day of ब्रह्मा: they then gain their old memory and by सान्ख्य and yoga they attain final release. Their mind-born daughter मेना is the wife of हिमवान्. M. १३. 3-6.(III)--the Brahmans living in the Virajasa world; this is said to be the first Kalpa of the वैराजास्. वा. ७२. 4; १०१. ६१-4.(I)--got by tapas; {{F}}1:  M. ९३. १३३; १४३. ३३; Br. II. ३०. ४४; IV. 2. ६०.{{/F}} a loka. {{F}}2:  Ib. IV. 2. १४१.{{/F}}(II)--the abode of ब्रह्मा. M. १६१. १७. [page३-336+ ३२](III)--a metre, creation of. वा. 9. ५२.--is ब्रह्मा. Br. IV. 1. ४०.--a सूक्तम् of the साम Samhita1 to be recit- ed in the ritual associated with the digging of a tank. M. ५८. ३६.--(see वैराजास्): performers of austerities; stand ten times until आभूतसम्प्लव, after Pralaya, enter- ing प्रणव aimed at Brahmaloka through Yogadharma and attained the आनन्द of ब्रह्मा; six characteristics of; deprived of three भावस् (body, mind and speech) do not regard द्वन्द्व (sukha duhkha, etc.); reach बुद्धावस्था. वा. १०१. ३७, ७१, ८०, ८१, १४०. [page३-337+ २५]--a त्रयार्षेय. M. १९६. ३९.--a son of ज्योतिष्मत् after whom came the रथाकार kingdom (a part of the कुशद्वीप). Br. II. १४. २७; Vi. II. 4. ३६.--the daughter of दक्ष so-called. Br. I. 1. ११२.--one of the wives of दक्ष, mother of १००० sons and ६० daughters. M. 5. 8; १४६. १५.--a wife of त्वष्ट. वा. ६५. ८५.--created from the west face of ब्रह्मा. Vi. I. 5. ५५.--a साम; {{F}}1:  वा. 9. ५१.{{/F}} from the face of ब्रह्मा, {{F}}2:  Br. II. 8. ५२.{{/F}} helped सुप्रतीक elephant to get सारूप्यम्। {{F}}3:  Ib. III. 7. ३४१.{{/F}}--also Vidarbha; the son of सैव्या and ज्यामघ after the former's severe austerities; married स्नुषा; got two sons and a third लोमपाद. वा. ९५. ३६.--the full moon day of the वैशाख month; good for gift of the ब्राह्म पुराण। M. ५३. १३.--(तृतीय) a युगादि for श्राद्ध. M. १७. 4; ५६. 3.--the १२थ् day of the bright half of वैशाख, the day on which उषा dreamt of her future husband. Vi. V. ३२. १४.--one of the १३ wives of Vasudeva, the son of कौशिक. वा. ९६. १६०, १७२.--a pupil of पराशर Kauthuma. Br. II. ३५. ४६.(I)--founded by king विशाल. भा. IX. 2. ३३; वा. ६१. ४६.(II)--one of Vasudeva's queens and mother of कौशिक. Br. III. ७१. १७४; Vi. IV. १५. २५.(III)--an आर्षेय pravara. M. १९६. 8.(I)--a pupil of व्यास in charge of the यजुस्; was taught Nigada (Yajurveda). His pupils were Ca- रकाध्वर्युस्. याज्ञवल्क्य was one of the pupils; was also a पौराणिक. {{F}}1:  भा. I. 4. २१; XII. 6. ५२ and ६१; XII. 7. 5. वा. ६०. १३; ६१. 5.{{/F}} A श्रुतऋषि, divided the Yajur Veda into ८६ parts and distributed them among his ८६ pupils; {{F}}2:  Br. II. 1. १३; ३३. 5; ३४. १३; ३५. 8-9, २०-22.{{/F}} did not attend the Meru conference and ordered his pupils to take to Brahma विद्या. {{F}}3:  वा. ६१. १४-16.{{/F}}(II)--a sage who was invited for the राजसूय of युधिष्ठीर. भा. X. ७४. 8.(III)--the sage who cursed king Jana- mejaya; questioned by शौनक for light on rituals condu- cive to realisation of one's desires. M. ५०. ५८; ९३. 1; वा