nded as a sign of receiving Hari's grace. Married the seven daughters of Devaka; six other wives of: {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २४., २३-45; Br. III. ६१. २३; ७१. १४६, १६०-1, १७४; M. ४४. ७२; वा. ८६. २८; ९६. १४४, १५९-161, १९८; ९८. ९४; Vi. IV. १४. १९.{{/F}} Father of कृष्ण by देवकी; when marrying her he promised Kamsa, who drove the chariot and who heard a voice [page३-174+ ४८] from air that her eighth son would kill him, to give him all sons born of देवकी to be killed by him. Took her first son to Kamsa who spared him; was thrown in prison with देवकी by Kamsa. Vasudeva's prayer to the new born कृष्ण; took the babe to Nandagopa's house and exchanged him for the daughter, born to यशोद at that time, without anybody knowing it. Released by Kamsa; {{F}}2:  भा. I. 1. १२; 2. 7; 8. ३३; III. 2. २५; X. २६. १७; 1. २३ to the end; ch. 3 (whole); 4. १४ and २४; Br. III. ७१. २१०-35; M. ४६. 1-2; ४७. 2-6; Vi. V. 1. 5; 3. १५-23.{{/F}} met Nanda who went to the capital for paying annual tribute and after enquiring of his welfare advised him to return home as he expected some trouble at the Vraja. Requested Garga to go to Vraja and perform सम्स्कारस् to his sons. {{F}}3:  भा. X. 5. २०-31; 8. 1.{{/F}} Visited by नारद. Vasu- deva enquired of भागवत धर्म; listened to the tradi- tional account of the talk between the nine sons of ऋषभ and Nimi and was pleased along with देवकी; {{F}}4:  Ib. XI. 2. 3; ३१. १५-22.{{/F}} met by कृष्ण at सुधर्मा sabha1 painted by चित्रलेखा; {{F}}5:  Ib. X. [६७ (v)  ४२, ४७]; ६२. २०.{{/F}} joined the Yadus in defeating पौण्ड्रक Ma1ya1. Vasudeva cut off साल्व before कृष्ण in battle. Welcomed कृष्ण after the Kuru- क्षेत्र war; went to स्यमन्तपञ्चक for the solar eclipse; here he met the sages and asked them how to get rid of karma by karma. नारद's praise of. The sages induced him to undertake a sacrifice; requested by Vasudeva to be his ऋत्विक्स् for the यज्ञ they agreed. At the end of the sacrifice, he had his अवभृत with all his eighteen wives to the great satisfaction of राम and कृष्ण, when all castes and even animals were fed; others were honoured with presents. At leave-taking Vasudeva took hold of Nanda's hands and showed that the tie of friendship was the greatest of all ties and wept in joy. Gave Nanda presents; praise of कृष्ण and राम and his joy. {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ६६. [2]; ७७. २५-9; ८०. [१३]; ८२. 5; chh. ८४. and ८५ (whole).{{/F}} Kamsa who heard from नारद that Vasudeva had kept his sons राम and कृष्ण under the safe custody of Nanda wanted to kill him. When he was persuaded not to do so, Kamsa imprisoned Vasudeva until कृष्ण released him; celebrated his उपनयन। {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ३६. १७-24, [२९ and ३१]; ४४. ३३ and ५१; ४५. 2-9, २६-9.{{/F}} Stationed to defend the eastern gate of मथुरा; consulted by कृष्ण on the eve of attack on जरासन्ध. His part in the third campaign of जरा; came with देवकी and कृष्ण [page३-175+ ३३] to रुक्मिणी's residence where Pradyumna and मायावती had already arrived. His concern at कृष्ण not returning for a long time from the cave of जाम्बवती. {{F}}8:  Ib. X. ५०. २० [2]; [५० (v)  8]; [५१ (v) २६]; ५५. ३५; ५६. २४.{{/F}} In previous births Sutapa and कश्यप (see देवकी). Heard of कृष्ण's decease and also of all the वृष्णिस् {{F}}9:  Ib. XI. ३१. १५ and १८.{{/F}} and wept; gave his sons सौमी and कौशिक in adoption to his brother, वृक; {{F}}१०:  Br. III. ७१. १९२, ७३. ९४.{{/F}} nine brothers and four sisters; {{F}}११:  Vi. IV. १४. २७-31.{{/F}} chastised by Kamsa in the यादव assembly; {{F}}१२:  Ib. V. १५. 4-5, १८.{{/F}} praise of कृष्ण by Vasudeva; {{F}}१३:  Ib. V. १५. २०-28.{{/F}} entered fire after कृष्ण's death. {{F}}१४:  Ib. V. ३८. 4.{{/F}}(II)--a कण्व and a minister of the शुन्ग king देवभूति; (म्। and ब्र्। प्।-देवभूमि); killed his master and became king. Father of भूमित्र; ruled for five years; began the line of काण्वायनस्. भा. XII. 1. १९-20; Br. II. ७४. १५६; M. २७२. ३२; Vi. IV. २४. ३९-40.(III)--a son of Cancu. Vi. IV. 3. २५.--a daughter of गादिनी. वा. ९६. १११.(I)--(also वसुन्धरा); ety. of. Br. II. ३७. 1; ३६. २२६; वा. ६३. 1.(II)--the deity to be remembered in install- ing a new image; the presiding deity is शर्व. M. २६५. ३८, ४०. [page३-176+ २३]--a Mt. where there are eight temples to the Vasus. वा. ३८. २३; ३९. ४४; ४२. ३०.--a son of श्रीदेवा and Vasudeva. भा. IX. २४. ५१.--a son of पुष्यमित्र, ruled for seven years. M. २७२. २८.(I)--a son of Vaivasvata Manu. भा. VIII. १३. 3. [page३-177+ २५](II)--a son of श्रुतायु. भा. IX. १५. 2.(III)--a son of Jamadagni. भा. IX. १५. १३.(IV)--a son of कृष्ण and जाम्बवती. भा. X. ६१. १२.(V)--a son of वसिष्ठ, and one of the seven sages of the Vaivasvata epoch. Br. II. ३८. २९; वा. ६४. २७, ३०; ६५. ४६-7.(VI)--with अष्टक, Pratardana and शिबि, all grandsons of ययाति by his daughter, performed a sacrifice and in that hall ययाति fallen from heaven, spoke with them and went back to heaven; {{F}}1:  M. ३५. 5.{{/F}} discourse of, with ययाति on differ- ent things of heaven; {{F}}2:  Ib. ३८. २२; ४१. १८; ४२. 1f.{{/F}} went to heaven with the above. {{F}}3:  Ib. ४२. १४, २६ and २८.{{/F}}--a son of हर्यश्व and दृषद्वती. वा. ८८. ७६.(I)--R. a river of the भद्रा country. वा. ४३. २७.(II)--a daughter of the वालेय Gandharvas; originator of Vasumati Suta गण. वा. ६९. २१.(III)--earth. वा. ९७. १६.--a son of सुज्येष्ठ (वसुज्येष्ठ-म्। प्।) and father of Bhadraka (Udanka-वि। प्।); ruled for ten years. भा. XII. 1. १७; Br. III. ७४. १५२; M. २७२. २८; वा. ९९. ३३९; Vi. IV. २४. ३५.--a son of Havya. वा. ३३. १६.--a वर्ष after his name. वा. ३३. १९. [page३-178+ २०]--from which the whole world springs and ends. वा. ६२. १९३.--a class of people in शाल्मलिद्वीप. भा. V. २०. ११.--a तीर्थ sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ७२.--a place of Rukmavat Agni. वा. २९. ४०.--another name for Brahmajyoti Agni. Br. II. १२. २५.--one of the five deities to be propitiated in installing a new image; the presiding deity is पशुप. M. २६५. ३८, ४०.(I)--the milk-man of the Gandharvas on the earth; in his guise, यक्ष enjoyed क्रतुस्थला. Br. II. ३६. २२१; III. 7. १०६; वा. ६९. १४०.(II)--an Apsaras. Br. III. 7. ११.--an Andhaka. Br. III. ७१. १