 flood it; hence the sages held him down and had his left hand churned by force; there came out a short black figure who stood trem- bling; the sages said निषीद, the forerunner of the निषाद- वम्श; then they churned his right hand and पृथु was born; Vena died; पृथु crowned by all; a good king; his rule and achievements, including the milking of the earth by all beings. {{F}}6:  वा. ६२. १०८-193.{{/F}} [page३-324+ ३०](I)--a तीर्थ sacred to अमृत; {{F}}1:  M. १३. ४९.{{/F}} sacred to the पितृस्. {{F}}2:  Ib. २२. ३४.{{/F}} [page३-315+ २७](II)--a R. from the Vindhyas; visited by बलराम. M. ११४. २७. भा. X. ७९. १२.--a R. in भारतवर्ष, from the Vindhyas. भा. V. १९. १८; Br. II. १६. ३३.--विष्णु at प्रयागा. M. १११. 9.--(च्) a kingdom through which ऋषभ passed. Its king was Arhat. भा. V. 6. 7 and 9.--a Mt. in भारतवर्ष: visited by बलराम. Its sages visited द्वारका. भा. V. १९. १६; X. ७९. १३; ९०. २८[3].--flute; {{F}}1:  वा. ४५. ४०; ५६. ३२; १०४. ४८; Vi. II. १४. ३२.{{/F}} in राम's अभिषेक; {{F}}2:  Ib. IV. 4. ९९.{{/F}} in पातालम्. {{F}}3:  Ib. II. 5. ११.{{/F}}--an ally of जरासन्ध: attacked the eastern gate of मथुरा and the northern gate of Gomanta during their siege by जरासन्ध. भा. X. ५०. ११[2]; ५२. ११[14].--one of the three sons of शतजित्. भा. IX. २३. २१; Br. III. ६९. 4; M. ४३. 8; वा. ९४. 4; Vi. IV. ११. 7.--a son of धृष्टकेतु. Br. III. ६७. ७७; वा. ९२. ७२.--a R. of the शाकद्वीप. M. १२२. ३३. Br. II. १९. ९६; Vi. II. 4. ६५.--(च्) a kingdom of कुशद्वीप after वेणुमत्. Br. II. १४. २८; १९. ५७; वा. ३३. २५; ४९. ५२.(I)--a son of ज्योतिष्मत् after whom वेणु- मण्डलम् took its name. Br. II. १४. २७-8; वा. ३३. २४; Vi. II. 4. ३६.(II)--a Mt. to the east of अरुणोद; {{F}}1:  वा. ३६. १९.{{/F}} the cities of विद्याधरस् in. {{F}}2:  Ib. ३७. 3, २६.{{/F}}--a R. rising from the पारियात्र hills. M. २२. २०. [page३-316+ २७]--a R. originating from the Vindhyas. वा. ४५. १०२.--married Nadhi; father of मरीच-Kas4yapa. वा. ६५. ११२.--a sage by garbha. वा. ५९. ९४.--the life and duties of a dancing girl; ऊर्वशी suffered for ad