nty-eight hells--a slaughter house for hypocritical sacrificers of animals; makers of lances, swords and other implements. भा. V. २६. 7 and २५; Vi. II. 6. 2 and १७.--a यामदेव. वा. ३१. 6.--a son of रेवती and Baladeva. Vi. IV. १५. २०.--a kingdom in general; qualities of a good one; {{F}}1:  M. २१७. 1-5.{{/F}} gift of. {{F}}2:  Ib. २७५. २५.{{/F}}--विषय is ब्रह्मा and अविषय is क्षेत्र. वा. १०२. ३६.--a commander of भण्ड. Br. IV. २१. ८४.--Mahat and others; from them came the अण्ड or universe; all water; from this came the fish (पुरुष) with body. हिरण्यगर्भ with four faces. वा. 4. ७५-8.--a son of शुकी and गरुड. Br. III. 7. ४५०.--a gem. M. २१८. ३५.--a son of विश्वेशा. M. १७१. ५०.--hills round about Meru; these are Mandara, गन्धमाधन, तिलाचल, (Vipula) and सुपार्श्व. M. ८३. ११, १९, ३६; ११३. ४५.--once asked of it by Sagara the sage Aurva narrated it to him; was repeated by पराशर to Maitreya. Vi. III. 8. 3-5.(I)--the name of the sun in the month of ऊर्ज (कार्तिक); {{F}}1:  भा. XII. ११. ४४; Br. II. २३. २०; वा. ६६. ६१, ६६.{{/F}} an आदित्य and Lord of आदित्यस्; {{F}}2:  Br. II. २४. ३४; III. 3. ६८; M. 6. 4; १७१. ५६. Vi. I. १५. १३०.{{/F}} in the sun's chariot in फाल्गुन. {{F}}3:  Ib. I. २२. 3; II. १०. १८.{{/F}}(II)--a god of आभूतरय group. Br. II. ३६. ५६.(III)--(उत्तमश्लोक) worshipped for dharma. His abode above the position of seven sages, where is found the great Dhruva with others; {{F}}1:  भा. II. 3. २२; III. ch. १३ (whole); V. २२. १७; २३. 1.{{/F}} different forms of; as Trivik- rama broke अण्डकटाह and let the Ganges in; as Sankar- [page३-285+ ५०] षण, worshipped by शिव in इलावृत; as हयग्रीव in Bha- द्राश्व country; as नृसिम्ह in हरिवर्ष; as कामदेव in केतुमाला; as Matsya in Ramyaka; as कूर्म in हिरण्मय; also सान्ख्यनिदर्शन; as वराह in Uttara Kuru country; also in the form of both यज्ञ and Kratu; as सीताराम in Kim- पुरुष; as नरनारायण in भारतवर्ष; as सूर्य in Plak- षद्वीप; as Soma in शाल्मलि; as Agni in कुशद्वीप; as a form of water in क्रौञ्चद्वीप; as वायु in शाकद्वीप; as ब्रह्मा in पुष्करद्वीप. {{F}}2:  Ib. V. १७. 1 and १६; chh. १८-20 (whole);{{/F}} Propitiated by दक्ष after his reconciliation with शिव, विष्णु came to receive offerings in person in the form of यज्ञ and was praised by all present including ब्रह्मा and शिव. He told दक्ष that he was not different from शिव or ब्रह्मा. {{F}}3:  Ib. IV. 7. १८-54; १४. २६.{{/F}} presented पृथु with सुदर्शन and addressed him to befriend Indra, to be devoted to Him and to conduct himself righteously. {{F}}4:  Ib. IV. १५. १६; २०. 2-१६, ३१ [1-2].{{/F}} His residence near क्षीरोद where he sleeps in yoga: vanquisher of Bali; saw a लिन्ग of efful- gence and with ब्रह्मा went down and up to know its origin and end, but could not get at that. शिव's remark that his right and left arms were ब्रह्मा and विष्णु. This is महा- यागम् and माहेश्वरम् balam; {{F}}5:  Br. II. २६. 2; २७. २२.{{/F}} cursed by भृगु to take १० (7 म्। प्।) incarnations on the earth; called पुरुष and यज्ञ. {{F}}6:  Ib. III. 3. ८५-106; ७२. 3-१७; M. ४७. ९९-103.{{/F}} In स्वायम्भुव epoch was born of आकूती, in स्वारोचिष, born of तुषिता as Ajita, in Uttama epoch, born of सत्या as Satya, in तामस born of हरिणी as Hari, in Vaivasvata, born of कश्यप and अदिती with the name वैकुण्ठ. {{F}}7:  Br. III. १०७-122.{{/F}} Overlord of आदित्यस्; gave peacock and fowl to कुमार. {{F}}8:  Ib. III. १०. ४६; २४. 6; ३३. १५; ४२. ४८; ७१. १७६ and २६२. M. 6. 4; १७१. ५६.{{/F}} Killed Daityas in तारकामय and especially कालनेमि. Aided Indra against Asuras. Introduced यज्ञ and other rites, divisions of time, three castes, three Vedas, three गुणस् and so on. {{F}}9:  Br. III. ७२. १८-64, १३३. १४२; M. ch. १७२.{{/F}} Got Indra redeemed of the sin of hitting his Purohita विश्- वरूप, by distributing it among the women, trees and earth. When दुर्वास cursed Indra for refusing to accept देवी's garland, the Asuras destroyed the Devas and entered heaven. Then Hari suggested churning of the ocean and distributed as मोहिनी nectar to Devas making them invincible. {{F}}१०:  Br. IV. 9. २३-81; १०. 4-5; १४. 2.{{/F}} Gave his sister देवी in marriage to शिव with wedding presents. {{F}}११:  Ib. IV. १५. १५-23; २८. ८९; ३०. 8; ३१. 6; ३४. ७१-2;{{/F}} [page३-286+ ५५] Fond of soma drink. Got विष्णुत्वम् by meditating upon ललितामन्त्र। {{F}}१२:  Ib. IV. ३८. ३९.{{/F}} Reflections of कालनेमि on his eternal enmity to Asuras. Killed कालनेमि after a fierce fight, described; re-establishes order and goes back to his abode. {{F}}१३:  M. १७८. 5-८०; ८७. 1.{{/F}} Lord of Ravis; as Kapila destroyed the Sagaras. {{F}}१४:  Ib. 8. 4; १२. ४१-3; १७. 1.{{/F}} Born in the family of क्रोष्ठु, helped the वृष्णिस्; {{F}}१५:  Ib. ४४. १५; ४७. २९, ३३.{{/F}} helped Indra by killing काव्य's mother; {{F}}१६:  Ib. ४७. ९९.{{/F}} worship of, in the विभूति dva1das4i- vratam; {{F}}१७:  Ib. १७४. ५१; २२५. १४; २४६. ४१, ६९. २४८. ४०.{{/F}} Icon of, with different postures described; {{F}}१८:  Ib. २५८. 4-१५; २६६. ४२.{{/F}} विष्णु (जनार्दन); {{F}}१९:  Ib. 7. २०; १५४. ३५१.{{/F}} blessed वैभ्राज of पाञ्चाल with a son, Brahmadatta; {{F}}२०:  Ib. 9. 1; २१. ११-6.{{/F}} in नारसिम्ह form; {{F}}२१:  Ib. २२. १७.{{/F}} in मेघकर तीर्थम्; {{F}}२२:  Ib. २२. ४०.{{/F}} blessed Soma with fulfilment of all his desires; {{F}}२३:  Ib. २३. १७-19.{{/F}} regained the jewel Syamantaka from the bear and gave it to सत्राजित्; {{F}}२४:  Ib. ४५. १६-17.{{/F}} spoke of आदिसर्ग and Pratisarga; {{F}}२५:  Ib. ५२. 2.{{/F}} worshipped by पुरूरवस् when he was a Brahman in previous birth; {{F}}२६:  Ib. ६५. 7; ११५. १२.{{/F}} came out of the arrow of त्रिपुरारि and drank of the medi- cinal tank of Tripuram; {{F}}२७:  Ib. १३६. ५८.{{/F}} overwhelmed by Asuras on all sides broke the chariot of कालनेमि who escaped; {{F}}२८:  Ib. १३६. ६५; १५०. २२२.{{/F}} cut off Grasana's neck by the cakra; {{F}}२९:  Ib. १५०. २४३; १५१. ३४.{{/F}} disabled in fight with other राक्षसस् especially Jambha and Nimi, fled with गरुड; {{F}}३०:  Ib. ch. १५२.{{/F}} Indra met him and praised his past exploits and promised to help himself with ११ Rudras; with Indra's army जनार्- dana went to war once more; {{F}}३१:  Ib. १५३. 1-4.{{/F}} vanquished the Asuras at भार्गवेश; {{F}}३२:  Ib. १९२. 1-2.{{/F}} residence of, in the Mandara hill; {{F}}३३:  Ib. २०६. १८; २४५. 9; २४६. २४, ३०f; २४९. ३२.{{/F}} meditation of; {{F}}३४:  Ib. २६६. ३५.{{/F}} spoke of the १६ gifts to Manu; {{F}}३५:  Ib. २७४. १६.{{/F}} fish form of. {{F}}३६:  Ib. २९०. २३.{{/F}} [page३-287+ ३३](IV)--a भार्गव gotraka1ra. M. १९५. २०.(V)--one of the nine sons of सावर्णि. वा. १००. २२.--incarnation of, at the time of कृष्ण's birth. See योगमाया. भा. X. 1. २५.--three-fold; ability to perceive the abso- lute truth, ability to perceive the nature of the embodied soul and thirdly inability to know one's nature; the technical terms used are परा, क्षेत्रज्ञा or अपरा and अविद्या कर्म- सम्ज्ञा। Vi. VI. 7. ६०-1.--a त्रयार्षेय. M. १९६. ३९.--met यमदूतस् at the death of अजामिल and argued that the uttering of Hari's name before his death was an expiation for all sins committed. Yama's tri- bute to them as objects of worship for they go about protect- ing the votaries of Hari. {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 1. २०; 2. 2-३९; 3. १७-18.{{/F}} Residents of विष्णुलोक. {{F}}2:  Br. IV. 7. ३८.{{/F}}--the abode of विष्णु {{F}}1:  वा. १०८. १९; १११. ६७; Vi. V. ३८. ९४.{{/F}} in पाण्डवेशम्; at- tained by one who bathes in चक्रतीर्थम्; {{F}}2:  M. १९१. २१, ६२.{{/F}} he who does तुलापुरुष goes to विष्णुलोकम्. {{F}}3:  Ib. १९३. ७४.{{/F}}--the celestial regions where Dhruva holds the भगवत्पदी on his head with intense devotion; {{F}}1:  भा. V. १७. 1-2.{{/F}} sacred for गन्गा. {{F}}2:  Br. III. १३. ११८.{{/F}}(I)--a lake in the निषध hill; {{F}}1:  Br. II. १८. ६७; III. ४३. १४; M. १२१. ६६; वा. ४७. ६४.{{/F}} sacred to पितृस्; {{F}}2:  M. २२. २५.{{/F}} the place where Dhruva is located. {{F}}3:  वा. ५०. २२२.{{/F}}(II)--the path where Dharma, Dhruva and others take their stand above the seven sages; the region between the seven ऋषिस् and Dhruva where live ascetics and yogis of a high order; the source of rain and the stay of the three worlds; from this proceeds the गन्गा; issuing from the nail of the great toe of विष्नु's left foot; {{F}}1:  Br. II. २१. १७६; Vi. II. 8. ९८-109;{{/F}} the third division of the celestial region. {{F}}2:  Ib. II. 8. १२२.{{/F}}(III)--a Mt. in गया; a hill where Dhar- maratha performed a sacrifice. M. ४८. ९३; वा. ९९. १०२; १०५. २६; १०९. १८; १११. ४६-7 and ५६. [page३-288+ ३०]--a R. of the भद्रा country. वा. ४३. २९.--one among the eighteen पुराणस्; com- prises २३,000 श्लोकस्. भा. XII. 7. २३. १३. 4.--sacred to विष्णु; attained by Heti after having been killed by विष्नु. वा. १०९. २५; २७४. ७६.--a name of परिक्षित्. भा. I. १२. १७.--here गन्गा was born and here are the footprints of वामन. Br. III. ३७. 4.--of योधनीपुरम्; where the Asuras were slain by वासुदेव in large numbers; {{F}}1:  M. १९१. ९९-101.{{/F}} more efficacious than the Ganges. {{F}}2:  वा. १११. ४१. 2.{{/F}}--in honour of विष्णु, leads to Parama- pada. M. १०१. ३७, ६४.(I)--क्षत्रियस् who became द्विजस्। Br. III. ६६. ८८; वा. ९१. ११७. [page३-289+ ३०](II)--the descendants of विष्णुवृद्ध, cognates of Angiras; Brahmans with क्षत्रिय dharma. वा. ६५. १०७; ८८. ७९.--another name of Kalki to be born to a Brahman of शम्भलग्राम. भा. I. 3. २५; XII. 2. १८; Vi. IV. २४. ९८. Br. III. ७३. १०४; वा. ९८. १०४.(I)--a son of त्रिवक्रा by कृष्ण, and devoted to him; the author of सात्वत Tantra for the good women, शूद्रस् and slaves. A disciple of नारद. भा. X. ९०. ३४ [1-2].(II)--one of the four sons in the ३०थ् kalpa of शर्व, red in colour, attire, etc. वा. २२. ३०.(III)--a son of Damana, an अवतार् of the Lord in the 3rd द्वापर. वा. २३. १२४.--a mind-born mother. M. १७९. २५.--removes one's difficulties and prepares the way for the final bliss; performed in honour of केशव or लक्ष्मी in the month of आश्वयुज: gift of bed with गुडधेनु after the पूज and other observances in the prescribed manner; the gift of गुड-dhenu on the beginning day of the ayana or days of विषु or eclipse, attended by music and dancing; the gift of a sugar cow. M. chh. ८१ and ८२. 