V. ११. २७-8.(II)--a son of सात्वत and father of Sumitra and युजाजित्; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २४. 6 and १२.{{/F}} darling of the Yadus; had two wives, गान्धारी and माद्री; the former bore Sumitra and the latter, five children; {{F}}2:  M. ४४. ४८; ४५. 1-2.{{/F}} suspected कृष्ण of having appropriated the syamantaka gem from which he honourably redeemed himself; {{F}}3:  Br. III. ७१. 1, ३६, १०२.{{/F}} belonged to the कृओष्ठु line; {{F}}4:  Ib. III. ७०. १५; ७३. ९१.{{/F}} originator of the वृष्णि kula. {{F}}5:  वा. ९५. १४.{{/F}}(III)--a son of Anamitra (a member of that family, वि। प्।) and father of श्वफल्क and चीत्ररथ. भा. IX. २४. १५. Vi. IV. १४. 5.(IV)--a son of भजमान. M. ४४. ५०; Vi. IV. १३. 1-2. [page३-313+ ३१](V)--a son of Kukura and father of Kapotaroman and धृति. Br. III. ७१. ११७; M. ४४. ६२.(VI)--the best of the Yadus and a son of कौसल्या. वा. ९६. 2.(VII)--a son of बाह्यक--two queens गान्धारी and माद्री. वा. ९६. 4, १७.(VIII)--a son of Satvata; had two sons सुमीत्र and युधाजित्. Vi. IV. १३. 1, 8.--its old fame was raised by the birth of Lord विष्णु. M. ४४. १५; ४७. १२ and ३३; ६९. १०.--a son of शुचिद्रव (शुचिरथ-वि। प्।) and father of सुषेण. M. ५०. ८०; Vi. IV. २१. १२. [page३-314+ २६]--the community of द्वारवती in which Bala- राम and कृष्ण were born; {{F}}1:  भा. I. 3. २३; ११. ११; १४. २५; Br. III. ६१. २३; ७१. ८५; वा. 1. १४५; ९६. ८४, १७५; ८६. २८.{{/F}} कुन्ती was attached to these people while Kamsa devised means to vanquish them. Were relieved at Kamsa's death. {{F}}2:  भा. I. 8. ४१; X. ३६. ३३; ३९. २५; ४५. १५;{{/F}} Its name derived from वृष्णि. {{F}}3:  Ib. IX. २३. ३०.{{/F}} They praised the heroic deeds of कृष्ण who was their Lord and who lived with them. But they did not recognise in Him the Almighty Lord; {{F}}4:  Ib. I. 9. १८; II. 4. २०; IX. २४. ६३; X. 1. ११ and ६२; ९०. ४६.{{/F}} ended their lives by fighting their kinsmen at प्रभासा. Attained Hari through relationship. {{F}}5:  Ib. XI. ३०. १८; VII. 1. ३०.{{/F}}--rules for the dedication of a bull; the characteristics and adornments of the bull intended for gift and of the cow, its mother; intended for all castes; different coloured bulls and their significance; gift of नील bull best for पितृस्; {{F}}1:  M. १८. १४; २०७. 1-४१; वा. ८३. १२, ४५-6.{{/F}} at गया. {{F}}2:  Ib. ११२. ५८.{{/F}}--(धृष्ट): his line was वार्ष्टक. Vi. IV. 2. 4.(I)--a son of सावर्णि Manu. M. 9. ३३. [page३-312+ ३१](II)--a son of Kakuda. वा. ९६. ११६.--a daughter of मरीचि. Br. II. ११. १२.--a son of Kaviratha, and father of सुषेण. भा. IX. २२. ४१.--a son of अश्विनी and अक्रूर. M. ४५. ३३.--one of the sons of कार्तवीर्य and a महा- ratha. वा. ९४. ४९.(I)--a son of त्वष्ट्रि, created out of a sacrificial offering with an ugly appearance to avenge Indra, the mur- derer of विश्वरूप. Hari advised Indra on the means to end वृत्र. In the battle वृत्र encouraged his soldiers and uttered words of heroism. Ran towards Indra as कैटभ against Hari and had one hand cut off. But in the contest the Vajra of Indra slipped and वृक asked him to take up the weapon and fight. He had his other arm cut off. But वृक swallowed Indra into his stomach from which Indra escaped and cut off his head. वृत्र attained Aloka due to his faith in Hari having been born as Citraketu (s.v.) in his previous birth. {{F}}1:  भा. VI. chh. 9-१२ (whole); ch. १४ (whole); १७. ३८-39; X. ७७. ३६; Br. III. ७२. ८३.{{/F}} Attained release by सत्सन्ग। His greed for more territory. {{F}}2:  भा. XI. १२. 5; XII. 3. ११.{{/F}} Killed by हालाफल अवतार्। An account of the death in the भागवत; an Asura of कृतयुग. {{F}}3:  M. ४७. ५१; ५३. २०; २४९. ६७.{{/F}} Brought forth sons from his terrible breathing during his fight with Indra in thousands. All followers of Mahendra, those who have realised ब्रह्मा, are happy, dharmic and live in small bodies. {{F}}4:  वा. ६८. ३४-6.{{/F}}(II)--a son of अनायुष. Father of Bakas in hun- dreds who followed Mahendra. Br. III. 6. ३१.--the ninth of the twelve incarnations of विष्णु. M. ४७. ४४.--a R. from the पारियात्र hill; from ऋष्यवान्; in भारतवर्ष. Br. II. १६. २७; M. ११४. २३; वा. ४५. ९७ [page३-305+ ३१]--is Indra; {{F}}1:  Br. III. १०. २३.{{/F}} got frightened at the prolonged love of उमा and शन्कर and asked Agni to disturb their sport. {{F}}2:  वा. ७२. २१.{{/F}}--an epithet of Indra. Vi. V. 1. ५८.--a son of शिष्ट. M. 4. ३९.--a daughter of ऋषा; mother of Tortoise, शन्ख, etc. Br. III. 7. ४१४-17; वा. ६९. २९१-92.(I)--means of living by ऋत, अमृत, मृत प्रमृत and सत्यामृत or सत्यानृत; never by श्ववृत्ति। भा. VII. ११. १८-20.(II)--transformation of जयादेवस् in the seven epochs of Manu. Br. III. 4. १२, ३७.--an अमिताभ god. Br. II. ३६. ५४. [page३-304+ ३५]--a R. of क्रौञ्चद्वीप. भा. V. २०. २१.--sacred as houses for the primitive man and supplied him with honey, fruits and clothing; Gandharvas live in them; these कल्पवृक्षास् deteriorated and man who took to caves began to build houses on the model furnished by the trees with the upward, downward and crosswise trees; {{F}}1:  Br. II. 7. ७५-91, ११७-20.{{/F}} milked the cow-earth; the essence was tender leaves; the vessel was of पालाश wood and the प्लक्ष tree acted as the calf. {{F}}2:  M. १०. २७.{{/F}}--a son of बाष्कल. वा. ६७. ७९. [page३-303+ २४]--milked the earth in पलाशपात्र. वा. ६२. १९१.--(पादपोद्यापन): festivities connected with the planting of trees and the laying out of gardens. M. ५९. १७.--a hunter who attained permanent fame. भा. X. ७२. २१.--of भार्गवगोत्र. M. १९५. २७.--a son of मृत्यु. वा. १०. ४१.--a शक्ति. Br. IV. ३५. ९९.(I)--a son of यातुधान and father of निरा- nanda. Br. III. 7. ८९ and ९६.(II)--one of the five sons of ऊर्द्ध्वदृष्टि and father of शरभ. Br. III. 7. २०५.(III)--the tiger, said to have eaten Garga's cow; {{F}}1:  M. २०. १०.{{/F}} its skin, the dress of शिव. {{F}}2:  Ib. २१७. 5; २५९. 6.{{/F}}(IV)--a snake with the sun in आवणि and पुरट्टाशि. वा. ५२. ११.(V)--a पिशाच. वा. ६९. १२७.(VI)--the राक्षस residing in the sun's chariot in the भाद्रपद month. Vi. II. १०. १०.(VII)--the राक्षस presiding over the month of Nabhasya. भा. XII. ११. ३८; Br. II. २३. ११.--a वासिष्ठ. M. २००. 2.--born of Hari and Pulaha; a वानरजाति and son of जाम्बवान्; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 7. १७६, ३०४, ३१९; ५१. 9.{{/F}} could be killed as wild animals. {{F}}2:  Ib. IV. 6. ५०; २९. ४१.{{/F}} [page३-348+ २४]--wife of जाम्बवत्; mother of जाम्बवती. Br. III. 7. ३०१.--daughters of सविता; {{F}}1:  भा. VI. १८. 1; III. १२. ४४.{{/F}} three in number. {{F}}2:  वा. ६४. १९.{{/F}}--a son of भृगु; a deva. Br. III. 1. ८९.--पाणिनि's grammar. Br. III. १९. २२; वा. ८३. ५२; Vi. V. 1. ३८. [page३-347+ २८]--the place where sages expound the Vedic lore. Br. III. २१. ५२.--from the hairs of the head of प्रजापति. ety. ahi, the vilest of creatures; Pannaga. ety. creeping on the ground; sarpa, from escaping or fleeting nature; all have their abode in the earth under the sun and moon; out of anger came विष or poison; then airy beings were created; चूटस्, पिशाचस् from eating flesh, Gandharvas sucking cows. वा. 9. ३४-40.--is शिव. Br. II. २७. ९९.(I)--a तुषित. Br. III. 3. १९; वा. ६६. १८.(II)--a mind-born son of ब्रह्मा in the २१स्त् Kalpa. वा. २१. ४७; ३१. ४१.--all pervadingness from apavarga; from that comes पुरुष. वा. १३. २३.--a शक्ति. Br. IV. ३५. ९९; ४४. ६२. [page३-349+ ३६]--a god of सुतार group. Br. IV. 1. ९०.--one of the ten branches of the सुपार group of devas. वा. १००. ९४.(I)--an अम्शावतार of विष्णु; also known as Dvai- पायन and कृष्ण; son of पराशर and वासवी (सत्यवती) in द्वापर yuga. Father of शुक; appointed by his mother, he begot three sons on his brother's wife being childless- धृतराष्ट्र, पाण्डु and Vidura. {{F}}1:  भा. I. 2. 4; 4. १४-15; IX. २२. २२-25; XII. 6. ३६; III. 5. १९-20; M. १५. 8; १८०. ६४; Br. III. १०. ७९-80; १३. ७७.{{/F}} Rearranged the Vedas into four parts, and taught each of them to four respective pupils--Paila, वैशम्पायन, Jaimini and Sumantu. Re- arranged इतिहास-Pura1n2as also; composed the भारत for स्त्रीशूद्र-dvijabandhus; composed also the भागवत and taught it to his son शुक, having heard it from नारद. {{F}}2:  भा. XII. 6. ४९-53; I. 4. १६-25; 7. 1-8; II. 9. ४४; III. 5. १० and १२; XII. 4. ४२; १३. १९; Br. I. 1. २५; II. ३१. २८; ३३. ३२-3; ३४. ११-12; III. १७. २९५.{{/F}}  When he felt a mental dissatisfaction, नारद met him and was praised. Asked as to the reason for his uneasiness, नारद emphasised devotion to Hari as the means of release and proceeded to narrate the story of his previous birth. When the sage left व्यास retired to his hermitage शम्या- प्रास on the सरस्वती and meditated on the Lord who appeared before him with माया depending on him. Learnt [page३-350+ ३७] devotion as the means of ending सम्सार। {{F}}3:  भा. I. 4. ३०-33; chh. 5 and 6 (whole); 7. 1-4;{{/F}} One of युधिष्- ठिर's party on a visit to भीष्म; was a Purohita at कृष्ण's sacrifice at कुरुक्षेत्र; told the history of Citraketu to शुक who bowed to him. {{F}}4:  Ib. I. 8. ४६; 9. 2; X. ९०. ४६[2]; VI. १४. 9; VII. 1. 5.{{/F}} Heard श्रुतिगीता from नारायण. Faith in क्रियायोग; a siddha. {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ८७. ४७-8; XI. २७. 2; VI. १५. १२.{{/F}} Taught लोमहर्षण about the future of the world and its history. {{F}}6:  M. ५०. ७२.{{/F}} An incarnation of the Lord in every द्वापर; {{F}}7:  Ib. ५३. 9.{{/F}} took a vow of silence and fasting for १२ years after which he wandered for food but could not get any in Benares; when he was about to curse the city, शिव and उमा took the guise of householders and offered him rich food. So he blessed it. {{F}}8:  Ib. १८५. १७-38.{{/F}} A तीर्थ in his honour. {{F}}9:  Ib. १९१. ४१; २०३. १४.{{/F}}(II)--a sage of the eighth manvantara. भा. VIII. १३. १५; Vi. III. 2. १७.--the sacred lake near शिव lake. Br. III. १३. ५२; वा. ७७. ५१.--near दृषद्वति; {{F}}1:  Br. III. १३. ६९, ८०.{{/F}} in दीपेश्वर, a तीर्थम् of the नर्मदा sacred to व्यास. {{F}}2:  M. १९१. ३८-42.{{/F}}--a son of भृगु. वा. ६५. ८७.--the second form of Parabrahmam. Vi. I. 2. १५, १८.--the absolute, developed out of avyakta; {{F}}1:  वा. १०१. २११.{{/F}} swallowed by avyakta in the stage of प्रत्याहर; {{F}}2:  Ib. १०२. 2.{{/F}} of five characteristics; {{F}}3:  Ib. ३४. ३७.{{/F}} seen by tarka an