n of दण्ड, used by, in the battle of Tri- puram; {{F}}१९:  Ib. १३५. ७७.{{/F}} seen by सावित्री while taking the life of her hus- band; blessed her with three requests of hers and finally the life of her husband; {{F}}२०:  Ib. २१०. 5, chh. २११-14.{{/F}} meting out justice impartially; {{F}}२१:  Ib. २१३. 3.{{/F}} father of two daughters उपदानवी and हिमा. {{F}}२२:  वा. ६८. २३; ६९. ६१; ७५. ५६; ८२. 1; १०१. १५०, २८६; १०६, ४६; १०८. 4 and ३१; ११० 10 and ३८.{{/F}}(II)--a याज्ञिय god. Br. II. ३६. ३३.(III)--a मुहूर्त of the night. Br. III. 3. ४२.(IV)--a Sukha god. Br. IV. 1. १८.(V)--a son of हविर्धान. M. 4. ४५.(VI)--an आदित्य. M. 6. 4.(VII)--the father of इलिना, (s.v.). M. ४९. 9. [page३-014+ २६](VIII)--a Vasu; a son of Dharma and सुदेवी. M. १७१. ४७.(IX)--the agent of a class of devas. वा. १०. ७२.(X)--the son of सुरेणु and Vivasvan; ill-treated by stepmother छाया, was about to kick her when she cursed him that he would lose his leg; he became Dharma- राज, lord of पितृस् and Protector of the world. वा. ८४. २२, ५६-61.(XI)--a mukhya गण. वा. १००. १८.--a commander of भण्ड. Br. IV. २१. ८२.--the offering to शिव at the प्रभास hill. वा. १०८. २३; ११०. ३८.--an अधिकार। M. २२५. १६; वा. १०८. 4.--met विष्णु du1tas at the death of अजामिल, and argued that punishment depended on the character of one's action, and that अजामिल a Brahmana deserved punish- ment for having forsaken his स्वधर्म and led an evil life with a दासि। Overpowered by Hari's दूतस्, they reported [page३-015+ २६] to Yama (s.v.) and wanted to know the truth of the matter. Instructed by Yama as knower of Dharma and ordained by Hari, his messengers cherished Hari's glory, and did not go near his devotees. भा. VI. 1. २०, ४०. ६८; 3. १०-34.--a region of the जम्बुद्वीप; here is Dutimat, a Mt. वा. ४८. १४, १९.--a Bhairava god. Br. IV. २०. ८२.--an eastern tribe. M. ११४. ४४.--servants of Yama. वा. ११०. ४५.--a दानव king. Br. IV. २९. १२४.--a name of कृष्ण. Br. III. ३६. २८.--of कौशिक gotra. वा. ९१. ९८.--the kingdom of Dharma. वा. १०६. २०; १०८. 3; Vi. V. २१. ३०.--(किण्कर): a servant of Yama with a noose. Vi. III. 7. १३, १९.--prescriptions. वा. १०४. १४.taken to the abode of Yama in two or three मुहूर्तस् covering about ९९००० yoja- nas; tortures in. भा. III. ३०. २०-28.--twins--Nakula and Sahadeva. भा. I. १०. 9; Vi. V. ३५. २८; ३८. ९१.--also known as Anuparvatam, west of the लौहिती and the Sindhu. वा. ६९. २४१.--of kings; to punish impartially. M. २२६. 4. [page३-016+ ४४]--a daughter of Vivasvan (सूर्य-वि। प्।) and सम्ज्ञा; also यमुना. भा. VI. 6. ४०: VIII. १३. 9: Br. III. ५९. ३८; Vi. III. 2. 2.--a शुक्रदेव. वा. ३१. 8.(I)--(कालिन्दी) (R.) in भारतवर्ष from the हिमालयस्; a divine stream. {{F}}1:  भा. V. १९. १८; वा. ४५. ९५.{{/F}} A महानदी. {{F}}2:  Ib. १०४. ५०.{{/F}} Here Vidura met Uddhava; {{F}}3:  भा. III. 1. २४; 2. २७; IV. 2. ३५.{{/F}} the co-wives who administered poison to Citraketu's son, had a purificatory bath in; Citraketu, who was initiated into the विद्या by नारद had his preli- minary bath in this river. {{F}}4:  Ib. VI. १६. १४ and १६.{{/F}} On its banks Vaivasvata Manu performed तपस् for progeny, and Bharata celebrated his horse sacrifice. On its banks stands Madhuvana near बृण्दावन. कृष्ण, his brother, and others played there and once defeated the Asura Vatsa. Gopi girls bathed there as part of the कात्ययनी व्रतम्। Nanda used to bathe here. {{F}}5:  Ib. IX, 2. 1; 4. ३०; २०. २५; X. ११. ३६-43; २२. 2, 6, ३६; २८. 1.{{/F}} Immersed in its waters Saubhari performed penance. Poisoned by the कालीय; कृष्ण sent away the reptile to the sea and made its waters drinkable; unapproachable to गरुड by a curse of Saubhari. {{F}}6:  Ib. IX. 6. ३९; X. १५. ४७-8; १६. 4, ६०-7; १७. 8-११.{{/F}} अक्रूर who took कृष्ण and राम to मथुरा, had his bath on the way in this river. Inside the waters he saw both कृष्ण and राम; also saw Hari on the शेष. Here कृष्ण killed Hamsa. {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ३९. ३८-46; ७६. 2 [8]; ७८. [1).{{/F}} On its bank जरासन्ध encamped to besiege मथुरा. Here कृष्ण had his अवभृत after the horse sacrifice. Here again कृष्ण and अर्जुण met कालिन्दी. {{F}}8:  Ib. X. [५० (v) 6 and १४]; ८९. ६३ [4]; ५८. १६-7.{{/F}} During his pilgrimage [page३-017+ ४३] बलराम visited this. {{F}}9:  Ib. X. ७८. २०.{{/F}} Was in floods when Vasudeva crossed it for Gokula with the new born babe, कृष्ण. {{F}}१०:  Ib. X. 3. ५०.{{/F}} Sacred for श्राद्ध; sometimes too hot and sometimes too cold; daughter of मार्ताण्ड and सम्ज्ञा and sister of Yama; got changed into a sacred river. On its northern bank is प्रयागा (प्रतिष्ठान). {{F}}११:  Br. II. १६. २५; III. १३. ७१-2; ५९. २३ and ८३; ६६. २१; ७३. ११७; IV. १५. २३; M. ११. 4, ३९; १०४. १९; १०८. २२; वा. ७७. ६९-70.{{/F}} Sacred to मृगावती; sacred to the पितृस्; {{F}}१२:  M. १३. ४०.{{/F}} a boundary of the kingdom of पितृस्; {{F}}१३:  Ib. २२. २०.{{/F}} in the chariot of त्रिपुरारि; {{F}}१४:  Ib. ११०. 5; ११४. २१; १३३. २३; १६३. ६१; २३९. १८.{{/F}} one of the १६ wives of हव्यवाहन (fire) {{F}}१५:  Ib. ५१. १३; वा. २९. १३.{{/F}} forms the left side of the Veda; {{F}}१६:  Ib. १०४. ७७; १०८. ७९.{{/F}} daughter of सुरेणु and सूर्य; {{F}}१७:  Ib. ५८. ८८; ८४. २२.{{/F}} a sacred river. {{F}}१८:  Br. II. १२. १४; वा. ९८. ११७; Vi. III. १४. १८; V. 3. १८; 7. 7ff; १८. ३३.{{/F}}(II)--(personified) sister of Yama. Once बलराम invited her for watersports, and got enraged at her delay. Hence he dragged her by means of his plough through बृण्दावन्. This changed her course; then she prayed for mercy which was granted. She presented राम with clothes and jewels. Even now the change in the course is noticeable. भा. X. 3. ५०; Ib. ch. ६५ (whole); Vi. V. २५. 8-११, VI. 8. ३१.--a mechanical contrivance used by त्वष्टा to diminish the तेजस् of the sun; the surplus तेजस् became विष्णु's cakra, Rudra's trident and Indra's thunder bolt. M. ११. २७-9.--a तीर्थ on the north bank of the Nar- मदा; a bath there secures the company of Gods for ५००० years. M. १९०. 1-2. [page३-012+ ६१]--an attendant on ललिता. Br. IV. १७. ४६.--the hairs of the Veda. वा. १०४. ७३.(I)--a son of कीर्ति. Br. II. 9. ६२; वा. १०. ३७.(II)--a वैकुण्ठ god. Br. II. ३६. ५७; वा. ६२. 9.(III)--one of the twenty Sutapa गणस्. वा. १००. १५; Br. IV. 1. १५.--the goddess enshrined at कार्तिकेय. M. १३. ४५. [page३-022+ ४०]--a Pratardana god. Br. II. ३६. ३१.--a दुर्गा and विश्वरूपिनी who got शूल from शिव, cakra from विष्णु, शन्ख from वरुण, शक्ति from Agni, bow and arrow from Marut, Vajra from Indra, चषक from Kubera, दण्ड and पाश from Yama, कुण्टिक from ब्रह्मा, खड्ग and केट from मृत्यु, jewels from विश्व- karman. Br. IV. २९. ८०-8; ४४. ९०.(I)--the wife of Nanda (gopa); {{F}}1:  भा. I. 8. ३१; X. 2. 9; M. ४७. 7; Vi. IV. १५. ३१.{{/F}} gave birth to a female child who was योगमाया incarnate. Without her knowledge, Vasudeva placed कृष्ण born on the same day in her bed and removed the girl to his residence. This was known to नारद. {{F}}2:  Bha. X. 3. ४७-53; ३६. १७; वा. ९६. २०६-9.{{/F}} Regarded कृष्ण as her own child; per- formed रक्षा to कृष्ण after his killing पूतना; her concern at कृष्ण's kicking the cart (शकटासुर) upside down, and शान्ति arranged; distressed at कृष्ण being carried away by the whirlwind (तृणावर्त); glad to see him alive; her con- cern at कृष्ण's eating mud, and wonder when he revealed his true form and the whole universe in his mouth; binding of कृष्ण with a rope for breaking the pot and stealing butter; took home कृष्ण playing on the river-bank; intense love to कृष्ण; joy at his escape from कालीय; surprise at कृष्ण holding Govardhana; recalled his exploits at Uddhava's visit, and gave him a hearty welcome. {{F}}3:  भा. X. 6. १९-29; Chh. 7-9 (whole); ११. १४-20; १५. ४४; १७. १५; २५. ३०; ४६. २८-9.{{/F}} Went to Syamanta- पञ्चक and was embraced with affection by रोहिणी and देवकी; {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ८२. ३६-9.{{/F}} represents the Mother Earth; {{F}}5:  Br. III. ७१. २१२-3, २३६ and २३९.{{/F}} remedy of, against बालदोष; {{F}}6:  Vi. V. 1. ७७; 2, 3; 3. २०.{{/F}} prayer of, to शकट; {{F}}7:  Ib. V. 5. १२.{{/F}} rope round the belly of कृष्ण for mischief. {{F}}8:  Ib. V. 6. 7, १४; 7. २०.{{/F}} [page३-023+ २४](II)--the mind-born daughter of उपहूत Pitr2s; wife of विश्वमहत्; mother of खट्वान्ग. Br. III. १०. ९०; वा. ७३. ४०-41.(III)--a mind-born daughter of the हविष्मन्त- पितृस्, wife of अम्शुमान्, daughter-in-law of पञ्चजन, mother of दिलीप, and grandmother of भगीरथ. M. १५. १८-19.--is कृष्ण. Br. III. ३३. २०.--is कृष्ण. Br. III. ३६. २२.--a queen of Brhanmanas and mother of Jaya- dratha. M. ४८. १०५; वा. ९९. ११५.--mother of कामदेव. वा. २८. ३०. [page३-024+ २६](II)--a daughter of Virocana and wife of त्वष्टा. Br. III. १८७.(III)--a daughter of Devaka and one of the seven wives of Vasudeva. M. ४४. ७३.(I)--the wife कनकपीठ. Br. II. ११. ३५.--a god of the Sumedhasa group. Br. II. ३६. ५९.--a brother of शिशुनन्दि; ruled from Kili- किला. भा. XII. 1. ३२-3.--the सभा of इशान in the eighth slope of Meru; bright with lustrous gold. वा. ३४. ९१.--staves and cudgels, used by the barbarians against the enemies; {{F}}1:  Vi. V. ३८. १७.{{/F}} used by the आभिरस् against Arjuna. {{F}}2:  Ib. V. ३८. ५२.{{/F}}--a son of अर्काग्नि. Br. II. १२. ४३.--an आर्षेय pravara (भार्गव). M. १९५. ३६.--a भार्गव branch. Br. III. 1. १००.--a वानर chief. Br. III. 7. २३६.(I)--a son of ब्रह्मा, who remained a celibate. भा. IV. 8. 1.(II)--the eldest son of नहुष who did not like to be king and who devoted himself to the realisation of आत्मन्; became a वैखानस yogi even as a boy; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. १८. 1-2; M. २४. ५०; Vi. IV. १०. 1-2.{{/F}} married गा, daughter of काकुस्थ. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ६८. १२; वा. ९३. १३-14.{{/F}}(III)--feeding of, in a श्राद्ध pleases ब्रह्मा; duties of; {{F}}1:  Br. II. 7. १६९; ३२. २५; III. १५. १६-30; ६८. 6; वा. ५९. २४.{{/F}} प्रायश्चित्तस्, for commissions and omissions; {{F}}2:  Ib. १८. 1-२२.{{/F}} शूद्र Yatis with bald heads and red robes at the end of Kali. {{F}}3:  Ib. ५८. ५० and ५९; ९३. 6; १०४. २३.{{/F}}(IV)--a शिव god. Br. II. ३६. ३३. [page३-010+ ४१]--a son of युधिष्ठिर by देवकी. M. ५०. ५६.--the capital of नृग (मृग-वा। प्।). Br. III. ७४. २१; वा. ९९. २१.--a queen of युधिष्ठिर and mother of Devaka. Vi. IV. २०. ४४.(I)--a son of अम्बरीष, and father of हारित; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. 7. 1.{{/F}} killed in a battle lasting for १४ months and more Aruddha and Ripu. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ७४. 8; वा. ९९. 8.{{/F}}(II)--a grandson of कावेरी. वा. ९१. ५८. [page३-041+ २२](I)--the food of नैमिषेयस्; havis of, in a श्राद्ध. Br. I. 1. १५९; II. 7. १४४; ३२. १३; III. १४. ११; १९. 3; Vi. I. 6. २१, २४; II. १५. ३०. Vi. III. १६. 6; IV. १०. २४.(II)--a measurement, eight times the यूका (s.v.) M. २५८. १८.--an asura who, induced by नारद besieged मथुरा with three crores of म्लेच्छस्; saw कृष्ण and ran [page३-020+ ३७] towards him when he fled to a cave. Yavana followed him and in the cave saw somebody sleeping; thought it was कृष्ण and kicked him, when he woke up and burnt the asura to ashes by his energy. The sleeping person was Mucukunda (s.v.). {{F}}1:  भा. X. ५०. ४४; ५१. 1-२३, ४२.{{/F}} Thus he was vanquished by कृष्ण. {{F}}2:  Ib. II. 7. ३४; X. ३७. १६; Br. III. ७३. १०२; वा. ९८. १०२.{{/F}}--a tribe on the west of India; a northern king- dom west of भारतवर्ष noted for horses; {{F}}1:  Br. II. १६. १२ and ४७; १८. ४४; ३१. ८३; IV. १६. १७; २९. १३१. M. ११४. ११. ४१; १२१. ४३; १४४. ५७; वा. ८८. १२२; ४५. ८२, ११६; ४७. ४२; ५८. ८२; ९८. १०७; Vi. II. 3. 8.{{/F}} attacked बाहु and was defeated by Sagara; escaped with their moustaches (heads वि। प्।) shaved and lived in hills and caves; van- quished by Bharata; unsympathetic false and unrighteous; no right for अभिषेक; eight kings ruled for eighty years (वा। प्।) (eighty seven म्। प्।); {{F}}2:  भा. IX. 8. 5; २०. ३०; Br. III. ४८. २३-6, ४४-9; ६३. १२०-134.{{/F}} after the शकस्; {{F}}3:  भा. XII. 1. ३०; Br. III. ७४. १७२-5, २००; M. २७३. १९-20, २५; वा. ९९. २६८, ३६०, ३६२, ३८८; Vi. IV. 3. ४२, ४७-8.{{/F}} purified of sin by devotion to Hari; {{F}}4:  भा. II. 4. १८; IV. २७. २७; २८. 4-5; Vi. IV. २४. ५३.{{/F}} originated from Turvasu a son of ययाति. {{F}}5:  M. ३४. ३०; ५०. ७६.{{/F}}--had no son, and hence appointed गार्ग्य to bless him with one; this son was कालयवन. Vi. V. २३. 4-5.(I)--(यशस्य)