II. 7. ५०.{{/F}} usurped the आनर्त kingdom of Kakudmi when he was absent at ब्रह्मा's court; {{F}}8:  Ib. IX. 3. ३६.{{/F}} came with the gods to see कृष्ण and saw कृष्ण retiring to his own region; {{F}}9:  Ib. VII. 8. ३८; XI. ३१. 2.{{/F}} (see पुण्यजनस्); vanquished by रावण; {{F}}१०:  Br. III. 7. २५५.{{/F}} worship the पितृस् and ruin the श्राद्ध; {{F}}११:  Ib. III. १०. ३८, १११; ११. ८१; IV. 2. २६; १४. 4; २०. ५०; ३०. 9; ३३. ७५.{{/F}} their kingdom; {{F}}१२:  M. २३. ३९; १२१. ४८.{{/F}} their loka; {{F}}१३:  Br. IV. ३९. ५६.{{/F}} the nails of वामन when he grew. {{F}}१४:  M. २४६. ५४.{{/F}} [page३-002+ २७]--is Kubera (स्।व्।); {{F}}1:  Br. IV. २०. ५०.{{/F}} a follower of शिव in battle; helped वामदेव S4iva in his war with Soma. {{F}}2:  M. २३. ३८.{{/F}}--one of the ten पीठस् for images with three मेखलस्; this gives one plenty of cows. M. २६२. 6, 8, १७.--a शक्ति; {{F}}1:  Br. IV. २०. १५.{{/F}} an image of; surrounded by the Devas, दानवस् and the नागस्; hoods and two tongues to be carved above the head; also the spirits of the air and the evil spirits encircle her. {{F}}2:   M. २६१. ४७-50.{{/F}}--women of the यक्षस्. भा. X. ९०. 9.--Phthisis which afflicted Soma as a result of दक्ष's curse. भा. VI. 6. २३. [page३-003+ ३७]--the middle son of नहुष and विरजा, the mind- born daughter of Ajyapas: married शर्मिष्ठा, daughter of वृषपर्वन्, {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 6. ३२; Br. III. १०. ९५; ६८. १२-4; M. १५. २३; वा. 1. १४३; ७३. ४६.{{/F}} and had three sons by her; pleased with him Indra gave him a golden chariot yoked with swift horses and which became the ratha of the Paurava kings. {{F}}2:  Ib. ९३. १६-20.{{/F}} Became king after his father: desire for more territory; placed his [page३-018+ ४४] younger brothers in charge of the four quarters of the king- dom; nature of his good rule described; in the course of a hunting expedition, he heard the cry of a girl coming out of a well and going near it found a girl inside standing help- less and naked; he gave her his upper cloth to wear and lifted her up. She was देवयानी, the daughter of शुक्र and she became his wife and bore him two sons, Yadu and Turvasu. शुक्र in offering his daughter to the king asked him not to share his bed with शर्मिष्ठा. In a weak moment, forgetting his promise, he yielded to the entreaties of शर्मिष्ठा and on this देवयानी departed to शुक्र's place. ययाति followed her and was cursed by शुक्र to become old; but शुक्र said that he could take the youth of somebody by exchanging it for his old age. He enquired of all his sons and all except पूरु refused to comply with his request. With पूरु's youth he enjoyed for long the company of देवयानी; narrated to her an old story of an ewe found in a well, loving a ram, who was not faithful at first but who spent ultimately a long time of enjoyment with her. He compared himself to that ram and said that he should thereafter bestow his thought on Hari. So he returned his youth to पूरु and led a life of penance at भृगुतुन्ग after anointing पूरु on the throne and appoint- ing his other sons in different parts of the kingdom; dis- courses of, to पूरु on gentleness and friendliness to all; was devoted to Hari. परीक्षित् compared to ययाति for his धर्म। {{F}}3:  भा. IX. ch. १८ (whole); १९. 1-२५; XII. 3. १०; X. ६०. ४१; I. १२. २४; Br. III. ६८. १४-105; M. २४. ५०, ६६; २७. १४-22; chh. ३०-35; ३४. 4-7; ३६. 6-१३; वा. ९३. १३-16 and २०-76.{{/F}} Cursed that Yadu and his line be debarred from succeeding to the throne, though five dynasties of his sons are distinguished like the sun's rays. {{F}}4:  भा. X. ४५. १३; ७४. ३६; Br. III. ७१. २०२; ७४. २७५; वा. ९३. ७६-102.{{/F}} Tenth in genera- tion from प्रजापति. {{F}}5:  M. २५. 4.{{/F}} Went to heaven but Indra sent him back; one version is that he stands in the अन्तरिक्ष and the other is that he went back to heaven; met Indra and narrated पूरु's coronation: Indra told him of the completion of his righteousness and hence birth on the earth. {{F}}6:  Ib. ३५. 4-5; chh. ३६-37.{{/F}} Falling down, met अष्टक and the other grandsons, who cleared him of his doubts regarding the course of fate and man's helpless- ress, the fruits of karma, the worlds enjoyed by him, the [page३-019+ २६] bhauma naraka, the means to get सम्ज्ञा, and the duties of four आश्रमस् and munis. {{F}}7:  Ib. chh. ३८-40.{{/F}} These with Pratardana, Vasuman and शिबि offered a part of their punyam to make ययाति enjoy heaven. शिबि leading ययाति to heaven in a golden chariot as a result of their good deeds and truthfulness. {{F}}8:  Ib. ४२. १३-28; २७३. ८०.{{/F}}(II)--a याम deva. Br. II. १३. ९२.--शौनक's narration to शतानीक. M. Chh. २५-43.--a horse of the moon's chariot. वा. ५२. ५३.--a place sacred to वासुदेव; bath in the तीर्थ here rids one of his Brahmahatti दोष. M. १९१. १००.--कश्यप gotraka1ras. M. १९९. 5.(I)--practices of: {{F}}1:  भा. I. 2. २८; II. 1. 6; 2. २३; M. 1. १२.{{/F}} eight-fold: its characteristics. {{F}}2:  भा. III. Ch. २८.{{/F}} Bhaktiyoga: {{F}}3:  Ib. III. Ch. २९.{{/F}} born of Kriya, क्रियायोग: {{F}}4:  Ib. IV. 1. ५१; वा. ७१. ६४.{{/F}} the course of: fol- lowed by नारद and others in their worship of नारायण: {{F}}5:  भा. V. १४. ४५; १९. १०; VII. 3. 9; ११. 3.{{/F}} System of. {{F}}6:  Ib. IX. १२. 4; X. 8. ४५; Ch. २९ (whole) ; XI. १४. २०.{{/F}} Also three-fold ज्ञान, भक्ति and कर्म: of this भक्ति is important. {{F}}7:  Ib. XI. २०. 6-8.{{/F}} Spoiled by bad association, especially association of women; {{F}}8:  Ib. XI. २६. 3 and २४.{{/F}} is an ऐश्वर्य, and possible through kriya and gurupriya: of २४ truths: त्रयी is its limb; {{F}}9:  Br. II. ३४. ६५; III. 3. ८९; 9. ६२ and ६६; १०. 4 and ११५; १९. २९ and ६२; IV. 3. ५५.{{/F}} other limbs, यम, नियम, {{F}}१०:  M. १३. 5; १८३. ४४ and ५०; १९३. ३८; २४७. 9; २४८. १७.{{/F}} यज्ञ, दान, वेदाभ्यास, and धारण; philosophy of; {{F}}११:  Ib. 2. १६; वा. ६६. ११०.{{/F}} the strength of the पितृस्, out of which soma grows; from ज्ञान; {{F}}१२:  Ib. ७१. ६६; १०१. ७५, २११, ३५०.{{/F}} methods of: control of the senses and the mind by fasting; a means to fructify austeri- ties, then knowledge sprouts; {{F}}१३:  Ib. ७७, १२४-35.{{/F}} praise of; {{F}}१४:  Br. I. 6. ४०; वा. १८. 5-6.{{/F}} of नक्षत्र and ऋषि; {{F}}१५:  Ib. ९९. ४२२.{{/F}} as a result of स्वाध्याय or study and vice-versa; {{F}}१६:  Vi. VI. 6. 2.{{/F}} explanation of the nature of yoga by केशिध्वज to खाण्डिक्य. {{F}}१७:  Ib. VI. 7. २६-92.{{/F}}(II)--a name of शिव. वा. ९७. १७५.--a शक्ति. Br. IV. ३२. १७.--Lord नारायण. M. १७१. 3.--by his quality of lordship, God assumes this shape in the world. वा. १०१. २१७.--the अवतार् of the Lord in the २८थ् dva1para with a bachelor's body; entered the Meru cave with ब्रह्मा and विष्णु and took the name of Nakuli. वा. २३. २१९-21.--the first of all धर्मस्; {{F}}1:  वा. ८३. ६०.{{/F}} hidden by कश्यप in a cave and discovered and published by Sanat- कुमार for the benefit of humanity; {{F}}2:  Ib. ८३. ८३-4.{{/F}} not to be discussed with Yogins; but implicit obedience to it leads to heaven, and non- conformity would lead to hell. {{F}}3:  Ib. ८३. ९१-94; १०४. १४.{{/F}}--Ordered by Hari to transfer the धाम of His in the womb of देवकी to that of रोहिणी; she was to take birth as the daughter of यशोदा and Nanda, at the same time he became कृष्ण. She would be worshipped by all as दुर्गा, भद्रकाली, अम्बिका. She did as was commanded. Born of यशोदा: taken to prison by Vasudeva leaving देवकी's babe at यशोदा's bed. Dashed against a rock by Kamsa, she predicted that soon a baby born already would kill him (See विष्णुमाया). भा. X. 2. 6-१५; 3. ४५[1]-५३; 4. 7-१३, २९.--of विष्णु on the waters: His primordial form; {{F}}1:  भा. I. 3. 2-5.{{/F}} his sleep at प्रयागा; {{F}}2:  M. २२. 9.{{/F}} left it for churning the ocean. {{F}}3:  Ib. १५०. २१२; २४९. ४५.{{/F}}--the signs in the body of; when the Yogi feels himself and the earth full of tejas, then siddhi is attain- ed; {{F}}1:  वा. ११. ६२-63.{{/F}} क्रियायोग. {{F}}2:  Ib. ७१. ६४.{{/F}}--works on Yoga. Br. IV. ३७. २७.--the sister of बृहस्पति and wife of Pra- भास, the eighth of the Vasus; son, विश्वकर्म, author of the सील्पशास्त्र. वा. ८४. १५-16. [page३-038+ ३६]--a son of Brahmadatta. वा. ९९. १८०.--authorship attributed to विष्वक्सेन. भा. IX. २१. २६. [page३-037+ ३४]--a manifestation of Hari in the epoch of XIII Manu: a friend of Indra Divaspati. भा. VIII. १३. ३२.--image of, with hanging tongue, knotted hair on the top of the head and a garland of skulls and bones, etc. M. २६१. ३३-6.--(Siddha) he who has practised brahmacarya, ahimsa, satya, non-stealing, and a parigraha and cultivated a sense of detachment; {{F}}1:  वा. ७६. २८; Vi. VI. 7. ३६.{{/F}} is superior to all for he performs तपस् for a hundred years standing on one foot and living on air; {{F}}2:  वा. ७१. ७३.{{/F}} धर्मशासनम् of: ahimsaka; walking on good roads, drinking clean and filtered water and speaking truthful words; after serving his guru for a year goes about begging alms; {{F}}3:  Ib. १६. 8-१७.{{/F}} gets the धारण and tries to avoid the उपसर्गस्; must understand the seven सूक्ष्मस्; महिसूक्ष्म, आप, तेजस्, वायु, व्योम, मनस् and बुद्धि सूक्ष्म, and the condition of these before these elements attain the स्थूलभाव; all of them inter-dependent; {{F}}4:  Ib. १२. 9, १७.{{/F}} always intent on प्राणायाम be- comes one with the great being; {{F}}5:  Ib. १०. ९४.{{/F}} the best to be fed on the occasion of the श्राद्ध; superior to the feeding of a thousand householders, a hundred वानप्रस्थस् and a thousand ब्रह्मचारिन्स्. {{F}}6:  M. १३. 5; १६. १०; वा. ७१. ६७; Vi. III. १५. 2 and २४.{{/F}} [page३-039+ २५](I)--a वर्ण s4akti: an attendant on शिव. Br. IV. ४४. ५९ and १०५; III. ४१. ३०.(II)--the goddess who stands in Kanakhala- तीर्थ and dances with शिव. M. १९३. ७०.--the mind-born daughter of काव्य Pitr2s. Br. III. १०. ८६.--८००० धनुस् make one योजन। Br. II. 7. १०१; IV. 2. १२६; वा. 8. १०७; ५१. ३७; १०१. ११३ and १२६.(I)--same as धूतपापा: a river in कुशद्वीप. M. १२२. ७१.(II)--the sacrificial fire-place, a वितस्ति in measure- ment and in appearance like the lips of an elephant. M. २६५. ३४. [page३-040+ २३](III)--from प्रकृति. वा. १०१. २२८.--the symbol pertaining to देवी; description of. Br. IV. ४२. १८; ४४. ११.--a sacred river of शल्मलिद्वीप. Vi. II. 4. २८.--contact with women, condemned. भा. III. ३१. ३४-42.--(युद्धमुष्टि, म्। प्।) a son of Ugrasena. वा. ९६. १३२; Br. III. ७१. १३३; Vi. IV. १४. २०; M. ४४. ७५.(I)--a मन्त्रकृत्. Br. II. ३२. १०५; वा. 1. १४६.(II)--a son of माद्रि and वृष्णि. Br. III. ७१. १९; M. ४५. 2; वा. ९६. १८; Vi. IV. १३. 8.--a son of Anamitra. M. ४५. २५.--a partisan of जरासन्ध stationed by him at the western gate of मथुरा during its siege, and on the southern gate of Gomanta during its siege; went to Sya- मन्तपञ्चक for the solar eclipse. भा. X. ५०. ११[5]; ५२. ११[9]; ८२. २६. [page३-032+ ४७]--a son of कुन्ती and पाण्डु born of Dharma, and father of Prativindhya and Sudhanu. Devaka was another son by पौरवी; descendants of अजमीढ; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २२. २७-30; I. १५. १३; Br. III. ७१. १५४ and २५९; M. ४६. 9; ५०. ४९; १०३. 2; १८९. 1; वा. ९६. १५३; ९९. २४४; ११२. ४४; Vi. IV. १४. ३५.{{/F}} was defeated in a game of dice and was banished to the forest with his brothers and their wife. Was met and consoled by कृष्ण and सत्यभामा. कृष्ण's respects to: heard from नारद that कृष्ण was the Supreme Hari and was much pleased. Enquired of Him when he met him at the city of the पाञ्चालस्. He and his four brothers were met by कृत- varman. {{F}}2:  भा. X. ६४. 4-१०; ५८. 4 and ११; VII. १५. ७९; X. ५२. [५६ (v) 5-8]; ५७. १०[4].{{/F}} His desire to perform the राजसूय; joy at कृष्ण's visit: provided suitable lodgings for कृष्ण and his family. Addressing of the assembly on his desire to perform the राजसूय, कृष्ण asked him to get ready by defeating all the kings and bringing thus all the earth under his control: sent out his brothers in the four directions who defeated kings and brought much wealth. Was glad of जरासन्ध's death at the hands of his brothers: Sent for Purohitas for the sacrifice and invited all his kith and kin. The यज्ञ comparable to that of वरुण; attended by all gods. For doing honour to the सदस्यस् there was some doubt about the first place, and Sahadeva's suggestion of कृष्ण's name was accepted by all except शिशुपाल who insulted him in the public assembly. कृष्ण's silence. The पाण्डवस् with the Matsyas and others unsheathed their swords, and कृष्ण sent his चक्र which cut off his head. After अवभृत, युधिष्ठिर shone like Indra. All took leave of him in joy except Duryodhana, who became jealous of the success of the राजसूय and of द्रौपदी, and of कृष्ण. Heard of Duryodhana's fall in the सभा and sent कृष्ण with dress and ornaments to him, which he rejected. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ७०. ४१; ७१. २३-6 and ४४; ७२. 1-१४; ७३. ३५; Chh. ७४ and ७५ (whole); ७६. 2[3]; ७७. 7.{{/F}} On the occasion of the राजसूय, asked नारद how Caidya, शिशुपाल and Dantavaktra, haters of Hari became merged with him after their death, as also about सनातन धर्म; {{F}}4:  Ib. VII. 1. १२-20 and ३०; ११. 1.{{/F}} was met by उपप्लाव्य, by कृष्ण and the other Yadus; {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ७८[95 (v) 2-5]; Ch. ७८ whole; ७९. २४; ८० [5-6], [१६].{{/F}} went to कुरुक्षेत्र for war. On his side were विराट, Drupada, शीखण्डि, धृष्टद्युम्न, सात्यकि, Kekayas, Saibya and others. Killed शाल्व in the field. Welcomed बलराम after [page३-033+ ३५] the war, and left for हास्तिनपुर and was anointed king: rule of righteousness. {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ७८[95 (v) 2-5]; Ch. ७८ whole; ७९. २४; ८० [5-6], [१६].{{/F}} Felt aggrieved over the slaughter of his kith and kin: agreed with द्रौपदी regarding the release of अश्वत्थाम, went with his brothers to see भीष्म in his death-bed, like Kubera with the यक्षस्. Requested भीष्म to give him the truth of मोक्ष धर्म। Did the funeral rites to him, and after returning to the capital, ruled righteously with the approval of धृतराष्ट्र and कृष्ण: three अश्व- मेधस् were performed by him at the suggestion of कृष्ण: Missed seeing धृतराष्ट्र and गान्धारी, and learnt of their life in the हिमालयस्. The rule was characterised by plenty of rains and crops and by absence of diseases and difficul- ties; {{F}}6:  Ib. I. 7. ४९; 8. ४७; Ch. 9. whole; १२. 4-6, ३४; १३. ३०-57; XI. १९. ११-12; III. 3. १८; M. ११२. 3.{{/F}} learnt the अन्गारव्रत from the sage, पिप्पलाद; {{F}}7:  Ib. ७२. 1.{{/F}} went to स्यमन्तपञ्चक for the solar eclipse and there met कृष्ण and other friends; was taken leave of by the sages: left it for his capital. {{F}}8:  भा. X. ८२. २७; ८३. 1-4; ८४. २७, ६९[3].{{/F}} Felt the advent of Kali everywhere: Installed his grandson परीक्षित् on the throne and Vajra at मथुरा: Prepared to go to स्वर्ग: Clad in bark, fasting, and silent, he went towards north with a view to attaining heaven: was followed by his brothers: Attained Hari through friendship. {{F}}9:  Ib. I. १५. ३२-48; VII. 1. ३०; Vi. IV. २०. ४०; २४. ११०-1; V. १२. २४; ३५. २८.{{/F}}--the intervening time between one yuga-san- ध्यपूर्व and सन्ध्याम्श; four in number; कृत, Treta, द्वापर and Kali. The extent is of १२,000 years of celestial measure; the duration of the yugas includes sandhya, १२,000 divine years, 1,००० caturyugas make a day of ब्रह्मा. {{F}}1:  भा. II. 8. १७; III. ११. १८; XII. Ch. 4 (whole) ; वा. 7. २२; २३. ८३; २४. 1; ३१. २१; Vi. I. 3. ११-15.{{/F}} A yugam of five years, commencing with श्रवण and ending with धनिष्ठा नक्षत्र--the five years are respectively Agni, सूर्य, Soma, वायु and Rudra; consists of Samvat- sara, Parivatsara, Idvatsara, Anuvatsara and Vatsara; revolves like the wheel owing to the movement of the Sun. {{F}}2:  Br. II. १३. ११५, १४७; २१. १३१; २४. ५७ and १४४; २८. २२; वा. ३१. २८, ४९; ३२. ५७-65; ५०. १८२; ५३. ११६; ५६. २१; Vi. II. 8. ७२.{{/F}} Social conditions in; {{F}}3:  M. Ch. १६५.{{/F}} of शप्तऋषिस्. {{F}}4:  वा. ९९. ४१९.{{/F}}--description of terrible state of, towards the end of a yuga. M. १४४. ६५-87.--a son of Brahmadatta. M. ४९. ५८.--a measurement equal to four hastas or dha- nus; equal to a धनुर्दण्ड. Br. II. 7. १००; वा. 8. १०६; १०१. १२५.(I)--a son of कुणि; with him the शैनेय line. भा. IX. २४. १४; Vi. IV. १४. 3-4.(II)--son of भूति--also Bhautya. Br. III. ७१. १०१; वा. ९६. १००.(III)--a son of Dyumni and शैन्य. M. ४५. २४. [page३-031+ २४]--a Mauneya. वा. ६९. 2.--(युधाजित् ब्र्। प्। and म्। प्।) son of माद्री and वृष्णि and father of शिनि. भा. IX. २४. १२; Br. III. ७१. १९; M. ४५. 2.(I)--a deva. Br. II. १३. ९४; वा. ३१. 8.(II)--a son of Raivata Manu. M. 9. २१.(III)--a sage of the XIV epoch of Manu. Vi. III. 2. ४४.--the son of शन्खण and father of विश्व- saha. Vi. IV. 4. १०६.--a measurement; eight times the लिख्या (स्।व्।), (लिक्षा). Br. IV. 2. १२१; M. २५८. १८; वा. १०१. १२१.--a sacrificial post; {{F}}1:  वा. ३०. १४८; ९४. १७; ९७. २८; १०६. ४३.{{/F}} circumambulation of the, leads to the fruit of वाजपेय; {{F}}2:  Ib. १११. ३१-2.{{/F}} in the Gaura hill on the banks of the Ganges where Indra made many sacrifices; {{F}}3:  Br. II. १८. २८.{{/F}} near ब्रह्मतीर्थ where ब्रह्मा performed sacrifice and planted a यूप. {{F}}4:  वा. १११. ३१.{{/F}}--धूम्र Para1s4aras. M. २०१. ३८. [page३-036+ ५१]--a god of the Lekha group. Br. II. ३६. ७६.(I)--a son of Candra, (Indu) and father of श्राव. भा. IX. 6. २०-21; M. १२. २९.(II)--a righteous king and a son of (Pra) सेनाजित्: Issueless though he had a hundred wives of whom गौरी was one; went to the forest, where he got up the Aindra इष्टि, a sacrifice in honour of Indra. One night he felt thirsty and drank the consecrated water from the sacri- ficial pot. In due time a son was born splitting open the right side of his stomach. He lived for some time and went to Heaven. This son was the great मान्धात (s.v.). भा. IX. 6. २५-32; 7. 1; Br. III. ६३. ६६; वा. ८८. ६५; Vi. IV. 2. ४८-63.(III)--An Angirasa and मन्त्रकृत्. By his curse half the Ganges came out. Br. II. ३२. १०८; III. ६६. २९; वा. ५९. ९९. [page३-035+ २८](IV)--a son of Andhra. Br. III. ६३. २७; वा. ८८. २६.(V)--the son of अम्बरीष, wife नर्मदा, and son सम्भूत (Harita-वा। प्। and वि। प्।). Br. III. ६३. ७३; वा. ८८. ७३; Vi. IV. 3. 2-3.(VI)--during his यज्ञ, there were differen- ces as to the division of पशु। ब्रह्मा interfered and appeased while शक्ति got angry. Br. IV. 6. ५९.(VII)--a son of रणाश्व and father of मन्धात; a मन्त्रकृत्. M. १२. ३४; १४५. १०२.(VIII)--a son of शूलि of the २४थ् dva1para. वा. २३. २०७.--the Crown Prince; {{F}}1:  वा. ९६. २१९.{{/F}} his initiation against a King, an instance of अन्तह्कोप; {{F}}2:  M. २२३. 8.{{/F}} the residence of, to consist of five wings as that of the Kings. {{F}}3:  Ib. २५४. १७.{{/F}}--one of the १४ gan2as of apsaras born of the sun's rays. Br. III. 7. १९.--a son of Vasvananta, and father of सुभा- षण. भा. IX. १३. २५. [page३-034+ ३४]--(see सात्यकि) the grandson of शिनि, and son of Satyaka, and father of Jaya. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २४. १४; Br. II. ७१. १०१; M. ४५. २३; वा. ९६. १००; Vi. IV. १४. 2.{{/F}} Learnt the धनुर्वेद from Arjuna. Approved of द्रौपदी's suggestion to release अश्वत्थमन्: accompanied कृष्ण to हास्तिनपुर; {{F}}2:  भा. I. 7. ५०; III. 1. ३१; X. ५८. 1; ६३. 3.{{/F}} took active part in the राजसूय of युधिष्ठिर: was sent to द्वारका for defence; {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ७५. 6; ७६. 7[5].{{/F}} went with the sacrificial horse of कृष्ण. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ८९. २२[2].{{/F}}--survived the कुरुक्षेत्र war: grieved at कृष्ण's departure from हास्तिनपुर: received Vidura in joy. भा. I. १०. 9; १३. 3; X. ८०.[4].